prod_description: If you don't have the tool, make the tool is the Carbon Tactics motto. The Epoch, the company's latest in a long line of tactical belts, is designed from the ground up for strength in the field or at a big dinner. It features a machined aluminum buckle with the handy quick-release mechanism that Carbon Tactics has built its name on. The mechanism allows you to put on and take off the belt fast, in case you need to shed it in an emergency. The curved buckle lays flat, so it won't impede movement or catch on your clothes. If you want to change straps or buckles, the design is field swappable. Get the Epoch in double-layer nylon or BioThane, a web-coated nylon that's even stronger than nylon and leather. It has the classic leather look with the performance of a much stronger belt.

prod_name: Eterna Adventic GMT Manufacture Automatic Watch
prod_description: Swiss-made since 1856, Eterna watches are a mark of quality craftsmanship. The Adventic GMT Manufacture is at once elegant and highly functional. Sporting a clean dial with a GMT subdial at 6 o'clock, it allows you to track not one, but two different time zones. Seconds are displayed via a secondary subdial at 9, which is opposite a date window at 3. The slim rectangular markers sit atop a guillochÃ©-engraved ring of grooves. The grooves match similar engravings on the crown for a cohesive look. Vibrating at 28,800 times an hour, the Calibre Maison Eterna 3914A movement has 29 jewels and offers a notable 65-hour power reserve. It's water resistant to 50 meters as well.

prod_name: Revue Thommen Diver Series Automatic Watch
prod_description: Revue Thommen's beginnings date all the way back to 1853 in the small Swiss town of Waldenburg. After nearly a century of crafting its own watch movements, the company began producing aviation instruments for the Swiss Air Force in 1936. Since then, it's been at the forefront of Swiss watchmaking tradition. This hefty Revue Thommen Diver Series has a traditional dive-watch design with large indices, 3 sub-dials and chronograph functionality, a unidirectional rotating bezel, and silvertone, lumed hands. Built for adventure, it boasts a high water-resistance rating of 200 meters. The engine of the watch is an automatic ETA movement. It's protected by a stainless steel case and a sapphire crystal.

prod_name: Massdrop x Ferrum Forge Dao Titanium Frame Lock
prod_description: Our sixth collaboration with custom knife shop Ferrum Forge, the Dao (which means knife in Chinese) is balanced, streamlined, and effective like any good cutting tool should be. It features the same premium materials found in other Ferrum Forge knives, including an S35VN blade, titanium handle, and an ambidextrous titanium pocket clip. The blade shape is a modified sheepsfoot that's similar to the Buc, but now with a downward-sloping tip for balance. Even with less weight at the tip, the knife opens with little effort applied on the flipper tab. The Dao's low-profile flipper tab makes it easier to carry and less aggressive in appearance. Once open, a titanium frame lock secures the blade.

prod_description: Our fourth collaboration with custom knife shop Ferrum Forge, the Buc (short for buccaneer) is the most daring yet and now it comes in milled patterns for a touch of extra flair. It takes inspiration from traditional Asian cavalry sabres, which is in large part thanks to designer Elliot Williamson's interest in historical edged weapons. Featuring the same premium materials found in other Ferrum Forge knives, including an S35VN blade and titanium handle, it now has a redesigned titanium pocket clip for added strength and flexibility. The blade shape is a modified sheepsfoot with extra weight at the tip. This creates extra momentum for smooth opening with little effort applied on the flipper tab. Once open, a titanium frame lock secures the blade. In addition, the hardened steel lockbar insert can be switched out if the lock wears out down the line. Carry it on the right or left side: the pocket clip can be reversed with ease.

prod_description: What began as a marketing experiment in the late 1980s has become the country's number-one lock pick manufacturer. Now the most recognized name in the industry, SouthOrd takes pride in producing long-lasting stainless steel tools fabricated entirely in the United States.

Founded in 1939, Oregon-based Gerber has been creating reliable tools for all walks of life for nearly a century. The Center-Drive Plus multi-tool is no exception. Featuring a 3.25-inch partially serrated blade, spring-loaded scissors, wire cutters, a bottle opener, pry bar, file, and more, it's got you covered for a wide range of jobs. The one-thumb opening system makes it easy to access most tools with a quick motion, so they're at the ready when you need them most. Made in America, the Center-Drive Plus also has spring-loaded needlenose pliers and a host of bits to tackle different tasks. To keep the tool out of harm's way, it comes with a premium leather sheath, too.

prod_name: Boker & CountyComm Carbon Fiber Anso Albatross
prod_description: If you looked up hefty in the dictionary, you might see a picture of the Albatross, a Jens Ansodesigned knife produced in collaboration with Boker and CountyComm. The knife boasts a massive 3.6-millimeter-thick titanium plate that forms the basis of the frame lock. On the other side of it is a gorgeous carbon fiber scale, which also helps keep weight down to a still-notable 4.5 ounces. Using the blue-anodized thumbstuds, you can access the blade, a chunky clip-point made from high-carbon-content VG-10 stainless steel. Whether you prefer tip-up or tip-down carry, the Albatross delivers with a reversible titanium clip.

Made in collaboration with EOD Robotics, this Breacher Bar Set from CountyComm is the result of extensive research and input from bomb technicians, SWAT operators, and patrol officers who regularly need to crack things open. Ideal for opening crates, windows, and punching through metal objects, the Breacher Bar Set comes with a small and large pry bar for different scenarios. The back edge of each bar is also flattened off like a coffin corner so it can be hammered on for more difficult prying tasks.

Whether you're watching an epic movie or jamming out to songs from your favorite artist, it's important that your entertainment system delivers powerful, clear sound that you can really feel. Combining killer dynamics, realistic reproduction, and spacious presentation, the Sierra-2 Reference Ribbon Monitor features a state of the art RAAL true ribbon tweeter and a custom SEAS cone woofer that you can really rock out to. More importantly, a speaker of this caliber is capable of creating a deep emotional connection to your music.

While often overlooked, headphone cables are one of the most important components of any audiophile's set up. If you are in search of replacement MMCX cables for your IEMs, these replacement cables from MEE audio are a great place to start. Compatible with the MEE audio M7 PRO, Pinnacle P1, Pinnacle P2, as well as earphones from Shure, Westone, Ultimate Ears, and other brands with MMCX earphones, these durable earphones have a clear finish that works well with any look. They also feature wire earhooks that conform to your ears for a secure, locked-in fit that won't fall out. Choose from two lengths, as well as an option with a mic.
prod_varities: ['51" Without Mic', '51" With Mic (+$1)', '72" Without Mic (+$1)']

prod_description: On their quest to bring lifelike sound to an IEM, the audio engineers at Final Audio Design found binaural audio to point them in the right direction literally. Focusing on the crucial differences between two-channel stereo and binaural sound, the Final Audio Design team developed the E500 IEM: a portable audio solution that gives listeners an unparalleled sense of direction. Onboard binaural hardware and small-aperture 6.4-millimeter diameter dynamic driver units come together to create a spatially detailed soundstage with vivid precision great for everything from music to VR. Each earpiece features a swing fit mechanism that allows it to be swung left and right, as well as tilted towards or away from the ear canal, to help create the perfect fit.

prod_name: Martu Leather Hand-Dyed Leather Watch Straps
prod_description: One-hundred percent handmade and hand-dyed, these Martu Leather watch straps are a work of true craftsmanship. They're also available in a wide range of colors, widths, and sizes to match your favorite timepieces. At 2.5 millimeters thick, the straps are durable and robust. Each one is finished by hand for a vintage look, with slightly burnt edges help to solidify the unique aesthetic.
prod_varities: ['Brown/Dark Brown Accents', 'Pebbled Brown/Dark Brown Accents', 'Pebbled Tan/Brown Accents', 'Tan/Brown Accents']

prod_description: Especially well suited for studio environments, the Beyerdynamic DT770 Pro headphones boast a closed-back design and a highly regarded sound. The sound signature is balanced and engaging with an improved bass response, thanks to the company's bass reflex technology. High quality out of the box, every part of the DT770 is replaceable, in case you want to do some modding down the line. The headphones are complete with a 9.8-foot-long cable and a plug adapter, and it's easy to see why they're the choice of music producers everywhere.

Fusing old-school style with modern technology, the Audioengine HDP6 speakers pair well with stereo receivers, integrated amps, and tube amplifiers. Available here in a pair, each speaker features a 5.5-inch aramid fiber woofer and a 1-inch silk dome tweeter that work together to project a soundstage typically found in larger floorstanding speakers. The 4-ohm impedance rating sounds great when connected to almost any receiver or power amp with a 4-, 6-, or 8-ohm speaker output impedance. With all that, it's no wonder why The Absolute Sound had this to say: "The Audioengine HDP6 is a handsome, high-level performer for the traditionalist the high-ender who still enjoys the rough-and-tumble mixing and matching of components."

New from Master & Dynamic, the MW07 Wireless IEMs are cutting-edge wireless earphones engineered to look as good as they sound. True wireless earphones, these IEMs use Bluetooth 4.2 to connect to devices and NFMI to connect with each other, free of cables. They're made with a sleek acetate body and a stainless steel case for unparalleled comfort and aesthetic appeal. Comfort is further maximized thanks to proprietary silicone Fit-Wings that sit securely in the ear without taking up too much room or interfering with sound. Sound itself is optimized via 10-millimeter beryllium drivers, while speech is picked up by MEMS omni-directional microphones. With 3.5 hours of battery life, easy case charging, and IPX4 waterproof engineering, the MW07s are ready for the gym, the road, or wherever else you want to wear them.

Another round of emails, another round of online games, another round of beer? That's right, your favorite beverage is now being served just a few inches from your monitor. Handmade by the keycap experts at UniqueKeycaps, the Beer artisan keycap looks just like a pint poured perfectly to the brim. Crafted from resin with astonishing detail, it features everything from the foam and the bubbles to the frosted tint of the glass. It's so realistic, you just might be scared to spill it. Standing 35 millimeters, it's a tall order but it's compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones for easy installation on most setups. So raise a glass, and set it back down right on your keyboard.

prod_description: For everything from toiletries and makeup to tech, art supplies, and other miscellaneous items, the High Line leather pouch from Rustico is essential on the go. Handsewn in Rustico's workshop in Orem, Utah, the pouch is made of top-grain cowhide that will develop a natural patina over time. Thanks to its durable and malleable construction, you can easily tuck the High Line into a purse, carry-on, or backpack.

prod_name: Pelican V100 Vault w/ Custom Foam Knife Insert
prod_description: Available exclusively on Massdrop, this protective case lets you take your precious EDC gear with you on business trips and outdoor excursions. Featuring a custom three-piece foam interior, it offers premium protection of your valuables. Inside are a whopping 19 slots for anything from knives to flashlights to wallets and accessories. Made from ultra-high-impact copolymer, it's watertight, dustproof, and crushproof. The automatic pressure equalization valve helps seal everything inside nice and tight.

prod_name: TOPS Knives Mini Scandi 2.5 Fixed Blade Knife
prod_description: A handy neck knife or a virtually unnoticeable blade for your bug-out bag, this small and mighty fixed blade is great for slicing, piercing, shaving, and much more. At 3 inches, the 1095 carbon steel blade is big enough to take on many outdoor tasks, and the full-tang construction won't break down on you in the field. Measuring more than 3 millimeters thick, the blade is crafted from thick blade stock for strength. As for the handle, it's made from micarta for grip in wet or greasy conditions. Also included is a Kydex sheath, emergency whistle, and beaded lanyard. If anything goes wrong (which it shouldn't), take it up with TOPS under their lifetime guarantee.

prod_description: The Kershaw Knockout is the best of two worlds. First, it has an aluminum frame to keep weight down. But though it's lightweight, it doesn't sacrifice lock strength thanks to the inset steel plate (where the frame has been knocked out). The blade is a wide-bellied drop-point that excels in slicing and still has plenty of tip for easy piercing. On this version, the blade is made from damascus steel, which is characterized by its distinct banding patterns and ability to hold an edge. To showcase the blade, there are no thumbstuds on this version, either. Deploy it by pressing on the flipper tab. This Kershaw knocks it out of the park in terms of portability, too. Position the clip on the right side for tip-up or tip-down carry, or on the left side for tip-up.

Keep your automatic watches powered at all times with these Viceroy watch winders from WOLF. Capable of completing 1,200 turns per day (double that with the bidirectional setting) in three directions (clockwise, counterclockwise, or bidirectional), they will turn all day without fail. You can even set a delayed start up to 72 hours away. The watch cuff is made to hold large, heavy watches up to 52 millimeters. Plus, with a sophisticated black faux leather exterior, chrome closure, and tempered glass case, these winders will certainly look the part in the office, bedroom, or lounge.

prod_description: Designed to be the best double-wall solo shelter supported by trekking poles, the X-Mid is the brainchild of Dan Durston, an experienced thru-hiker and established member of the ultralight community. It aims to solve the common issues seen in trekking-pole-supported tents: Most are single-trekking-pole pyramids, which lack headroom, or overly complex multi-pole designs, which are tedious to pitch. The X-Mid, on the other hand, offers a generous living space with dual doors and an easy setup using four stakes and no guylines. All told, it's simpler, roomier, and more functional than its competitors and at just 28 ounces, it's lighter, too.

With a dark color reminiscent of dusk on a summer's day, these polarized sunglasses from Serengeti have a special kind of laid-back feel. Appearance aside, this feel is apparent when they're worn: Each pair features polarized, photochromic lenses that get darker as conditions get brighter. Available here in two styles the Italian-made, acetate Giacomo and the Japan-made, metal Brando these glasses offer a look for every occasion. For maintenance and travel-ready protection, each pair comes with a carrying case and cleaning cloth.

prod_description: With the Aether R Universal-Fit IEM, Lime Ears had a clear goal: to create earphones that sound like an acoustically treated sound system, subwoofer included. Driving the Aether R sound are six balanced armatures per channel, two of which are engineered to act as subwoofers, adding body to the lowest frequencies. The remaining drivers contribute to what reviewers on Headfonics describe as a sweet timbre, musical but nicely balanced sound signature, and excellent vocal performance. The Aether R also features a switch that allows listeners to boost and cut the subwoofer, plus a brass nozzle for strong cable connection. Each pair is fully handmade in the EU and branded with the Lime Ears and Aether logos. Available here with premium, mix-and-matchable shell and faceplate designs for no extra charge, the eye-catching and ear-pleasing Aether R is an excellent choice for big sound on the go.

prod_description: As the industry leader in stainless steel locksmith tools, SouthOrd has a reputation for providing quality lockpicking tools for government professionals, repo men, Special Ops forces, locksmiths, and hobbyists alike. SouthOrd Tubular Lockpicks are professional grade lockpicks with rubber slip resistant handles and an adjustable tension locking collar. Tubular locks are arranged on a circular plane and each pin is open and visible. With a more sophisticated design, use these lockpicks for more sensitive and difficult tasks. This drop features both the 7 and 8 Pin Picks.

prod_name: Gerber Spine Fixed Blade & Devour Multi-Fork Combo
prod_description: Camping just got a whole lot easier. This dynamic duo from Gerber outfits you with everything you need to scarf down dinner in the great outdoors. First in the bundle is the Spine fixed blade. Measuring over 8 inches long with a tough 7Cr17MoV stainless steel blade, this camp knife gives you an edge when cutting up food for a meal or cutting down brush to clear the trail. The other key component is the Devour Multi-Fork, which is much more than meets the eye. Complete with nine total tools including the mini multi-tool that fits flush on the back of the handle this utensil can do it all. The multi-tool even acts as a stand, so you don't have to leave your spoon in the dirt between bites.

The Bestech Sky Hawk is agile, powerful, and fast, just like the bird of prey its named for. In terms of materials, the knife has everything going for it, including a rock-solid S35VN blade and a titanium frame lock. For a touch of elegance (as if it needed any), the titanium scales have a carbon fiber insert that gleams in the light when held at different angles. Flipping the knife open is smooth and steady, thanks to the flipper tab and internal bearing system. Available in multiple colors, the Sky Hawk comes fitted with a right-handed tip-up clip.

prod_name: QSP Locust VG-10 Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: Like the insect its named after, the QSP Locust is long and agile. Unlike the locust, it won't require a swarm to make a serious impact. Measuring nearly 9 inches long yet weighing just 4.1 ounces this VG-10 flipper offers superb cutting power. The 3.9-inch wharncliffe blade is built for control, whether you're slicing lightly or applying pressure on the spine. Deployment on the Locust is smooth as butter, thanks to the ceramic ball-bearing opening system. The handle scales are made of flax micarta with crescent-shaped grooves throughout for added retention. To finish the design off, there's also a titanium pocket clip for right-handed tip-up carry.
prod_varities: ['Gray w/ Blue Clip ', 'Tan w/ Gold Clip ']

prod_name: Seiko SNA Flight Alarm Chronograph Watch
prod_description: Like the dashboard of a cockpit, the aptly named Flightmaster is packed with information that can be difficult to interpret at first glance. With practice, however, you'll be able to use this Japanese quartz watch to summon all kinds of info: time, speed, and distance calculations; fuel consumption; climbing altitude, rate, and time; unit conversion; square root and rule-of-three calculations; and much more. That's all thanks to the slide rule bezel, which features two logarithmic scales in addition to a tachymeter scale. But you don't have to be a pilot to appreciate the Flightmaster.

prod_name: CCCP Black Sea CP-7043 Automatic Watch
prod_description: From the design mind of Alexander Shorokhoff comes the CCCP Black Sea. Featuring sandwiched, lumed markers; a large numeral 12 at due north on the dial, and a colored seconds hand, the Black Sea makes a statement. As opposed to a traditional diver's bezel, it carries an internal bezel with minute markings in increments of five. To adjust it, simply twist the second crown either which way. Powered by an automatic movement, the watch is water resistant to a solid 100 meters. It comes in four different styles to match your wardrobe.

The CEntrance DACport HD takes everything you loved about the original DACport Classic and Massdrop-exclusive DACport Slim, and ramps up the power for running high-end headphones from a compact device. It pairs the highly regarded AKM4490 DAC with a Class-A headphone amp that brings 775 mW of output power all without the use of an internal battery. Connect the DACport HD to your favorite headphones and experience 32-bit/384kHz music, as well as DSD files, in full resolution with ultra-low noise and jitter. One Head-Fi reviewer says, Big cans are where the DACport shows its brilliance most of all. For the last 5 days, I've listened to the DACport HD with HIFIMAN's HE400s, and I think it's one of the best combos by price/sound ratio."

Building on the groundbreaking design of the Pinnacle P1, MEE audio's Pinnacle P2 makes high-fidelity audio more accessible than ever. This IEM pairs a phone-friendly low impedance with a warm, dynamic sound that retains the company's hallmark clarity and resolution. Equipped with a 10-millimeter dynamic driver in each ear, the P2 also has a user-replaceable MMCX cable and an ergonomic design. Wear the IEM cable up or cable down, and use the inline microphone and remote to take calls and control your music. Audiophile Heaven says, If you're looking for an IEM that's well built, isolates well, and has an engaging, V-shaped sound with a strong bass and a touch of sparkle in its treble, the P2 is surely worth checking out.

New from Shouer, the Singer IEM delivers powerful, lifelike sound in a portable package. Inside each IEM, unique two-driver combination creates a one-of-a-kind listening experience that works well with any style of music. An electrostatic driver achieves an ultra-low distortion rate, fast frequency response, and impressive sound separation, while an 8-millimeter dynamic driver adds power and low-end definition. The Singer's neat, cylindrical shape nearly disappears in the ear, creating a comfortable seal that does a good job isolating music from external noise. Each earphone also features reinforced 2-pin connectors for easy cable replacement. Compatible with a wide range of eartips for a custom fit, the Singer is one IEM that feels as good as it sounds.

Deck out your arrow keys in style with these novelty shine-through keycaps. Included are eight different keycaps (W, A, S, D and arrow keys), each of which is compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones. Sculpted in OEM profile, they're made from etched ABS plastic with top- and side-printed graphics to shake up your favorite keyboard.

You asked for it, and we delivered. This zipperless version of the front-pocket wallet from Allegory is even sleeker than before and it comes in a right-and left-handed version to suit any carrier. A great way to organize all of your EDC gear in one easy-to-access place, it's a solution to a problem you didn't know you had. Designed to line the contours of the pocket, it features two expandable elastic pockets and a card holder on the outside. With all that space, it can hold cash, cards, a small cellphone, a knife, a flashlight, and anything else you can cram into it all directly in the front pocket, where you need it most. Made from Ecuadorian Latigo leather, which has become synonymous with the Allegory name, the wallet is handcrafted in three different colors.

If there's two main complaints we hear from most flask owners, it's that their vessel corrupts the taste and they can never find a funnel to fill it up properly. Addressing both issues with superior construction, the Vargo Titanium Funnel Flask gives you a tasteless and highly durable titanium body with a silicone funnel that stays securely on top. Based on customer suggestions, Vargo has improved this model with a mouthpiece that is 44% larger than the previous model.

One of the most trusted names in the EDC community, Kershaw is at it again with this four-pack of EDC value. It features an 8-inch folder with Kershaw's iconic SpeedSafe assisted opening system for easy deployment, a compact flashlight with nine LEDs, and a handy multi-tool with a bottle opener, wire cutter, oxygen tank opener, and a flathead screwdriver. Each item in the kit is either blacked out or stonewashed to help you keep a low profile. Also included is a set of dog tags for lanyard carry.

Movado takes a bold leap into the future with the Bold Touch. This intelligent watch has a ton of functionality built-in, but maintains the minimal and sleek look that Movado has made famous. The round dial is as minimal as it gets. It has an LED display that springs to life when called upon. Functions include a 24-hour dial, tracking of multiple time zones, a timer, a calendar, a pedometer, a backlight, and more. Preserving the internals is a stainless steel case, which is PVD-coated in black for a discreet aesthetic.

Thieaudio turned heads with its Phantom planar magnetic headphones. Now, the company is making a splash in the IEM market with the Voyager series, whose flagship and entry-level models you'll find here. The entry-level Voyager 3 features three Knowles balanced armatures, 3-way crossover technology, and two sound bores. The flagship Voyager 14 takes things several steps further with 14 balanced armatures, 5-way crossover technology, and four sound bores per channel. On the Voyager 14 driver list are two different Knowles drivers and two different Sonion drivers, each selected to fill out an impressively wide dynamic range. Both Voyager models come with a detachable cable, metal storage case, and three sets of silicon tips in different sizes.

With the Q2 IEM, BGVP has taken listening versatility to new levels. Unlike nearly every TWS IEM on the market today, the Q2 can switch between true wireless and wired modes a great choice for low-battery situations and listeners who prefer to plug in. Inside, the Q2 features two Knowles balanced armatures in each earphone: the Knowles 32873, which delivers warm bass frequencies, and the Knowles 33518, which helps articulate the mids and highs. For wireless listening, the Q2 has Bluetooth 5.0, a 50mAh battery, and a charging case that can provide up to 26 hours of playback. For wired listening, it features an MMCX connection. In both modes, it sounds amazing, according to reviewers on Headfonia. Listen both ways with an included MMCX cable, charging case, and other accessories.

With three subdials, a day-and-date window at 3 o'clock, and a tachymeter scale, the Revue Thommen Airspeed Chronograph watch packs a lot of function into a robust case. Powered by a reliable Valjoux 7750 movement, the watch runs efficiently for over 40 hours on a full charge. The stainless steel case is armed with a durable sapphire crystal. Also made from sapphire is the exhibition caseback, where the movement is on center stage. Cylindrical pushers at 2 and 4 o'clock are used to operate the chronograph, and the crown in between them is knurled for added grip retention.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/0ztStV6YT4GCbhcMLgvK_I01302 Profile Side.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/oyiXS4sRcGodk1h9MAYZ_I01302 Back.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/AjJx5jEYRciuhlytj9oz_I01302 Buckle.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/x3ffcvKNR46NL3zs0RRb_I01301 Dial detail.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/EJTWuYJuQbuVjnRBpYLC_MAxUudLR5m6RVIZuTjwW_ingersoll_boxpackagingSS18.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/5P9ieIYfRumFJ0rK2OYv_I01301.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/wSXr45NoQs3syzHm4zxA_pcbanner.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/ingersol-hatton-automatic-watch/FP/GfFvRZ1LSKi3T1DnYr0t_I01303.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Ingersoll's take on the pilot watch is known as the Hatton. Refined, legible, and strong, it has the qualities you'd seek in a good aviator-style timepiece at a great value. Fitted with a Miyota 820A automatic movement, a stainless steel case, and a scratch-resistant mineral crystal, the Hatton is sized at a prominent 47 millimeters wide. The dial resembles a target, with a balanced mix of Arabic numerals, cylindrical indices, and of course, a large Flieger-style 12 o'clock indicator. Whether you prefer a more traditional look or something more modern, there are three styles to choose from.

Citizen's line of light-powered Eco-Drive watches offers the accuracy of quartz movements with the hassle-free nature of automatic watches that never need a battery replacement. This model pairs the innovative Eco-Drive movement with a look and build to handle the Great Outdoors. Measuring 42 millimeters, the watch is sized appropriately for wrists big and small. The stainless steel case is a svelte 11 millimeters thick not to mention it's water resistant to 100 meters and set on a tough canvas strap. Functionality is the key attribute of the dial. With compass markings on the chapter ring, luminous hands, and a date window, it makes timekeeping in any setting easy.

Now sourced directly from Seki Edge, this two-piece grooming kit features the same great essentials previously offered on Massdrop, but with the improved quality that comes from working directly with Seki. From the stainless steel and shaping of the blades to the finishing on the tools, the craftsmanship is second to none. And each piece is branded with the Seki name to prove it.

Designed by Ryan Johnson, who's earned a solid reputation at RMJ Tactical making tomahawks and fixed blades, the Gulf folding knife has the same curl to it that it's name suggests. A beastly 9.6-inch liner lock, the Gulf is as imposing as the body of water it represents. The blade is a wide clip-point made of corrosion-resistant 8Cr13MoV. Thanks to its black stonewashed finish, it won't show much wear which is good, since the sheer size of this knife is enough for you to call on it for virtually any job. Opening the folder is easy with either thumbstud. Carrying it is, too, courtesy of the tip-up deep carry clip that can be positioned on either side.

prod_name: Edifier E25 Luna Eclipse Bluetooth Speakers
prod_description: The Edifier e25 Speakers are designed for wireless connectivity with Bluetooth-enabled devices, offering at-home and on-the-go compatibility. For power, volume, and track-changing, they offer a touch-sensitive design on the left side of the piano-lacquered housing. Each speaker is equipped with a .075-inch silk dome tweeter and a 3-inch full-range speaker driver, not to mention two 3-inch passive bass radiators. The result is 74 watts of output a much larger listening experience than these mid-size speakers let on. To minimize distortion at high volumes, the speakers feature DSP and DRC. Upgrade to the HD version at checkout to add an optical-digital input so you can connect your speakers to your TV or home theater system.
prod_varities: ['E25 Luna Eclipse  Black', 'E25 Luna Eclipse  Red', 'E25 Luna Eclipse  White', 'E25 HD Luna Eclipse  Black (+ $35)', 'E25 HD Luna Eclipse  Red (+ $35)', 'E25 HD Luna Eclipse  White (+ $35)']

prod_description: Shrapnel can do serious damage in the field. So can this new folder from Bestech. Measuring 8.3 inches long, the Shrapnel sports a super sharp 3.4-inch blade with a two-toned finish. Offering lots of belly, the S35VN blade is thick throughout the body and tapers to a fine tip for detail work and piercing. The shape is slightly unconventional, jutting upward like a shard of glass. Opening the knife is achieved with a press on the flipper tab, and closure comes from the built-in frame lock in the titanium handle. For a touch of color, the tip-up clip and pivot collar are anodized in different colors.

Take your smartphone's sound to the next level with the Bluewave GET: a wireless DAC/amp that combines powerful amplification with a compact, super-portable design. It allows you to enjoy music with the highest level of clarity and answer phone calls, thanks to the integrated MEMS mic. Plus, you can pause a song, shuffle tracks, and adjust the volume without ever reaching for your phone. For those using Android and iOS phones without a 3.5-millimeter jack, the GET is a great way to make wired headphones work without dongles and with the practicality of wireless. When you're on the go or at the gym, use the clip to attach the DAC/amp to your clothing. The GET can fit into your existing home audio system, too. It adds Bluetooth reception to any home system, or adds wireless streaming capability when connected to its auxiliary input.

The pinnacle of the Arozzi Vernazza line, the Vernazza Soft Fabric chair combines ergonomic comfort with ultra-soft fabric for a feel unlike any other. Outfitted with 3D-adjustable armrests, an adjustable backrest, an extra-high seat back, and a wide seat to accommodate owners of any size, the Vernazza allows you to dial in your perfect seating settings. The sculpted foam head pillow reduces strain on the neck, while a lumbar support pillow helps to support the spine and back. For unparalleled comfort, this chair is equipped with more cold-cured molded foam than any other model Arozzi model. Plus, this particular Vernazza chair is upgraded to premium upholstery fabric for a high-end look and sustained, breathable softness.

Precision engineered from aircraft-grade aluminum, the Just Mobile HeadStand Avant makes a sleek, functional addition to any workspace, side table, or nightstand. It features a radial brushed finish, polished to a shine to complement your desk setup. Thanks to its perfect balance and high clearance 9.8 inches to be exact the HeadStand Avant is suitable even for oversized headphones, like those in the Audeze LCD Series. And because the base measures just 5.1 inches across, it won't take up much space.

Featuring rugged magnetic titanium housings, the Echobox Ti-22BT Bluetooth IEMs are a great companion for the gym or your daily commute. They're naturally hypoallergenic and sweat resistant, with Secure Fit ear-hook technology that keeps them in place when you're on the move. The Comply foam tips provide world-class noise isolation, while the inline microphone lets you take calls and control tracks. Tuned to sonic perfection, these IEMs boast 8 hours of continuous playback on a single charge so you'll never miss a beat.

For its size, the Kershaw Skyline is one of the lightest knives on the market. While it measures more than 7 inches overall, the Skyline weighs in at just 2.5 ounces, which makes it effortless to carry and virtually unnoticeable in your pocket. With a 3.1-inch blade made from Sandvik 14C28N stainless steel, the Skyline delivers impressive edge retention and performance, without the added bulk of larger knives. A flipper on the blade makes deployment a breeze. The Skyline's handle is constructed with two textured G-10 scales that provide a grippy feel. For even more control, slide your finger into the deep index-finger contour.

A Singapore-based brand run by audio enthusiasts, Alpha & Delta has earned a great reputation for delivering high-quality sound at a lower price point. The KS3 IEMs do that exactly, equipped with custom-tuned 6-millimeter drivers with a warm sound signature that's suitable for all kinds of music genres. The custom housing is compact and built for any size ears in fact, it's 20 percent smaller than the leading competitor's universal custom housing. Plus, with 0.78-millimeter 2-pin connectors, replacing the cable is easy if you want to swap it out down the line.

While many headphones make you choose between an open- and closed-back construction, the Beyerdynamic DT880 Pro splits the difference with a semi-open design that allows for increased airflow and a wider soundstage. It brings full depth and excitement to the entire range, with a smooth, extended treble; a transparent, detailed midrange; and a punchy, layered bass. Because this headphone covers all frequencies without difficulty, it's ideal for a variety of genres and is perhaps most impressive when listening to dense electronic jams.

prod_name: Massdrop x Koss ESP/95X Electrostatic System
prod_description: A revival of the standard-setting ESP/950 released by Koss in 1990, these headphones bring electrostatic quality into a whole new price bracket. Initially designed for live recording, the ESP/950 came with a large carrying case and a battery pack to power the required energizer: a special amplifier for electrostatic drivers. Made for the modern audiophile's listening purposes, this version skips the case and battery pack to save on weight, space, and cost. The color has been updated to Massdrop's exclusive midnight blue and the pleather ear pads swapped for thicker, more comfortable foam wrapped in velour. The rest stays true to the original: same clean bass and unmatched sound quality; same pivoting cups and adjustable, detachable headband; and same energizer, now with new graphics and colorway all backed by the same lifetime warranty.

Grilling in the great outdoors just got easier. From Vargo, a company that specializes in titanium accessories, this titanium grill features a bifold system that packs down small and opens up big. Weighing just under 4 ounces total, the grill unpacks in a jiff: Just place it over your fire and start cooking right away. What's more, the flat grilling surface is much easier to clean than traditional rods not to mention its non-corrosive and non-reactive, and it won't impart any flavor on your favorite outdoor dishes. To go with it, we're including a nylon carrying pouch.

The wonderful world of spinning tops is a rabbit hole. Designers these days are cranking out tons of wacky and intriguing spinners made from materials that run the gamut but ultimately, all you need is a balanced top and a good surface to spin it on to get started. The Vorso beginner's spinning top set is just that. Included in the set is the company's signature MK1 brass spinning top with a finish and contact point of your choice. The MK1 consists of a metal body and a knurled spindle with an aluminum center. The bearing promises long spin times and smooth rotation for several minutes at a time with a clean spinning surface. Here, that surface comes in the form of the included concave glass spinning base that'll look great on a desk or on the coffee table.

HogDoggins specializes in keychain tools and metal curios. Its latest creation is the PocketPuck XL: a larger version of its popular stash can for anything from cash and coins to spices, pills, and tinder. Constructed from aluminum with a hard anodized finish, this container will protect any precious cargo you stowe inside. Thanks to three N52 neodymium magnets (currently the strongest on the market) and an O-ring seal, the PocketPuck XL is waterproof and dustproof. It opens and closes with a bold, satisfying snap.

If you don't have the tool, make the tool is the Carbon Tactics motto. The Epoch, the company's latest in a long line of tactical belts, is designed from the ground up for strength in the field or at a nice dinner. It features a machined aluminum buckle with the handy quick-release mechanism that Carbon Tactics has built its name on. The mechanism allows you to put on and take off the belt fast, in case you need to shed it in an emergency. The curved buckle lays flat, so it won't impede movement or catch on your clothes. If you want to change straps or buckles, the design is field swappable. What's more, the belt comes in tons of sizes and colors to match your everyday garb.

Skagen watches embody the clean architecture, playful energy, and modern spirit of Denmark, where the company was born more than three decades ago. The Hagen is sparse and artistic, with a look that thrives in virtually any setting. It pairs long, svelte hour markers and hands with a large subdial at 6 o'clock that tracks running seconds. Subtle differences in color at the 60-second and 30-second mark on the subdial give the watch a touch of sportiness. With relatively small lugs and a 40-millimeter case, the Hagen is easy to wear with any outfit. It gets power from a quartz battery, which is set inside a stainless steel case and under a mineral crystal.

Most gamers use certain keys a lot more than others. Whether you prefer the WASD or traditional arrow setup, you'll need a good set of keycaps to last through battle after battle. Arm your keyboard with a set of stainless steel keycaps from Teamwolf and your defenses will hold forever. Featuring a rock-solid backlighting-compatible construction, these hefty keycaps are a sure bet for any competitive gamer or casual typist.

A family-run Swiss company since 1983, Charriol makes luxury timepieces, fine jewelry, and other accessories. The Alexandre C is part of the company's couples concept, which includes matching timepieces for men and women. This particular model sports a multi-colored dial filled with geometric complexity. Amid the avant-garde colors, you'll find slim stick markers for easy timekeeping. The stainless steel bezel is engraved deep with the Charriol name in two places. Adding to the watch's functionality is a date window between 4 and 5 o'clock.

In 1944, Swiss engineer Hans Hilfiker designed what would go on to become the Official Swiss Railway Clock. About 40 years after the clock's debut, Mondaine received official license from the Swiss Federal Railways to use this design as a tribute to Swiss watchmaking tradition. While primarily used in the company's watches, Mondaine now offers the iconic look in its line of clocks. This travel clock goes anywhere you do in style. Made from a solid chunk of metal, it sports the signature Mondaine look. Use it as a desk clock, an alarm, or even in the kitchen. All it needs is a single AA battery to function not to mention it comes with a leather travel pouch for on-the-go protection.

Looking at either side of the Rike Knife M3 folder is a totally different experience. On the show side is a G-10 scale in your choice of color. Flip the knife over and you'll find an anodized and stonewashed titanium frame lock that looks like something out of a futuristic universe. The M3 is distinct in shape, too: It features a ramped spine for thumb placement and a skeletonized handle to reduce weight a mere 4.6 ounces despite a 9-inch frame. The blade is made from some of the best steel on the market in 154CM. To open it, press the flipper tab and it springs into action, locking in place via the titanium lockbar. The milled pocket clip, which features a ceramic ball insert, is set for tip-up carry.
prod_varities: ['Black G-10 - Stonewash', 'Khaki G-10 - Bronze Gold', 'OD Green G-10 - Bronze Green']

prod_description: This collection of watches has the rugged build and bold look you'd expect from Technomarine, sized more modestly for smaller wrists. For this run, we're offering three different models, each with a stainless steel case that's water resistant to 200 meters, an anti-reflective sapphire crystal, and a quartz-powered movement you never have to wind. Each model also has a different array of jewels from diamonds and sapphires studded around the bezel to a ring of sapphires on the dial itself. Speaking of the dial, every watch has one made from brilliant mother of pearl for a luxurious look.

What began as a marketing experiment in the late 1980s has become the country's number-one lockpick manufacturer. Now the most recognized name in the industry, SouthOrd takes pride in producing long-lasting stainless steel tools fabricated entirely in the United States.

Sometimes it's good to keep a burnout by your side. Featuring a G-10 and carbon fiber handle that looks like tire tread, plus a sharp, tapered clip-point blade that clocks in at 3.7 inches, the CRKT Burnout has a flair for style and strength. This blacked-out folder comes to us from MJ Lerch, an up-and-coming knifemaker who trained at the side of her husband, former jeweler and knifemaking great Matt Lerch. Fitted with the Outburst opening system, the Burnout comes to life fast: Just press the blade by either of the thumbstuds and watch it fly into the open position. Rounding out the features are a tip-up pocket clip and a stainless steel frame lock.

New from NF Audio, the NA1 IEM combines a unique driver configuration with a premium case build to deliver powerful audio with a comfortable fit. Inside each NA1 earphone is a double-cavity dynamic driver that precisely controls air pressure to smoothen diaphragm movement, widen the soundstage, and improve detailing across all frequencies. In the words of one top Head-Fi review, these drivers extract the best qualities of BA drivers: speed, accuracy, clarity, separation, resolution, detail, richness of nuance but with a timbre and naturalness, [that] only good dynamic drivers can provide. To minimize weight and maximize durability, the NA1 Features an all-aluminum shell and silver-plated OFC cable with a 2-pin connector.

prod_name: Status Audio BT One Bluetooth Headphones
prod_description: The BT One Bluetooth Headphones from Status Audio make it easy to listen to your favorite songs with a wireless or wired connection. Onboard Bluetooth 5.0 with aptX support facilitates easy pairing to all devices, plus lag-free listening once connected. A 40-millimeter dynamic driver delivers impressive detailing with plenty of low-end and some noise isolation, despite a small form factor. One 5-star reviewer on Head-Fi proclaims that this highly portable pair of headphones has literally the best bass I've heard from an on-ear set, let alone a wireless one. Adding to the BT One's portability, Qualcomm's QuickCharge technology speeds up charging via USB-C, and an onboard battery delivers 30 hours of playback time. Sporting virtually no branding and easy to operate buttons, the BT One is a solid true-wireless choice for any headphone user that's out and about.

The Bestech 1707 Dolphin is aptly named. When closed, the flipper looks like a dorsal fin poking out as a dolphin charges forward through the water. The arched spine resembles the back of a dolphin as well. Aside from looks, the 1707 is built with the best of the best. Its 3.5-inch blade is made from premium S35VN steel, which is perhaps the best commercial steel on the market in terms of all-around performance. It's housed inside a 6AL4V titanium frame that's anodized in multiple colors a real eye catcher. Blade deployment is as smooth as a dolphin gliding through the water. The blade opens effortlessly with a press on the flipper tab. Rounding out the knife is a slim tip-up clip to match the agile frame.

Based in Obrigheim, Germany, GermanMAESTRO has a long tradition of building high-quality headphones for recording engineers and music lovers alike. Take the GMP 8.35 Mobile: a closed-back headphone known for its rugged, nearly indestructible design. Ideal for studio environments, it works just as well for portable use, due to its low impedance. The highly sensitive drivers produce a dynamic bass response, along with an overall transparency in the midrange and high frequencies. Plus, in response to customer feedback following the launch of the GMP 8.35, the company made this model with a detachable 5-foot cable, which connects to the headphone via a 3.5-millimeter jack socket.
To learn more, check out these Head-Fi reviews.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/baldieri-magnum-m-48-automatic-watch/FP/1DwrbWgLQaC73dzGIzxv_SSBKD.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/baldieri-magnum-m-48-automatic-watch/FP/o1EU7lUToOBDu2hcJR6g_Baldieri Magnum M-48 Automatic Watch MD-869024392.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/baldieri-magnum-m-48-automatic-watch/FP/lk9npbcQvRgPhnz8rdfg_Baldieri Magnum M-48 Automatic Watch MD-869024389.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/baldieri-magnum-m-48-automatic-watch/FP/7iHHNDEJTwmRmn0eBGJH_BKBGD.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/baldieri-magnum-m-48-automatic-watch/FP/1DwrbWgLQaC73dzGIzxv_SSBKD.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/baldieri-magnum-m-48-automatic-watch/FP/V1dchvFFRUSfGLNjnC9u_pcbanner.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/baldieri-magnum-m-48-automatic-watch/FP/7iHHNDEJTwmRmn0eBGJH_BKBGD.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Part of a limited-edition run of 150 pieces, the Baldieri Magnum M-48 is a hefty timepiece you can knock around without worry. Sporty in appearance, the watch has a minimally styled dial with a date window slightly offset at 4 o'clock. The hour markers look like digital hieroglyphics. They pair well with the thick, lumed sword hands and 120-click unidirectional bezel. In terms of construction, the watch is armed with a thick stainless steel case that's water resistant to 300 meters. An IT3HD 25-jewel movement keeps the timepiece ticking for 42 hours on a full charge.

prod_name: B Swiss by Bucherer Prestige Chrono Automatic Watch
prod_description: To call the Prestige Chrono automatic an open-heart watch would be an understatement. Open chest might be a better classification. The entire right side of the dial is skeletonized, proffering a serious view of the 46-jewel movement inside. Look closer at the opening and you'll also see a date track huddled up against the moving parts. Appointed with three subdials, this chronograph tracks minutes in 30-minute increments, hours, and seconds. Each subdial has a circular guillochÃ© pattern to highlight the impressive craftsmanship (after all, Bucherer, its parent company, has been making luxury timepieces and jewelry since 1888 and also manufactures the esteemed Carl F. Bucherer brand of watches). Finally, made with a sapphire crystal, a stainless steel case, and a display caseback, the watch looks and feels the part on the wrist and it comes in four different styles, to boot.

Boasting high-end specs and the looks to match, the Opus #2 digital audio player is built with two Sabre32 ES9018K2M DACs for outstanding performance in native DSD playback, as well as high-res audio files up to 32 bit/384 kHz. If you'd like to make further use of these excellent DACs, the player can also be used as a USB DAC. Along with a 2.5-millimeter balanced output, it has a 3.5-millimeter earphone/headphone audio output that allows it to connect to SPDIF-input audio equipment using an optical cable. You'll get a hefty 128 gigs of built-in memory, plus the option to add 200 gigs with a micro-SD card.

prod_name: Massdrop x Naked & Famous Karui Stretch Selvage
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-karui-stretch-selvage/nOUWBLoqSrulCUeV4zWH_AI7B4971 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-karui-stretch-selvage/pWXM0knIRrWq2b8rul6w_AI7B1453 copy liquified page new.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-karui-stretch-selvage/9xfclL6tTZKJbHNB3wid_AI7B1479copypage.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-10oz-weird-guy-stretch/00Y8Yn4kRqONVBkc5F5p_AI7B1379 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-10oz-weird-guy-stretch/4VAZqOyNRWiPkPEs0oGZ_AI7B1384 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-10oz-weird-guy-stretch/UNMpOCeaTtyCIt0n0GkQ_AI7B1491 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-10oz-weird-guy-stretch/wEbNURXlRQGTqKkSGFGm_AI7B1400 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-karui-stretch-selvage/JlxKXwGZSrOrE4sILSER_AI7B5004 copy liquified.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-naked-famous-karui-stretch-selvage/FP/b8qR1ttQH619Griy7rHJ_Screen_Shot_2017-06-19_at_3.22.36_PM_20170619154751_20180221143016.png?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: There's a reason 10-ounce denim is one of the most popular denim weights around. It offers a great balance of durability and comfort in all kinds of weather, and it breaks in a whole lot quicker than its heavier counterparts. For our latest collaboration with Naked & Famous, we used 10.5-ounce rope-dyed red-line selvage from the denim capital of the world: Okayama, Japan. The fabric is woven on vintage low-speed shuttle looms with 2 percent elastane for stretch, then cut and sewn in Montreal. And because it's rope-dyed, it'll fade faster into a unique pattern that reflects your use. Whether you're looking for your first pair of raw denim jeans or you need a lightweight pair for year-round or more active wear (like biking to work), these jeans will be tough to beat.

Made in collaboration with our friends at Allegory, a Kickstarter-born Chicago shop dedicated to handcrafted, small-batch manufacturing, this custom leather pen wrap is available exclusively on Massdrop. Each of Allegory's products aims to tell a story, and this pen wrap is no exception. A timeless piece designed to give your favorite writing instruments a sturdy, beautiful home, it comes with Allegory's legendary lifetime guarantee.

prod_description: For everything from toiletries and makeup to tech, art supplies, and other miscellaneous items, the High Line leather pouch from Rustico is essential on the go. Handsewn in Rustico's workshop in Orem, Utah, the pouch is made of top-grain cowhide that will develop a natural patina over time. Thanks to its durable and malleable construction, you can easily tuck the High Line into a purse, carry-on, or backpack.

prod_name: SK61 Optical Switch Mechanical Keyboard Kit
prod_description: The SK61 Optical Switch Mechanical Keyboard Kit is ideal for anyone looking to build a 60-key keyboard that won't quit. The new Gateron optical switches in this kit are rated for an impressive 100 million keystrokes double the industry standard. They use infrared beams to detect each keystroke, a precise method that leads to an extremely fast response time of roughly 0.2 milliseconds great for gaming and other tasks where speed is essential. This kit also features RGB lighting with 16.8 million LED color combinations, rhythm and sound lighting control, and key programming and macro-creation for three definable layers. It's equipped with hot-swappable switches for fast and easy hardware customization, as well rubber anti-sliding feet for increased stability.

The N1 is the flagship in-ear monitor from Echobox, a company known for delivering excellent value in products like the Finder X1. Designed for gaming and music enjoyment, this IEM has solid titanium housings for best-in-class durability and Comply ear tips for top-notch noise isolation. Echobox's PEEK dynamic drivers produce powerful, expansive audio, while its AFT (Acoustic Filter Tuning) customization system lets you fine-tune the sound signature based on your preferences. Hypoallergenic, sweat resistant, and durable, the N1 is fitted with easily replaceable MMCX cables.

Herculean in just about every way, the latest timepiece from Aragon could just be the new hero of your watch collection. Stainless steel from head to toe, this hefty watch has all the features you could ask for in a rugged diver: a durable construction, a reliable automatic movement, excellent visibility (courtesy of the T-100 tritium tubes throughout the dial), and high water resistance. Timing tasks are easily handled with the 120-click bezel, which has a glassy quality that draws the eye. Unlike most divers, this one has a display caseback, where you can take a gander at the 24-jewel movement in action. To suit watch lovers of all styles, the Hercules comes in two heroic sizes and four bold colors.

Lightweight yet strong, sporty yet sophisticated, Breed sunglasses are made to be worn anywhere. A thin titanium frame creates a shape that's unmistakably classic and a look that's pleasingly minimalistic. Adjustable nose pads optimize comfort, while a spring-loaded stainless steel hinge makes folding and unfolding a breeze. Polarized anti-scratch and anti-fog TAC lenses deliver 100-percent UVA/UVB protection perfect for exercising, traveling, or just walking around on sunny days. Impact-resistant and available here in eight styles,  Breed sunglasses are a great choice for any setting.
prod_varities: ['Black Titanium - Bronze', 'Bronze Titanium - Black', 'Brown Titanium - Black', 'Brown Titanium - Brown', 'Green Titanium - Black', 'Gunmetal Titanium - Black', 'Gunmetal Titanium - Green-Blue', 'Silver Titanium - Blue']

prod_name: MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte Teutonia II Kleine Sekunde Watch
prod_description: While its name may be hard to pronounce, this timepiece from German watchmaker MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte is easy on the eyes. Here, we're offering four different styles, each of which has a dial that's sectioned off into three parts. Slim eyedropper hands and polished markers give the watch a stately aesthetic. Look closer at the dial and you'll see MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte's fine craftsmanship on full display in the form of clean guillochÃ© engravings. There are models with a more minimal look and models with a world timer that track different time zones. Whatever you choose, it's backed by an accurate automatic movement, a stainless steel case, and a domed anti-glare sapphire crystal. Flip the watch over and you can see the movement in action via the display caseback.

Versatile in both style and performance, chronograph watches in the Aeroscope collection from JEANRICHARD are staples for any man. Available here in three styles, these Swiss-made watches feature Swiss automatic movement, chronograph functionality, and elegantly inscribed tachymeters. On each watch, 12-hour, 30-minute, and small-second subdials sit alongside a central second register in the center of the dial. A titanium case with a fixed bezel, screw-down caseback, and push-and-pull crown completes the exterior of each timepiece. Water resistant to 100 meters and outfitted with flexible rubber bands, these watches are ready for adventure.

Made from a combination of black walnut and cherry hardwood, these wrist rests look and feel the part. Designed to support the wrists over long periods of work and play, they're crafted with a slight angle for ergonomic comfort. The base has anti-slip rubber pads to keep the wrist rests in place. As for the wood, it's finished with a semi-clear surface and resistant to warping. Each Orcas wrist rest is made in Seattle, Washington not to mention they come in four sizes to match your board.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/carrera-1001-sunglasses/FP/mEZkwcGqQhadDxmzO9TQ_Carrera 1001 Sunglasses MD-877064402_blueredwhite.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/carrera-1001-sunglasses/FP/eeSfzDvZShqbfpAAxPv8_1500x1000_MD-93511_02.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/carrera-1001-sunglasses/FP/dMzKzkqvRR6EZ4ucWcot_Carrera 1001 Sunglasses MD-877064407.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/carrera-1001-sunglasses/FP/GEDSy8gWQ4q7MXSjC2iw_1500x1000_MD-93511_01.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/carrera-1001-sunglasses/FP/XD5YTJwTBGDcEy7a9erf_Carrera 1001 Sunglasses MD-877064406.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Founded in 1956, Carrera takes its name from the Carrera Panamericana: a border-to-border sedan and sports car race in Mexico. The company started out making motorcycle goggles and other sports accessories, later focusing its lineup on more fashion-minded sunglasses and optical eyewear. The 1001 sunglasses feature a prominent frame with a thick single-piece bridge. The lenses offer 100-percent UV protection. Here in two styles, each model offers excellent coverage and distinctive style.

prod_description: The Black Reef quartz watch from Technomarine is water resistant down to 500 meters. At those depths, there isn't much light. There, this watch looks and feels right at home. With a black dial, black ion-plated rotating bezel, jet-black stainless steel case, and matching silicone band, it's got the dark look covered except when it doesn't. To provide legibility in any setting, the Black Reef features luminescent hands and markers. It also comes equipped with hour, minute, second functions, plus a date display above the 6 o'clock position each colored white for visibility. Rounding out this diver are a solid caseback and scratch-resistant sapphire crystal.

prod_name: Dekoni Pads for Sennheiser PC37X, HD 700 & HD 800
prod_description: Get a different finish on your headphones when you upgrade to Dekoni Audio's highly regarded line of audiophile ear pads, available in four variants that mold the sound and comfort to your ears. They come in Elite Velour, Elite Hybrid, Elite Sheepskin, and Fenestrated Sheepskin, each with their own set of sonic and comfort properties. Each finish provides a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening all while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. Also available are the soft and supple Choice Leather earpads for PC37X and HD598 headphones. Unlike other aftermarket ear pads, these are made to exacting standards and are higher-quality and vastly more comfortable than stock pads. Plus, everyone at Dekoni wears glasses, so comfort is ensured for glasses-wearers and non-glasses-wearers alike.

prod_name: Dekoni Premium Ear Pads for Beyerdynamic DT
prod_description: Your headphones might deliver clear, powerful sound but if they're not comfortable, you won't be wearing them for long. Upgrade your pair with Dekoni ear pads, available here for the Audio-Technica ATH-M50x, the Beyerdynamic DT Series, and other popular cans. These pads provide a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening, while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. Under the outer layer of comfort, the YM80 memory foam has a super-slow rebound time, adhering to every curve on your head and blocking out unwanted sounds. Plus, since everyone at Dekoni wears glasses, this was taken into account when designing the pads.

If you value portability but don't like the tight, earplug-like feel of IEMs or the loose fit of earbuds, look no further than the Koss KDE250. From an audio pioneer that's been in the business since 1958, these earphones look like nothing else on the market, featuring a retrofuturistic metal design that's entirely adjustable and entirely cool. The disc-shaped housing contains a pair of dynamic drivers one 20-millimeter low-frequency driver and one 13-millimeter driver for the mids and highs and the hinged frame allows you to adjust the angle of the driver assembly relative to your ears. Then there are the ear clips. Take your pick of the three included sizes, and fine-tune the fit by spinning the metal knob on the side. Wherever you go, the Koss KDE250 will stay comfortable and stay put.

In the IEM cable industry, Effect Audio (EA) is a big name. Used by audiophiles worldwide, Effect Audio cables combine premium materials with precise engineering to deliver impressive durability and signal transmission. Upholding this standard of quality, the Origin IEM cable features UPOCC multi-stranded litz wire copper that's silver-plated and insulated with Effect Audio's unique Ultra Flexi insulation. Originally available as part of the company's trade-up program, the Effect Audio Origin IEM cable is described by reviewers on Head-Fi as the perfect entry into the hi-fi cable arena. It's available in a 2-pin or MMCX configuration with a 2.5-millimeter or 3.5-millimeter termination.

Legend has it that the Yasha were an ancient class of spirits who presided over subterranean treasures. Before they were assimilated into Japanese culture, however, they were also seen as man-eating demons and devils the kind you see depicted here in six different styles. Made by hand by B.O.B. Handcraft, these detailed artisans show the spirits in all their demonic glory, with horns and teeth bared around a katana sheath. The sheath in their mouths can actually be removed if you prefer a simpler look. Made from resin, the caps are compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

prod_name: Carbon Tactics Ti Slice Aluminum EDC Keychain Tool
prod_description: From Carbon Tactics, the Ti Slice is a compact keychain-ready utility blade you can count on. This version is equipped with an aircraft-grade aluminum body instead of titanium, making it even more cost effective. Weighing just 1.5 ounces, this handy sidekick clips to a keychain or slips in a pocket. Inside the aluminum body is a bronze slider that houses the blade. Press the button and slide your thumb forward to reveal the blade, and press down and slide it back to conceal it again. Changing out the blade is as easy as removing the slider and popping in a new one, or reversing the blade for a fresh edge. Get the Ti Slice in your choice of finish to match your carry.

Whether you wear IEMs in the studio, at the gym, or during your daily commute, the Dekoni Bulletz earphone tips can take your listening experience to the next level. They're made from dense, slow-rebound memory foam that contracts when pushed and expands once inserted, closely conforming to the inner ear to provide a noise-isolating seal and a comfortable fit. This water-based foam is extremely durable and washable, so you can rinse your tips after a workout or as part of your regular maintenance. You can also add optional True Wireless tips to your order to bring unparalleled comfort to any pair of wireless headphones.

prod_description: Delivering on both quality and value, the Zorloo ZuperDAC was a big hit with the Massdrop community and now, the Zorloo ZuperDAC-S takes things up a notch. It's 40 percent lighter than the original (important for a portable DAC/amp) and boasts the addition of hardware volume buttons. Powered by the well-regarded ESS Sabre 9018Q2C DAC, this unit is a great fit for connecting to Android and iOS phones or PCs. USB Type C, micro-USB, and USB Type A cables are all included.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sharpedge-zdp-189-135mm-petty-knife/FP/3Y05HTwWQB2FA9X14cev_pcbanner.JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sharpedge-zdp-189-135mm-petty-knife/FP/DN2j7Yr5T2imP4tHIB5b_ZDP-189 Petty Black_details15.JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sharpedge-zdp-189-135mm-petty-knife/FP/KAbqHUdbReSWYAPq63LG_ZDP-189 Petty Black_details16.JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sharpedge-zdp-189-135mm-petty-knife/FP/GTIyalh2TmWJvSBIguIZ_ZDP-189 Petty Black_details13.JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sharpedge-zdp-189-135mm-petty-knife/FP/509oDZWoSfWNYkSFjuzr_ZDP-189 Petty Black_details11.JPG?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: A smaller version of the ZDP-189 Bunka Black, the ZDP-189 Petty Knife is the ideal all-around kitchen knife for compact settings. Made in the workshop of esteemed Japanese knifemaker Yoshida Hamono, this petty knife features a ZDP-189 steel blade inscribed with Japanese characters and an ambidextrous walnut handle in the traditional Japanese Wa style. The petty blade shape showcases a curved belly optimized for rocking, peeling, mincing, and paring. The blade is just over 5 inches long and the entire knife is exactly 10 inches long the perfect size for tasks that require the cutting power of a chef's knife and precision of a finer instrument.

Our third version of the Massdrop AAA flashlight, this model features a hefty copper body that will develop a natural patina over time. About the size of a tube of chapstick, it pumps out up to 110 lumens and casts a beam as far as 154 feet. The titanium button allows you to cycle from moonlight mode (great for not disrupting others in tight spaces) to medium mode to high mode. Perhaps best of all, it runs on a single AAA battery for a whopping 36 hours on the lowest setting. At checkout, you'll have your choice between the CREE XP-G3 LED, which casts a brighter white beam, and the brand-new Nichia 219C LED. Based on community preferences from the last run, the Nichia 219C LED is more efficient and approximately 6 percent brighter than the Nichia 219B, with only a modest amount of warmth lost.

Both a water bottle and a pot, the Vargo Titanium BOT is an all-in-one system that saves you weight and space. Made of lightweight, biocompatible titanium, each bottle features a screw-top lid with a temperature-resistant O-ring to prevent it from leaking in your bag. It can double as a backup water bottle, measuring cup, mug, bowl, storage vessel, and more. When used as a container for presoaking dehydrated and freeze-dried meals, the BOT allows you to decrease fuel usage and the time you spend cooking (and waiting for) meals. Just add your meal and the necessary amount of water about an hour before you get to camp. Once you're there, fire up the stove, flip the lid into cooking mode, and you're ready to go.

Carbon fiber is hailed for its durability and lightweight composition. These wallets from XC Carbon are crafted from carbon fiber, stainless steel, and high-quality elastic to help slim down and toughen up your daily carry. The U-shaped groove at the bottom makes it easy to retrieve cards (up to 12) quickly, and the built-in money clip can be used to secure the wallet in a pocket or hold folded bills. What's more, the design has RFID-blocking technology to prevent identity theft and cyber crime. Here in a matte or glossy finish, it weighs just over 2 ounces.

Seiko has a knack for creating quality automatic timepieces. Here, we're offering two different styles, both with a complication at 10 o'clock. The first watch, model SSA231, features an open heart that offers a peek at the 4R39A automatic movement. Vibrating at 21,600 beats per hour, this 24-jewel movement is capable of hacking and hand-winding. Overlapping the open heart is a 24-hour subdial. This subdial can also be found on the second watch, model SSA391. Instead of an open heart, this model has a more straightforward look with stick indexes and incremental markings every 5 minutes. Flip the watch over and you can still get a look at its 4R37 movement via the display caseback. Both models employ a stainless steel case and tough Hardlex crystal for durability.
prod_varities: ['White Dial - Brown Strap - SSA231 (+$30)', 'Blue Dial - Blue Strap - SSA3391']

prod_name: GSR Level-3 Practice Lockpick Kit  Drop Exclusive
prod_description: Available exclusively on Drop, this lockpicking kit is ideal for beginners and intermediate lockpickers. The kit includes two 5-pin cutaway practice locks and two 5-pin non-cutaway practice locks in both Schlage and Kwikset keyways. To hold the locks, you'll have your choice of stand. Go for the Cyclops model (with one slot) or upgrade to the TriPik-2 model (with three slots). All practice locks are pinned randomly to be challenging, but not so challenging that they'll discourage the picker. Also included? The Southord 8-piece professional pick set and an instructional book with tips and tricks of the trade.

The clean, subtle Eternity watch from Eterna has slim hour markers and hands for a handsome look you can dress up with ease. This version sports a grab-and-go quartz movement, which helps it maintain an overall thickness of just 7 millimeters. Also different on this model (compared to the traditional Eternity) is the date window and Arabic numerals at the cardinal hours. These details add a bit of dimension to an otherwise classic design. Stainless steel is used for the case and anti-reflective sapphire is employed on the crystal a formidable combination that will keep your timepiece protected for years to come.

From designer Sylvain Lacroix, the innovative mind behind SLD Timepieces, the N-Core 001 could be considered more of a work of art than a time-keeping instrument. Featuring a sculpted, bowl-shaped case with a two-piece construction, it's specifically geared toward NATO straps. The beauty of this design is its versatility. Swap from a leather band to a nylon strap and the N-Core 001 instantly goes from handsome and elegant to rugged and outdoorsy. Internally, the watch features a Miyota 8215 automatic movement, which is protected by a stainless steel case and double-domed Hesalite crystal. The dial is just as intriguing. With large geometric hands and deep, engraved indexes, it has a mesmerizing 3D look. Another unique element is the 12 o'clock crown, which can be operated easily with the right or left hand.

prod_name: NPKC 60% Wooden Wrist Rest Keyboard Case
prod_description: Why carry a wrist rest and a keyboard, when you can simply combine them into one? New from NPKC, the 60% Wooden Wrist Rest Keyboard Case is a seamless all-in-one design with a built-in wrist rest at the base of the wooden frame. Made from your choice of bamboo or walnut wood, this handsome case features a USB cutout, rubber feet for stability, and M2 screws to secure the PCB not to mention it's compatible with most universal 60% PCBs.

prod_name: TW Steel CEO Canteen Quartz Watch
prod_description: The Canteen quartz watch from TW Steel is the company's flagship model, understandably so. This bold timepiece gets its name from the canteen-style crown: to set the time and date, you'll need to twist off the crown just like you would your water bottle. The watch's other bold features include large Arabic numerals at the cardinal hours, stout rectangular hands, and two sizable dots at 12 o'clock near the TW Steel logo. Made from stainless steel, the case is 45 millimeters wide, and even larger with the oversized crown so it's bound to make a statement on the wrist. Backed by quartz movement, the watch has a mineral crystal and is water resistant to 100 meters.

You never know when you might encounter some rough terrain. When the time comes, be prepared with a pair of Pocket Cleats from Vargo. These one-size-fits-all titanium spikes wrap around any pair of shoes and secure by way of TPU-coated nylon straps. Great for icy environments and uneven surfaces, the cleats have lateral stability brackets to prevent side-to-side movement and reflective nylon cord for visibility in dark conditions. At just over an ounce each, they're easy to take on any mission especially with the included stuff sack.

prod_name: Kanemoto Inox Stainless Steel Kitchen Shears
prod_description: A good pair of kitchen shears can save time and a whole lot of effort. This pair from Kanemoto is crafted with hammer-forged stainless steel blades with mild scalloping on one edge. The most important feature, however, has to be their removable construction. If you need to clean, sharpen, or store the shears, all you have to do is pull them fully open and detach them; clipping them back together is just as easy. Also notable are the built-in bottle jaws for twisting off stubborn bottle caps.

Nope. Your eyes do not deceive you. You can't consider yourself a true fidgeter unless all aspects of your workstation are fidgetable. Hammer (the same team behind the Lagoon and SA Carbon spacebars) understands this better than almost anyone. So they went ahead and made an artisan keycap with a spinnable top shaped just like the spinners you see on the streets. While we can't promise you it will help you focus, we can promise you it will make your keyboard more fun not to mention it comes in seven vibrant colors, from transparent watermelon to spotted cheetah and everything in between.
