prod_description: Bolster your keyboard's defenses with the PAM artisan keycap from Dwarf Factory, the same company who brought you the Anura Frog and Miracle Island artisans. Featuring the PA2, M54, and AFV tank, each keycap is set in a different microclimate, from the arid desert to the snow-capped mountains. All of them are painted by hand to ensure they live up to Dwarf Factory's high standards. Sculpted in SA profile, these keycaps are a miniature reminder of the vehicle that revolutionized military combat.

As the industry leader in stainless steel locksmith tools for professionals, SouthOrd has a reputation for providing quality lockpicking tools for government professionals, repo men, Special Ops forces, locksmiths, and hobbyists alike.

prod_name: CRKT Full Throttle Spring-Assisted Folding Knife
prod_description: Fast and ready for action, the CRKT Full Throttle is the latest from Matthew Lerch. Originally trained as a jeweler, the Wisconsin knifemaker's designs are noted for their ornate aesthetic appeal. These attributes are on bold display in the Full Throttle, on both the lock and show side of the handle. A combination of G-10 and stainless steel, the handle provides a good grip and secure lockup. It features CRKT's Outburst opening mechanism for lightning-fast deployment at the push of a thumbstud. The blade clocks in at just under 3 inches long. It's made from corrosion-resistant and easy-to-sharpen 8Cr13MoV stainless steel, which is bead blasted to a smooth finish.

A classic IEM that's been refined over decades, the Etymotic ER4 gets its latest update in the ER4SR and ER4XR: two models that deliver accurate, reference-quality sound with excellent noise isolation up to 42 dB of reduction, to be exact. Each features precision-matched and custom-tuned balanced armature drivers inside sleek anodized aluminum housings, along with a detachable 5-foot-long cable that ends in a 3.5-millimeter gold-plated stereo plug. Plus, their design completely seals the ear to block out the outside world. Improving upon the ER4S's tonal accuracy, the ER4SR IEM is ideal for engineers, audiophiles, and discerning music lovers. If you appreciate a bit of extra presence in the lower end, opt for the extended-response ER4XR IEM. To learn more, check out this Headfonics review.

The Alpha & Delta D6 in-ear monitors were made with two goals in mind: First, a clear, balanced sound signature; and second, the kind of durability that allows you to enjoy it year after year. On both fronts, these IEMs deliver big time. Paired with a dual air chamber design licensed through HDSS (High Definition Sound Standard), the custom-tuned 10-millimeter dynamic drivers bring a spacious soundstage, reduced distortion, and ample detail. The silver-plated-copper cable ensures excellent signal transmission, and for maximum durability, it uses eight cores double that of most earphone cables. To help the IEMs withstand daily use, there's reinforced strain relief at the Y split and a spring-protected 3.5-millimeter jack. Finally, it's all backed by Alpha & Delta's 3-year warranty.

prod_name: Arozzi Verona/Verona Pro V2 Gaming Chairs
prod_description: Building on the success of the original Verona gaming chair, Arozzi has made some key improvements with the V2 version. To start, it's 0.6 inches wider than before, allowing for a little more wiggle room. It also features a sturdier nylon composite base and thicker, more durable pleather upholstery. For those who like to lean all the way back, they've increased the recline range up to a full 180 degrees. Undoubtedly, it still has all of the features that made it a standout in the first place, like adjustable armrests and a lumbar and headrest pillow that can be maneuvered to your liking.

The alpha dog, the behemoth, the undisputed heavyweight champion of your desk: This massive switch tester is an absolute marvel. Featuring a whopping 63 different switches in a 9-by-7 layout, the Super Switch Tester gives you a chance to test out pretty much any switch out there from Cherry to Gateron to Kailh to ZealPC. Made with DSA keycaps, rubber pads, and an acrylic base, it's nice and sturdy. Use it as a display for your favorite artisan caps or make a beautiful scene with different-colored keycaps. It'll make a fantastic fidget toy as well, if you don't mind bothering those around you. Refer to the key below to see what each switch corresponds to.

prod_name: A&H Leather Goods Full-Grain Billfold Wallets
prod_description: Good work at a fair price. That's founder Tony from A&H Leather Goods' calling card. Done in a classic bifold style, these wallets from A&H Leather have plenty of room for all of your cards, cash, and miscellaneous things. Made from full-grain leather in a variety of different finishes (including the new Massdrop-exclusive espresso colorway), each wallet is RFID protected to keep your identity and personal information from being stolen. For bills, they've got a bill compartment with a divider to separate your things; for cards, the billfold with the ID pullout offers five pockets, while the billfold is crafted with six pockets (three on each side). Two side-entry pockets are good for lesser used cards and coupons, too.

prod_description: A portable digital audio player that looks like a flask, the Echobox Explorer fits comfortably in your pocket for easy use on the go. It's handcrafted from your choice of wood types and equipped with the highest specs, including the highly regarded TI Burr-Brown 1792 DAC and a powerful 300mW amplifier. Because the player runs Android 6.0 with wireless connectivity, you can connect to streaming services like Spotify and Tidal. And to help you take full advantage of the player's streaming capabilities, it comes with a complimentary 90-day subscription to Tidal. To learn more, check out this Headfonics review.

prod_name: KBDfans S60 Mechanical Keyboard DIY Kit
prod_description: New from KBDfans, the S60 Mechanical Keyboard DIY Kit is an enthusiast's dream. With a space-efficient standard ANSI 61-key layout, low profile, and lightweight aluminum case, it's great for those in search of a compact keyboard that doesn't compromise on quality. The DZ60 PCB features per-key SMD RGB LEDs, plus Kailh hot-swappable sockets for solder-free customization. It's QMK programmable too great for programmers, gamers, and users looking to create quick macros. Choose from four different case colors, add on optional Gateron switches or Kailh box switches, and select from two optional keycap sets to complete your keyboard.
prod_varities: ['Black', 'Dark Red', 'Gray', 'Silver', 'DSA 9009 Dye-Subbed PBT  (+$20)', 'Cherry Hami Melon Dye-Subbed PBT (+$20)']

prod_description: It's not every day you find a mummy's tomb, let alone one you get to touch with your own hands. On this crypt-turned-keycap, witness an unearthing unlike any other as a skeletal mummy emerges from its sarcophagus to wreak havoc on nearby fingers. Handmade from resin by the keycap artisans at BEE, this keycap gets all the details right: from the mummy's bones and wrap to its authentic Egyptian tomb and the ancient brickwork around its grave. Compatible with cherry MX switches and clones, it makes a great addition to most boards. Choose from six different colors including three shine-through options to fit your style.

It's hard to go wrong with a minimal Swiss-made timepiece. They're accurate, reliable, and fit for most occasions especially this one from Movado. Introducing the Heritage: a modestly sized Swiss automatic that can just as easily match a collared oxford shirt as it can a vintage tee. The dial on this watch is studded with triangular markers at the hours, all of which point toward the center for a symmetrical look. Made of stainless steel, the case features a scratch-resistant sapphire crystal on top and a display caseback on the bottom for a peek at the movement in action. Get your Movado Heritage in sporty blue and black or tasteful black and brown.

prod_name: Alpha & Delta Type-C and Lightning Adapters
prod_description: The removal of the headphone jack in many of today's new smartphone models has caused complications for some users. Those who want to connect headphones, aux cords, or other devices that have cords with 3.5-millimeter jacks can't do so without an adapter. Engineered by Alpha & Delta, these adapters offer solutions for smartphone users with Type-C connections and Lightning connections. Made using an 8-core, braided silver-plated copper cable and equipped with audiophile-grade Realtek DAC technology, these adapters not only optimize versatility they improve sound quality, too.

If Jack Sparrow wore a timepiece, it might look something like the L. Kendall K6. Set against a mother-of-pearl dial, the K6 has a rustic, worn-in look. It presents three separate complications: a cryptic, rotating date wheel at 12 o'clock; a 12-hour display with an anchor for a counterbalance at 8; and a small seconds subdial at 4 that looks like the wheel of a pirate ship. Bringing everything together is the lumed minutes hand with a large sextant-shaped counterbalance. The wheels of this vessel turn courtesy of the automatic ETA 2824-2 movement, which offers a 38-hour tank. Fitted with a thick, curved sapphire crystal, the watch also has a display caseback to admire the engine. It comes on a handmade calf leather strap with a distressed look to match.

Great for adventures and the day-to-day, the Citizen Chandler will suit the functionally and aesthetically inclined. It features a 1-second chronograph measuring up to 60 minutes, a date window at 4 o'clock, and luminous hands and markers for legibility in dark conditions. The dial is a combination of black and white that blends well with the green canvas strap. Also of note is the watch's 100-meter water resistance rating. Of course, as part of the Eco-Drive lineup, it's powered by light and can hold a charge for months even if you leave it in a drawer which you most likely won't, given its everyday appeal.

prod_description: Just like the bird it's named for, the Hummingbird from Rike Knife is small, agile, and beautiful. This drop highlights three brand-new colors that you won't find anywhere else but on Massdrop. Measuring just 3.75 inches overall, the Hummingbird isn't exactly a workhorse but that's not the point. A great letter opener, box slicer, and nail picker, it'll make a great gift and a fun way to round out any collection. The overall construction is impressive: the flipper is made with a Damascus steel blade, titanium handle, and ceramic ball bearing washer system. Plus, it's got everything you'd expect in a Rike Knife with precision-machined details and a smooth-as-butter opening system. Tack it onto your keychain, pop it in a purse, or gift it to that special someone.

During adventures in the great outdoors, igniting a fire isn't always as easy as it should be. Damp conditions, sub-par kindling, and lack of lighter fluid can quickly rain on any pyrotechnic parade. Here to solve those problems and more is the Vargo Blaze, a portable fire-igniter with tools for every step of the fire-lighting process. Only slightly larger than an everyday pen, this tool features a built-in lighter that can be deployed up close or at long range via an extendible bellows. Turn off the flame and use the bellows to breathe life into your fire. Refillable and made from tough stainless steel with an attachment ring for easy carry, the Vargo Blaze helps you bring the heat wherever you go.

Your headphones might deliver clear, powerful sound but if they're not comfortable, you won't be wearing them for long. An inexpensive replacement for worn-out ear pads, these Dekoni pads are compatible with the Audio-Technica ATH-M50x, ATH-M20x, ATH-M30x, and ATH-M40x, as well as the Sony MDR-V7 506. Along with providing a breathable, cushioned feel for hours of fatigue-free listening, these ear pads create an air-tight seal for excellent noise isolation. The standard pads use leather with foam, while the velour pads use a higher-grade memory foam. Also available as upgrade options are several Choice Series earpads, Elite Velour earpads, and Elite Sheepskin earpads with extra durability , breathability, and softness.

prod_description: Since launching our original Massdrop Brass AAA flashlight, we've been able to create other versions thanks to your support. And now we're back with another: the Massdrop Aluminum AAA Flashlight. Made from lightweight aluminum with excellent heat dissipation, it's available in five different colors to match your EDC. Measuring just 2.9 inches long, it pumps out 110 lumens and casts a beam as far as 154 feet. The titanium button allows you to cycle from moonlight mode (great for not disrupting others in tight spaces) to medium mode to high mode. Perhaps best of all, it runs on a single AAA battery for a whopping 36 hours on the lowest setting. At checkout, you'll have your choice between the CREE XP-G3 LED, which casts a brighter white beam, and the Nichia 219C LED, which is more efficient and approximately 6 percent brighter than the Nichia 219B, with only a modest amount of warmth lost.

prod_name: Vargo Sobata 398 Sintered Titanium Alloy Folding Knife
prod_description: From Vargo, a company that specializes in titanium accessories, the Sobata 398 folding knife is a stellar outdoor companion. Instead of a stainless steel blade, the Sobata employs a sintered titanium ceramic-silver alloy, which is far more corrosion and rust resistant great for wet environments. The titanium blade, in combination with the titanium handle, makes this one of the lightest folding knives in its class at just 2.3 ounces. However, that certainly doesn't mean the Sobata can't handle tough cuts. Measuring over 7 inches long with a sturdy wharncliffe blade and reliable frame lock, it excels under pressure. Fitted with a tip-up pocket clip and a flipper and thumb slot, this blade is as easy to take on the go as it is easy to open.

Designed for audio professionals who demand absolutely clear, neutral sound, the Status Audio CB-1s are an excellent alternative to pricier studio headphones in fact, The Verge says they might be the best headphones under $100. The 50-millimeter drivers provide true-to-life sound reproduction without adding any bass, midrange, or highs, while the soft and thick ear pads offer pressure-free comfort for those long listening and mixing sessions. Ideal for traveling and commuting, the bifold design collapses into a small form factor when not in use. And to suit multiple applications, the closed-back headphones come with two cables: one coiled and one straight, both detachable via a keyed locking mechanism.

Most portable chargers are designed for phones and tablets, but what if yours could charge your entire laptop? Now it can. Enter this Ultra-Thin USB-C power bank from Naztech. With a massive 20000mAh battery and 75 watts of power, this compact charger can power a laptop to full charge, or an iPad Pro twice. The device has all the protections you could ask for, including short-circuit, overvoltage, overcurrent, temperature regulation, and a TSA-approved construction. Capable of charging three devices simultaneously, it has a USB-C PD port, a Qualcomm Quick Charge 3.0 port, and a USB port. Thanks to Rapid Charge technology, it takes just 2 hours to fully recharge, too.

For workouts, commutes, and all your on-the-go audio needs, the Force Audio Twin Bluetooth IEMs have a lot to offer. Equipped with dual graphene drivers (one for the low frequencies and one for the high), they deliver better separation and rich, high-resolution sound across the frequency range. The nozzles are machined from a block of solid brass, with an IPX5 waterproof rating to help them stand up to sweat and rain. The built-in battery gives you up to 7 hours of playback time, while the inline mic/remote lets you control your tracks and calls. Thanks to the Bluetooth range, you can wander away from your phone and keep listening.

From Gen.S, who brought you the Monitor Screen and Gem artisans, the Prism is like nothing before. Like a glowing obelisk or a monument to a higher power, this stunning keycap stands tall. At over 16 millimeters, it's bound to make a statement on any keyboard. Made from resin in a variety of colors (all new ones offered here), the Prism has an ever-changing luster. And because of the different colors of the bases, each keycap shines a little bit differently. Put them on your Cherry-MX compatible board for an unforgettable look.

After seeing a few lockpick sets pop up, you found yourself interested in the art of locksport, but you were waiting for a compact set that fit neatly in your pocket. Arriving in a build that looks and measures about the same as a ballpoint pen, the SouthOrd Pen Pick Set gives you an easily transported kit with all the tools you need to get in almost anywhere.

From Team Hammer, the minds behind the MUMMIE and Carbon artisan spacebar, comes the Carbon SA artisan 1u keycap. Designed to pair with the popular Carbon SA set , it's made by hand with resin. The keycap sports the infamous Carbon skull for a truly unique upgrade to one of the most popular keycap sets of all time. Sculpted in SA profile, it's also compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

prod_name: Dekoni Premium Earpads for Koss ESP/95X Headphones
prod_description: For most audiophiles, electrostatic headphones are an undeniable step up from the usual setup. Unparalleled sound deserves uncompromising comfort, and the Dekoni Premium Earpads designed for our highly regarded Koss ESP/95X Electrostatic Headphones deliver just that. Made with ultra-slow-rebound memory foam that's just the right blend of firmness and yield, these earpads feel like high-end mattresses for your ears. Tuned to optimize audio from the Koss ESP/95X, they're finished in fenestrated sheepskin for excellent breathability and softness.

prod_name: Massdrop Path Convertible CR123 Pocket Flashlight
prod_description: With the success of the Massdrop AAA and Vega flashlights, we knew our next flashlight had to be a knockout. But rather than go with a conventional step up in battery power, we wanted to offer something the EDC community could really make their own. The result of extensive research and a product-specific survey filled out by Massdrop community members, the Massdrop Path is unlike any other torch on the market. How? This convertible 1,050-lumen flashlight is divided into four sections. It supports one (R)CR123 battery or two (R)CR123 batteries when you add the extra middle section which is great when you need more output and longer runtimes. If you want to put your own spin on it, the modular construction allows you to mix and match brass and copper any way you like.

prod_description: Our second collaboration with Bob Terzuola known as the godfather of the tactical folder the Cyrus takes its name from Cyrus the Great, the founder of the first Persian Empire. Based on Terzuola's custom design, our version is about 1.8 inches shorter to save pocket space. As the name alludes, the Cyrus features an upswept Persian-style blade made from premium S35VN stainless steel, arguably the most balanced steel on the market. Press the flipper tab and the blade deploys effortlessly thanks to the caged bearings. To keep the blade securely locked open, the titanium lockbar is fitted with a hardened steel insert. Equipped with your choice of linen micarta, canvas micarta, or carbon fiber handle scales, the Cyrus is as handsome as it is effective.

prod_name: Massdrop x Tashi Bharucha Heat Seeker Folding Knife
prod_description: Our second collaboration with Tashi Bharucha, the Heat Seeker is a production version of one of his most popular custom knives. From its skeletonized, aggressively angled handle to its wide trailing-point blade, it's instantly recognizable. However, this version is even stronger. Unlike traditional frame locks, there are no backspacers or standoffs to connect the two sides of the frame; they meet almost seamlessly at the spine for improved strength and ergonomics. The handle is milled with heat vents, which help reduce weight, promote a sure grip, and add a touch of signature Bharucha flair. And it's no surprise a knife with this much swagger is made with premium materials. Look to the 3.7-inch Damasteel RWL34 blade to breeze through all kinds of slicing and piercing tasks.

prod_name: Massdrop x Zslane Mercury Rocketeer Keyboard
prod_description: Like putting on an old record or driving a stick shift, there's nothing quite like typing on a typewriter. With their heavy actuations, old-school colorways, and audible clicks and clacks, mechanical keyboards come close and with the Mercury Rocketeer they've inched even closer. Designed by Zslane (who also designed the Dasher & Dancer and G20 Semiotic custom keycaps), the Mercury Rocketeer is based on the Swiss-made Hermes Rocket typewriter. Originally developed in the 1940s, the typewriter was known for its portability, build quality, and well-rounded features all of which are on bold display here. Made with a tall, curved powder-coated aluminum case in soothing seafoam green, the Rocketeer evokes the nostalgic vibes of the classic original. What's more, the keycaps are done in the same vintage green color, with themed novelties that further emphasize the design of the legendary typewriter.

prod_description: This slick version of the Ferrum Forge Falcon features everything you loved about the original, but with a milled front scale that resembles the bird of prey's powerful wing. And now we're offering the brand new blacked-out version with a black stonewashed DLC blade to match the handle. Designed by Ferrum Forge Knife Works, a two-man operation out of San Diego known for producing small batches of custom knives, this folder is small enough to take anywhere, yet rugged enough to open boxes, cut rope, slice food, and much more. The blade is made from S35VN stainless steel for excellent edge retention and resistance to corrosion. It flips open effortlessly thanks to the caged bearing system a mechanism used in nearly all of Ferrum Forge's custom knives. The 6AL4V titanium handle is both lightweight and strong. It comes in multiple finishes to complement the blade.

prod_description: Elegance, functionality, and precision define knifemaker Ray Laconico's work. Never one to overcomplicate a design, Laconico has become known for his minimalist style and emphasis on utility. Our latest collaboration, the Keen, is right in Laconico's wheelhouse. This 7.9-inch titanium frame lock is as clean as it gets. Featuring a smooth, slightly curved titanium handle and a satin-finished spear-point blade, the Keen is a work of art but it's robust enough to perform strenuous tasks if you need it to. The full flatground S35VN stainless steel blade measures 3.4 inches. It's easy to control for slicing, and the spear-point tip provides exceptional piercing power. Deployment is smooth thanks to the caged ceramic-bearing system and subtle flipper tab. What's more, the knife comes in three different finishes and three handle patterns. (There's even a lefty version!)

prod_name: Drop + Eric Ochs Lynx Titanium Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: Custom knifemaker Eric Ochs is no stranger to the outdoors. A childhood spent in the Oregon countryside helped him learn the utility of a good knife in the field, which ignited a passion for making them himself. Our second collaboration with Ochs, the Lynx is a compact titanium liner lock with a premium RWL34 steel blade and a G-10 handle the same materials found in the larger Orca folding knife. Measuring 6.9 inches long, the Lynx is far smaller than the Orca, but it has plenty of size for daily cutting tasks, like opening boxes, piercing through packaging, cutting food, and more. Opening the knife is smooth and easy, courtesy of the flipper tab, dual thumbstuds, and caged ceramic bearings. Rounding out the Lynx is a curved titanium pocket clip that mimics the contours of the handle, and matching anodized titanium liners and hardware.

prod_description: After the first shipment of the Ferrum Forge Falcon, we received tons of positive feedback but there was one thing that could be improved. Based on member feedback that the original pocket clip was too easily bent out of shape, we went back to the drawing board. The result of multiple rounds of prototyping between Ferrum Forge and WE Knife, these updated clips are nearly 20-percent stronger than before. How? The thin middle section has been extended to spread out the applied force, which allows more deflection before the material yields and permanently deforms. To ensure their stability, we even sent samples to a lab to perform cantilevered force testing. In addition to the original gray bead-blasted finish, we're offering them in three other colors so you can mix and match with your Falcons, Cruxes, Bucs, and Daos.

A reliable fullsize keyboard with 104 keys, the Durgod K310 Taurus comes in two different colorways with your choice of Cherry MX switches, allowing you to get just the feel you want whether you prefer a switch with some bump or a speedy linear feel. On top of the switches go the doubleshot PBT keycaps, which also come in different colors to match the case. Thanks to full N-key rollover and anti-ghosting technology, the keyboard will register all of your commands, even when input rapidly. The case, made from plastic, comes with adjustable feet so you can prop the keyboard up at an angle to relieve your wrists. Included is a dust cover, two USB cables, a keycap puller, and a logo sticker.

Manley has a 30-year history of manufacturing excellent tube amplifiers, and in the Absolute Headphone Amplifier, it certainly shows. Combining beautiful design with audiophile-grade tube performance, this feature-packed amp boasts 15 independent controls, each exhaustively developed for convenient adjustability and aural variety. Two selectable stereo RCA jack pairs receive the input signals, and even these are original Manley designs. Control the volume using the large front thumb wheel or the included Radio Frequency remote control both operate a precision-stepped relay ladder matrix attenuator in half-decibel steps. The RF remote can be used anywhere in the home, even through walls and cabinetry, and it's especially helpful when using the unit as a standalone preamplifier.

Citizen made waves in the watch world with its Eco-Drive movement introduced in the 1990s. Since, Eco-Drive watches have become a staple in the watch community and it's not a wonder why. Powered entirely by light, Eco-Drive can last for months without a charge, and never needs to be replaced if maintained properly. Here, we're featuring five watches of the Eco-Drive family, each of which has a slightly different look to suit that special lady in your life. From more minimal approaches in a single color to two-toned versions with mother-of-pearl dials, there's a look for everyone.

For musicians, music lovers, firearms users, and anyone who wants to protect their hearing, the  Rooth C&P M02 earplugs offer a comfy, discreet solution. Made from soft silicone, these transparent tips feature an ergonomic, triple-flange design with a short, clear stem. Inside, an attenuation filter reduces noise evenly to maintain the full spectrum of sound without any muffling a common issue with foam competitors. Compared to the company's M-fit earplugs, the U-fit model tends to attenuate more of the high and low frequencies. And based on members' requests, this release now includes earplugs specifically for the firing range. They provide maximum hearing protection from firearms while maintaining clarity of normal level sounds, like speech and environmental noise.

prod_description:
Unveiled at Rocky Mountain Audio Festival, the Koss KPH30iW is a lightweight, portable headphone with lots of stylish, retro-inspired appeal. It's a descendent of the popular KTXPro1 and Pro35, now equipped with modern features like an inline microphone and remote. The open-ear design delivers smooth bass, clean treble, and an exceptionally spacious sound. Plus, this headphone's 60-ohm impedance allows it to be easily driven by most portable devices, making it ideal for on-the-go use. The headband is adjustable with patent-pending suspension for a comfortable fit, and the rugged 4-foot-long cable has spring-reinforced strain relief for durability.
To learn more, check out these reviews in InnerFidelity and CNET.

prod_name: Allegory Goods Leather Zipper Coin Pouch (2-Pack)
prod_description: Offering proven protection for small tech items like earbuds, flash drives, chargers, and more and a great place to store loose change, a lighter, and other small things the Leather coin purse from Allegory Goods is the perfect travel buddy. Handcrafted from a single piece of Ecuadorian Latigo leather, it's been treated with hydrophobic coating to keep it from retaining moisture.

prod_name: Dekoni Blue by Fostex Planar-Magnetic Headphones
prod_description: This new variant of the renowned T50RP MKIII is a collaboration between Fostex and Dekoni, a company well loved on Massdrop for its excellent line of headphone pads. Done in a distinctive light blue, these headphones feature Fostex's proprietary planar-magnetic drivers and come installed with Dekoni's Elite Hybrid ear pads. These pads improve upon the original model's sound, making it less fatiguing and smoother all around with an extended bass response. The sheepskin outer ring gives you all the isolation you need, while the velour face has a soft, luxurious feel. You'll also get an extra pair of Elite Velour pads. Both sets use slow-rebound, high-density memory foam.

The military-inspired Snyper Two is made to accompany you on any mission. Water resistant to 100 meters, it features a chunky stainless steel case and sapphire crystal. The result is a rock-solid feel on any wrist. Another aspect of the watch's utility is the rail system opposite the shrouded crown. This gives you the ability to attach other modules like lighters, laser pointers, and more. The dial is equipped with thick and chunky markers that pair with large skeletonized hands for maximum visibility, plus a date window at 3 o'clock. Inside the case rests Snyper's own F100 24-jewel automatic movement with a 48-hour power reserve. Flip the case over and you'll see the caseback is engraved with crosshairs, solidifying the robust, combat-inspired look.

Inspired by vintage watches, but sized for the modern era, the Ingersoll Trenton looks like a piece of classic Americana and it is. Made by Ingersoll, which was founded in New York in 1892, the watch has an old-school look and feel. The details are everything on this timepiece. From the polished stainless steel case and leather strap to the large onion crown and wire lugs, it's got plenty of retro vibes in its favor. On this version, the 44-millimeter housing holds a Seiko VD78 quartz movement and a mineral crystal that's resistant to scratching. At 50 meters water resistant, the Trenton will keep ticking even in the face of a splash, too.

prod_name: Rike Knife RK-TR02 Tactical Bolt Action Pen
prod_description: Engineered to take on writing tasks whenever they arise, the RK-TR02 tactical bolt action pen is one tough utensil. It's made from lightweight, ultra-strong TC4 titanium for durability that won't drag you down. An onboard bolt-action locking mechanism ensures that the tip is deployed when you need it and safely stowed when you don't. Simply push, twist, and release for a secure hold. Available here in an eye-catching dark gray colorway, the RK-TR02 makes an excellent addition in any EDC rotation.

The first generation of Shanling's MTW100 IEM offers two earphone models, each with a unique set of drivers configured to specific listening preferences. First up are the black and red options, which feature a Knowles balanced armature driver for balanced sound with strong detailing and sensitivity. Next is the white option, which is equipped with a graphene dynamic driver variant for extra power with a wide soundstage. Both options feature Bluetooth 5.0 and automatic pairing once removed from their charging cases. They're also IPX7 waterproof, making them great choices for listening at the gym or in inclement weather.
prod_varities: ['White with Graphene Dynamic Driver', 'Red with Balanced Armature Driver (+$5)', 'Black with Balanced Armature Driver (+$5)']

prod_description: The UE 7, UE 11, and UE 18+ Pro custom in-ear monitors have received serious acclaim and earned Ultimate Ears a reputation for delivering top-of-the-line CIEMs for music monitoring and enjoyment. Now, for a limited time, these three models are available as universal-fit IEMs great for anyone who wants the legendary Ultimate Ears sound with the versatility and hassle-free ordering of a universal-fit IEM. The UE 7 Pro is made for those who like their mixes to sound loud and punchy. The company's best-selling monitor for stage use, the UE 11 Pro brings that same punch with a bit more feel. Finally, the UE 18+ Pro offers even more headroom and separation with certified Hi-Res performance, low-end power, and impact in the mids. Also available in universal fits are the UE Reference Remastered (a collaboration with Capitol Studios) and the flagship UE Live. Learn more about these two models below.

prod_description: Fusing old-school style with modern technology, the Fostex PM03G studio monitors pair well with stereo receivers, integrated amps, and tube amplifiers. Featuring a solid wood enclosure, each speaker has a 3-inch fiberglass cone woofer and a 0.75-inch silk dome tweeter that work together to project a soundstage typically found in larger floorstanding speakers. For convenience, you can connect the speakers to a receiver using the RCA inputs or use the -inch stereo mini input.

Handsewn in Rustico's workshop in Orem, Utah, the new Highline Leather Pouch is making its debut on Massdrop. The single roomy compartment measures 9 inches long and 3 inches wide, and works well as a pen case or storage for your cash, keys, glasses, lip balm, and other essentials. It's made with top-grain cowhide sourced from American tanners, stitched together with waxed-linen thread, and secured with a sturdy zipper across the top.

Designed to fit most universal 60% keyboard cases, the DZ60 Rev. 3 PCB is fully programmable via QMK firmware, which means, once assembled, you can program any key you like to do whatever you like. With RGB underglow, this version of the PCB can help you create a radiant look on your desktop when paired with an acrylic or polycarbonate case. It's made with the latest USB-C connection as well. The DZ60RGB models feature Kailh hotswap sockets and per-key SMD RGB, with your choice of either a standard 61-key ANSI or 64-key arrow layout.

HogDoggins specializes in keychain tools and metal curios. Its latest creation is the PocketPuck: a compact stash can for anything from cash and coins to spices, pills, and tinder. Constructed from aluminum with a hard anodized finish, this little container will protect any precious cargo you stowe inside. Thanks to three N52 neodymium magnets (some of the strongest on the market) and an O-ring seal, the PocketPuck is waterproof and dustproof. It opens and closes with a bold, satisfying snap.

From its clean dial and diver's bezel to its high water-resistance rating and reliable Swiss-made movement, the Glycine Combat Sub is a favorite of the watch community. This model employs an accurate quartz movement and a chronograph, which allows you to use the timepiece like a stopwatch. To make room for this new complication, the dial features three evenly spaced subdials, plus arched day and date windows at 12 and 6 o'clock respectively. Water resistant to 200 meters, the watch features a sapphire crystal and stainless steel case. The caseback is adorned with the signature Glycine logo.

Built sturdy and styled for timeless appeal, these Hugo Boss sunglasses feature a foldable design to optimize portability. A matte blue frame makes matching easy, and a slim wayfarer-inspired silhouette creates a look that's both classic and modern. Safety and space-efficiency are maximized with metal frames that fold midway down the temple bars, so you can store your pair wherever and whenever you need to. With 100-percent UV protection, these non-polarized sunglasses are perfect for the sunniest occasions.

prod_name: Massdrop x ArmourLite Ember T100 Tritium Watch
prod_description: Tactical watches are great when you're in the field or going for a swim, but they don't transition well at the office or out on the town. Dress watches look great, but you'd never wear one on a camping trip. With the help of ArmourLite, we set out to build a timepiece with the best characteristics of both. Enter the Ember. Designed with a strong and lightweight titanium case, it's easy to wear and tough as nails. It's also easy to read in the dark: Made with 15 tritium tubes for a total rating of T100 (currently the brightest rating in the world), the Ember glows bright for decades with no external power. With Arabic numerals at the hours and a dual-language day-date window at 3 o'clock, the Ember's dial is clean, minimal, and sophisticated. Driven by a Swiss-made Ronda 517 quartz movement, it's accurate and precise not to mention it's water resistant to 100 meters and has a sapphire crystal to prevent scratching. The watch comes on a nylon band, but you can upgrade to titanium at checkout.

prod_description: With a great reputation for producing high-value IEMs, 1MORE is now bringing its triple-driver technology to the world of over-ear headphones. These closed-back cans feature a unique driver construction, with a 40-millimeter graphene dynamic driver, a ceramic tweeter, and a bass reflector. These work together to deliver a hyper-realistic, detailed sound with silky highs, precise mids, and deep bass. Well suited for use at home and on the go, these headphones collapse to fit conveniently inside the included carrying case. Plus, they isolate sound well in noisy environments. Made of durable, fingerprint-resistant aluminum alloy, the rotating ear cups are fitted with cushioned leather pads and a detachable 4.4-foot braided cable.

prod_name: Dango Coin Capsule & Tether Paracord Clip
prod_description: The perils of key jangle are well documented, but what about coin jangle? It's an afterthought until now. From Dango, the Coin Capsule offers a secure, compact space for your loose change. Made from aerospace-grade aluminum with your choice of a silver or jet-black finish, the capsule is lightweight and strong. It contains enough space for 16 quarters, 10 dimes, 7 nickels, and 9 pennies (that's over 5 bucks in change!). Accessing your coins is easy, thanks to the twist top, and carrying it is even easier by way of the belt clip or the included paracord tether.

From Allegory, a Kickstarter-born Chicago shop dedicated to handcrafted, small-batch manufacturing, this padfolio is great for carrying all your writing essentials. It's made of supple vegetable-tanned leather and features a flexible Kydex Core construction that allows it to return to its original shape no matter how far it's bent. Along with a dedicated tablet pocket and room for extra paper or a notebook, you'll find a two-pen pouch, a pair of card pockets, and zippered pockets for your pencil and accessories. Secured with a two-button snap cover, this padfolio looks smart and is super functional, too.

prod_name: Tommy Hilfiger Matte Black Modified Pilot Sunglasses
prod_description: Combining a classic shape with minimalist design and modern performance, these matte black pilot sunglasses from Tommy Hilfiger take the aviator to new heights. Circular lenses and a standard double-bridge are streamlined with an edgeless metal frame and rail-thin temples. The frame's matte black color is subtly accented with the gray-blue lenses (which offer 100-percent UV protection) and translucent brown temple tips. Lightweight and elegant, these take-anywhere Tommy Hilfiger shades come with a carrying case and cleaning cloth.

The Acoustic Research Bolt 1.0 Bluetooth speaker is less than 10 inches wide, but still it packs a powerful audio punch. It delivers clean, detailed sound, due in part to its 20W RMS with active subwoofer and best-in-class impulse response. Great for indoor and outdoor use, the Bolt speaker aims to have an unbiased audio response regardless of the angle it's heard from. Finally, dedicated Bluetooth technology allows direct and automatic connection to the device.

prod_name: Eterna Artena Day Date Quartz Watch
prod_description: The Eterna Day Date quartz watch is minimally styled and easy to wear. At just 9 millimeters thick and 40 millimeters wide, it bears no burden on the wrist. However, thanks to its two-toned rose-gold look, it will make a nice impression wherever you wear it. The Artena's indices are slim and rectangular. At the cardinal hours, they dip into the center of the dial for an almost crosshair-like look. At 3 o'clock, there's a day and date window, which has an ever-so-subtle gold border for continuity. Giving life to the watch is a Ronda 517 quartz movement.

A no-frills diver as technically sound as it is easy to read, the MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte ProMare Go is up for any jaunt through the woods or dip in the ocean and it won't look out of place with a collared shirt, either. The movement is an SW 400-1 MÃ¼hle Version that will run for 38 hours on a full charge. To protect the crisp black dial, there's a thick, domed sapphire crystal. This also factors into the timepiece's 300-meter water resistance rating it's not called the ProMare, meaning for the sea, for nothing. Set on a waterproof leather strap, the watch has a screw-down crown, an exhibition caseback, and SuperLuminova-coated hands and markers.

prod_name: Porsche Design 1919 Datetimer Ti Automatic Watch
prod_description: Porsche, a name synonymous with high-performance automobiles and elegant style, has a notable reputation crafting many other goods under its subsidiary brand, Porsche Design. Titanium from head to toe, the 1919 Datetimer has a clean look absent of frills. Aside from a date window at 4 o'clock and the company logo, the inner dial is jet black. Arabic numerals at the cardinal hours are complemented by slim hour markers for legibility. The lugs are rather unique: they leave a slight gap between the case and strap, creating an aerodynamic look.  The watch has a sapphire crystal and a 100-meter water-resistance rating.

Rike Knife has quickly earned a reputation for its precise machine work, and the newest edition of the 1508s folder raises the bar yet again. Producing an integral handle frame in which a pocket is created for the blade by removing material from a solid bar of TC4 titanium is an impressive feat of engineering to begin with. Now Rike has upped the ante by integrating the stop pin into the frame, eliminating all hardware that connects the two sides of the knife aside from a single bolt inserted from the clip side of the frame. The Rike Knife won't disappoint in blade material, either. It's got a 3.25-inch clip-point made from M390 Bohler steel a fine-grained, easy-to-sharpen alloy that's extremely resistant to wear and corrosion. Thanks to the ceramic ball-bearing washers, it flies open effortlessly with a push on the flipper. Though slim in profile and crafted from titanium, the knife's strong integral frame has a solid feel in the palm. Use the titanium clip for right-handed tip-up carry.

prod_description: With a solid build that lives up to the CEntrance name, the Reserve Series speaker cables feature polyethylene insulation on the inside and a polyester grain finish on the outside delivering strong environmental protection in a sleek package that'll stand the test of time. Using patented MultiBraid technology, these copper cables offer incredibly high reproduction accuracy, and the gold-plated terminals feature low connection impedance. Topped off with a gunmetal finish, three-layer core protection, a braided outer shield for added durability, and banana plugs that pair with most amps and speakers, they're a perfect match for your high-end speaker system.

prod_name: Tascam DR-60DMKII, DR-70D, & DR-701D DSLR Recorders
prod_description: Designed to be used in tandem with today's top cameras, the Tascam DR-60DMKII, DR-70D, and DR-701D DSLR recorders are portable audio-recording solutions for serious filmmakers. The DR-60DMKII is four-track solid-state recorder offering HDDA mic preamps with 64dB of gain for quiet performances, phantom power, 96kHz/24-bit WAV file recording, and several other recording modes. More compact, the DR-70D features four XLR mic inputs with phantom power, 5532 op amps, and Dual Recording Mode (which records a safety copy of your audio tracks). Lastly, the DR-701D is a six-track recorder equipped with HDMI in and out ports, as well as a timecode generator for location reference and jam-syncing from an SMPTE generator. All three Tascam recorders can be easily attached to any camera and/or tripod setup.

prod_name: Dekoni Pads for Audeze LCD Series
prod_description: Dekoni is bringing its highly regarded line of ear pads to Audeze's LCD Series, which covers the LCD-2, LCD-3, LCD-4, LCD-X, and more. They're also a good fit for the Monoprice 1060. Designed to take your listening experience up a notch, these pads feature slow-rebound, high-density memory foam wrapped in your choice of velour, sheepskin, or a combination of the two. They provide a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening all while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. Plus, everyone at Dekoni wears glasses, so this was taken into account when designing the pads.

Made of premium cotton that's breathable and soft to the touch, the Ethohome Gravis weighted blanket feels like a gentle hug. Its deep-touch pressure stimulation helps relieve stress and anxiety, so you can relax after a long day and fall into a deep, restful sleep. And thanks to the machine-washable outer cover, the blanket is easy to keep in good condition.

Plan on making your own 60% keyboard? Put it in a solid aluminum case to ensure the contents are protected. CNC'd from aluminum with an anodized finish, these cases are smooth and heavy. From the front to the back, there's a 5-degree angle for a natural incline. Each one comes with rubber feet to keep it secure on your desktop, plus metal blocks and screws.

You don't have to be a Yahtzee fan or a craps player to roll the dice on a new set of keycaps. Designed for numbers one through six on your keyboard (but compatible other places, too), these keycaps feature a translucent construction to pair with backlit keyboards. And if one thing's a sure bet about them, it's that they're strong and vibrant. Made from ABS plastic, these caps are compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones and they come in multiple colors to match your existing set of caps.

By nurturing the ideas that most excite them, the folks at Dango Products are coming up with simple solutions to everyday problems like how to make a wallet that balances minimalism and comfort, ample security and a distilled design. Enter the S1 Stealth Wallet. Made of textured, water-resistant DTEX material, it can hold up to six credit cards and some cash, plus keys or SD cards in the mini pocket. The integrated RFID lining guards your information, the push notches provide theft protection, and the built-in steel D-loop allows you to attach a cord or chain for extra-secure handling. Want to take your everyday carry to the next level? Add the MT03 multi-tool, which works as a money clip, comb, ruler, bottle opener, screwdriver, phone stand, and more.

The Kershaw Shuffle has been in the hands of both EDC enthusiasts and those who know next to nothing about knives. After all, it's a compact tool that offers tons of utility and it won't break the bank. Now the popular Shuffle is back and bigger than before. The Shuffle II sports a 2.5-inch blade, a longer handle, and a tanto profile that can pierce even better than before. It's still got a bottle opener and a flathead screwdriver, and it's still got texturing on the GFN scales for grip. And even with the change in size, it's not going to weigh you down at just 3 ounces. Carry it with the tip-down pocket clip on the right side.

prod_name: Golden Star Monkey King Reborn Artisan Keycap
prod_description: An (in)famous figure in Chinese folklore, the Monkey King has quite the resume. Highlights include rebelling against the gods, butting heads with the Buddha, and conquering demons on a quest through China. His latest position? A place on your keyboard. Available in 10 eye-catching colorways, the Monkey King Reborn Artisan Keycap from Golden Star displays the face of the Monkey King, wearing an expression worthy of a thousand-year lifetime. Hand-cast from smooth-yet-durable resin and compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, this keycap continues the legend of the Monkey King on any keyboard worthy of the crown.

Think of the Seiko 5 SNZG as the big brother of the company's popular SNK. While both share the same military aesthetic, and both make excellent introductions to automatic watches, the SNZG is at 42 millimeters in diameter slightly larger than its counterpart. And while the SNK is fitted with S726 21-jewel movement, the SNZG features 7S36C 23-jewel movement. The SNZG also has the addition of an internal bezel, which lends added depth and complexity to the watch. And instead of Flieger-style hands, the SNZG dons lumed baton hands. Though, like its counterpart, it features a seconds hand tipped in red.

prod_name: Moon Key Little Easter Bunnies Artisan Keycap
prod_description: No matter where you stumble upon a bunny rabbit, it can make your day. So just imagine if you could have one atop your favorite keyboard. Now you can two, in fact. From Moon Key, the Little Easter Bunnies artisan may be the cutest thing yet to hit the mech keys world. Crafted and painted by hand, these keycaps are made of a combination of resin and clay for durability. They feature two small bunnies huddled around a carrot, or an Easter egg if you're feeling the holiday spirit a little early. Each keycap is compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

Sporting a unique shape and rock-solid build, the Agave D2 folding knife from CJRB looks as natural as it feels. The knife's name evokes an organic origin, which is echoed in its curved handle (available in G-10 or aluminum) and satisfying texture. Like the best performers in the natural world, the Agave has been honed at every edge to do its job just right. It features an elegant D2 steel drop-point blade with a flat grind for effortless slicing and impressive durability. Ceramic ball bearings facilitate friction-free deployment, while a liner lock ensures a strong hold when the knife is open. Choose from four styles, and carry the Agave your way with a steel pocket clip or with the small lanyard hole at the base of the handle.

Whether you're looking for a minimal everyday companion or a more technical-looking timepiece, this collection from Fossil has you covered. The Flynn model features three subdials to track the day, date, and 24-hour scale. It combines Roman numerals and stick indices for a balanced, handsome look. The other available model is the Hutton. Spare of any complications, this watch defines minimalism. It comes on your choice of leather or stainless steel, depending on your style. All watches in the collection run on a quartz battery and are 50 meters water resistant.
prod_varities: ['BQ2316-Flynn Blue Dial', 'BQ2438-Hutton Blue Dial (-$10)', 'BQ2439-Hutton Black Dial (-$10)']

prod_description: Improving on the design of the popular Form 1.1 IEM, Shozy has released the Form 1.4: an IEM engineered with high-quality materials and drivers to spare. Where the Form 1.1 had one balanced armature and one dynamic driver, the Form 1.4 has an impressive four balanced armatures and one dynamic driver per earphone. This configuration has been tuned to achieve a lush, natural sound across every frequency. But the natural character of these earphones doesn't stop there. Shozy has also outfitted its new IEM with a faceplate made from imported wood materials. Combined with a 3D-printed medical resin cavity, the Form 1.4 has a comfortable fit with a truly unique look. No two pairs are exactly alike

If you're like us, you have a lot of keycaps in your rotation. Don't settle for plastic bags and cardboard boxes. Get a polycarbonate storage tray from JTK and give your favorite sets a nice home. Made from durable polycarbonate, these transparent trays display your keycaps in their best light and protect them from fading. The Standard Storage Tray is compatible with all kinds of keycap profiles, like Cherry, OEM, and DSA. If you need space for taller keycaps like SA and MT3 profile go for the Max Storage Tray.

Fitted with large Roman numerals and a prominent open-heart dial, the Heritor Harding automatic watch has vintage charm. In place of a seconds hand, the Harding features a subdial with 60 second markings, which is partially obscured by the open heart. Alongside it is another subdial (also partially obscured) that tracks a 24-hour scale. For visibility, the Harding features lumed hands and markers. Giving them life is a Japanese Miyota automatic movement of 21 jewels, which is visible via the display caseback. Here in six different styles, the Harding clocks in at 44 millimeters and is set on a crocodile pattern leather strap.

Is it any wonder that tops have entertained humanity for more than 5,500 years? Like watching a fire, spinning a top is both incredibly easy and surprisingly satisfying even addictive. Only recently, however, have we been able to achieve  8-, 9-, and 10-minute spin times by creating precision-machined tops fitted with high-performance bearings. The Mk1, made by England-based Vorso, is one of these. Offered with a standard ceramic bearing or upgraded ruby, the Mk1 is now available in Copper and Stainless Steel, in addition to the original Brass. Also new for this drop, you can select Brass and Copper in a subtle Machine Finish or choose the Polished version of all three metals.
prod_varities: ['Brass Machine Finished', 'Brass Polished (+ $4)', 'Stainless Steel Polished (+ $12)', 'Copper Machine Finished (+ $18)', 'Copper Polished (+ $22)']

prod_name: CLICKEYbits Fidget Switch Tester DIY Kit
prod_description: You'd be hard pressed to find a more fun way to test switches than with CLICKEYbits and this DIY version allows you to put it together yourself, and to add your own switches if you like. Though CLICKEYbits were originally developed as switch testers, people loved them so much that they started buying them as fidget toys. Building on the success, the father-son team that created them set out to expand the lineup. Each CLICKEYbits is made with authentic mechanical switches. At about 2 inches wide, they're the perfect size to fill the palm for a satisfying feel in the hand.

From TFZ, one of the industry's top names in portable audio, comes the S2 Pro: an IEM equipped with state-of-the-art drivers and 2-way crossover technology. The latest VGP Award-winning K4U drivers 11.4-millimeter graphene Tesla magnetic group drivers pack impressive power with distinct detailing for rich sound across all types of audio. Sound quality is improved further with 2-way crossover technology, which uses filtering to ensure a Hi-Fi acoustic curve and balanced articulation for all frequencies. Shaped for comfort and stability, the S2 Pro is lightweight and equipped with a 2-pin 0.75-millimeter jack for easy cable replacement.

Whether you're out on the town or the trail, these Geigerrig RIG hydration packs are a great solution for staying hydrated and bringing your gear along for the day. At the core of each pack is the Geigerrig Hydration Engine: a water reservoir that's easy to fill and provides quick access via a silicone bite valve. Because it's pressurized, you can drink from it, spray yourself off to stay cool, clean your gear after a hike, or share your water with a buddy. It has a slide-top opening for easy filling and cleaning, as well as a quick-release valve that depressurizes the reservoir. For effortless cleaning, the bladder can be reversed and put in the diswasher. Both the accompanying backpacks are made from heavy-duty ripstop nylon and feature a sizable main compartment, external zippered pockets, compression straps, gear loops, and a waist belt. The 700M comes with MOLLE webbing so you can lash gear to the outside of the pack.

prod_name: MEE audio X10 True Wireless Bluetooth 5.0 IEM
prod_description: Sporting the latest in wireless technology and acoustic hardware, the MEE audio X10 IEM cuts the cord without cutting corners on sound quality. The X10 establishes pristine wireless connections with Bluetooth 5.0. When it comes to sound, the X10 sports 5-millimeter HD microdrivers tuned for deep bass, warm mids, and crystal-clear highs. Great for taking calls and playing music from any genre, it automatically powers on and takes calls once in the ear using Smart technology. Equipped with a responsive built-in mic and compact charging case, this IPX5 waterproof IEM is an all-in-one wireless audio companion.

Combining two sought-after features in travel headphones portability and noise-cancelling capability the PSB M4U 2 headphones are an excellent option for listening on the go. Using RoomFeel technology to create a more spacious and natural sound, these headphones come equipped with three selectable modes. The first, Active, uses a built-in amplifier to deliver precise and powerful sound from any listening source. The second, Active Noise Cancelling, adds mic-monitoring to detect sound and cancel it out. The third, Passive, allows for up to 55 hours of listening with amplification and noise-cancelling deactivated. Sized for travel, they deliver what reviewers on SoundStage! call a spacious, more immersive soundfield than you might expect from such relatively small 'phones."

prod_name: Fallkniven F1Z Survival Knife VG-10 w/ Zytel Sheath
prod_description: A premium fixed blade that comes complete with a sleek carrying case, the Fallkniven F1z Knife features enough function for survival and utility. As the official survival weapon of the Swedish Air Force, the F1 is made with extra tough laminated VG10 steel. The fixed blade features a tapered shape and an immaculate grind, providing excellent cutting ability and awe inspiring aesthetics.

Part of Kershaw's value line of folders, the Misdirect offers excellent performance on a budget. This nearly 7-inch folder comes with a sturdy frame lock and a blade made from 4Cr13 stainless steel. Shaped with a modified wharncliffe, it can be used for both precision scoring and slicing, as well as cutting that requires a little more effort. The pocket clip on the Misdirect can be positioned for tip-up or tip-down carry on the right and tip-up carry on the left. Stick one in your pocket and the other in the glove box, or give one to a friend or sibling.

prod_name: Massdrop x Schwarz Perpetua EDC Folding Knife
prod_description: Esto Perpetua, or let it be forever, is the state motto of Idaho and it's where this heavy duty EDC knife gets its name. Designed by Idaho-based knifemaker TJ Schwarz and made by Millit Knives, this American-made folder is built to take on anything. If the locking mechanism looks familiar, it should; developed by McHenry and Williams, this style of lock has been a key component of Benchmade knives over the last two decades. That's because it's widely recognized as the strongest and safest locking mechanism there is, which is crucial to folders as the lock is the most common point of failure. The blade is made from premium Nitro-V: a nitrogen-enriched steel with excellent edge retention, high hardness, and extreme corrosion resistance. For a secure grip, there's a smooth G-10 handle in stealthy gray and a removable tip-up clip for righties and lefties.

Looking for a pair of top-notch wireless in-ear monitors? We've partnered with MEE audio to offer an exclusive selection of goodies, featuring well-reviewed products that pack a heck of a punch for the price. And because it's not a Blue Box without some extra excitement, we've included special prizes for a few lucky members.

Montblanc's TimeWalker Collection is inspired by the golden era of vintage racing, when precision made the difference between victory and defeat. Designed with this level of performance in mind, these Swiss-made watches are a great fit in front of a crowd or behind the wheel. Though they're available in a wide range of styles, each timepiece has a few things in common: an automatic movement, scratch-resistant sapphire crystal, 100-meter water-resistance rating, ceramic bezel, and transparent caseback. Whatever you choose, you'll get a sporty Swiss-made piece you can wear for years to come.

Your ideal keyboard is waiting for you. The new GK64 Mechanical Keyboard Kit will help you build it. Designed by the GK brand, this fixed-layout, 60-percent PCB kit fits 64 keys, including arrows, in a compact layout ideal for any desk. Its sturdy-yet-lightweight aluminum plate optimizes both durability and portability, while its plastic case adds a tasteful protective layer in either black or white. With hot-swappable Gateron sockets, you can change MX switches in seconds without soldering. Connect to your smartphone, tablet, or computer via the onboard USB-C connector to program your keys and make macros for three defined layers. You can also set this kit's 16.8 million color LEDs to respond to sound, or you can use the included software to create your own custom lighting scheme.

Founded in 2017, new British-American venture HELM Audio is making waves in the world of sound. Leading the way is the HELM Audio True Wireless 5.0, an audiophile-worthy IEM with high-powered rare polymer- and alloy-enhanced drivers that deliver detailed audio across every frequency. Equipped with apt-X-enabled Bluetooth 5.0 and a HELIX antenna for 60-foot wireless connectivity, these true-wireless earphones simplify listening in any setting. Enjoy up to 8 hours of music playback plus an additional 30 hours of battery with the chargeable carrying case and exercise without worry thanks IPX4 water resistance. Receiving a 9/10 review of Hi-Fi Trends, the HELM Audio True Wireless 5.0 IEM earns its exceptional status with strong performance across the board.

Second to your head, the best place for your headphones is a headphone stand. Combining function with refined natural form, these headphone stands from Beveled Edge make an elegant addition to any audio setup. Choose from the stout-yet-lengthy Cronus, the angular and space-efficient Urth, the two-sided Dionysus, and the all-in-one Audio Station with a built-in headphone stand and shelf for a DAC/amp. Handmade with peerless precision and carefully finished for striking aesthetic appeal, these stands will fit all types of headphones and interior styles.
prod_varities: ['Cronus', 'Urth (+$8)', 'Dionysus (+$17)', 'Audio Station (Headphone Stand with DAC & Amp Shelf) (+$42)']

prod_description: In a way, books are magical in and of themselves. They transport us to faraway lands, and take us through the trials and tribulations of their characters' lives. To capture the mythical appeal of our favorite page-turners, Keycraft created the Magic Book Artisan. Styled like a sorcerer's spell book, or an oracles prayer book, the keycap commands attention. There's even a watchful eye on the front side of the cap, as if to warn any trespassers they best be on their toes. Because books come in all shapes and sizes, the Magic Book does, too: Choose from six colors and two profiles to match your unique aesthetic.

prod_name: Boker Kwaiken Damascus Titanium Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: The Lucas Burnleydesigned Kwaiken is based on a short-range combat and household knife used in ancient Japan. Shaped like a samurai sword only shorter it offers exceptional piercing power and slicing ability. Though it's been done in many materials, this model is the top of the line. It features a handsome titanium handle and a damascus blade with ripples throughout for a truly show-stopping look, each and every time you use it. The blade is deployed with the IKBS pivot system for smooth action, and it locks in place with a liner lock. This smooth-flipping folder comes with a right-handed tip-up clip for convenient carry, but you can slip it in a breast pocket if you like, too.

The Mangrove from CJRB has an unconventional design. The blade, which measures 3.5 inches long, has a teardrop shape with a large belly and an upswept groove along the spine. However odd it may look, the design delivers excellent slicing power you won't find very often in other knives. To ensure a solid grip, the G-10 handle has snakeskin-like texturing not to mention it comes in your choice of four colors. Flipping the knife open is easy, courtesy of the ceramic ball bearings. Carrying it is just as simple: Place it on either side in a tip-up orientation and it secures with a sturdy steel pocket clip.

prod_name: CJRB Feldspar & Small Feldspar D2 Folding Knives
prod_description: Whether you're seeking a compact folder to pocket discreetly every day, or a trusty companion for larger jobs, the CJRB Feldspar has your back. Available in a 6.9-inch frame that weighs 2.8 ounces, or an 8.2-inch frame that clocks in at just 4.2, the Feldspar is built for precision cutting tasks. That's thanks in most part to its sturdy D2 blade that tapers to a fine point for detail work. Adding to the knife's appeal is the strong liner lock and ceramic ball bearings for smooth-as-butter deployment and closure. No matter what model you choose or what color each knife comes equipped with an ambidextrous clip for deep, inconspicuous carry.

prod_description: The ever-minimal Eternity Gent watch from Eterna is simple and refined. Slim hour markers and hands give the watch a delicate look you can dress up with ease. In the name of wearability, the watch is sized at a modest 40 millimeters, with a case that's just 8 millimeters thick. This version utilizes a Swiss-made quartz battery that you'll never have to worry about winding. Stainless steel is used for the case and scratch-resistant sapphire is employed on the crystal a formidable combination that will keep your timepiece protected for years to come.

prod_name: Dekoni Premium Earpads for AKG K7XX & More
prod_description: These Dekoni premium ear pads provide a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening all while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. They're compatible with the Massdrop x AKG K7XX headphones, along with the K701, K702, Q701, Q702, K601, K612, and K712 Pro models. Under the outer layer of comfort, the YM80 memory foam has a super-slow rebound time, adhering to every curve on your head and blocking out unwanted sounds. Plus, since everyone at Dekoni wears glasses, this was taken into account when designing the pads.

prod_name: Dekoni Premium Ear Pads for Fostex
prod_description: Following the success of its premium ear pads for the Massdrop x Fostex TH-X00 and TR-X00, Dekoni Audio has expanded its lineup to include ear pads for the Fostex T50-RP and TH-900 headphones, too. These pads provide a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening, while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. Under the outer layer of comfort, the YM80 memory foam has a super-slow rebound time, adhering to every curve on your head and blocking out unwanted sounds. Plus, since everyone at Dekoni wears glasses, this was taken into account when designing the pads. Swapping them in is easy: Simply take the plastic ring off your existing pads and insert it into your new pads before installation. To learn more, check out this Head-Fi review.

Flexible, durable, and rich in color, Kent Wang's Keyhole sunglasses are named for the keyhole-shaped gap between the bridge and nose pads. Unlike most frames, which are formed in plastic molds, these are crafted from blocks of cellulose acetate. For a custom fit, the design incorporates spring hinges, allowing the arms to flex and conform to the shape of your head. The sunglasses are fitted with polarized Mazzucchelli CR-39 lenses that offer 100-percent UV 400 protection and meet US ANSI Z80.3-2009, EU EN 1836:2005 standards.

New from respected audio company NF Audio, the NA2 IEM delivers detailed sound in a lightweight package. While most IEMs use dynamic drivers with only one back cavity, the NA2 comes equipped with double-cavity dynamic drivers, which control air pressure more precisely to smoothen diaphragm movement, widen the soundfield, and improve detailing across all frequencies. The NA2 also features an ergonomic shape that mirrors the contours of the human ear for a comfortable fit that won't come loose.

prod_name: Ice Watch BMW Motorsport Quartz Watch
prod_description: BMW fans, you've come to the right place. From official partners of BMW, the Ice Watch BMW Motorsport quartz watch combines a sporty automotive look with an emphasis on functionality not unlike the German-engineered machines it takes inspiration from. Equipped with a date window and rotating unidirectional bezel, this 100-meter-water-resistant watch is more pared down than its chronograph counterpart, resulting in a cleaner look. It comes in two sizes, in case you want an extra-large 48-millimeter timepiece or something a bit smaller, like a 43-millimeter case width. The bezel isn't shy about its BMW roots (and why would it be?). Spanning the first quarter chunk are the company's letters on bold display.

The Trifoglio Italia Millimetro is, in a word, dynamic. A rotating dial watch with an automatic movement, it looks like a puzzle to crack open a vault of treasure. But looking past the spinning discs, it's actually very easy to read. The triangular guide at 12 offers an easy way to tell the time at a glance: Just line up the numbers from the outside in and there you have the time. Crafted with a stainless steel case and a raised acrylic crystal, it's water resistant to 50 meters. The 21-jewel Miyota movement offers a 40-hour power reserve and is manual-wind compatible.

prod_name: NPKC Hangul (Korean Alphabet) PBT Dye-Subbed Keycap Set
prod_description: Whether you're learning Korean, embracing another culture, or just want to shake things up, this set of 104 keys gives you the chance to do so. Available in a neutral gray colorway (or a colorful gradient), these Cherry MX-compatible keycaps will fit on most boards. They're made from PBT for a long-lasting build plus, the legends won't rub off thanks to a dye-sub printing process.
prod_varities: ['Light gray with gray modifiers', 'White with light gray modifiers', 'Sky gradient (+ $10)', 'Sunset gradient (+ $10)']

prod_description: Today's ultra-slim TVs may have excellent picture quality, but they often underwhelm in the sound department. Solving that problem is the Alpha VS21 Sound Bar, an aesthetically-pleasing speaker that's both space-efficient and big on sound. Just under two feet long and just over a foot wide, this speaker is housed in a braced wood cabinet tough enough to work as a TV stand. Two tweeters, two mid-range amplifiers, and two woofers totalling 100 watts of power optimize sound articulation across all frequencies. Listen in Stereo and WideSound modes for a true cinematic experience, and use Dialogue mode to enhance vocal volume on your favorite shows and movies. The Alpha VS21 also features onboard Bluetooth aptX, so you can play music from any Bluetooth-enabled device.

The Kershaw Fatback gets its name from its wide, aggressively textured glass-filled nylon handle, which provides a secure grip in the harshest conditions. It features a 3.5-inch modified drop-point blade with a tapered shape, making it excellent for piercing tasks. A non-reflective black-oxide coating increases the folder's wear and corrosion resistance. Equipped with Kershaw's signature SpeedSafe opening system, the blade effortlessly flies into the open position with a simple press on the flipper tab. Plus, it accommodates both lefties and righties with the four-way pocket clip.

prod_name: Bestech 1708 Tercel Titanium Framelock w/ S35VN
prod_description: The Bestech 1708 is a full-size folder that pays equal respect to function and fashion. It features a 3.5-inch clip-point blade that's suitable for detail work and tasks that require more power. It's made from corrosion-resistant and tough-as-nails CPM-S35VN stainless steel with a stonewash finish to complement the handle. At 4 millimeters thick, it's primed for tough tasks. Made from titanium with a built-in frame lock, the handle has ergonomic cutouts for a natural feeling in the hand. Inside it is a ball-bearing washer system that aids in blade deployment. A simple press on the flipper tab and it will rotate open. The clip, also made from titanium, offers right-handed tip-up carry.

When you're on the road and space is limited, you can't go wrong with this portable lantern from industry stalwart Nitecore. The Nitecore LA10 fits in a pocket with ease, but it delivers a wide 10-meter beam with 135 lumens of output on high mode that's all with a single AA battery, too. To access the built-in diffuser, just twist the bottom like a tube of chapstick. This retractable design also helps cut down on space. Cycle down to low mode and you'll get 23 hours of battery power. Furthermore, the LA10 features a magnetic tailcap if you want to stick it on the hood or on the grill, and it comes with a lanyard if you want to attach it to your pack or to a branch. Also included are spare O-rings for the IPX-6 waterproof body.

prod_name: XC Carbon: Carbon Fiber Playing Cards
prod_description: No more frayed edges, stains, or fading: if cared for correctly, carbon fiber playing cards can last a lifetime. Made from 100 percent carbon fiber, these thin and durable cards have a twill pattern and a matte surface. In case things get a little rowdy during gameplay (it happens), they're waterproof as well. Spades and clubs have crisp white faces; hearts and diamonds are styled in striking red.

It's no coincidence that the Citizen Promaster watch looks like the dashboard of a cockpit. It's a flight watch, after all, and it's packed with complications a pilot would find handy, including a slide rule dial with two logarithmic scales and a time-distance conversion index. But you don't have to be a pilot to appreciate this solar-powered watch. The Promaster Eco-Drive Watch is as attractive as it is useful, with its stainless steel bracelet, applied hour markers, Roman sword-style hands, and a solid water-resistance rating. Plus, many of the complications offer practical applications for everyday use.

Silent switches are great for office environments and places where you'd rather not disturb your seat mates. Here, we're offering four different switches from Zeal PC. Whether you prefer a linear or tactile feel, a heavy or a lighter switch actuation, this run has you covered. The RosÃ©lios and Sakurios switches are silent linear switches engineered for smooth and satisfying keypresses. At 62 grams, the Sakurios are the lighter of the two options. If you prefer a heavier keypress, opt for the RosÃ©lios, which clock in at 67 grams. Also available are the Aqua Zilent switches, which come in both a 62- and 67-gram tactile weight. prod_description: The third version in the popular Mako series from Orient, the Mako III offers even more functionality for the dive-watch enthusiast. First, the movement, an Orient F6922, now has a manual reassembly and a stop-second. The bezel has been reworked with 120 clicks instead of just 60. Like before, the case is still made from stainless steel and the watch is still water resistant to an impressive 200 meters (it is a diver, after all). The window at 3 tracks the day and date, while the lumed hands offer visibility in conditions devoid of light.

Combining impressive brightness with responsive functionality, the 360X1 flashlight from Klaurus is engineered for the most critical use cases. Ideal for outdoor enthusiasts, law enforcement officials, and those working in low-light conditions, the 360X1 features a new 360-degree switch ring on its tailcap that makes it easy to turn on from any grip. An adjustable CREE XHP-35 HD E4 LED delivers up to 1,800 lumens of brightness and 807 feet of throw. Choose from four different output modes plus SOS and strobe settings to select the perfect lighting parameters for your needs. Made from lightweight and durable anodized 6061-T6 aluminum alloy and outfitted with AR-coated scratch-resistant tempered glass, the 360X1 is IPX-8 waterproof, rechargeable, and ready for the roughest conditions.

This Seiko 5 Sports watch is affectionately nicknamed the Fifty Fathoms, as it features design elements from the iconic diver of the same name. The watch utilizes a Seiko 23-jewel 7S36 automatic movement set inside a 42-millimeter stainless steel case. The polished block hour markers are tipped with Lumibright, and the sword hands are large and lumed as well. A 120-click unidirectional rotating bezel features a triangle at 12 o'clock and Arabic numerals. Set within the bezel is a domed Hardlex crystal. The watch features a day and date window at 3 o'clock, while a display caseback offers you a peek at the inner workings of the movement.

prod_description: Standing over a mound of bones and scorched earth, the Gnarly Drakon is an intimidating presence. Sitting atop your keyboard, the Gnarly Drakon artisan keycap is a glimmering gemstone worthy of a dragon's treasure hoard. Made from resin and hand-painted by the keycap artisans at Dwarf Factory, this mythic keycap can handle your most intense keystrokes and look good while doing it. Choose from five colorways, and get lost in the intricate details of the Gnarly Drakon and his otherworldly environment. Available in both SA Row 1 and DOM profiles, this keycap is compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones

More tools, less hassle. That's the motive behind the MoTool 9-in-1 multi-tool from NexTool. Precisely engineered from 30Cr13 stainless steel, this ergonomic device contains nine different tools, all in one pocket-sized solution. Tools in the Mo-Tool include: needle-nose pliers, standard pliers, fine wire pliers, thick wire pliers, a wood saw, an adjustable wrench, a main knife, a Phillips screwdriver, and a word screwdriver. With a patented folding design that's both powerful and compact, the MoTool is the ultimate companion for taking on life's many quick fixes.

The Nitecore EA45S is a rock-solid handheld flashlight made to maximize beam distance. Because its body is molded from a single piece of liquified aerospace-grade aluminum, the EA45S is up to 200 percent stronger than traditional three-piece flashlights. Plus, the CREE XP-L HI V3 LED is designed with a highly concentrated beam and Nitecore's Crystal Coating technology for maximum throw. At full blast, it pumps out an impressive 1,000 lumens and casts a beam over 1,300 feet. And when the light gets hot, it maintains its temperature by dissipating up to 30 percent more heat thanks to the external cooling fins.
