prod_description: We could all use a breath of fresh air. Your keyboard is no different. Styled in wintery blue or forest green, the Deep Forest keycap set from Tai-Hao is a cool addition to any keyboard. Made of thick PBT plastic with bold shine-through legends, the keycaps work in perfect concert with backlit boards. The OEM profile provides a satisfying feel from row to row, while the doubleshot construction ensures the keycaps will last for many cold fronts to come. The base kit includes a whopping 132 keys, but you can add a set of 8 additional keys for ISO layouts if you like.

Brad Zinker's Urban Trapper is hailed as one of the most easy-to-carry everyday folders on the market. And because of its popularity, it's been riffed on over the years with different sizes and blade shapes. This version sports a lengthy tanto blade measuring 3.4 inches. Designed for piercing, the tanto features a compound grind for added strength at the tip. The blade is made from VG-10, a high-carbon-content steel manufactured in Japan, and the handle is made from tough and lightweight titanium. Skeletonized to reduce weight, the handle has a futuristic look. To deploy the blade, simply press on the flipper and it rotates open, locking via frame lock.

prod_name: CJRB Barranca D2 Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: The definition of a barranca is a steep cliff or bluff. Seeing the blade shape on the CJRB Barranca, the definition rings even truer. A powerful 3.7-inch wharncliffe, the blade is tall and craggy, with a prominent curve on the spine not unlike the unpredictable highs and lows of a rocky desert outcrop. Made from D2 steel, the blade is as tough as it looks. G-10 scales and a liner lock make up the handle. A shingle-like texture runs through the middle of the G-10 slabs for added grip retention. Wrapping up the design is a tip-up pocket clip suitable for carry on either side. If you prefer a heavier feel (it's nearly twice the weight!), go for the copper model.

Scotch, wine, clothing, what have you: You don't earn the title of Red Label unless you deserve it. The same goes for timepieces. Swiss-made, the Movado Red Label watch has looks that kill. This sophisticated, astonishingly minimal watch is perfect for a nice occasion. Absent of indexes, date windows, and even a seconds hand, it's as clean as it gets. Because of this dial layout, the eye is drawn to 12 o'clock, where lies a concave dot a signature Movado motif. Powered by an automatic Swiss movement, the Red Label stays in shape thanks to a polished stainless steel case and sapphire crystal. Get yours in a 38- or 42-millimeter case width.

prod_name: Dekoni Premium Ear Pads for Sony WH-1000XM2 & XM3
prod_description: These ear pads bring the excellent reputation of Dekoni Audio pads to one of the world's most popular wireless headphones. Using cutting-edge technology and measurement devices, Dekoni has been able to make an ear pad that not only improves the headphone's passive isolation by about 6 dB, but also accentuates the sound. The pads come in two finishes: Choice Leather and Choice Suede. Both are extremely soft, durable synthetic materials that offer a vegan alternative to true leather and suede options. A plastic attachment bracket is included. Please note these pads are not compatible with Sony's WH-1000XM3.

prod_description: Today's top earplugs deliver strong ear protection with excellent audio fidelity. The Rooth C&P U-03 Earplugs take things a step further. Unlike other models with single acoustic filtration systems, the U-03 earplugs are available in four filters each with its own unique design to suit specific listening preferences. The white filter offers 27 dB of attenuation, great for the ultra-loud industrial environments or job sites. The red filter offers 25 dB of attenuation, perfect for those who want to filter damaging high frequencies while retaining the ability to communicate. The green filter offers 23 dB of attenuation, making it a good choice for concert-goers, factory workers, and those who need to hear more of their immediate environments. Finally, the black, blue, and orange filters offer 20 dB of attenuation, perfect for moderately noisy environments like warehouses and smaller construction sites.

The sequel to hiliDAC's well-received Beam, the Beam 2 is a high-performing DAC/amp that easily fits in your palm. To deliver exceptional sound and amplification that punches way above its weight class, the Beam 2 is equipped with an audiophile-grade ESS9281C Pro DAC and an amplifier capable of outputting 240 mW at 32 ohms. It also features a 3.5-millimeter single-ended headphone port and 2.5-millimeter fully balanced port. The Beam 2's left and right channels have independent op amps and high-thrust circuit designs, and the light on its body changes color according to the decoded music format: red for SD audio, blue for HD audio, and rose red for MQA audio.

The Flash 1.0 Bluetooth speaker from Acoustic Research delivers premium sound in a portable package. Weighing just over one pound, the Flash 1.0 is equipped with two 5-watt speakers capable of reaching 90 decibels in volume together. High-quality hardware and strong quality control from Acoustic Research deliver lush overall sound quality, while Bluetooth with aptX ensures excellent wireless connectivity. Additional ports and hardware on the Flash 1.0 include a 3.5-millimeter line-in, a USB-device charging port, and a digital microphone with cVc Echo Cancellation. Capable lasting up to one year on standby mode without needing a charge, this speaker is ready for any outing.

Known for making some of the finest headphones around, Beyerdynamic puts years of audio research and expert design into every set of cans. Another entry in the company's successful DT line, the DT990 Pro headphones have a lighter weight and a slightly adjusted sound signature compared to their Premium counterparts. Set onto a stainless steel frame, the adjustable padded headband and velour ear pads keep you comfortable for hours of listening, removing headphone fatigue from your vocabulary. Finally, the 9.8-foot cable extends your roaming range.

What began as a marketing experiment in the late 1980s has become the country's number-one lockpick manufacturer. Now the most recognized name in the industry, SouthOrd takes pride in producing long-lasting stainless steel tools fabricated entirely in the United States.

Featuring 82 keys, this Magicforce keyboard makes excellent use of its compact form factor. The keyboard features a floating-key design for easy cleaning and maintenance. The doubleshot PBT keycaps are compatible with both Gateron and Cherry MX switches, and they're shot with clear legends to enhance the backlighting. Speaking of backlighting, this beauty has nine lighting modes and six brightness levels to set the tone. Also notable are the three DIP switches that allow you to disable the Windows key, swap the Caps Lock with the left Ctrl key, or swap the Windows key with the functions. Of course, because typists come in all forms, we're offering tons of different switches to customize the feel, too.

For the objectivist audiophile seeking a complete desktop solution, there's the Massdrop O2 + SDAC: a DAC/amp that brings two great products together in one affordable, easy-to-use package. It features the Massdrop Objective 2 (or O2), the community's favorite solid-state amp, alongside the Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC (or SDAC), a collaboration with a company long known for its incredibly accurate, transparent studio gear. The result is an all-in-one unit that measures objectively well and works with a variety of headphone impedances. Plus, its small form factor is designed to stack with the Massdrop Ã Cavalli Audio Liquid Carbon X Amp and other Massdrop Made audiophile products.

The Nitecore NU25 rechargeable headlamp is about the size of a box of matches, but it delivers 360 lumens. Featuring a remarkable 10 different modes, it allows you to adapt in low light, harsh light, on the hunt, and in distress. The 100-degree beam angle is wide enough to guide a group through the forest or work under the hood of your car. Capable of blasting a beam nearly the length of a football field, it's nothing to underestimate in terms of beam distance, either. What's more, it's IP66 waterproof and 1.5-meter impact resistant and comes with a comfy adjustable headband.

The Tissot Titanium Quartz Watch is a versatile timepiece with style and functionality to spare. Made in Switzerland, it features a quartz movement, ETA-caliber G10.211 engine, and titanium case with matching band. To take on timing tasks of all kinds, it's equipped with a calendar, chronograph, and three subdials (60-second, 30-minute, and tenth-of-a-second). Water resistant down to 100 meters and available here in three styles, this watch is one you'll want to take with you wherever you go.

prod_name: Oris Artix GT Day Date Automatic Watch
prod_description: Having produced timepieces for more than a century, Oris has earned its reputation among watch enthusiasts and casual wearers alike. The Artix GT Day Date automatic pairs a solid build with a versatile look for the everyday and a nice occasion. The dial layout is relatively straightforward, but at 6 o'clock is where the watch really shines. Featuring a circular day-date complication that partially covers the 6 o'clock index, the dial has an avante garde element to it. (If you prefer a more traditional look, opt for the Oris BC3 Advanced model, also available.) Within the stainless steel case lies an Oris 735 26-jewel movement that'll tick for 38 hours on a full charge. If you take it in the water, it's protected to 100 meters not to mention the dial is fitted with a sapphire crystal.

prod_description: Whether you're impressioning, picking, bumping, or just learning the tricks of the trade, this kit has more than enough to facilitate it. Combining a handful of lockpicking standbys, it's suitable for beginners and those with more experience in the field. As far as contents, it's got a Southord 14-piece professional lockpick set, a practice stand, and a set of eight domestic bump keys, plus a 5-pin mortise cylinder and a 6-pin KIK cylinder in two keyways with working keys for each. The kit also comes with some materials to help you study and perfect your skills, including multiple ebooks, a printed lockpicking manual, and a Keys to Impressioning CD.

The Nitecore TINI is the perfect keychain light you'll hardly notice in your pocket until it's time to use it, of course. With a 380-lumen beam and 64 meters of throw on turbo mode, this compact light boasts much more power than meets the eye. It's outfitted with a built-in 280mAh battery, which means you don't have to replace it every time; just plug in a micro USB cable and it will fuel up fast. Don't worry about dropping it or getting it a little wet, as the TINI is both impact and water resistant. What's more, it comes in multiple colors to match your keychain carry.

Available on Massdrop before anywhere else, the BG01 Lion G-10 series is an exciting new direction for Bestech. It features G-10 scales (in your choice of three colors) and a blade made from tough D2 tool steel. The G-10 handle is smooth yet grippy, with ridges surrounding the blade pivot that make it look as if the blade is charging forward in the wind. The blade rides on a ceramic ball bearing system for smooth deployment. Just press the flipper and it will rotate open. For lockup, the knife has stainless steel liners that have been skeletonized to reduce weight. Also notable, the lanyard hole is connected to the backspacer and protrudes from the pommel. It could be used as a backup glassbreaker in dire straits.

prod_name: LAMY Safari PokÃ©mon Pikachu Limited-Edition Set
prod_description: A special edition from LAMY and The PokÃ©mon Company, this fountain pen set was released in China in late 2018 and is available in the US exclusively through Massdrop. It features everyone's favorite electric mouse, Pikachu, on the light, comfortable, and beginner-friendly Safari model. With a yellow body and a red pocket clip, the pen's color scheme is spot on. Attach either of two included figures to the clip so Pikachu can come along on your writing adventures. When you're done, your pen can rest in the weighted PokÃ© Ball pen holder. Along with a yellow carrying case, you'll get a heavier-duty gift box with a special surprise: it says, Pika, Pika, Pikachu!

New from respected speaker-maker HiVi, the AW-65 wireless headphones bring big sound to any environment. Listen wirelessly with built-in Bluetooth 4.1 technology, featuring support for A2DP, AVRCP, HSP, and HFP formats and a 10-meter range. A powerful 400-milliamp lithium battery will keep your music playing for up to 20 hours, and if that battery ever runs low, you can easily switch to a wired connection in seconds. No matter which way you listen, you'll experience powerful and detailed sound from 40-millimeter drivers plus a featherlight form factor weighing just 7.4 ounces.

prod_description: Founded in New York in 1892, Ingersoll specializes in watches with American heritage. Over the last century plus, the company's made a lot of timepieces, but perhaps the most indelible is its Mickey Mouse series, which sold more than 5 million pieces throughout the 1930s and 40s. The Ingersoll New Haven automatic may not have a cartoon mouse on it, but it has a classic look that jives in virtually any setting. Pairing slim indices and hands with a clean, rounded case, the watch is comfy and elegant. Aside from a day-date window, it's very spare, owing to its versatility. Powered by a Miyota 820A automatic movement, the New Haven is water resistant to 50 meters and available in five styles.

prod_name: hiliDAC Audirect Atom Pro Portable DAC/Amp
prod_description: High-performing digital-to-audio conversion shouldn't have to take up a lot of space. That's the central idea behind the Audirect hiliDAC Atom Pro: a portable DAC/amp smaller than most USB drives. The Atom Pro includes MQA Renderer technology, which can connect to an MQA Core signal and complete the final processing of an MQA file. It glows magenta to indicate that it's rendering an MQA stream or file. (Note that a separate MQA core decoder is needed to achieve MQA audio.) Driving the Atom Pro's impressive audio is an ES9281C PRO chip from ESS and a crystal oscillator capable of delivering 119 dB DNR and 0.0003% THD + N.

Bringing isolated audio and custom listening features to an IEM form factor, the IMR R2 Red IEM delivers strong sound in a space-efficient package. The R2 Red uses the same chassis shape as IMR's highly regarded R2 Aten, except the Red has a closed design for extra isolation. Inside, each earphone features a high-resolution piezo ceramic driver and a new 13.5-millimeter beryllium-composite dynamic driver with uprated neodymium motors. Together, these drivers create a large soundstage with precise instrument placement and a frequency range of 10 to 45,000 hertz. Equipped with a single-crystal, oxygen-free copper braided cable, the R2 Red also comes with several interchangeable nozzles that allow users to customize its sound signature across bass, mid, and treble frequencies.

A newly released iteration of the DAC-X6, this DAC/amp from FX Audio shines in the sub-$100 category. It uses the highly regarded CS4398 and CS8416 in its DAC chipset, along with the OPA2134 opamp, and supports files up to 16 bit/192 kHz and 24 bit/96 kHz. Compact and adaptable, it's ideal as a desktop unit for sending a signal out to PC speakers, or for use as a powerful headphone amp. On the back panel, you'll find inputs for USB, optical, and coaxial, plus an RCA signal output. On the front, there's a stepped attenuator for super-smooth control over your music's volume.

prod_description: These are Dekoni Audio's much-anticipated ear pads for Focal, compatible with the Elear, Clear, Clear Pro, and Utopia headphones, along with the Massdrop x Focal Elex. Designed to take your listening experience up a notch, the pads feature slow-rebound, high-density memory foam wrapped in your choice of velour, sheepskin, or a combination of the two. They provide a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening all while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. Plus, everyone at Dekoni wears glasses, so this was taken into account when designing the pads.

Made from durable PBT, the caps are resistant to oils that accumulate from the skin.

Available in a neutral gray colorway, these Cherry MX-compatible keycaps will fit on most boards. They're made from PBT for a long-lasting build plus, the legends won't rub off thanks to a dye-sub printing process.

BLON has established itself as one of the industry's premier audio brands, building products that are both high-performing and affordable. Newest in the BLON product line is the BL-03, an IEM outfitted with a 10-millimeter dynamic driver to deliver powerful, precise sound for all types of audio. From audioblog18's 5-star review on Head-Fi: [The BL-03] has very good bass with deep and textured presentation. Midrange sounds natural with commendable timbre. Treble has a good amount of air and sparkle. Made from the composite alloy Kirsite with mirror-polished cavities, this heart-shaped IEM catches eyes and sits comfortably in any ear.

Italian craftsmanship. That's what you get with Salvatore Ferragamo products. Here, these versatile sunglasses embody style and performance.  The sunglasses made in Italy and come with a carrying case, cleaning cloth, and soft carrying pouch.

prod_description: Headphone amplifiers come in a variety of circuit designs, each with its own advantages and drawbacks, but there's one main determining faction: distortion level. Credited with having the lowest possible distortion, Output Transformer-Less (OTL) headphone amps cut out a key part of conventional amplifier design to eliminate a major cause of audible distortion. Without the Output Transformer, you get clearer sound, powered tubes, and overall better amplification. Arriving with an OTL design, the DarkVoice 335SE OTL Headphone Amp gives you a blank backdrop to properly broadcast your favorite jams.

Wrist rests can do more for your keyboard setup than simply enhancing ergonomics; they can add a whole-new look to your desktop. That's why mStone has been making them out of innovative materials, to provide a wide range of options for keyboard lovers everywhere. These are made from frosty K5 glass, like something you might find on the walls of a steam room. Available in three sizes, they're heavy and fitted with rubber feet to stay put while you type.

The Massdrop ALT High-Profile is just like the original ALT, but now  it comes with a tall CNC-aluminum case that covers the switches.  Machined at a 6-degree angle, the case is ergonomically crafted for a  natural feel. Absent of function keys, the keyboard wastes no space but  it still has a full set of arrows and numerals. Thanks to the Kaihua  switch sockets, it allows you to swap switches whenever you want with no  soldering required. It's also fully programmable via QMK, meaning you  can assign macros or custom keybinds to every key. With dual USB-C  connectors, the ALT High-Profile is outfitted with the latest  connections. What's more, it has customizable RGB backlighting and  underlighting. Set it to a single color or light it up with a rainbow  wave pattern.

prod_name: Sabbat E12 Ultra TWS Bluetooth 5.0 IEM
prod_description: New from Sabbat, the E12 Ultra TWS Bluetooth 5.0 IEM is an excellent wireless companion with versatile performance features. An upgrade from the E12, the E12 Ultra features a Qualcomm chip with Bluetooth 5.0 and added APTX decoding, all of which improve audio quality. At the center of this IEM's Hi-Res audio build is a 10-millimeter dynamic driver with bio-fiber paper film, which vividly articulates sound details across all frequencies. For those who want to talk, the E12 Ultra has support for binaural calls, plus new microphone noise-reduction technology to increase clarity. For added convenience, the included case charges each earbud and supports wireless smartphone charging. With an ergonomic ear shape and premium metal plating, the E12 Ultra is ready for listening (and talking) wherever you want to take it.

Take your IEMs to the next level with the Tripowin C8 IEM cable. Available for MMCX, 2-pin, and recessed 2-pin IEMs, the cable features eight cores made of silver and copper. The 3.5-millimeter audio jack is designed for cellphones and standard music players, while the 2.5- and 4.4-millimeter balanced audio jacks are predominantly used for professional audio players.

The successor to the popular Orient Mako, the Mako II is outfitted with a new movement and a more precise 120-click unidirectional bezel. Powered by F6922 caliber automatic movement, it's manual-wind compatible and has hacking seconds. Aesthetically, it's the same as the original Mako, save for the exclusion of the second crown at 2 o'clock. The case is still made from stainless steel and the watch is still water resistant to an impressive 200 meters (it is a diver, after all). The window at 3 tracks the day and date, while the lumed hands offer visibility in conditions devoid of light.

prod_name: Ballast Swiss Made Ladies' Quartz Watches
prod_description: Combining a bold construction and design with ladylike styling, the Ballast Vanguard and Valiant watches are made in Switzerland and are perfect for an outdoor adventure or a night on the town. Starting with the Vanguard, this 200-meter water-resistant timepiece features an integrated silicone strap and a reliable quartz movement. Design-wise, it measures 38 millimeters wide and has thick diver-style indexes and hands, a date window at 3, and a bezel studded with gems to catch eyes. The Valiant, on the other hand, measures 42 millimeters. A 100-meter water-resistant watch, it features a different dial design and the large canteen-style crown that Ballast has come to be known for. Get the Vanguard or the Valiant in your choice of many styles.

prod_description: Keep your belongings safe and secure (no matter the time, place, or weather forecast) with the Hopkins backpack from Olympia USA. Made of water-resistant, high-density 1680d ballistic polyester, it's ready for rainy bike rides, travel days, and commutes. The breathable padded back panel and shoulder straps keep you comfortable, while the interior laptop sleeve and exterior pockets help you stay organized. As an extra defense against the elements, the bag has a drawcord closure topped by a foldover lid with a magnetic strap and buckle. Finishing touches include a sternum strap, a side and top handle, and a printed lining.

prod_name: ChenYi Harvest Season Stitched-Edge Desk Mat
prod_description: A quality desk mat can be the perfect missing piece on your desktop. Feeling fruity? This array of desk mats highlights some of the most popular fruits around, from strawberries and oranges to bananas and the ever-popular avocado (it's actually considered a fruit!). Made from Jacquard fabric with a soft rubber lining, stitched edges, and a grippy bottom, these desk mats are in for the long haul. Each one has a consistent pattern fruit, with a darker, more prominent fruit in one corner.

Great for cooking food on a stove or over a campfire, these titanium utensils are durable, lightweight, and easy to pack. The set includes two forks, two spoons, and two cases perfect for you and a friend or significant other. Thanks to the nesting design, the spoons and forks take up little space. Of course, because they're made from titanium, they're rust and corrosion-proof as well.

Until World War I, wrist watches weren't commonplace. Once soldiers returned home wearing the reliable and rugged timekeeping instruments they wore in battle, they set a lasting trend: the field watch. Today, Szanto has reimagined the traditional field-watch design in this 42-millimeter Japanese quartz version. Armed with large, stylized Arabic numerals and 24-hour markings inside of them, the watch stays true to tradition in some respects. However, the fluted seashell bezel and super-lumed hands and markers bring this timepiece right into the 21st century. Bringing it all together is the half onion crown at 3 o'clock.

prod_name: Bestech 1710 IMP Titanium Frame Lock Knife
prod_description: Just like its larger brother, the Goblin, the Bestech IMP features a stout, aggressively jimped blade and thick handle. A compact folder with premium materials, the IMP is easy to control and easier to carry. The pudgy modified wharncliffe blade is great for small, repeatable tasks, and thanks to its CPM-S35VN build, it'll keep an edge for a long time. The handle is short and stubby, but offers a surprisingly full grip in the hand. Made from a combination of titanium and carbon fiber, it'll hold up through stressful work and it looks the part, to boot. Inside it is a strong frame lock to secure the blade. The outside is fitted with a tip-up clip, also made from titanium. If you don't want this little monster wreaking havoc in your pocket, you can clip it to a lanyard if you like.

prod_name: Boker Kwaiken Duplex G-10 Folding Knife
prod_description: Combining the best features of a gentleman's folder and a tactical knife, the Boker Kwaiken has undergone many variations over the years and this one may be the boldest yet. Designed by Lucas Burnley, this flipper features a streamlined, tapered look and a 3.5-inch blade made from VG-10 stainless steel: a high-carbon-content steel manufactured in Japan. On this version, the blade is cut with a duplex grind. Because the heel is thicker than the tip, it offers extra strength for things like cutting rope and hard materials, while the tip can be used for tasks that require more precision. The blade is easily deployed using the flipper tab, which doubles as a finger guard once opened. For the handle, Boker has chosen G-10: a grippy composite that'll hold up in any weather.

Ray-Ban knows its way around a pair of sunglasses after all, it's been making em since 1937. Today, the company reimagines time-honored styles in new models like the Blaze Clubmaster. These shades take the shape popularized in the 1950s and update it with a flat lens-over-frame design. The result is a clean-cut, contemporary style complete with a metal frame and adjustable nose pads for comfort.

Treat your ears to a rich soundstage and a distinct retro feel with the all-new BLON B20 Planar Magnetic Headphones. Vintage and contemporary design intersect at the B20's audio cavity, which is made from real wood and delivers vivid acoustics while sitting over the entire ear. Together with an open-back structure and full-size planar magnetic drivers, this design creates an expansive sound stage with expressive articulation and low impedance. (It's also the same internal structure used in the highly regarded SendyAudio Aiva.) The stylistic blend is completed with a stainless steel expansion bracket and axis of rotation, while comfort and convenience are topped off with all-leather earpads and a detachable cable.

prod_description: TFZ's lineup of affordable IEMs has garnered praise throughout the audiophile community for its accurate sounds and ergonomic, comfortable designs and the No.3 IEM is another shining example of the company's dedication to its craft. It features an 11.4-millimeter, double-magnetized, double-cavity driver with a warm sound signature. Thanks to the 0.78-millimeter connector, you can swap out or upgrade cables with ease. With all that, it's no surprise why cqtek from Head-Fi had this to say: "No.3 is a V-alternative that offers a more focused sound in the sub-bass and high mids. In addition, their mids are closer with nearby voices and very enjoyable. Its profile differs from the typical V of sunken, darker and distant mids, guaranteeing a more vivid, clear, and sharp listening without treble hammerings.

prod_name: Topping DX3 Pro LDAC Version 2 DAC/Amp
prod_description: New from Topping, an industry leader in professional-grade audio equipment, the DX3 Pro LDAC Version 2 DAC/amp is a next-generation audio solution for your desk. Equipped with much of the same hardware that made the original DX3 Pro so popular an XMOS XU208 USB chip with dual AK4493 DACs, an OPA1612 op amp, and an AK4118 receiver this version adds LDAC connectivity for high-resolution listening over Bluetooth 5.0. It also packs impressive power for headphone listening: 700mW in each channel at 32 ohms, or 125mW at 300 ohms. Prefer to use a more powerful headphone amp? The DX3 Pro LDAC Version 2 can operate as a DAC via its RCA output. Less than 5 inches long and 2 inches tall, it fits well on most desks.

prod_name: Kyoto DSA PBT All Over Dye-Subbed Keycap Set
prod_description: Like taking a relaxing stroll through a garden of cherry blossoms, or sitting in a city park admiring a view of Mount Fuji, these keycaps create a sense of peace of mind. Featuring a combination of pinks with green, pink, and black legends, the caps are inspired by traditional elements of Japanese culture. Sculpted in DSA profile, the set features 122 total keys (including some bonus keys to further customize your board) and is compatible with Cherry MX switches. For durability's sake, they're made through a process of dye sublimation from strong PBT plastic.

Designed for MX-compatible PCBs, these gold-plated PCB screw-in stabilizers from Zeal prevent regular Cherry PCB mount stabilizers from popping out of your custom build while removing stabilized keys. A break from the standard white or black stabilizers, this unique set gives your board a clear (and golden) edge. The insert is "pre-clipped, so there's no need to clip the feet. Plus, the outer casing is specifically designed to prevent threads from stripping.

prod_name: NPKC Gradient PBT Doubleshot Side-Lit Keycap Set
prod_description: This set of PBT keycaps produces a spectacular multi-colored fade as it crosses your keyboard. Each keycap is made of individually colored plastic never painted while the laser-etched legends will stay true over time. On these sets, the legends are printed on the front, which helps preserve the minimal look on top. All sets come with 108 Cherry MXcompatible keycaps in OEM profile.

Packing 720 lumens into a 2.5-inch frame, the Nitecore TIP2 is a little brick you'll never leave home without. Powered by a 500mAh internal battery and two CREE XP-G3 LEDs, the TIP2 drastically outperforms its small stature. Boasting a max runtime of 55 hours, it'll last a long time, too. Don't worry about dropping it or throwing your keys around: thanks to the waterproof CNC aluminum body, the TIP2 can take a beating in the field.

prod_name: Massdrop x Apogee Slice & Dice Bundle
prod_description: A good set of kitchen knives can quickly take your meals from good to great. That's why we've bundled our best Apogee blades to help you make the cut literally. Now for a limited time, get our Apogee Vital 8 chef's knife, our Takumi Nakiri 7 vegetable knife, and your choice of our Takumi paring or petty knife for only $150. Japanese-inspired and crafted with premium materials, the knives in this set can handle crucial cutting tasks, ranging from garnish preparing to vegetable chopping to turkey carving.

Perhaps best known for its 24-hour Airman tool watch, Glycine has been producing timepieces since 1914. This drop features 6 different styles of three different models of the Purist version of the famous Airman: a timepiece that only makes one full revolution in 24 hours. The dial is fixed with Arabic numerals all the way up to 24, and has a date window at the traditional 3 o'clock position. Based on Glycine's own GL293 21-jewel movement, each model has a 42-hour power reserve. The movement is protected by a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal, which combine for a water resistance of 100 meters. A stainless steel bezel surrounds the crystal. Twist the crown at 4 o'clock to access and set it.

prod_description: The Fallkniven Pro series of fixed-blade survival knives is backed by over 30 years of expertise in Swedish hunting and fishing tradition. All three knives in the series feature a blade made from laminated cobalt steel that's heat treated to a Rockwell hardness of 60. This new and improved steel delivers better edge retention than the laminated VG-10 used in the standard series.

Weighing just 1.7 ounces, the Maratac A/B dual compartment cache is designed for easy accessibility to small items. Machined from your choice of brass, stainless steel, or titanium (nearly half as heavy), this airtight capsule features two openings. On one side is a keychain loop so you can secure it to your daily gear. The other is only connected to the body, so you can just detach one side and leave it secured to your keychain on the go. Great for carrying emergency cash, tinder, medicine, water tablets, and other small objects, the durable container is made to withstand harsh treatment.

prod_description: What has two opposable thumbs, a futuristic fashion sense, and a bad attitude? Diesel: the no-nonsense ape ready for battle and built into the top of a keycap. He may not look happy, but he's on your side. Designed and manufactured by the keycap team at Hot Keys Project, the Diesel artisan keycap is made from smooth and sturdy resin and shaped with impressive realism. From Diesel's detailed helmet and matted fur to his bared teeth and shine-through eyes, Hot Keys Project has done this ape warrior justice. Choose from six colorways, and add Diesel to a backlit keyboard for full effect.

Tin Audio has earned a lot of praise from audio enthusiasts for its T2 and T2 Pro: two IEMs whose sound and build quality punch well above their price. A continuation of this series, the T3 promises more of the same, with dual drivers (one 10-millimeter dynamic and one Knowles balanced armature) and an upgraded 5N eight-core oxygen-free-copper-plated silver cable. This IEM excels in the detail retrieval and soundstage departments, and delivers a good sense of balance with a tone that's neither too bright nor too dark. Plus, it's built with MMCX connectors for easy cable replacement.

prod_name: Amare Creator Slip Joint by Tashi Bharucha
prod_description: Tashi Bharucha's work leans toward the arty side of knifemaking. Real Steel's leans toward the tactical, functional side. Put the two together and you've got a perfect pair. The Creator is a handsome 10-inch slip joint with a 4.4-inch blade. Though the knife is built with rugged materials like a VG-10 blade and a G-10 handle it maintains the elegant form factor that Tashi Bharucha has made famous. Adding to the knife's charm is a luminous backspacer (Black version only*), visible in dark conditions. Overall, the Creator feels like a dream in the hand, thanks to the aggressive curvature of the handle and scalloped spine for thumb placement. It's a brilliant meeting between form and function.

Sturmanskie is known for its watches that harken back to the Cold War era. A good example is the Heritage Polar Automatic watch: a true 24-hour timepiece that completes just one full revolution each day. Adorned with large Arabic numerals and cyrillic markings, it calls to mind a Soviet train station or an officer's watch. To further emphasize the Russian heritage, the watch utilizes a true Russian automatic movement built by the Vostok company of Chistopol.  An oversized triangular crown makes the watch easy to adjust. As far as materials, it's crafted from stainless steel with an acrylic crystal.

prod_name: QSP Puffin S35VN Frame Lock Knife
prod_description: A mid-sized folder built with premium materials, the QSP Puffin is a handsome manual-opening knife you can take anywhere with ease. This titanium frame lock boasts a strong 3-inch S35VN blade that deploys manually via thumbstud an improvement over the original version, which had a difficult-to-open thumb hole. This new thumbstud construction not only adds an element of elegance, but it rides as smooth as butter, thanks to the ceramic ball bearings. Another classy touch is the carbon fiber insert, which has a cutout for the pocket clip for ambidextrous tip-up carry. Available with a stonewashed or satin-finished blade, the Puffin is a perfect fit for any discerning gentleman.

prod_name: CCCP Golden Soviet Submarine Automatic Watch
prod_description: The CCCP watch company began with a mission to engineer watches based on the storied timepieces created by the Soviet Union. The CCCP Golden Soviet Submarine automatic watch is all business. The 46-millimeter dial is appointed with large Arabic numerals and flanked by an aggressively knurled crown for a rugged look. A set of thick hands indicates the current time, which is accurately presented thanks to a Slava 2427 automatic movement. A traditional 3 o'clock date window rounds out the dial for a handsome and masculine look one you can get in your choice of five styles.

Whether you're commuting, shopping, or speeding through foot traffic to get to your gate, the Hillside Meridian puts comfort at the forefront. This bagpack converts from a backpack to a messenger bag in seconds by simply dropping a shoulder strap or sliding another one on. Made with your choice of vegetable-tanned leather or water-resistant nylon, the bag features a water-resistant liner, durable YKK zippers, and plenty of internal storage. Take advantage of five storage pockets, a zippered outer convenience pocket, and a dedicated TSA pocket for your laptop perfect for traveling efficiently.

prod_name: Little Dot MKIII & MKIII SE Tube Headphone Amps
prod_description: Instead of a single cheap tube that gives off muddled sound, the Little Dot MKIII features four tubes: two dedicated input tubes and two dedicated output tubes. Letting your left and right audio channels enter through separate RCA ports and pass through channel specific input and output tubes before joining up at the headphone jack, you get a clear signal on both sides with little to no crossover. Encased in solid aluminum, this headphone amp features solid metal construction throughout the entire device. And in case you're also looking for a partner for your speakers, the Little Dot MKIII Headphone Amplifier can also be used as a preamp via the RCA outputs on the back.

prod_name: Durgod Taurus K320 TKL Mechanical Keyboard
prod_description: A reliable TKL keyboard with 87 keys, the Durgod Taurus K320 comes in two different colorways with your choice of Cherry MX switches, allowing you to get just the feel you want whether you prefer a switch with some bump or a speedy linear feel. On top of the switches go the doubleshot PBT keycaps, which also come in different colors to match the case. Thanks to full N-key rollover and anti-ghosting technology, the keyboard will register all of your commands, even when input rapidly. The case, made from plastic, comes with adjustable feet so you can prop the keyboard up at an angle to relieve your wrists. Included is a dust cover, two USB type-C cables, a keycap puller, and a logo sticker.

Audiophiles in search of an all-in-one DAC/amp that doesn't skimp on specs will find a strong candidate in the xDuoo TA-30 Tube DAC/Amp. The TA-30 is equipped with an ESS ES9038Q2M DAC and a headphone amplifier that can output an impressive 3000 milliwatts at 32 ohms enough to drive the most demanding headphones. Within the headphone amp are two tubes: a thick-sounding 5Z3P used for high-voltage rectification, and a precise-sounding ECC82 tube used to process the audio. To meet all connectivity needs, the TA-30 has USB, coaxial, and optical inputs. It also features Bluetooth 5.0 powered by a Qualcomm CSR8675 chip which supports SBC, AAC, aptX, aptX LL, aptX HD, and LDAC formats.

It's not often that a fully balanced DAC/amp comes along at a price like this. The Topping DX7s improves upon the well-regarded DX7 by taking both the DAC and headphone amp sections up a notch. It features two ES9038 DAC chips and a more powerful amplifier especially the four-pin balanced out, which is rated at 1,000 mW x 2 at 32 ohms and 546 mW x 2 at 300 ohms (compared to the original DX7, which outputted 420 mW at 300 ohms). Equipped with two XLR outputs, a coaxial input and output, and a USB input, the DX7s can be paired with a computer or used as the center of an audio setup. It can run either 110V or 220V, has a power mode switch on the left side, and is complete with an OLED display.

The BG06 Kendo G-10 series is an exciting new direction for Bestech. It features G-10 scales (in your choice of three colors) and a blade made from tough D2 tool steel. The blade is done in a tanto style like that of traditional Japanese swords, only shortened to fit in most any pocket. Smooth yet grippy, the G-10 handle is straight and about half-an-inch thick for a solid feel in the hand. The blade rides on a ceramic ball bearing system for smooth deployment. Just press the flipper and it will rotate open. For lockup, the knife has stainless steel liners that have been skeletonized to reduce weight. Also of note is the deep carry pocket clip to help you keep a low profile.

The WOLF Windsor watch box is both a storage and display case, and it comes in three different sizes, accommodating as few as five watches or as many as 15. Each one is finished with a padded, black-pebbled leatherette exterior, silver silk lining, and a tempered glass lid that doubles as a viewing window. The watch cushions are spaced 1.5 inches apart from one another, and they can accommodate watch cases as large as 52 millimeters. The 10-piece watch box can be purchased with a drawer, which features eight ring rolls and 17 jewelry compartments.

prod_name: SMSL SU-8 Version 2 DAC, SH-8 & DA-8
prod_description: Ideal for placing at the center of your hi-fi system, the SMSL SU-8 boasts high-end DAC features at a surprisingly low price. It's built with many of the current specs you might expect to see in a more expensive model, including dual ES9038Q2M DAC chips, an xCORE-200 XMOS USB audio solution, and dual XLR outs for a fully balanced output. It also has optical, coaxial, and USB inputs, as well as an RCA out. The nine types of sound color settings use the DSP of the ES9038 to adjust the levels of distortion and make your music sound different. If you're running a more complex setup, you can use the included remote to switch between sources. Also available to bundle or order as standalone options are the SH-8 and the DA-8 , powerful amps great for use with the SU-8 or other DACs. When stacked with the SU-8, these amps create a sleek, compact, and fully balanced setup great for powering any pair of headphones.
prod_varities: ['SU-8 DAC', 'DA-8 Digital Power Amplifier', 'SH-8 Headphone Amp (-$40)', 'SU-8 and SH-8 Combo (+$110)']

prod_description: The Nextool Taobar is a key-shaped multi-tool that won't open doors but it will open just about anything else. Constructed with a cutting hook and a small, locking blade edge, it's capable of slicing through cardboard, paper, rope, straps, and much more. The hook's unique shape protects the contents of packages from being punctured when opened, and its nonstick Teflon coating ensures the tool won't get caked up. The other half of the tool features a mini pry bar, bottle opener, and a flathead screwdriver. Plus, at just under an ounce, it goes virtually unnoticed on a keychain or lanyard.

Ortholinear keyboards are designed to increase efficiency and reduce finger travel when typing. Though it's large for an ortholinear board, the ID75 gives you free reign over every key so, if you get good with it, it's bound to make work and play a lot more fun and effective. This kit comes with everything you need to build a functioning mechanical keyboard (sans switches), from the plate and PCB to the case and screws. And if you like LEDs, it also comes with an acrylic insert to emphasize the lighting. Crafted with CNC'd aluminum, the case is durable and sleek. What's more, the hot-swappable switch inserts allow you to swap out switches on the fly, without ever picking up a soldering iron. Backed by a Type-C USB connection, the keyboard connects to most new laptops and computers.

Capable of producing a 1,000-lumen beam with 360 feet of throw, the Nitecore HC65 headlamp is a solid option when biking, hiking, setting up camp, and working under the hood. Featuring a remarkable 11 different modes, it allows you to adapt in low light, harsh light, on the hunt, and in distress. Among the modes are seven brightness levels and multiple modes for signalling and emergencies. The built-in red LED is great for night photography, astronomy, and hunting. What's more, the headlamp is IPX-8 waterproof and 1.5-meter impact resistant and comes with a comfy, adjustable headband, an 18650 battery, spare O-rings, and more.

This comprehensive lockpicking bundle is designed to help you work your way up from easy-to-pick locks all the way to the nearly impossible. Comprising seven different locks, including the EZ Rekey cutaway lock in SC and KW keyways, three different types of clear view locks, a 5-pinned mortise cylinder, and a 5-wafer cam lock cylinder, the kit has a wide variety of styles to help you master the art of lockpicking. The EZ Rekey locks include extra pins, springs, and spool drivers so you can set them up in virtually any combination you see fit. If you need a solid mounting base, feel free to add the stand at checkout.
prod_varities: ['Practice Lock Mega Pack', 'Practice Lock Mega Pack With LocksportXPC Stand']

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nextool-16-in-1-flagship-pro-multi-tool/FP/JHjL71TmTlePf3JFn1LE_Nextool 16-In-1 Flagship Pro Multi-Tool MD-874264320.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nextool-16-in-1-flagship-pro-multi-tool/FP/svhYkUsfRm2CvEGCzarv_Nextool 16-In-1 Flagship Pro Multi-Tool MD-874264319.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nextool-16-in-1-flagship-pro-multi-tool/FP/I8kqTx4RQUu6KycsQlnd_Nextool 16-In-1 Flagship Pro Multi-Tool MD-874264321.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nextool-16-in-1-flagship-pro-multi-tool/FP/4DjG5HXoTkKLwH3GaOWM_Nextool 16-In-1 Flagship Pro Multi-Tool MD-874264318.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nextool-16-in-1-flagship-pro-multi-tool/FP/EH5uMvetS4aH0GcwM1Sa_Nextool 16-In-1 Flagship Pro Multi-Tool MD-874264316.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Handy and portable, the Nextool Flagship multi-tool comes with an array of tools to help you get through most daily tasks. Made from stainless steel, it measures just over 4 inches long, so you can take it pretty much anywhere you need it. The Flagship's standout tool is definitely its spring-action needlenose pliers and scissors. Both tools spring back into the open position after closing instead of having to be manually opened again. As far as other tools, it's got a saw, a blade, a Phillips and flathead screwdriver, a glass breaker, and a can opener just to name a few.

Equally sporty and outdoorsy, the Citizen CA0641 transitions well from a hike to a nice dinner afterward. The dial has a lot going on, but it's well balanced in layout. Pushers at 2 and 4 o'clock control the chronograph, while a 24-hour dial at 9 tracks the full day. There's also a black tachymeter bezel to track speed based on time. The internals are Citizen's Eco-Drive B612 solar movement. They're protected thanks to the stainless steel case, which offers a solid 100-meter water-resistance rating.

prod_name: Fanmusic 4-Pin Balanced Cable for HD 58X & HD 6XX
prod_description: Take your headphones to the next level with this 6.5-foot-long cable, compatible with the Massdrop x Sennheiser HD 58X and HD 6XX headphones, along with the Sennheiser HD 580, HD 600, and HD 650. It uses a high-end professional Sommer cable from Germany, made of tightly braided oxygen-free copper that's covered in fabric below the Y split. Durable, not prone to tangling, and soft to the touch, it's ideal for powering your headphones out of a high-powered balanced amplifier to achieve their full potential.

Streamlined and strong, the RB3569 Polarized Sunglasses from Ray-Ban set a high bar for stylish activewear. Sporting a black and silver metal frame that wastes no space, these shades are built for backcountry outings, black-tie affairs, and everything in between. Green polarized lenses protect against glare and UV rays, while rubber temples ensure excellent stability during any activity. Each pair comes with a carrying case and cleaning cloth for upkeep.

From storied Swiss manufacturer Montblanc comes the Heritage Chronometrie: a modestly sized and carefully crafted automatic beauty. Sporting a clean dial in silvery white, this watch has a balanced aesthetic with dual subdials, one for running seconds and the other for the day of the month. Despite the subdials, the watch measures just 40 millimeters wide a manageable size for most. Equipped with the company's own Calibre MB 24.23 movement, the Heritage Chronometrie has a 38-hour power reserve. Golden hands and markers bring a welcome touch of luxury, while an exhibition caseback delivers the detailed look many gearheads can't get enough of.

prod_name: TuyaKnife M390 Envy2 & D2 Boot Knife Combo
prod_description: TuyaKnife's Envy2 is even more enviable than the original Envy. Why? This time around, it features a deep hollow grind for better slicing ability, plus a smoother opening mechanism with ceramic ball bearings. Measuring nearly 8 inches, the Envy2 is strikes a great balance between portability and performance. The blade is made from Bohler M390 stainless steel, which is hailed for its excellent edge retention and corrosion resistance. The handle is a titanium frame for secure lockup. Get it with either black or silver hardware to match your style. In addition to this rock-solid folder, we're throwing in a boot knife and sheath. Styled to match the Envy2, it's the perfect knock-around knife for jobs you don't want to risk your favorite folder on.

The duster of choice for the keyboard community, the O2 Hurricane offers gusts up to 225 miles per hour. Each charge is equal to more than five cans of air, and the unit can be charged up to 500 times, with each charge lasting about 12 minutes of continuous use. Designed for corporate and IT department use, it's great for cleaning keyboards, large computers, server rooms, camera lenses, mirrors, high-end medical equipment, retail displays, complex circuit boards, and more. Each unit comes with two regular straws, two sets of the three-piece attachment kit, and a five-year warranty.

One of Seiko's signature lines of divers, the SNZF series stands out for its clean design and rugged construction. In true diver fashion, the watch has chunky, lumed markers and hands. They pair well with the unidirectional rotating bezel, which comes in handy for keeping track of elapsed time. For the case, Seiko opted for a stainless steel construction with a scratch-resistant Hardlex crystal, contributing to a solid water resistance of 100 meters. A Seiko Caliber 7S36 movement powers the timepiece for 40 hours on a full charge without wear. If you want to see it in action, just flip the watch over.

If you like to build keyboards yourself, this kit from KBDFans gives you the chance to do so. Done in the increasingly popular 75% layout, the keyboard is compact enough to fit on most desktops. The case is made from anodized aluminum and is machined at a 5-degree angle for a natural feel when typing. The PCB is fully programmable, which allows you to assign any key any command you like when you set it up. Outfitted with the latest USB-C connection, the board is fast and efficient, too. Though it doesn't come with switches, you can add them along with a bold 9009 keycap set at checkout if you like.

Datamancer has built a solid reputation making wooden cases for popular keyboards like the Pok3r, Preonic, and ErgoDox. Now, the company has created one for 60-percent keyboards. Available in cherry or walnut, the case has been fitted with 24 total 3-millimeter neodymium magnets that create a secure hold when you're on the go. Pull off the top lid and it will magnetically attach to the edge of the case, acting as a natural wrist rest. The base is fitted with rubber feet to keep it stable, and there are machined holes for the USB cord.

prod_name: Advanced Sound Eartune Live U Earplugs
prod_description: The purpose of earplugs is to protect your ears from loud noise but that protection shouldn't have to come at the expense of audio quality. Designed for concerts and other live shows, the Eartune Live U Earplugs from Advanced Sound Group (ADV) bring listeners the best of both worlds: strong noise reduction and excellent audio fidelity. Designed by ADV's innovative engineers, the Eartune Live U Earplugs feature proprietary acoustic filters that can attenuate (reduce) noise by up to 23 decibels, while maintaining audio clarity and full-spectrum richness. Made with 100-percent hypoallergenic silicone for adaptive comfort and longevity, they won't irritate or itch like some PVC or plastic earplugs.

Powered by six CREE XHP35 LEDs, the Nitecore Tiny Monster TMK10 pushes the boundaries of LED technology. The 10,000-lumen burst mode is one of the most powerful beams you can find, especially given the 4.3-inch body of the light. Located along the side of the body are the power and mode buttons, and the tail button offers direct access to turbo and high outputs. Each output is displayed and navigated on the built-in LED screen. Another nice feature is the adjustable high mode, which allows you to pick exactly how bright you want the light within a 400-to-2,000-lumen range. Built from aerospace-grade aluminum, this IP68 waterproof flashlight is quick to charge, too. Using the include quick-charging type-C cable, you can go from dead to nearly full in just a half hour.

prod_name: Georg Jensen Delta Classic Automatic Watch
prod_description: Designed in Copenhagen since 1904, Georg Jensen watches are a breed of Scandinavian minimalism you won't find in many other brands. The Delta is named after the fourth letter of the Greek alphabet, a triangular shape that's clean, bold, and resolute characteristics you'll find throughout the whole line. The numerals on this minimal watch are large and easy to read, with slim indexes interspersed between them. The hands, like the markers, have a no-frills look to them that jibes in any setting.  The GMT models (which tracks a second time zone) are powered by an ETA 21-jewel movement with a 42-hour reserve.

A newcomer in the audiophile market, Tin Hifi has built a reputation by offering high-quality audio products that don't break the bank. Building on the success of its T series, the P1 IEM is a game changer when it comes to sound and construction. In each ear you'll find a 10-millimeter planar magnetic driver that strikes a great balance between dynamic drivers and balanced armatures. The ultra-nano diaphragm allows for a higher resolution and faster transient response, which helps create a more natural soundscape. In addition to the sleek 304 stainless steel shells, the P1 comes with a 5N oxygen-free copper-plated MMCX cable.

An upgraded version of KZ's highly regarded ZS10 IEM, the ZS10 Pro features a five-driver configuration with four balanced armatures and one dynamic driver per ear. The configuration includes two 30095 drivers for high frequencies and two 50060 drivers for the mids, resulting in a transient, dynamic sound. The ZS10 Pro retains many of the audio characteristics of its predecessor while adopting a second-generation Tesla double magnetic dynamic unit and extending the high end to 40 kHz. A notably well-built IEM, the ZS10 Pro has a faceplate made of 304 stainless steel and a cavity made of imported resin. Along with being durable and practical, this use of mixed materials creates an elegant look with a bit of shimmer. Rounding out the IEM, removable two-pin connectors make for easy cable replacement.

Here we are offering our remaining inventory from the 2015 run of GMK Triumph Adler, which was the first GMK set to use custom colors. Given that these were produced in 2015, the kit composition is locked. Images shown are of the 1989 Triumph Adler Dario 286 Cherry MX keyset and are not a precise color representation of the set sold here (the reproduction is more blue than teal). The kit render is to show what is included and is not a precise representation of color. At checkout, you have a choice between the legacy packaging (V1 of the GMK tray that snaps together) and updated packaging (V2 of the GMK tray with pins). Quantities for each are limited and prepackaged. We cannot substitute packaging.  These keycaps exhibit uneven shine through when used with backlighting.   All sales are final.

prod_name: HLYM Mt. Fuji & Full Moon Artisan Resin Wrist Rests
prod_description: A wrist wrest is a great way to improve ergonomics and add a touch of comfort to your typing. With the Full Moon and Mt. Fuji Artist Resin Wrist Rest from HLYM, that comfort goes beyond the physical. Hand-painted in vivid colors encased in multi-layered resin, these luxury wrist wrests depict the natural world in its most serene settings. The first option features a full moon front and center amidst a glittery, star-covered night sky. The second option shows a snow-capped Mt. Fuji, hand-painted with extraordinary level and detail, against a blue sky with wispy white clouds in the background and Cherry blossom branches in the foreground. Angled for extra comfort and outfitted with rubber bump-ons for stability, these wrist wrests make a beautiful and functional addition to any setup.

A watch that can just as easily pair with a blazer as it can a golf shirt, the Citizen AN8150 is distinguished by its stainless steel look and clean styling. The dial available in two colors is textured and well balanced. It's outfitted with three subdials, two of which are tied to the chronograph, the other showing running seconds. Around the outer chapter ring are tachymeter markings for use when calculating speed, distance, and much more. The hands look like old-school mercury thermometers, a style not typically seen on dress watches. As the timepiece is water resistant to 50 meters, you won't have to worry about splashes or spills, either.

A combination of cassette-like looks with cutting-edge electrostatic drivers, the Shuoer Tape electrostatic IEM delivers exceptional sound inside of a retro shell. Shuoer's custom mini electrostatic drivers achieve ultra-low distortion with a quicker frequency response and smooth separation. The Tape's specially shaped cavity optimizes noise reduction and offers a comfortable wearing experience with a pre-shaped over-ear hook. Shuoer managed to strike gold in terms of sound quality, write reviewers on Headfonia, and as a result [the Shuoer Tape] hits way above its price tag.

Take your cold-weather wardrobe to the next level with these deerskin gloves from Kent Wang. Widely considered the best leather for gloves, deerskin has a smooth texture that pairs well with suits and other formal attire. Plus, it won't develop wrinkles like lambskin, capeskin, and other soft leathers. The cashmere lining keeps your hands warm and dry, and makes these gloves suitable for cold, snowy nights in the city. The gloves feature a deerskin back side with nanotechnology-treated calf leather on the fingers and palm. This special touchscreen leather makes these gloves responsive to smartphones, tablets, and other devices.

prod_name: A&H Leather Goods Full-Grain Money Clips / Wallets
prod_description: Good work at a fair price. That's founder Tony from A&H Leather Goods' calling card. Made from full-grain leather in a variety of styles, these wallets are a great way to consolidate your carry. The first wallet offered is the money clip, with four credit card pockets, an adjustable metal clip to secure bills, and an ID window. The second available is the money clip wallet, which has four credit card pockets, a small receipt pocket, two side-entry pockets, and a clear ID window, featuring a thumb cutout, which allows for better access when removing the ID. It also allows you to access cash from the money clip without even opening the fold. Both models feature RFID protection.

Is there anything cuter than a puppy? The answer is no, which is why MEMEDA is giving keyboard lovers everywhere a chance to have one by their side every day (without all the training and cleanup). Crafted and painted by hand, these resin keycaps come in seven different colors to represent different puppies. Done in the signature MEMEDA style, the little furry friends are round and plump, with different expressions on each face. Get one (or a few) for your Cherry MXcompatible keyboard to brighten up your day every time you type.
prod_varities: ['Brown  Bandit', 'Brown  Regular', 'Dark Gray  Regular', 'Dark Gray  Bandit', 'Yellow  Bandit', 'Yellow  Regular', 'White  Plain']

prod_description: A powerful balanced tube headphone amp with a variety of interfaces, the xDuoo TA-20 brings classic analog flavor to your audio setup. It features a durable aluminum alloy shell designed with anti-inference in mind, and has a small footprint about the size of a sheet of A5 paper to save space on your desk. The pair of 12AU7 tubes make for vivid vocals with natural details, and the balanced out delivers an impressive 2,000 mW of power. The inputs include XLR, ideal for pairing with a balanced DAC for a fully balanced output, plus two sets of RCA inputs. The TA-20 can also function as a preamplifier through the RCA out. A class-A transistor expansion, customized hi-fi capacitor, and professional volume IC complete the package.

prod_name: Boker & CountyComm Carbon Fiber Mollusk Knife
prod_description: The Mollusk, a collaboration between Boker and CountyComm, is almost more blade than it is handle which isn't a bad thing. In fact, thanks to the C-shaped blade, you get even more edge than you would with a typical folder. Added jimping on the spine makes the knife easy to control in tight places. Plus, at just 2.9 inches closed, the Mollusk carries anywhere without skipping a beat. The handle is perhaps just as striking as the blade. Made from marbled carbon fiber with a titanium frame lock, it's lightweight and comfortable. For carry, you'll have two options: attach the knife to a pocket with the clip or slip it in the included pouch.

prod_name: S.T. Dupont Phoenix Renaissance Line D Fountain Pen
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/bPc40qRnQ6SN3zPNZcpf_pc.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/qxG4JCCWQoWoEX6jBvgi_FP nib.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/fXjzzU2tTsqBJn8gUhHt_FP cap 3.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/2YONC5BTbKd82ERt2cWA_FP cap.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/22Jd6zKXTvqzdIp3sWOu_Roller Ball.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/racI3GqST42YCif0ZSdI_Screen Shot 2019-05-13 at 11.10.32 AM.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/bPc40qRnQ6SN3zPNZcpf_pc.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/s-t-dupont-phoenix-renaissance-fountain-pen/FP/ReHL2YZZSj24IK50Ooza_rollerball.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Founded in Paris, France, by Simon Tissot-Dupont, S.T. Dupont has been making luxury items since 1872. These days, the company offers everything from handbags and fragrances to lighters and collectible pens. An update to the iconic Line D model, the Phoenix Renaissance has been expertly adorned to represent the iconic firebird. The body has a sleek smokey gray and black fade that's coated with a natural lacquer and sparkling meteorite dust that calls to mind something rising from the ashes. The cap has been artfully engraved with the wings of a Phoenix. And, so you know it's the real deal, it comes with S.T. Dupont's certificate of authenticity. The fountain pen features a 14k gold nib with rhodium plating.

Klarus's E1 Deep-Carry Pocket Flashlight is perfect for those who like to carry a torch discreetly. Measuring just over 4 inches long with a deep clip, the light looks like it might as well be a pen when secured in a pocket. However, thanks to its CREE XP-L HI V4 6500K LED, it can pump out a whopping 1,000 lumens for an hour and a half. If you don't need that much power, freely cycle down through medium, low, moonlight, strobe, and SOS modes using the fifth-generation dual tailcap. To ensure the internals run smoothly, the IPX-8 waterproof aluminum body is armed with an intelligent thermal protection system. To charge the E1's included 18650 battery, plug the micro-USB charging cable directly into the body.

prod_name: Domikey x Kailh Cyberpunk Tactile Mechanical Switch
prod_description: The cyberpunk aesthetic is one cherished by many a mech keys enthusiast. If you count yourself among the cyberpunk faithful, outfit your keyboard with the Domikey x Kailh Cyberpunk Tactile Mechanical Switch for a colorful and tactile typing experience. Choose from two bright colorways to light up any board, and select one of two stainless steel spring options to suit your actuation-force preferences. Engineered with a lifespan of 50 million keystrokes, these tactile keys may just last all the way into a true cyberpunk future.

Made in Japan, this kitchen knife features a blade made by Kanemoto from VG-10 Damascus steel, which is known for its edge-holding ability. The hammered texture on the flats gently transitions to the classic Damascus pattern towards the blade edge. The whole blade is polished for a gleaming look. With the profile of a traditional Santoku, the knife makes quick work of chopping vegetables and slicing up virtually any kind of meat. You can use the wide blade to scoop up food and drop it in a pan or bowl. The mahogany handle, held together by stainless steel bolsters, offers a nice contrast to the blade.

The Seiko SKS Chronograph is characterized by its polished case and balanced dial. Suitable for a dinner party or a walk in the wilderness, it features a date window and a chronograph that's accurate down to a tenth of a second. To operate the chronograph, use the pushers at 2 and 4 o'clock. Water resistant to 100 meters, the watch is made with a stainless steel case and mineral crystal for durability. It comes in your choice of three styles, each of which gets power from a Seiko 4T57 quartz movement.

prod_name: YMDK Split 64 Hot-Swappable Mechanical Keyboard Kit
prod_description: While split keyboards may seem odd at first, they can make a world of difference for your fingers and wrists. From YMDK, this 64-key mechanical keyboard is split in half to promote a more comfortable position with both hands. However, comfort is just one of its many cutting-edge features. Built with a solid aluminum case, it's heavy and durable. The Kailh hotswap sockets allow you to pop in any kind of switch you want, at any time all without a soldering iron. Backed by a mini-USB connection, the keyboard also lights up, thanks to an acrylic diffuser that glows around the base. To keep the two halves steady, there are rubber feet, too. The base kit does not include switches or keycaps, but you can add them at checkout. Tack on the animal-themed keycap set for a playful look.

The Tripowin Zonie balanced cable reduces electrical noise and improve sound quality when connected to any portable audio device. To accomodate all types of IEMs and headphones, the Zonie is available in three different connector types (MCMX, 0.78 2-pin, and recessed 2-pin/QDC) and three different termination types (2.5 mm, 3.5 mm, and 4.4 mm). Each cable is made from SPC wire coated in ultra-strong and smooth 16-core silver plating.

Ideal for pairing with headphones or power amplifiers, the compact Topping D10 DAC is sure to significantly improve the sound quality of your audio system. It features the well-regarded ESS ES9018K2M DAC chip, an XMOS XU208 USB interface, and a Thesycon custom driver. It can play PCM files up to 32 bit/384 kHz, along with DSD64 to DSD256, and features a front display that shows the quality of the file type playing. Because the D10 synchronously powers on and off with your PC, no power button is needed. Finally, there's good news for those who enjoy tweaking their gear: This DAC has a replaceable opamp socket, which allows you to swap in different opamps to change the sound signature.

We've accumulated quite a few keycaps over the years. From color-coded collaborations with top designers to funky one-off sets, we've seen it all and now you can, too. Introducing the Keycap Grab Bag: a random collection of keycaps from past sets, ready to take your favorite boards to new heights. Comprising full kits, special runs that are never to be made again, and other assorted gems, each Keycap Grab Bag is filled with anywhere from 0.8 to 1.5 pounds of keycaps (depending on the included kits). All bags will include at least one or two random kits and a random assortment of other keycaps. Below is a list of available sets.

Shaped like a scimitar with its trailing point and broad tip, this Bestech folder is just as well off slicing as it is piercing. The blade is made from D2 for toughness across a wide range of tasks. It comes with your choice of a stonewashed or satin finish, whether you like a gritty or more polished look. The handle, available in three different colors, is done in G-10 for a tight hold in the elements. The pommel curves downward to secure your hand during more demanding tasks. Riding on ceramic ball bearings, the Scimitar opens by way of the jimped flipper tab. Once open, the tab acts as a natural finger guard. The pocket clip, which is suitable for right-handed tip-up carry, is shaped to complement the sleek design of the handle.

prod_name: Drop + Glycine Combat Sub "Soda" Automatic Watch
prod_description: From its clean dial and diver's bezel to its high water-resistance rating and reliable Swiss-made movement, the Glycine Combat Sub is a favorite of the watch community. It's been released in different colors and finishes, but never before with this one-of-a-kind combination. This Drop-exclusive version of the Combat Sub has everything you loved about the original, only now it features a two-toned "soda" bezel reminiscent of the red and blue colorway popularized in the 1960s. Also notable is the cyclops eye to magnify the date window and the reversion to the original Glycine logo throwback changes that will delight any vintage watch lover. Crafted with a stainless steel case and a sapphire crystal with a triple dose of anti-reflective coating, the timepiece works as hard in the depths of the ocean as it does in an important meeting.

When you think of Swiss watches, Tissot comes to mind right away. In business since 1853, the company has a knack for making impressive timepieces that can be passed down for generations. The PRS 516 Chronograph is a detailed quartz watch that toes the line between dressy and sporty. The dial is a sleek and sophisticated display of carbon fiber and black with subtle blue accents for welcome pizzazz. Featuring a 60-second, 30-minute, and 10th-second subdial, the watch offers precise timekeeping functionality. Using the tachymeter bezel, you can actually track distance and speed in a pinch, too. Built around a stainless steel case and rubber bracelet, the Tissot PRS 516 is water resistant to 100 meters.

prod_name: Platin Monaco WiSA Wireless 5.1 Sound Speakers
prod_description: Engineered for exceptional audio for easy installation, the Platin Monaco WiSA Wireless 5.1 Sound Speakers can turn any space into a cinematic listening environment. Designed with simplicity in mind, these speakers are free of extraneous audio wires: Simply plug them into an AC wall outlet and play your favorite audio. Tuned by the renowned audio engineers at THX, these speakers deliver an audio experience worthy of today's top home theaters. WiSA-certified and compatible with 24-bit High-Resolution audio, they can be used with WiSA-Ready TVs, LG 2019-2020 OLED and NanoCell models, Xbox One, Windows 10, and USB Audio for PC and Mac systems. Connect your Bluetooth-enabled devices with a free Axiim LINK Wireless Home Theater USB Audio Transmitter, and control your audio with the free iOS/Android app.

Ideal for workdays and weekends alike, the Homme sunglasses from Dior deliver luxury made for the modern man. Crafted in Italy to Dior's exacting standard of quality, these shades are durable, lightweight, and eye-catching down to the finest detail. Choose from two double-bridge models: one with azure mirror lenses and a silver khaki frame, the other with silver mirror lenses and a silver matte frame. You can also choose a single-bridge model with blue lenses and crystal frame with black temples. All available models have non-polarized lenses and come with a Dior carrying case and cleaning cloth for upkeep.
prod_varities: ['Crystal  Blue  51-20-150mm', 'Matte Silver  Gray Silver Mirror  52-23-145mm', 'Silver Khaki  Azure Mirror  52-23-145mm']

prod_name: Tin Audio T2 & T2 Pro IEMs
prod_description: Featuring a dual-driver configuration with one dynamic 10-millimeter woofer and one 6-millimeter tweeter per ear, the Tin Audio T2 IEM delivers a clean, clear sound. The build quality belies the price, too, with metal housings ending in red and blue plastic rings that differentiate the right earpiece from the left. Equipped with an MMCX connector and a 3.9-foot braided silver cable, the T2 allows for easy cable replacement if needed in the future. One Reddit review praises the IEM's neutral sound presentation, saying that, for the price, it has no comparison. Meanwhile, Audio Budget's five-star review calls the T2 a beast with super-deep and stable sub-bass, vivid and natural-sounding mids, and sharp and crisp yet not fatiguing treble.

prod_name: Topping D50s DAC, A50, PA3, & P50
prod_description: The much-anticipated sequel to the popular Topping D50 DAC is here. The Topping D50s brings users improved sound quality with a wider array of connectivity options. Outfitted with dual ESS ES9038Q2M DACs with excellent THD+N levels, high accuracy, and impressive leading dynamic range, the D50s improves sound across all frequencies and volumes. It also does away with the ESS IMD hump: a slight rise in intermodulation distortion (IMD) that sometimes occurs when ESS DACs are played at mid levels. Added Bluetooth connectivity allows users to stream from phones or other Bluetooth-enabled devices, while the onboard XU208 USB interface enables improved support for DSD native. Connect in more ways with inputs for USB, coaxial, and optical, as well as support for Android, Windows, iOS, and Mac OS X.  Add to your personal audio system with the well-regarded A50 headphone amp, the P50 linear power supply for extra power to the system, or a PA3 power amp for passive speakers.

prod_name: WinMix Retro Beige Uniform SA Keycap Set
prod_description: Retro-looking keyboards are on the rise. Get that old-school look on yours with this set from WinMix: a combination of beiges that never goes out of style. Sculpted in uniform SA row-3 profile, the set is tall and pleasing to the fingers. It's durable, too: Made from dye-subbed PBT plastic, the caps are resistant to fading over time. Here, we're offering a host of kits to cover various keyboards from classic TKL layouts to Plancks, numpads, and more. Each set is compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

Ideal for meetups, commutes, and mech keys enthusiasts on the go, MelGeek's Keyboard Carrying Case is a safe and stylish carry solution for 60% and 65% keyboards. To deliver durability without extra weight, it features semi-hardshell casing made from canvas and EVA plastics. A high-quality zip closure keeps things contained, while internal velcro straps immobilize any packed-up board inside. A tasteful gray-black colorway is capped off with MelGeek's unmistakable bee logo in the center of the case a testament to the brand and a playful touch to the case's overall aesthetic.

Small but mighty, the Klarus Mi7 is a take-anywhere torch with plenty of power. With a typical AA battery, it offers up to 330 lumens, but load it with a 14500 battery and you'll get an impressive 700 lumens of output and a beam that shines over 100 meters. Featuring three output modes and two strobe patterns, the light has more than enough function for daily use. The titanium body is IPX8 waterproof, in case you accidentally drop it in a puddle but that probably won't happen, thanks to the knurling. What's more, the Mi7 is built with proven technologies like reverse polarity protection, over discharge protection, and constant current control to prevent damage or overheating. It comes with a pocket clip, lanyard, key ring, spare O-ring, and a battery.

prod_description: From Chicago Comb Co., creators of the most successful Kickstarter campaign for a comb of all time, these carbon fiber combs can take your grooming to the next level. Made of carbon fiber composite, they're good enough for professional barbers, with rounded edges that won't scratch or pull. Far more durable than regular plastic combs, they're also heat resistant, chemical resistant, and naturally antistatic. For men, they're great for a full head of hair and beards; for women, they're perfect for detangling, styling, and lifting. The Model No. 1 comb measures 5.5 inches long with medium-fine teeth, making it great for travel and everyday use. Meanwhile, the ultra-versatile Model No. 6 comb measures 7 inches long with a curved shape and both fine and wide teeth. Finally, the No.7 comb measures 5.8 inches long and has an ergonomic circle at the top for hanging and extra grip.
