prod_name: Womier Stacked Acrylic RGB Mechanical Keyboard
prod_description: White gets its hue by reflecting all colors on the visible light spectrum. In a sense, it's a rainbow in disguise. Combining white's false rainbow with a real one created by RGB lighting, the Stacked Acrylic RGB Mechanical Keyboard by Womier delivers a standout aesthetic experience. The typing experience isn't half bad, either. Featuring a 66-key layout with doubleshot shine-through ABS keycaps, this keyboard is both space efficient and durable. Full anti-ghosting technology facilitates precision typing, while strong rubber feet add stability. Alongside the shine-through keys, a frosted three-layer acrylic case gives the RGB LED base ample opportunity to light up the board. Choose from four types of Gateron mechanical switches to get the perfect feel.

prod_name: Vostok-Europe GAZ Limo Power Reserve Watch
prod_description: The GAZ Limo Power Reserve Watch from Vostok-Europe combines a variety of different aesthetics into one cohesive look. Featuring tall, rigid Arabic numerals at the hours and slim, triangular hands, it's both fashionable and functional. Dominating the dial at 12 o'clock is the power-reserve indicator, showing 40 for a full charge and 00 when the watch needs a wind. You'll see a bit of pilot's watch influence on the chapter ring, which is divided into intervals of five for minutes. Twenty two jewels make up the Seiko Epson YN85 movement. Depending on your style, the timepiece comes in four different versions, each with a leather strap and 50 meters of water resistance.

prod_name: Aune S7 Pro Balanced Headphone Amp
prod_description: The Aune S7 Pro is the second generation of Aune's highly regarded S7 balanced headphone amplifier. A step up from the original S7, the S7 Pro features a second-generation amp output module with ultra-low internal resistance and optimized tuning. This results in more power, more stability at low frequencies, better ambiance, and improved naturalness and delicacy in sound. Equipped with two gain controls, two balanced output sockets, and a 6.35-millimeter headphone output, the S7 Pro is engineered for all types of connectivity. Its max output of 3400 milliwatts at 32 ohms makes it one of the most powerful headphone amps in its class. Made from laser-engraved, CNC-machined aluminum, the S7 Pro is a sturdy and stylish addition to any desk.

If you like automatic chronograph watches but don't like the price they command, the Reign Gustaf is a nice middle ground. Though it doesn't have chronograph functionality, the dial is laid out with three separate subdials (just like a chronograph) to track the the time of day (a.m. or p.m.), the day of the week, and the month. Completing the ensemble are lumed hands, geometric markers, and an onion crown that ties into the royal Reign aesthetic perfectly. Inside the 100-meter water-resistant stainless steel case lies a Sea Gull 1780 movement of 21 jewels. Flip the Gustaf over and you can see it beat through the exhibition caseback.

prod_name: Revue Thommen Diver GMT Automatic Watch
prod_description: Revue Thommen's beginnings date all the way back to 1853 in the small Swiss town of Waldenburg. After nearly a century of crafting its own watch movements, the company began producing aviation instruments for the Swiss Air Force in 1936. Since, it's been at the forefront of Swiss watchmaking tradition. The Revue Thommen Diver GMT is an homage to the Rolex GMT. It features chunky indices, a cyclops lens at 3 o'clock, and a knurled bezel that you can rotate to align with the GMT hand. An ETA 2893-2 movement with a 42-hour power reserve keeps the watch ticking. Take a look at the movement through the display caseback. Feel free to take it for a swim, as it's backed by 300-meter water resistance, too.

prod_name: Grifos Bog Oak Wood Fountain Pen
prod_description: Writing with this Grifos Nero Muse fountain pen is like holding a piece of history in your hand. The barrel is hand-turned from an ancient wood known as bog oak, found in the swamps of eastern Europe and carbon-dated to be up to 5,460 years old that's roughly 1,000 years older than the Great Pyramid of Giza! Gleaming against the matte black of the barrel, the cap and grip section are made of sterling silver and plated in ruthenium (also called black gold). An intricate guilloche pattern completes the executive aesthetic.

Setting off into the wilderness just doesn't feel right without a solid light by your side. With the Klarus 360X3, you get an impressive 3,200 lumens in just 6 inches of body. Complete with six different modes including strobe and SOS this torch gives your three different ways to activate it. Use the standard side switch, the silicone-coated tailcap, or the user-friendly secondary tailcap switch to quickly navigate through each mode on a dime. An aerospace-grade aluminum body means the 360X3 is tough, IPX-8 water resistant, and 1-meter submersible in water. Charging the flashlight is easy, thanks to the micro-USB port on the body. For convenient carry, stuff the light in the nylon holster or use the included pocket clip.

Combining true wireless convenience with impressive battery life, the YH623 TWS IEM from Kinera is a portable audio solution aimed at listeners on the go. Onboard Bluetooth 5.0 and a Qualcomm QCC3020 chipset allow for seamless connectivity with support for the latest codecs, including apt-X. Its built-in battery provides up to 24 hours total playback on a single charge. An included charging case can power the YH623 three times before needing to be plugged in.

prod_name: Boker Plus Tactical Pen CAL .45 Titanium
prod_description: Brought on by a collaboration between Rainer Wenning and knifemaker Thomas Braunagel, the Boker Plus Tactical Pen is a durable, reliable pen with remarkable utility. Compatible with LAMY #M22 ink refills and built with a sturdy integral clip, it can be easily secured inside of a pocket.

No DAC/amp stack is completed without a quality connection. Designed for DACs with two XLR outs and headphone amps with two XLR ins, the C006 XLR Interconnect Cables from Fanmusic bridge a balanced connection for distortion-free listening. Electromagnetic noise is blocked effectively, thanks to a Japan-imported pure-copper hi-fi wire with an impressive 94-percent copper density. A soft yet strong PVC and neoprene coating ensures lasting durability, while a 7.9-inch length makes connecting your equipment easy without any extra cable slack.

Perhaps best known for its 24-hour Airman tool watch, Glycine has been producing timepieces since 1914. This version of the Airman allows you to track multiple different time zones thanks to the bidirectional rotating bezel and GMT hand. The guts of the watch are Glycine's own 21-jewel automatic movement, which vibrates 28,800 times per hour and has a reserve of 42 hours. Water resistant to 100 meters, the watch has a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal. Lumed markers and hands help with visibility. The GMT versions of the watch feature a 12-hour sweep.

prod_description: LZ has made a splash in the audiophile world with popular models like the A3, A4, and Big Dipper. A new addition to the company's growing collection of excellent IEMs, the A5 is a five-driver hybrid IEM with the layout of one dynamic and four balanced armature drivers. The housing's bright pink wing design stands out from the crowd, while the detachable MMCX cables offer flexibility for users who might want to switch them out down the road. And because LZ knows everyone likes their music to sound a little different, the A5 comes with four removable nozzle filters. Swap them in and out to customize the tuning to your preference.

HogDoggins specializes in keychain tools and metal curios. Its latest creation is the PocketPuck: a compact stash can for anything from cash and coins to spices, pills, and tinder. Constructed from aluminum with a hard anodized finish, this little container will protect any precious cargo you stowe inside. Thanks to three N52 neodymium magnets (currently the strongest on the market) and an O-ring seal, the PocketPuck is waterproof and dustproof not to mention it comes in six different colors to match your daily carry. It opens and closes with a bold, satisfying snap.

Make sure you always have the right tools on hand with these Maratac titanium pocket tool cards. Made from Grade-4 titanium, both cards are laser cut to 0.001 millimeters and have ultra-smooth corners that won't cut your wallet. The Fishing card comes with 14 different hooks, a bi-course saw, and three different spoons, while the Ti-Lock Pick card has six different picks that'll help you open a variety of locks.
prod_varities: ['Covert Titanium Lock Pick Card', 'Survival TI Fishing Card']

prod_name: Inspirs Design Vortex TTi-300 Spinning Top
prod_description: As one of civilization's most enduring toys, the spinning top has been used for thousands of years around the world. The Vortex TTi-300 the second in Inspirs Design's line of tops highlights that worldly connection with a compass engraved on the bottom. Thanks to a silicon nitride bearing at the very center of the compass, the TTi-300 will spin for up to 8 minutes at a time with a good twist and solid spinning surface. CNC'd grooves make it easy to get a secure grasp on the stem. Made from grade-5 titanium that's been polished by hand, the top is a sight to behold, and it's available in six different stunning finishes.

Stash extra cash, store medicine or water tablets, keep tinder, hold your favorite spice, or attach a zipper pull: the uses of the Maratac Pico Pull are boundless. And this drop comes with three of them, each made from a different material. On top of the screw-down cap is a lanyard hole for keychain attachment.

When listening to music through earphones, it's crucial to maintain an excellent signal from beginning to end. Between these two points is your cable: the bridge from source to speaker. Make this bridge the best it can be with the LSC08 IEM cable from Linsoul. Made from 
6N OCC single-crystal copper with 88 strands per wire, this cable uses high-end densely woven materials to ensure near-lossless transfer of your music's signal. Choose a 2-pin or MMCX connector and a 2.5-, 3.5-, or 4.4-millimeter termination to fit your equipment, and connect the LSC08 for lossless listening on the go.

Topping has gained a loyal following for its line of accurate, competitively priced DACs, which includes the DX7 series and the D30. For those looking to pair with a high-end headphone amplifier, look no further than the Topping D70. It's stocked with all the specs you could want, including dual AK4497 DAC chips that are coupled with low-noise, low-dropout linear regulators. There's an AES, USB, optical, and coaxial input, all of which support 24-bit 192K audio. As far as outputs go, it has a balanced XLR and single-ended RCA output.

prod_name: JWK RARA Tactile Custom Mechanical Switches
prod_description: Durable, responsive, and engineered with user-friendly tactility, RARA Tactile custom mechanical switches from JWK take typing to the next level. Created by switch designer 43, these switches use white polymer nylon for the housing and green POM material for the stem. They are PCB mounted, and feature gold-plated cross-points, and galvanized, gold-plated springs for extra strength and durability. To achieve a satisfying feel and sound, each switch is equipped with a metal tactile leaf. With a medium actuation force and an overall travel of 4 millimeters, RARA Tactile custom mechanical switches add just the right amount of resistance to the typing experience.

Ray-Ban knows its way around a pair of sunglasses after all, it's been making them since 1937. Today, the company reimagines the classics in new styles like the Justin. An update on the iconic Wayfarer, the Justin pairs a transparent frame with gradient mirror lenses. Choose from a polarized option with gray gradient lenses and a black nylon frame,  or non-polarized options with green gradient lenses and a brown nylon frame. On each pair, the lenses are coated for 100-percent UV protection. A Ray-Ban carrying case and cleaning cloth are included.

Established in 1972 as a subsidiary of the legendary Porsche automobile company, Porsche Design has a reputation for quality and precision. As a matter of fact, the company was the first to create a matte black watch, and the first to make a chronograph entirely of titanium. The Chronotimer series is made of titanium from head to toe, too. It features three separate subdials: one 30-minute counter, one 12-hour counter, and one for running seconds. At 3 o'clock is a date window, and around the bezel is a tachymeter scale for tracking speed and distance in a pinch. Powering all that function is an ETA Valjoux 7750 automatic movement with a 48-hour power reserve. Fitted with a sapphire crystal, each piece in the diverse collection is water resistant to 50 meters.

prod_description: There may not be a watch more deserving of the term presidential. Worn by the likes of Dwight Eisenhower, Harry Truman, Richard Nixon, and Lyndon Johnson, the Vulcain 50s Presidents' automatic watch keeps important company. It's no wonder why: Crafted with a reliable automatic movement, a stainless steel case, and two sapphire crystals, the watch is tougher than it looks. It's also easy to read, thanks to the lengthy stick markers, a date window (with a white background), and large Arabic numerals at the cardinal hours. Bringing the look together is a calf leather strap with a polished pin buckle.

prod_name: QSP Pelican S35VN Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: Named for its wide, scooped blade, the QSP Pelican may not be able to fly, but it can certainly elevate your everyday carry. The blade is made from S35VN, arguably the best commercial steel on the market. That means you can use this knife over and over without worrying about constant sharpening or corrosion buildup. Opening the knife is as simple as pressing the flipper tab. Courtesy of the ceramic ball bearings, it deploys fast and effortlessly. Once deployed, the Pelican seals shut with a strong liner lock, not unlike the bird of prey closing its spacious pouch. Fitted with flax micarta handle scales and a tip-up clip, the Pelican will make an excellent addition to any EDC rotation.
prod_varities: ['Gray & Blue - Two Tone Satin', 'Gray & Blue - Satin Black', 'Tan & Gold - Black Satin']

prod_name: Aquacy Cave Diver Open-Heart Automatic Watch
prod_description: It's not often you see a dive watch with an open heart let alone one that actually carries a legitimate water-resistance rating. New from Aquacy, the Cave Diver Open-Heart Automatic Watch toes the line between performance and sophistication. Sized at a manageable 42 millimeters, it's made of stainless steel with a sapphire-coated mineral crystal. To keep things clean, the dial has straightforward geometric indices, which are partially obscured by the open heart at 9 o'clock. A rotating bezel allows the wearer to track elapsed time, and lumed coating on the hands and markers emphasized legibility. Equipped with a Seiko NH38 automatic movement, the Cave Diver comes in array of models, including the one-of-a-kind mother of pearl and abalone editions.

prod_description: If you listen on the go, you need an IEM that delivers exceptional audio no matter what you listen to. New from Shozy, the Form 1.1 IEM combines a balanced armature and large-diameter Beryllium dynamic driver to precisely articulate all frequencies, from the finest treble details down to the deepest bass notes. The Beryllium-coated dynamic driver moves air while keeping attack and decay fast and lifelike, minimizing distortion, strengthening bass, and maintaining durability across long-term usage. The precision-balanced armature showcases a natural build that adds lushness to all frequencies, particularly higher-end treble details. Coated with 3D resin featuring handcrafted cosmic designs, each Shozy Form 1.1 IEM is unique, comfortable, and eye-catching.

Pushing the boundaries of wireless audio, the X3 Bluetooth 5.0 TWS IEM from TFZ showcases an all-new design to deliver pristine, portable audio. Doing away with the traditional axisymmetric double-drive iron-box concept used in many IEM driver configurations today, the X3 adopts two balanced armatures of different sizes, each welded and compounded according to the golden ratio, which has been shown to deliver superior acoustics. The result is detailed, low-distortion audio with a distinctly natural character. To meet the demands of the modern wireless user, the X3 features Bluetooth 5.0, Qualcomm aptX decoding support, and a 65-foot range. The 3D-printed metal earphones are shaped for comfort and outfitted with mics for taking calls. The included USB-C charging case can charge the X3 three times before needing to be plugged in.

prod_name: S.T. Dupont Wild West Fountain Pen
prod_description: Inspired by legends of the old west, the S.T. Dupont Wild West fountain pen is an ode to the settlers of the American Frontier. The body is crafted with a misty black, natural lacquer with a subtle meteorite dust that gets lighter the closer it gets to the grip. The cap itself is a sight to behold: it's made of etched palladium that depicts the infamous battle between a white and black cowboy hat. Wrapping up the writer is a medium 14k gold nib with rhodium plating.

Delivering audiophile-grade performance in a compact form factor (that weighs just 4 ounces), the M7 from Fiio is a pocket-ready audio player with desktop-level output. Equipped with an ESS Sabre 9018Q2C chip with independent power supplies for the digital and analog sections, it has an adjustable low-pass filter and an amp delivering 70 mW at 16 ohms plenty of power for loud listeners. What's more, the M7 has a quad-core Exynos 7270 14nm processor with 2 GB of internal storage and space for up to 512 GB more with a microSD card. The internal battery offers up to 20 hours of playback, too. Summing up the M7 is this Headfonia review, It's a back to basics' device, but it comes with an FM Radio, looks great, and most important of all, it sounds more than just good."

prod_name: Vulture Premium Wickett & Craig Harness Watch Strap

prod_description: Wickett & Craig Tannery produces some of the best vegetable-tanned leather in the world. These straps are made from harness leather, which is hot dipped in waxes, oils, and fats for a weatherproof finish and a distinguished depth of color. Upon special request, the straps have not been glazed. Why? Glazing is the process that mechanically burnishes the surface of the leather. Without it, the leather will immediately begin to age specifically with your use. All of the scuffs and nicks you put on it initially will begin to polish down on their own, resulting in a better aging strap over time, unique to each wearer. What's more, the straps come in three different colors, two different stitch colors, and a wide range of sizes. They're fitted with two keepers, have five holes, and are 3 millimeters thick.

prod_name: BM Workshop BM43A 40% Programmable Keyboard Kit
prod_description: Small enough to take to a friend's house or the cafÃ©, the BM Workshop BM43A has just 43 keys. All 43 can be programmed to your liking, too, whether you prefer a more standard key layout or something a little more unconventional. Plug the keyboard in via the USB-C port and witness the bright RGB underglow LEDs. With support for MX stem switches, plus your choice of seven different aluminum case colors, this little keyboard makes a great side project.

Simple and modern, these TIMZE keychains are a great alternative to clunky carabiners. Made from titanium, they feature an innovative FLEX mechanism that operates like a normal gate but doesn't have any actual moving parts. To ensure the mechanism is ready for daily use, it's been tested to withstand up to 1,200 megapascals of pressure.

Like its name would suggest, this GSR lockpicking training kit is suitable for brand-new pickers and seasoned veterans alike. For beginners, it's got cutaway practice locks and a Master Resource CD-ROM to show you the ropes, complete with illustrated instructions for the EZ-ReKey locks. For those with some prior experience, there are a host of practice locks in the Kwikset and Schlage keyway to get you to the next level. And if you've already got lockpicking acumen, there's a PXS-14 professional pick set, plus spools and serrated drivers to create extremely difficult combinations for advanced practice sessions. You can even rekey certain locks yourself and have total control over the difficulty to give yourself a challenge.

prod_name: Bertucci DX3 Plus Performance Field Watch
prod_description: When you're on the trail, at the campsite, or on the job, the last thing you should be worried about is your timepiece. The Bertucci DX3 Plus performance field watch is built for anything that comes your way. It's got a patented fiber-reinforced poly-resin body that's water resistant to 50 meters and super tough. The numerals are prominent and easy to read, so you don't have to waste time when you need a quick glance at it. Set on a nylon strap, the DX3 Plus has a scratch-resistant mineral crystal and an accurate quartz movement. The crown is positioned at 4 o'clock to prevent wrist impingement.

prod_name: Citizen Eco-Drive Promaster Solar Dive Watch
prod_description: The Citizen Eco-Drive Promaster is an excellent representation of a classic dive watch. From the thick, lumed hands and markers to the unidirectional rotating bezel with minute markings in increments of 10, it has a quintessential diver's look. What's more, it's water resistant to 200 meters, so if you want to take it for a swim you're more than welcome. Though it's designed for the water, it's powered by the sun more specifically, a Citizen Eco-Drive E168 solar movement. There are two different models available: one with chunky hands and indexes, and another with slimmer hands and indexes. Get it on a rubber band or stainless steel bracelet.

A great pairing for laptops and smartphones, the Topping NX4 DSD is a compact DAC/amp loaded with impressive specs. It's equipped with the well-regarded Sabre ES9038Q2 DAC, along with an XU208 USB bridge, and it supports some of the highest-resolution audio including 32 bit/768 kHz, DSD256 (DoP), and DSD512 (native). For easy use when you're on the go, the NX4 DSD comes with rubber bands and Velcro feet to attach to your smartphone or digital music player. It provides 28 hours of playback when the headphone amp is used and 7.5 hours of playback when the DAC and amp are used together. Featuring a full aluminum shell, the unit is smaller than your average phone and weighs just over 5 ounces.

Building on the success of the highly regarded Xduoo XD-05 a DAC/amp that changed the game with its versatile desktop-to-pocket portability the Xduoo XD-05 Plus keeps old favorites while adding a host of new features. New on the XD-05 Plus are an AK4493EQ DAC and XMOS XU208 USB chipset to improve sound quality, as well as onboard USB-C ports to update connectivity. Another new feature is the lithium 5000mAH battery, which is capable of 13 hours of playback via USB, 21 hours via SPDIF, and 40 via aux in. Also upgraded is the power output: The XD-05 plus boasts an impressive 1000 mW at 32 ohms ideal for even the most demanding headphones. Like its predecessor, the XD-05 Plus allows you to change out op amps without soldering to suit your listening preferences. Add the optional XD-05BL to bring Bluetooth 5.0 functionality with a 10-meter range to the XD-05 Plus.

prod_name: DOMIKEY ABS Doubleshot SA Seals Keycap Set
prod_description: Bring battle-ready aesthetics to your keyboard with the military-inspired ABS Doubleshot SA Seals keycap set from DOMIKEY. Featuring no-nonsense yellow, dark green, and matte black keys with easy-to-read doubleshot legends, this set looks and feels military-issued. Alongside its doubleshot construction, strong ABS material contributes to impressive durability. With keys sculpted in SA profile, the Seals set is compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones to fit most boards.

prod_description: Prepare your keyboard for futuristic battle with an artisan keycap that's out of this world. At once an extraterrestrial and a high-tech warrior, the Mechanical Armor Artisan Keycap by MEMEDA is meticulously crafted from resin and shaped to stand out. Like a true mech fighter, this keycap features both suit and pilot. The first layer, the alien pilot, has a shine-through horn that showcases lighting from any board. The second layer is a removable armor suit piece that attaches over the base layer, while still showing off the horn. With the armor equipped, this mech key can take on all challenges, and keystrokes.

prod_name: M.7 Handheld Gaming Aluminum Artisan Keycap
prod_description: Take a trip back to simpler times, when your biggest source of stress was saving Princess Peach, or defeating the final trainer of the Elite Four. From M.7, the Handheld Gaming Aluminum Artisan Keycap looks just like the portable machine that took over many of our lives for years. Complete with two buttons, a directional pad, and a shine-through screen with a digital heart, this cap brings back all the nostalgia of the late 90s. Just like the device it's based on, the keycap comes in a wide range of colors. Get one to match your favorite Cherry MXcompatible keyboard.

One of the joys of owning a mechanical keyboard is the opportunity for upgrades and custom additions. From changing out keycaps to installing new switches, each customization task can help you fine-tune your board to fit your preferences. Each task also requires a specific tool. In the Mechanical Keyboard Tool Set from MelGeek, get one wired keycap puller and one rubber-gripped MX switch puller to take care of keycap and switch removal in seconds. The set also includes a cleaning brush for precise keyboard cleaning in all nooks and crannies.

The Aragon Divemaster 3 is a robust mechanical watch that makes an impression on the wrist. Available in 45- and 50-millimeter sizes, it's built like a tank with a thick stainless steel case and 200 meters of water resistance. Powered by an SII NH35A movement of 24 jewels, the watch ticks with a satisfying sweep. Look to the K1 hardened crystal for strength and durability, and to the screw-down crown for assurance this timepiece won't take any water damage. Available in a bevy of bold styles.

prod_name: Fox Knives Suru M390 Frame Lock  Drop Exclusive
prod_description: The Jesper Voxnaesdesigned Suru won Blade Show's 2018 Overall Knife of the Year award. Sporting a Drop-exclusive combination of Bohler M390 steel, a Ergal 7075 aluminum handle, and a bold blue colorway, this version is even better. Like many Jesper Voxnaes knives, the Suru is stout and beefy. It packs a wide 2.3-inch blade into a less-than-6-inch aluminum frame to keep weight down. To further reduce weight, the scales are skeletonized with spotted holes, like drops of water in a pond. Thanks to the dual-choil design, the handle carries very comfortably despite the knife's overall length. You can deploy the blade by way of the flipper tab or the thumb hole.

Wharncliffe blades have had a recent revival. Delivering versatility, strength, and precision, they make a great choice for everyday cutting tasks. The CJRB Rampart features a thick, sturdy blade made of D2 steel. The blade transitions into a slimmer handle, which takes up less space for those conscious of pocket real estate. The handle comes in your choice of G-10, carbon fiber, or copper. Copper clocks in at nearly 2 ounces heavier than the former options and it'll develop a natural patina over time. No matter what you choose, the Rampart is backed by a liner lock and rides on ceramic ball bearings for easy deployment.

Named after the cold, brutal Gobi desert located in Northern China, this folder takes design cues from knives of traditional desert dwellers. Armed with a 3.5-inch upswept trailing-point blade, the Gobi offers plenty of belly and room for wrist extension through long cuts. The blade is made from tough and resilient D2 steel with a stonewashed finish to hide scratches and nicks. The handle, a slim and comfy silhouette with a strong liner lock, comes in your choice of four colors. It's bonded together by screws that connect to an aggressively ridged backspacer, which provides an even better hold. Finally, for fast and effortless deployment, the Gobi has a flipper and rides on ceramic ball bearings.

Flashlights these days are becoming more and more impressive. Take the Klarus G20 for example, a mini tank that drastically outperforms its small stature. Though it measures just under 5 inches long, the light is capable of a 3,000-lumen output and a beam distance of 180 meters. That's not all, either. It also comes with four brightness settings and two signalling modes. The body is made from aerospace-grade aluminum that's IPX-8 waterproof and 1-meter impact resistant. Operation couldn't be easier. Use the side switch or the tail switch to quickly cycle between modes. There's also an integrated micro-USB charging port to refuel.

Designed to help relax the mind and body, the Luxton Home weighted blanket can help you feel more alert and clear-minded throughout the day. Made from 100-percent natural cotton, it distributes weight evenly across the whole surface for a comforting feeling through naps and sleep. While you might think you'd overheat with a weighted blanket, that's not the case: thanks to the microfiber layering, these blankets are breathable and cool when temperatures rise. The stuffing is environmentally friendly, hypoallergenic, and odorless.

Sporting a silver and black look, the Silvback from YOBOTOOL is aptly named. Luckily, it's aptly constructed, too. Made with a 3.5-inch VG-10 blade, the knife holds a good edge. As for the shape of the blade, it's long and slim, lending itself to piercing and slicing tasks. The handle is a mashup of G-10 and stainless steel G-10 for a solid grip and stainless steel for sure lockup. Deploy the blade with a press on the flipper tab and it opens effortlessly. Here in three distinct styles, the Silvback carries confidently with the right-handed tip-up clip.

prod_description: As powerful as it is compact, the Aurender Flow DAC/amp pumps out an impressive 380 mW at 32 ohms. The high-end specs are headlined by an ESS9018K2M DAC chip and an mSATA slot for up to 1 TB of additional music storage. Plus, the Flow keeps noise levels ultra low, making it a great match for IEMs and CIEMs. Headfonia says, It sounds great, works with every bloody USB device you can throw at it, packs in a Vessel screwdriver, and has enough power to punch most every headphone, and most ears, into orbit around Saturn. And that punch: poised attack, coupled with softening high-end decay and filters aplenty, really hits home. And never, ever, does it give way to hard-to-drive earphones or headphones.

The Bambino features Orient's updated F6724 22-jewel automatic movement, manufactured in-house to ensure every detail of the watch meets Orient's standards. The watch's 40-millimeter stainless steel case (42 millimeters on version 4) uses a classic combination of brushed and polished finishes. The dial, which is protected by a domed mineral crystal, features a classic dress-watch design: simple and easy to read. The watch comes with a leather strap and Orient's insignia neatly engraved on the caseback.

Named among the best nail clippers by Wirecutter in 2018, the Seki Edge clippers check all the boxes when it comes to your nail-trimming needs. They're made of stainless steel with an ergonomic handle and hand-finished edges. The diecast lever gives you extra leverage for a smooth, easy action, while the built-in nail file is great for fine finishing. Even thick nails are no match for these made-in-Japan clippers. Wirecutter says they cut cleanly through both finger- and toenails without much force and also have a nice heft, calling them sharp and comfortable to use. What more could you ask for?

prod_description: Based on community feedback from our first standing desk, the Drop Lift Sit-to-Stand Desk, this updated version features dual motors with a three-stage telescoping frame for faster and quieter operation. It also has four built-in memory modes as opposed to just three. Like before, it has a sturdy steel frame and comes in multiple styles to match your setup at the office or at home. However, now the Drop Lift 2.0 Sit-to-Stand Desk can now hold up to 256 pounds (compared to 180) and can be height adjusted nearly 26 inches (compared to just 19). If you need more space, upgrade to the larger desktop for a full 60 inches of desktop surface. Because shipping can be a pain with large items, we've included it in the price.

prod_description: This traditional three-fold full grain leather wallet unfolds to expose left and right flaps that each have three credit card pockets. Plus, there's another side-entry pocket on each flap to hold even more ATM cards, gift cards, or pictures. The center section has a window that allows you to show your identification without having to remove it from the wallet. There's also a wide pocket for bills or receipts. All credit card pockets have RFID blocking to protect from electronic pickpocketing.

prod_description: A modern dress watch backed by more than 100 years of watchmaking expertise, the Glycine Combat 6 Classic features hands, pips, and indices painted with Super-LumiNova coating for visibility. This drop features three different models, each with a slightly different look. The Glycine Combat 6 is powered by a GL224 automatic movement. This Swiss-made movement complete with a Glycine-decorated rotor offers a 38-hour power reserve and features a sweeping seconds hand that vibrates at 28,800 beats per hour. It's housed under a sapphire crystal in a stainless steel case that's waterproof to 50 meters.

prod_description: The original Preonic keyboard was praised for its build quality, compact form factor, and intuitive layout and the new version is no different. However, this time around we're offering the case in your choice of seven styles, including the new transparent acrylic and red colorways. What's more, this version has a new ARM STM32 processor that provides more power to the PCB and the USB-C connector. Another upgrade? The new Preonic has Kaihua hotswap sockets (which support grid 2x1u, 1x2u, and 2x2u bottom row layouts), so you can swap out your switches whenever you want without even picking up a soldering iron. Plus, If you're new to keyboard kits, the compact Preonic is a great way to learn about keyboard programming.

Sporting a touch of tortoiseshell and Persol's peerless standard of craftsmanship, these sunglasses make a great addition to any wardrobe. Available here in three styles, each pair is made in Italy and comes with a carrying case and cleaning cloth. The first pair features a dark tortoiseshell acetate frame, a half-rim shape, and green-gradient polarized lenses with 100-percent UV protection. The next pair has a light tortoiseshell acetate frame, a half-rim shape, and blue-gray lenses with 100-percent UV protection. The final pair gets a gold-colored metal frame, a full-rim shape, and light brown lenses.

prod_description: Styled to suit every occasion, the Hugo Boss B0960S polarized sunglasses deliver timeless elegance with strong sun protection. Made from smooth and durable optyl, the frame features a matte-black finish accented by silver-tone metal hinges and temple tip detailing. Subtle Hugo Boss insignias can be found on both temples and the upper right lens. Dark gray polarized lenses provide 100-percent UV protection and a welcome gradient in any weather, while an included carrying case and cleaning cloth help keep these shades in great condition for years to come.

The highly anticipated successor to the Tin Audio T3 IEM has arrived. Retaining much of what made the T3 loved by listeners here on Drop, the new Tin HiFi T4 adds several features to improve sound, comfort, and durability. Among these are ultra-compact 10-millimeter carbon nanotube (CNT) dynamic drivers, which deliver high-resolution sound across the T4's 1020kHz frequency range. These drivers also contribute to the T4's exceptionally low total harmonic distortion: only 1% at 1kHz. On the outside, the T4 showcases elements from automotive and aviation design to ensure comfort and deliver up to 32dB of noise isolation. It also gets an upgraded silver-plated copper cable for improved durability and signal transmission.

Optoma NuForce's HEM line features the latest balanced armature driver technology, custom-designed linear-phase crossovers, and the excellent sound quality we've come to expect from the company. The HEM6 is equipped with three Knowles drivers per side, while the HEM8 is equipped with four per side, and both can be used for professional monitoring and music on the go. The sound is pure and balanced with accurate bass and nearly twice the frequency range of other balanced armature IEMs. Along with a selection of ear tips, you'll get two replaceable cables: one with a microphone, and the other a high-end proprietary cable made from silver and OFC copper.

Add a little denim to your devices with the Denim Style USB cable from YouMo. Just like your favorite pair of jeans, this USB cable features an authentic denim-stitched coating with a blue colorway. At 5 feet long, it's got several more inches than your standard inseam, but this length adds flexibility for charging and pairing devices. Available here with a USB-A input and either a USB-C or Micro USB termination (all in complementary light blue), this cable is the perfect casual complement to any setup.

prod_name: Hot Keys Project: MiTo Bucket Head Keycap
prod_description: A collaboration between Hot Keys Project and MiTo (who you may know from fan-favorite keycap sets like Laser, Pulse, and Canvas), this exclusive artisan features the designer's signature Bucket Head character. The Bucket Head has X's for eyes and a cheeky smile that create somewhat of a dichotomy between happiness and mystery. It comes in four sleek colorways anything from Laser-inspired pink to subtle royal blue. Each cap is constructed from resin and compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

prod_name: Victorinox Swiss Army Knives Spartan PS
prod_description: Victorinox has become synonymous with multitasking. The Spartan PS lives up to the brand's dignified reputation with 13 stainless steel tools in one compact design. However, in breaking with the company's signature red color, this tool sports a shimmering, mirror-surface finish known as Polispectral. Hold it at different angles and the tools will appear to shift in color. Among its many functions, the knife has a small and large blade, can opener, wire stripper, bottle opener, corkscrew, and a pair of tweezers and it's all packed into a 3.6-inch frame.

Great for home or office setups, the Advanced Sound suspension headphone hanger helps free up space on your desk while still providing easy access to your audio gear. Made from steel, it's designed to hold multiple headphones and cables. The simple clamp-style mount is compatible with desks ranging from 0.5 to 1.5 inches thick. For convenience, the hanger has a 360-degree neck that lets you tuck your headphones under your desk when not in use.

From famed knifemaker Hiroshi Suzuki comes a pair of nail clippers masterfully crafted to deliver where it counts. Manufactured in Saitama, Japan within a small Suzuki family factory operated exclusively for precision nipping tools, these nail clippers feature smooth action and precise closure. They're made with bead-blasted stainless steel for durability and strength. At 5 inches long, they're small enough to handle difficult spots and large enough to take care of the gnarliest nails with ease. For elegant presentation and storage, they come in a wooden gift box.

prod_name: Montegrappa "The Secret Life of DalÃ­" Fountain Pen
prod_description: Surrealist painter Salvador DalÃ­ may have led a bizarre life, but his cultural impact in the 20th century can't be overstated. In 1942 the artist published his autobiography, The Secret Life of DalÃ­, in which he details his many exploits and rare ideologies. Thanks to his prose a highly detailed style that layered words the same way as paint the book rose to international acclaim. In tribute to the book and DalÃ­'s legend, Montegrappa created this fountain pen. Featuring a resin body engraved with one of the many illustrations from the book, these pens feature a decorative stainless steel nib and polished silver accents. Fittingly, the pen comes in multiple colors to express the varied tones DalÃ­ used throughout his work.

prod_name: Advanced Sound Nismo Jr. Gaming IEM
prod_description: Designed for gamers in search of detailed audio without heavy hardware, the Nismo Jr. Gaming IEM from Advanced Sound is a lightweight listening solution that doesn't skimp on sound quality. No larger than a standard pair of earphones, the Nismo Jr. is equipped with Advanced Sound's proprietary 6-millimeter dynamic drivers, which are specially tuned to optimize stereo imaging and spatial accuracy necessities for gaming. It also comes with a detachable boom mic that eliminates excessive low and high frequencies for smoother, clearer communication during gameplay. Plus, it features an in-line remote for controlling music playback, answering calls, and more.

Flashlights with long throw are excellent for lighting the way, signaling, and pointing things out. Capable of producing a beam up to 1,000 meters, the Klarus XT32 does all that to a tee and it fits comfortably in one hand. Of course, with that much throw, it has to be powerful: thanks to the CREE XP-L HI V3 LED, it can pump out up to 1,200 lumens. In addition, it features a body made from hard-anodized aluminum with the Intelligent Temperature Protection System. This innovative system monitors internal temperature and adjusts output for maximum brightness without overheating. As for modes, the XT32 has six, including four brightness levels and two special modes for emergencies. To go with it is a lanyard, holster, batteries, and spare O-rings.

prod_name: Vostok-Europe GAZ 14 Limo Quartz Chronograph Watch
prod_description: Chock full of function, the GAZ 14 Limo has a chronograph, date window, and tachymeter, as well as lumed hands and dot markers for visibility. The accurate Miyota OS22 quartz movement means you won't have to wear the watch every day and it will keep on ticking. The case is polished, made from stainless steel, and measures a solid 43 millimeters not too large and not too small. The numerals are tall and slim, which jives with the svelte, pointed hands. Water resistant to 50 meters, the GAZ 14 Limo can take a detour in the water if need be. It's set on a handsome leather strap.

prod_name: Little Dot MKII Tube Headphone Amp
prod_description: A great introduction to the world of tube headphone amplifiers, the Little Dot MKII is ideal for pairing with a desktop amp and can also function as a preamp to your speakers. It uses a single-ended push-pull OTL circuit operating in Class A, and delivers plenty of headroom and dynamic impact, along with a touch of tube warmth and tonal richness. While its high voltage swing is best suited for high-impedance headphones, the MKII can be fine-tuned to any cans you have from 32 ohms all the way up to 600 ohms using its multiple gain settings. Best of all, you get to experiment with tube rolling to achieve your desired sound signature. At the factory jumper setting, this amp can roll 6JI, WE403A/B, GE5654, M8100, CV4010, EF95, and other tubes. With its jumper pins shortened, you can roll EF92, CV131, and all equivalents and drop-in replacements.

prod_name: TFZ Q1 True Wireless Bluetooth 5.0 IEM
prod_description: Free of wires and meticulously shaped to fit the ear, the TFZ Q1 True Wireless IEM is the next step in listening comfort and convenience. The Q1 optimizes wireless performance with Bluetooth 5.0 compatibility, and achieves an ultra-comfortable, sound-isolating fit with a case shape designed from TFZ's large eardrum database. Inside, each earbud comes equipped with a dynamic driver and exterior soundhole partitions to provide greater power and clarity across all frequencies. The Q1 also features a dual-control design for easy one-click call answering. Using the 450mAh USB-C charging case, you can charge the Q1 four times, with each charge providing up to 5 hours of music and talk time and up to 80 hours of standby time.

The BA5 IEM from TRN earns its name with an impressive five balanced armatures per earphone. These include three 30095 balanced armatures working together as an integrated 3-tweeter solution for high frequencies, one 29689 balanced armature for midrange frequencies, and one 22955 woofer balanced armature for bass frequencies. To suppress internal resonance and deliver a warmer sound, the BA5 adopts a high-density magnesium-alloy housing engineered with 5-axis CNC machining. This housing also increases durability and accommodates 2-pin jacks for easy cable plugging and unplugging. Meticulously shaped to fit the human ear, the BA5 delivers comfort and sound isolation alongside detailed audio.

New from hot audio brand Tipsy, the Dunmer Pro IEM delivers on both looks and sound. An improved version of the popular Tipsy Dunmer IEM, the Pro model features three drivers in each earphone one 9.2-millimeter graphene dynamic driver and two balanced armatures for booming bass, fine-tuned treble, and detailed mid frequencies. On the outside, this IEM features a handcrafted resin shell with an ergonomic shape and several stylish color options. A single-crystal copper cable ensures durability and strong signal transmission.

prod_description: When the Massdrop community asked for a closed-back headphone that redefined price-to-performance expectations, the TH-X00 was our answer. Made in collaboration with Fostex, a brand that's produced innovative audio gear since 1949, these headphones feature mahogany ear cups, a magnesium alloy frame, Fostex's signature biodynamic drivers, and a highly reviewed sound signature. Now, in another response to the community's requests, we've updated the original with a removable cable. Introducing the TR-X00 (the R stands for removable): everything you loved about the TH-X00, now with a detachable cable for greater flexibility.

The NYM96 Wooden Mechanical Keyboard Kit is a unique piece that looks and feels like few others. Its innovative and uncommon 96-key layout is the sweet spot between fullsize and tenkeyless keyboard configurations a great choice for users that need arrow keys, a function row, and a numpad without the extras. Made by the NYM brand, this kit features a high-profile, angled wooden case that complements wood furniture, plants, and other natural home accents. Available both assembled and unassembled in a wide range of colors, this keyboard kit is also QMK programmable, meaning you can set key commands to create the optimal board for programming, gaming, or whatever your fingers do best.

In the Swiss luxury timepiece market for well over a century, Oris has earned a loyal following. These chronograph watches prove why the outfit is here to stay. Backed by the company's own Calibre 774 movement, each timepiece is built for precision and accuracy not to mention they have a 48-hour power reserve. The chronograph functionality on each watch allows you to time things with ease (and certain models have a tachymeter scale to track speed and distance). Made of 100-meter-water-resistant stainless steel, all chronographs offered feature a sapphire crystal and lumed hands and markers.

prod_description: No bigger than your closed fist, the SMSL M100 DAC features an impressive list of high-end hardware to pack a punch. Standout equipment on the M100 includes AKM's highly regarded AK4452 DAC chip, as well as a second-generation XMOS processing module that can process files up to 32-bit/768kHZ and support DSD512 decoding. Built with anodized CNC aluminum housing that will stand the test of time, the M100 has USB, optical, and coaxial inputs, plus RCA and USB outputs. Great for even the most space-scarce setups, it makes an excellent pair with any SMSL amp or other desktop amplifier.

prod_description: After 3 years of extensive research and development, SendyAudio has released their flagship Avia planar magnetic headphones to overwhelmingly positive reception. Equipped with an ultra-nano composite planar-magnetic diaphragm unit inside zebra wood housing, these headphones deliver a rich sound signature with a distinctly natural feel. PinkPowers, a popular Head-Fi reviewer, called the Avia a triumph of performance, design, and comfort with ample treble sparkle. CNC machined and meticulously crafted for lightweight comfort and coherence across all frequencies, Aiva Planar Magnetic Headphones deserve a place in any audiophile's arsenal.

prod_name: SMSL AD18 Bluetooth & USB Power Amplifier
prod_description: A compact, versatile DAC/amp for powering your entire audio setup, the SMSL AD18 supports a wide range of inputs, including USB, optical, coaxial, auxiliary, and Bluetooth 4.2. Connect it to your computer and use it to drive your headphones with an amp or to power your passive speakers. This DAC/amp uses the TI TAS5508C and TAS5342A chipset and stands vertically to save space making it an ideal addition for anyone who prefers an unobtrusive desktop setup. To help get you listening right out of the box, it comes with a power supply, USB cable, antenna, and remote control.

Put them together and you get leather goods that are built to withstand the test of time¦ and look great doing it. From Da Luca, these 100-percent shell cordovan straps are crafted with a single piece of leather for a uniform look on your favorite timepiece. Available in multiple colors and sizes, the straps don INOX sport-spring clasps and leather keepers.

prod_description: From the makers of the original Swiss Army Knife comes the SwissTool Spirit. Loaded with 22 tools in a compact package, the Spirit has everything you need to tackle virtually any job. Among its wide range of gadgets is a 2.5-inch serrated blade, needlenose pliers, scissors, three separate screwdrivers, a wire cutter, a metal file, and multiple saws. To prevent accidental closing, each tool locks in place and can be released by pushing the mechanism on the handle. Weighing just over 7 ounces and measuring only 4.25 inches, it's easy to throw in a pocket or pack or use the included leather sheath to clip it to a belt loop.

prod_name: Victorinox Swiss Army Knives:Wine Master Multi-Tool
prod_description: The perfect tool for a romantic picnic or the tailgate, the Picnic Wine Master combines the functionality of a classic Swiss Army Knife with the sophistication of a five-star restaurant. The tools a large blade, foil cutter, professional corkscrew, bottle opener, two-step lever, and keyring are all crafted from stainless steel. Unlike most Swiss Army Knives, the blade locks when open. Just press the red Victorinox logo in the scales to close it. The body of the Picnic Wine Master is made from handsome olive or walnut wood that's sanded to a smooth finish. It weighs just 4 ounces and can be stored in the included leather pouch on the go.

The Citizen Eco-Drive Axiom is a modern take on the chronograph. It features three subdials equally spaced in the center, with a date window tucked in at 4 o'clock. The resulting look is informative without being crowded. Powered by a Citizen Eco-Drive H504 solar movement, the watch will keep on ticking for months as long as you let it gather light. Made with a stainless steel case and mineral crystal, it feels solid on the wrist. The edge-to-edge glass design on the crystal makes it look like it's almost hovering, which adds to the modern aesthetic.

Building on the success of the BS1 earbud, Penon is back with a second IEM release that delivers hi-fi sound at an attractive price point. The all-new Penon Sphere IEM features balanced armatures in each earphone to deliver natural sound across all frequencies. In the words of Twister6's review: Penon did a great job with [the] tuning, which has a neutral-balanced sound sig[nature] and a natural detailed tonality you can enjoy during extended non-fatigue listening. For durability and lightweight performance, the Sphere is equipped with a simple resin housing. It also features 2-pin 0.78 mm connectors for easy cable replacement.

prod_description: Featuring a faceted body reminiscent of a gemstone, the BENU Briolette fountain pen will make a special addition to any collection. It comes in colors like Arabian Night, Snow Season, Island Breeze, Secret Garden, and more, each evoking a different place and time. Along with allowing the complexity and brilliance of the colors to shine through, the pen's long facets prevent it from rolling on your desk. And if you're looking for a design that really shines, opt for a luminous pen. Made with fluorescent paints, they glow in the dark (and semi-dark) after an hour of exposure to light. The sustained glow can last for 12 hours, fading gradually over time.

prod_name: Flower Power Spacebar + WASD + Arrows Set
prod_description: If you really want your keyboard to blossom, you need some flowers on it. With this set of 9 keys, you can put a bouquet on your favorite keyboard in all the right places: the spacebar, WASD keys, and arrows. Available in eight different colors and two profiles, the caps are made from dye-subbed PBT for durability and a long-lasting legends.

prod_description: Want to make your earphones wireless? Now you can, with these three products from MEE audio. The first option, the BTX1, turns any pair of MMCX in-ear monitors to wireless Bluetooth earphones. Featuring a 30-foot range, a built-in headset, and a battery life of 7 to 8 hours, the BTX1 offers support for AAC and aptX codecs. The second option, the BTC2, is designed to deliver Bluetooth 5.0 wireless connectivity to MEE audio's M6 PRO and MX PRO IEMs. It features aptX and aptX Low Latency support. The third option, our exclusive BTN 2-pin Bluetooth cable, turns any pair of 2-pin in-ear monitors into wireless Bluetooth earphones. Great for use in any setting, it features a 30-foot operating range, aptX support, and an IPX5 water-resistance rating.

prod_name: Xiudi Cospad Custom Mechanical Numpad Kit
prod_description: A numpad can be critical if you input data, assign custom macros, or just like having a dedicated space for numerals. Delivering the quality you'd expect in a custom keyboard and the compact form factor of a numpad, the Xiudi Cospad is a desktop companion for any mech keys enthusiast. It's composed of a hefty, solid aluminum frame (in your choice of color), a stainless steel plate, and PCB-mounted stabilizers. Thanks to the adjustable build, you can raise or lower the numpad to your liking. Once you fill it out with switches, you can use the KLE configurator to program buttons as you wish.

prod_name: WinMix SA Chalk Dye-Subbed Keycap Set
prod_description: Hopscotch, foursquare, hangman: chalk played a crucial role in the childhood of many. Now it can play a crucial role on your keyboard. Featuring neutral alphas with colorful, pastel mods, WinMix's SA Chalk keycap set recreates the nostalgic feel of the blacktop. The caps themselves are constructed from dye-subbed PBT, which is durable and long-lasting. Sculpted in SA profile, they stand tall on the keyboard for a comfy feel.

An update to the popular TA-03, the Xduoo TA-03S tube DAC/amp is loaded with audiophile-grade features that'll take your music to a whole new level. Designed to fit perfectly on most desks, it comes with a high-performance XMOS U8 USB chip and dual CS4398 DAC chips. The TA-03S uses a 12AU7 electric tube as a preamplifier and two 6C19 tubes to expand the current for a mellow timbre. Along with a powerful NIPPON CHEMI-CON capacitor, the DAC/amp is driven by a low-noise E-type transformer that's specially designed to drive tube amplifiers.

prod_name: QSP Penguin D2 Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: Quality, service, and price. Those are the tenets that guide QSP's business. The appropriately named Penguin is a cute albeit very handy folder with a sturdy wharncliffe blade. A manual-opening knife, it features a reversible pocket clip for carry on either side. The handle is made of linen micarta with enough grit for a sure grip in any conditions you might face. Sporting a two-toned finish, the blade complements the handle well. Overall, the Penguin measures just over 7 inches large enough to tackle most everyday tasks, but not so large it makes a big dent in the pocket. To secure the blade, it's armed with a trusty liner lock.

prod_name: Fallkniven DC521 Diamond/Ceramic Dual Bench Stone
prod_description: A dual sharpening stone, the Fallkniven DC521 features an aggressive diamond stone (the yellow side) and a slow, fine ceramic stone (the dark side). For most sharpening tasks, you'll use the diamond side. Simply stroke the edge of your blade along the edge up to 10 times on one side; then flip the knife over and repeat the process. If you want to get your knife to a super fine edge, turn the stone over to the slow, fine ceramic side and use the same technique. Because it's finer, it takes off less material, thus honing the edge further. Measuring over 8 inches long, the stone is long enough that you can take broad strokes, but not so long that it's hard to bring with you.

prod_name: Fujiwara Kanefusa FKM Series Kitchen Knives
prod_description: Steeped in 800 years of sword-making history, Fujiwara Kanefusa is a family operation that now uses their traditional blade forging expertise to make a line of budget-friendly, Western-handled kitchen knives. Each is made with molybdenum vanadium stainless steel with a Rockwell hardness of 57-58. The handles are made from smooth black pakka wood with stainless steel bolsters. Thanks to the full-tang construction, these knives are well-balanced and built to last. The smallest available is the Petty, which is good for peeling, cutting garnishes, and less strenuous tasks that require more precision. The next is the Santoku, which is a great all-around knife for chopping and slicing, with a wide blade that is great for moving ingredients from the cutting board to the pot or pan. Last up is the Gyuto, which is large enough to slice through large cuts of meat, fish, and thick-skinned vegetables.

With a hefty 3.3-ounce body made from solid brass, this new version of the ReyLight AA flashlight makes itself known in the hand. Grooves around the midsection create a secure hold in slippery conditions. Inside the body is a XPL 5000K LED with four different modes. On the lowest "moonlight" setting, it offers a soft 0.3 lumens, while the high delivers 220 (with an AA battery). All modes are accessed by clicking the tail switch. If you want over triple the power, grab a 14500 battery and the power level jumps up to a whopping 800 lumens on high mode. Click eight times and you can activate the memory function. Another eight clicks turns the function off. When on the go, use the included clip to attach it to your belt or pocket.

prod_name: Evil Artisan Acrylic Keycap Collector Box
prod_description: Artisan keycaps are only getting more popular, and if you're like us, you have plenty of extras laying around. For those artisans you don't feel like giving a space on your keyboard, put them in the Evil Artisan keycap collector box. Made from acrylic with space for up to 35 different artisan keycaps, it offers a flattering, protective space for your collection. Each slot in the 7-by-5 grid is compatible with all kinds of keycap profiles, so don't worry about your most flamboyant artisans fitting inside.

Known for its accurate tunings and high-end designs, Moondrop offers a whole lineup of audiophile-grade products at an affordable priceand the A8 IEMs are no exception. Each ear has two low-frequency BA drivers, four medium-frequency BA drivers, and two high-frequency BA drivers that work together to create an ideal harmonic frequency response. Everything comes encased in a crystal-clear housing that gives you a view of all the internals.

"If a cleaner and more precise sound is what you're after, the Shuoer H27 is here to deliver. That's Prime Audio's take on Shuoer's latest IEM: a lightweight, precisely tuned pair of earphones engineered for audiophile-grade sound. Inside each earphone, one Knowles TWFK-31736 dynamic driver brings power and presence, while two balanced armatures add vivid detail across all frequencies. A strong and ultra-light aluminum casing ensures durability while minimizing weight, delivering what Prime Audio calls outstanding build quality, topped off with a gorgeous stock cable. Easily remove yours and swap cables thanks to an MMCX connection, and enjoy detailed audio wherever you take the H27.

prod_name: Fallkniven Kolt KKLz Fixed Blade Knife
prod_description: A medium-sized fixed blade fit for the great outdoors, the Fallkniven Kolt KKLz is made with the company's laminated cobalt steel, which is hardened to 60 on the Rockwell scale for an edge that'll hold through taxing work and light duty. At 3.4 inches, the blade is large enough to handle most tasks, like shaving wood, piercing cans, cutting rope, and more. To keep your hands from slipping, it's got a rubber handle. Looking at the knife from the side, you'll notice an almost yin-yang appearance as the straight edge blade flows back to the handle, a direct reflection of the same shape. This shape creates excellent balance that you can feel when cutting. To go with the knife, there's a leather belt sheath and a Zytel edge cover.

Carbon Tactics has established itself as a serious player in the world of EDC belts. The company's ninth successful Kickstarter, the Ti Hook Belt is a quick-release belt that allows you to put it on and take it off without affecting size adjustment. Made from tactical nylon also known as nylon scuba webbing for extreme tensile strength, it can be used not only as an EDC or gun belt, but also as a tow rope or a sling in an emergency. And, like every other product in the Carbon Tactics collection, the belt is made entirely in the USA and overseen by designer Michael Sargent.

prod_description: If you like to be able to check the time at a glance, the TW Steel Pilot quartz watch is a solid option. Fitted with sizeable white hands and Arabic numerals, the watch is super easy to read. The tip of the seconds hand is a ruby color to go along with the minute markers on the outer chapter ring. The 3 o'clock position is appointed with a date window that slightly overlaps the large numeral 3. Set on a leather strap, the watch has a stainless steel case, mineral crystal, and a diameter of 45 or 48 millimeters, depending on the model you choose.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nitecore-br35-usb-rechargeable-bike-light/FP/ZBjMQSezQ3KY9BZbi7qg_Screen Shot 2018-11-15 at 1.24.12 PM.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nitecore-br35-usb-rechargeable-bike-light/FP/jeMNWj0MSreHogbBjlHW_Screen Shot 2018-11-15 at 1.24.18 PM.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nitecore-br35-usb-rechargeable-bike-light/FP/V5EQIQh3TLKeTyGvB9XO_Screen Shot 2018-11-15 at 1.24.22 PM.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nitecore-br35-usb-rechargeable-bike-light/FP/JBjd6vp9QnyB2mPT5uph_Screen Shot 2018-11-15 at 1.24.15 PM.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/nitecore-br35-usb-rechargeable-bike-light/FP/fyFUxZyoSfOd5AvTxZXl_20180703161755_89484.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: As the days get shorter and the nights get longer, staying safe on the road is paramount. With the Nitecore BR35 you can light up the road ahead and stay visible to oncoming vehicles, no matter the conditions. Utilizing two CREE XM-L2 U2 LEDs, the BR35 delivers an impressive 1,800 lumens on the highest setting. When you don't need that much power, just click to cycle through a bevy of modes, including caution mode in case of emergency. Another unique feature is the dual-zone lighting. Just like on a car, this bike light offers a dual-distance beam for near and far illumination. Of course, if you only need one, you can use the short-range or long-range output on its own. With the included remote switch, you get full control at your fingertips, so you don't need to take a hand off the handlebars if things get slippery.

The Kershaw Mixtape was designed with ease of carry in mind. Featuring a backspacerless design with skeletonized glass-filled nylon handle scales, the knife weighs a mere 2.6 ounces. However, despite the lean construction, the Mixtape can spin through heavy-duty tasks fast. Thanks to a 3.1-inch reverse tanto blade made from corrosion-resistant and easy-to-sharpen 8Cr13MoV stainless steel, this folder packs a punch. Deployment can be achieved manually via the thumb disk, or by pulling out the blade with two hands, the old-fashioned way.

With its thick, full-rim double-bridge design, these Marc Jacobs sunglasses are an adventurous choice to combat the sun. In addition to their wide 59-millimeter lenses, which offer excellent coverage, the lenses are coated with a mirrored finish to help hide your eyes and add extra protection. Made to Marc Jacobs' high standards, each pair comes in a carrying case with a cleaning cloth to keep them pristine.

Powered by light, Citizen Eco-Drive watches can last for up to 6 months on a full charge without wear. The AW5000 collection features field-inspired designs that are highly legible and robust. Made from stainless steel, the case measures just over 42 millimeters and is water resistant to 100 meters. Arabic numerals are used for the 12- and 24-hour markers, which pair with a date window at 3 o'clock. There are three different colors to choose from, and each model has a different accent color at the cardinal hours and on the minutes hand. For versatility and a hint of hardiness, they're set on nylon straps.

Functional, comfortable, and designed for unique aesthetic appeal, the Maxim automatic watch by Heritor makes a decorative addition to any ensemble. A case made from 316L stainless steel ensures lasting shine and durability, while a genuine leather wristband keeps things comfortable while adding a degree of elegance. At the watch's center, a semi-skeleton dial reveals meticulously engineered inner mechanisms, and an NH35 Japanese automatic movement facilitates precise timekeeping. Five style options are available here, each one with a different combination of case, dial, chapter ring, and band colors.

The compact profile of a 60% or even tenkeyless board is great, especially in transit. But there comes a time when a numpad is indispensable. For those moments data entry, tax time, Garry's Mod the KC21 is your companion. It offers various light modes and is equipped with all the keys of a regular numpad as well as an ESC key.

A follow-up to the impressive multi-driver H3, the Kinera IDUN kicks things up a notch with improved sound, craftsmanship, and nozzle design. This IEM is built with two balanced armatures and a single 7-millimeter dynamic driver per ear, which work together to deliver a smooth, balanced, and warm sound signature. Despite its universal fit, the IDUN looks like a pair of high-end CIEMs, with eye-catching designs and a naturally contoured shape that fits comfortably inside the ears.

prod_description: Equip your ears with an IEM as unique as your musical taste. The Peacock Audio P1 IEMs feature inner cavities sketched by expert designers and processed with over 20 procedures. Each one is entirely unique. These IEMs come equipped with a macromolecule diaphragm with a powerful driving force, rich low frequency, and a high resolution for strong overall sound quality. Bluetooth 4.1 compatible, IPX6 waterproof, and usable for 8-10 hours on a single charge, they're compatible with most portable devices in virtually any environment. Made from imported Egger resin that's both comfortable and long-lasting, the Peacock Audio P1 IEMs are available in myriad color options including color-changing UV-WR to suit all styles.

A new and improved version of the popular TA-01, the xDuoo TA-01B DAC/amp can easily drive high-end headphones, packing a lot of power into a compact piece of gear. The 12AU7 tube brings some warmth to the sound signature, hitting the sweet spot between analytical reference and homemade hi-fi. Meanwhile, the dual Cirrus Logic CS4398 chips allow each channel to be processed independently, resulting in lower crosstalk and noise, and a cleaner overall performance. The RCA jacks pull double duty as input for the amp and output for the DAC, and the upgraded XMOS U8 USB interface makes for a more stable performance.

The sequel to the popular KZ ZS5, the Z6S continues the company's history of producing some of the best values in IEMs today. This model features four drivers (two dynamic units and two balanced armatures) and a sturdy aluminum-alloy shell qualities that are extremely rare in an IEM of this price. The driver layout gives the Z6S an impressive soundstage, and its 15-ohm impedance allows it to be easily driven by smartphones and other low-power sources. It comes with a removable cable and two pairs of ear tips to make sure you get the right fit.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/linsoul-hc-08-iem-cable/FP/fjuvb12ROiVa35IdDJXw_Linsoul HC-08 Earphone Cable MD-883264750.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/linsoul-hc-08-iem-cable/FP/mluZZa7MRCKcOKGczQB6_Linsoul HC-08 Earphone Cable MD-883264751.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/linsoul-hc-08-iem-cable/FP/7wPNcCQyyXdpSXG80PVA_Linsoul HC-08 Earphone Cable MD-883264752.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/linsoul-hc-08-iem-cable/FP/D6BvDvF3RpGZ4VxcTx6T_Linsoul HC-08 Earphone Cable MD-883264754.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Take your IEMs to the next level with the Linsoul HC-08 cable. Available for MMCX and 2-pin 0.78-millimeter earphones, the cable features eight different strands and 19 cores that create a natural sound with a punchy bass and midrange. The 3.5-millimeter audio jack is designed for cellphones and standard music players, while the 2.5- and 4.4-millimeter balanced audio jacks are predominantly used for professional audio players.

From Salvatore Ferragamo, a name synonymous with Italian luxury since 1927, these shades will bring a classic, sophisticated touch to your sunny-day ensembles. They feature a full-rim Havana plastic frame with a logo on the left temple. Done in green, the polarized lenses provide a clear, glare-free view. To keep your sunglasses clean, safe, and looking their best, you'll get a hard case, a soft pouch, and a microfiber cloth.

Sometimes you need your trusty lock pick set for an emergency lock-out, while other times you just want to practice your picking technique. Whether for backup or for enhancing your skill set, try the SouthOrd Jackknife Lockpick Set, the key to all your lockpicking needs.

Featuring stainless steel and ceramic hardware finished with a wide array of eye-catching colors, the Armand Nicolet A487 Series watches add a little something extra to their classic looks. Available here in 11 styles, these watches showcase an array of colors, including deep blue, brilliant red-orange, glimmering rose gold, and simple black. Each watch features a mechanical automatic movement and GMT functions, plus a scratch-resistant sapphire crystal. Both rubber and stainless steel bands are available as well as deployment and non-deployment clasps depending on the model.

prod_description: Fallkniven has made a habit of creating durable fixed blades ideal for outdoor pursuits. The S1x doesn't stray from that pedigree. This 10-inch full-tang fixed blade is armed with a chunky drop-point blade for all kinds of rigorous cutting tasks. The knife features Fallkniven's premium laminated cobalt steel, which is hardened to 60 on the Rockwell scale for an edge that'll hold through taxing work and light duty tasks. A grippy Thermorun handle forms the backbone of a sure hold. Available in two finishes (satin or non-reflective black), the S1x is built for any mission.

As if unearthed from the crypt, the Bone Dragon artisan keycap from MEMEDA is a creepy, detailed piece that can elevate any keyboard. This handmade resin keycap depicts a dragon's skull and carcass atop a rocky outcrop, like something you might stumble upon in a dungeon. Compatible with Cherry MX switches, the keycap comes in eight different colors to match your favorite board.

When you wear a Hamilton watch, you wear a piece of Swiss-made history. The Khaki collection is arguably the most revered in the company's lineup. This model is pilot-inspired with large Arabic numerals, a date window, and a chronograph that's accurate down to the second for 30 minutes. Backed by a reliable grab-and-go quartz movement, the watch is a manageable 41 millimeters wide. It's built for adventures in air or under water, thanks to the 100-meter depth rating and scratch-resistant sapphire crystal. Set on a thick leather strap, this pilot's timepiece is comfortable, no matter the mission.

prod_description: To put it simply, the CTRL mechanical keyboard has it all. Constructed with a solid aluminum frame with a built-in switch plate, it's stable and fortified. And thanks to the Kaihua switch sockets, it allows you to change switches whenever you want with no soldering required. It's also fully programmable via QMK, meaning you can assign macros or custom keybinds to every key if you like. With dual USB-C connectors, the CTRL is outfitted with the fastest available connections. Aesthetically, the CTRL impresses, too. Featuring customizable RGB backlighting and underlighting, it puts on a show in myriad colors; or you can set it to a single color for a more subtle look.

prod_description: The ever-minimal Eternity watch from Eterna is simple and refined. Slim hour markers and hands give the watch a delicate look you can dress up with ease. In the name of wearability, the watch is sized at a modest 40 millimeters, with a case that's just 11 millimeters thick. Fitted with a mechanical movement, the Eternity (like its name implies) will tick forever if you keep it wound and a solid 38 hours if you don't. Stainless steel is used for the case and anti-reflective sapphire is employed on the crystal a formidable combination that will keep your timepiece protected for years to come.

prod_name: Edox Les Vauberts Moonphase Quartz Watch
prod_description: Les Vauberts, where this collection of Edox watches takes its name, is a small area near Les Genevez, famous for hosting the first watchmakers more than four centuries ago. In tribute to these skilled artisans, the Les Vauberts Moonphase quartz watch has a dressy, minimal look but plenty of functionality to go with it. The layout of the dial is well-balanced and clean. Even with a date window at 6 o'clock and a moonphase indicator in the center of the dial, it maintains plenty of whitespace, so as not to overwhelm the wearer. The stainless steel case houses an accurate Swiss quartz movement, which is protected to 200 meters thanks to the screw-down caseback.

Sporting a design dating back to 3,000 BCE, ForeverSpin tops are modeled after the terra cotta ceramic spinners found in Troy. Today they make great desk distractions, conversation starters, or toys to show off to friends. Each top in the collection is precision crafted from precious metals on a CNC lathe to ensure the utmost quality and performance. Here, you'll find everything from stainless steel and titanium to sought-after silver and tungsten. Whatever you choose, spin it with precision by adding a concave spinning base.
