prod_description: Pumping out 1,000 lumens in a compact frame, the Nitecore TUP is a necessity on nighttime adventures. Outfitted with five separate modes, it can be catered to any setting on the go. The anodized aluminum body protects the internals, as does an advanced power cutoff feature, a temperature-regulated body, and the micro USB charging safeguards. For an easy look at the output and to monitor the status of the light it comes with a bright OLED display. Carry it in a pocket or clip it to a keychain: The TUP goes anywhere you go and is bright as can be.

Seiko's SNK collection is a perfect entry into automatic watches. Engineered with a modest 37-millimeter stainless steel case, the watch is equipped with a Seiko caliber 7S26 movement with a 40-hour power reserve. Any time you want to take a look at the movement, just flip the watch over and look through the exhibition caseback. Due to the popularity of the SNK collection, these watches come in a variety of colors, too five of which are on display here. Each model is armed with a tough Hardlex crystal, luminous hands and markers, and a military-inspired dial that works in virtually any setting.
prod_varities: ['5 Beige Dial - SNK803', '5 Black Dial - SNK809', '5 Blue Dial - SNK807', '5 Green Dial - SNK805', 'Series 5 Automatic - SNK809K1']

prod_description: The CCCP watch company began with a mission to engineer watches based on the storied timepieces created by the Soviet Union. Accurate in its aesthetic appeal, chosen materials, and engineering, the Sputnik-2 automatic watch is a faithful representation of many of the top watches used in Russia in the mid 20th century. Central to its design is a Slava automatic movement: one that was created and employed by famed Russian watchmakers, though rarely used today. Available here in five styles, this watch features arabic numerals, three hands with a date readout, an indexed dial, and a stainless steel case.

If you ever find yourself on the Italian Riviera, take a look at the wooden runabout boats sprinkled across the water. It's these little sailboats that inspired the Spinnaker Vessel watch. Made with a hybrid bracelet of stainless steel and wood, the Vessel has handmade nautical appeal. Thanks to the chronograph, it can be used to time events by land or by water with a few simple presses on the pushers at 2 and 4 o'clock. Each subdial looks like a gauge the skipper might use to navigate the water, and the bezel is fixed with six studs, just like the wheel of a boat. Of course, a watch with such maritime vibes deserves a good water-resistance rating in this case a solid 100 meters.

prod_name: NPKC PBT Gradient Keycap Set (122 Keys)
prod_description: This set of PBT keycaps produces a spectacular multi-colored fade as it crosses your keyboard from left to right. Each keycap is made of individually colored plastic never painted while the laser-etched legends will stay true over time. The minimalist can opt for a blank set of keycaps instead to really highlight the bright colors. Both sets come in OEM profile and are compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

For those who don't like too many watch complications but also don't gravitate toward a simple dial, the Orient Power Reserve finds a happy medium. Powered by the Orient 46U40 21-jewel automatic movement, this watch is handsome and purposeful, with everything you need and nothing you don't. The dial features a date display, a 40-hour power reserve indicator, luminous hands and markers, and a mineral crystal. Meanwhile, the stainless steel case has a slide rule bezel and a see-through caseback to peek at the movement. Get this beauty in your choice of three styles.

These PBT keycaps feature dye-sublimated legends of popular emoticons. Designed to replace your modifier keys, they're a whimsical addition to the keyboard of any Internet-savvy individual. The set of three comes in Cherry profile with Cherry-style stems.

prod_name: Advanced Sound Dual Suspension Headphone Hanger
prod_description: If you have one or more pairs of headphones that you use at your desk, you know that finding a place to put them isn't always as easy as it should be. The Dual Suspension Headphone Hanger from Advanced Sound (ADV) is your solution. Clean, compact, and engineered for any desk setup, this headphone hanger uses a durable steel clamp capable of attaching to desks up to 40 millimeters thick. It also features 360-degree rotation to clamp at any angle. The headphone hangers themselves are equipped with silicone padding and ample space to accommodate growing headphone collections.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/everglide-switches/FP/OJNSWuPyQOqE4krrYm34_Everglide Switches MD-8611935752.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/everglide-switches/FP/Td79lG1FTIyQWJKIoqDd_Everglide Switches MD-8611935662.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/everglide-switches/FP/wDUlNF6QyhPOR9VCjCYQ_Everglide Switches MD-8611935702.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/everglide-switches/FP/PON8y2r8SAinEhJolQCx_Everglide Switches MD-8611935682.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/everglide-switches/FP/51eMWAxS2mbUk7lQCehZ_Everglide Switches MD-8611935712.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Available in both tactile and linear styles, the new Everglide switches offer a satisfying typing experience. Four styles are offered here, from the lightest Sakura Pinks on the low end to the heaviest Coral Reds on the high end. Get the switches in quantities of 70 or 110 to fit your favorite keyboard.

While many headphones make you choose between an open- and closed-back construction, the Beyerdynamic DT880 and DT990 split the difference with a semi-open design that allows for increased airflow and a wider soundstage. They bring full depth and excitement to the entire range, with a smooth, extended treble; a transparent, detailed midrange; and a punchy, layered bass. Because they cover all frequencies without difficulty, they're ideal for a variety of genres and are perhaps most impressive when listening to dense electronic jams.

Take your hydration game to the next level with the Geigerrig RIG 500 hydration pack. At its core is the Geigerrig Hydration Engine: a water reservoir that's easy to fill and provides quick access via a silicone bite valve. Because it's pressurized, you can drink from it, spray yourself off to stay cool, clean your gear after a hike, or share your water with a buddy. It has a slide-top opening for easy filling and cleaning, as well as a quick-release valve that depressurizes the reservoir. For effortless cleaning, the bladder can be reversed and put in the diswasher. The accompanying backpack is made from heavy-duty ripstop nylon and features a sizable main compartment, external zippered pockets, reinforced compression loops, and a removable waist belt.

prod_name: Drop + Zambumon GMK Nautilus Nightmares Keycap Set

prod_description: Zambumon's Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Seathemed keycap set, GMK Nautilus, captured the spirit of the open sea. His latest keycap set takes place in the same universe but it brings the colorway to a darker, more sinister place. Introducing Nautilus Nightmares: a deep green spinoff evoking the frightful Cthulhu sea monster. A monstrous array of greens, dark greens, and darker greens, Nautilus Nightmares is made of durable ABS plastic and sculpted in GMK's popular Cherry profile.

prod_name: KeySmart Nano Torch XL LED Flashlight
prod_description: Slim and lightweight, the KeySmart Nano Torch XL LED flashlight easily fits into any pocket. Powered by two (included) AAA batteries, it pumps out a 120-lumen beam for up to 2 hours. Depending on the task at hand, you can adjust the sliding barrel around the head from a wide spill to a narrow spotlight. In the name of durability, the torch is made with a machined aluminum body that's both splashproof and impact resistant. Clip this compact light to a shirt or pants pocket, and get it in your choice of black or silver.

prod_name: Glycine Combat 6 Classic Moonphase Automatic Watch
prod_description: Backed by more than 100 years of expertise, the Glycine Combat 6 Classic Moonphase has all of the features of the original Combat 6 Classic, but it keeps track of the moon's position at 6 o'clock. The hands, pips, and indices are painted with Super-LumiNova for visibility, while the window at 3 keeps track of the date. As for movement, the watch is powered by an in-house GL280 automatic movement of 25 jewels. The back of the case offers an exhibition of the movement at work. Of course, with a reputation like Glycine has, the watch is highly durable, too. With its stainless steel case and sapphire crystal, it's water resistant to 50 meters.

From Ingersoll, the Apsley is a pilot's watch that's big on style. Measuring 45 millimeters with a sizable crown and large Arabic numerals, the Apsley pays homage to traditional aviation watches. Where it diverts from tradition is what sets it apart. At 9 o'clock there's a subdial with a 24-hour scale, allowing you to track a.m. and p.m. There's also a window at 3 to track the date. All that function is packed in a 100-meter water-resistant stainless steel case with dark, non-reflective coating. The case houses an automatic movement and is fitted with a scratch-resistant mineral crystal.

Ready for all your workout and travel needs, the TFZ B.V2 wireless IEM boasts Bluetooth 5.0 lossless transmission and an IPX5 waterproof rating. It doesn't skimp on sound, either: each channel features a balanced armature driver, a rarity among fully wireless IEMs. The built-in battery gives you up to 15 hours of playback and can be charged in an hour. The IEM also comes with a high-definition microphone for hands-free calls and controlling your phone's voice assistant.

Fallkniven has made a habit of creating durable fixed blades ideal for outdoor pursuits. The F1x doesn't stray from that pedigree. This 8.7-inch full-tang fixed blade is armed with a chunky drop-point blade for all kinds of rigorous cutting tasks. The knife features Fallkniven's premium laminated cobalt steel, which is hardened to 60 on the Rockwell scale for an edge that'll hold through taxing work and light duty tasks. A grippy Thermorun handle forms the backbone of a sure hold. Available in two finishes (satin or non-reflective black), the F1x is built for any mission. It comes with a Zytel sheath, to boot.
prod_varities: ['Fallkniven F1x  Satin Blade ', 'Fallkniven F1xb   Black Blade  (+$40)']

prod_description: KeySmart made a name for itself in the EDC community with its compact key holder. Now the company sets its sights on the backpack industry with the Urban21: a sleek commuter backpack with space for your tech, gear, and accessories. Made from water-resistant ripstop nylon, the pack is ready for inclement weather. It features a padded compartment for laptops up to 15 inches, memory foam shoulder straps for comfort, and a hard-shell pocket to protect things like sunglasses, phones, and headphones. Also notable are the discrete anti-theft pockets with RFID blocking technology if you plan on taking the bag to a high-traffic area.

Sleek yet protective, compact yet spacious, the KeySmart Urban Portfolio Briefcase is a commuter's dream. Featuring a whopping 12 internal pockets, the briefcase makes it easy to organize and access all of your essentials on the go. Inside, you'll find a 15-inch padded laptop compartment, a designated pocket for a Tile (or other GPS tracking device), cable pass-through holes, and dividers for separating your things. Made of water-resistant material with a shockproof hardshell and waterproof zippers, the Urban Portfolio Briefcase can stand up to inclement weather and impact. For even easier access, the handles and certain pockets are magnetized for rapid opening and closure.

The Nitecore MT21C is one of the most adaptable flashlights on the market. Perhaps its most important feature is the 90-degree adjustable head. Use it like a normal flashlight or rotate the light into an L shape to shine a beam on hard-to-reach areas. Aside from its innovative design, the light packs quite a bit of power 1,000 lumens to be exact. Use the side switch to cycle through its many other modes, including five brightness modes and specialty modes like SOS, strobe, and beacon. Another nice feature is the magnetic tailcap, which allows you to attach the light to the hood of your car, on objects, and more. Of course, like most Nitecore torches, it's tough as nails and made from waterproof and impact-resistant aircraft-grade aluminum. Look below for a handful of extras listed in the included section.

From the renowned audio engineers at IMR Acoustics comes the new R2 Aten: an IEM that sounds like a pair of high-end headphones. The R2 Aten features an open-back design, which gives it an expansive and natural soundstage. Inside, this IEM is equipped with IMR's all-new Aten beryllium composite dynamic driver, which showcases upgraded Neodymium motors. This is paired with a high-resolution piezo ceramic driver to deliver detailed, precise sound across all frequencies. For fine-tuned customization, the R2 Aten includes interchangeable acoustics nozzles and dampeners that allow users to adjust several sound signature characteristics. For improved connectivity, it also includes a single-crystal, oxygen-free copper braided cable.

prod_name: Gerber Flatiron Cleaver Frame Lock Knife
prod_description: If you want control when your cutting and slicing, turn to the Gerber Flatiron. This cleaver-style blade is as easy to wield as they come. The 3.5-inch blade is thick and easy to sharpen. Choke up on the knife with the finger choil and you can get even closer to the task at hand without risking your extremities, of course. Available with a handle in stonewashed aluminum or G-10, the knife is practical and versatile. For reliable lockup, it's outfitted with a frame lock; for carry, there's a tip-up pocket clip. Deployment is quick, whether you use the thumb hole in the blade or manually open the knife with two hands.

Packed with high-performing hardware, the TSMR-2 IEM from Tansio Mirai is ideal for earbud users in search of a customizable listening experience. To deliver powerful and detailed sound across all frequencies, the TSMR-2 features two highly regarded balanced armatures in each earbud: a Knowles CI-22955 and Knowles ED-29689. The TSMR-2 IEM also comes equipped with three tuning switches on each side, allowing for seven different tuning settings to help listeners find the ideal sound signature to suit their preferences. Summed up by Audio123 Reviews: The Tansio Mirai TSMR-2 is a perfect entry level to the Tansio Mirai lineup."

With a crisp and responsive tactile bump at the top and a cushy feeling when bottoming out, the Everglide Oreo mechanical switches are a joy to type on. Rated for 50 million presses, Oreos have a smokey housing and clear stems for a sweet two-toned look. For keyboard PCBs with two extra holes near the center post, these switches will add extra rigidity to your build; for keyboards PCBs without the extra holes, simply cut the small plastic legs off and make the switches plate-mounted.

prod_name: NPKC Sushi PBT Dye-Subbed Keycap Set
prod_description: Pay tribute to Japanese culture with these all-over dye-subbed keycaps. The set is loaded with allusions to the island country, including pagodas, bullet trains, and of course, sushi. And it's all done in bright turquoise, yellow, and white to make a colorful impression on your desktop.

You love everything about your keyboard and mechanical switches, except for the overbearing click-clack from the keycaps hitting the bottom. To reduce the noise output from your typing and add in a touch of ergonomic optimization, slide some Cherry MX Rubber O-Rings onto your mechanical keyboard.

A compact power amplifier, the SMSL SA-98E is ideal for driving bookshelf speakers as part of a desk setup. It's built with a TDA7498E class-D audio amplifier chip, a strong output short circuit, and thermal overload protection. Highly efficient, it won't generate much heat even when operating at high power for extended periods of time. At its recommended uses with minimum distortion, the SA-98E can drive 120W per channel. The black aluminum chassis is complemented by a thick front panel in your choice of colors and a matching large aluminum volume knob.

A high-performance headphone amplifier from xDuoo, the TA-05 is designed to give you the warm-sounding experience of a tube amp on a budget. It's built with two preinstalled 69I tubes, which can easily be swapped out for tubes of your choice if you'd like to experiment with the sound signature. The TA-05 can drive demanding headphones with ease, adopting transistors for a Class-A buffer and outputting 780 mW at 32 ohms. It also features built-in over-voltage and over-current protection to prevent damage to the unit should the input voltage or current exceed the limit value.

If you were around during China's Han Dynasty, you would have seen roof tiles adorned with animals like rabbits, deer, oxen, and horses. More than just decorations, they stood for the wealth and prosperity of the dynasty. Here to capture the glory of these intricate tiles is the Imperial Guardian keycap from mmcaps. Styled like a gargantuan demon with a toothy grin, these artisans are made from resin with detailed grooves at every turn. The demon comes in five different colorways, so you can match it to your favorite keyboard.

prod_description: The GK84 has everything you could ever ask for: good looks, compact form factor, Bluetooth wireless capability, customizable backlighting, and a variety of different switch options to suit your typing style. That's not all, either. This handsome board is made with a rosewood case and comes in three colors to set the tone on your desktop. It features full RGB lighting with dedicated software for adjustments. Use the same software to program hotkeys and macros to your liking. What's more, the keyboard has a hot-swappable PCB, which means you can simply pop in switches without even picking up a soldering iron. Outfitted with the latest USB-C connection, this do-it-all keyboard also comes with a set of PBT dye-subbed keycaps that won't fade over time.

prod_name: Topping MX3 Power/Headphone Amp w/ Bluetooth
prod_description: A digital amplifier with a built-in Bluetooth receiver, DAC, and headphone amp, the Topping MX3 does it all. This versatile, compact unit can be used to power your passive speakers or headphone amp. And in systems that already have a discrete headphone amp (like Topping's conveniently stackable A30), the MX3 can function as a DAC or preamplifier. It outputs an impressive 247 mW of power at 32 ohms in the headphone amp section a 190 percent improvement over its predecessor, the VX3, and enough to power demanding headphones like the Massdrop x Sennheiser HD 6XX. Connect the MX3 to your bookshelf speakers with banana plugs or a speaker wire, and it'll deliver 38 W per channel at 8 ohms. Featuring a digital display with adjustable brightness, this unit can also be connected to Bluetooth using NFC.

prod_name: Massdrop x Klymit Ultralight V Sleeping Pad
prod_description: Following the success of the Static V Ultra Light sleeping pad, we're excited to announce our second collaboration with Klymit: the Massdrop x Klymit Ultralight V. It features the original's 20d nylon fabric, 60 g/m2 insulation, and V-chamber design, plus a couple of notable updates. First, the flat valves allow for faster, easier inflation, and second, the non-slip treatment helps keep your pad in place on slippery shelter floors. And because we know different backpackers have different needs, we made this new pad in three different sizes: short, regular, and long.

Great for adventures and the day-to-day, the Citizen Chandler will suit the functionally and aesthetically inclined. It features a chronograph that measures in second increments for up to a full 24 hours, a date window at 4 o'clock, and luminous hands and markers for legibility in dark conditions. The dial is a combination of black and white that blends well with the sporty orange chapter ring. Also of note is the watch's 100-meter water resistance rating. Of course, as part of the Eco-Drive lineup, it's powered by light and can hold a charge for months even if you leave it in a drawer which you most likely won't, given its everyday appeal.

Built on a foundation of TC4 titanium and S35VN stainless steel, the Rike Knife 1507s is apt to take on any kind of task you put before it. It features Rike Knife's signature futuristic aesthetic, achieved by precision machining on every single angle. The flipper tab makes for quick action, while the frame lock keeps the blade nice and tight. To ensure the lock doesn't wear out over time, it's fitted with a hardened steel lockbar insert. At 4 millimeters thick, the blade is stout and tough and the S35VN only makes it that much more impressive. A titanium pocket clip facilitates tip-up carry on the right side.

prod_name: Oris Big Crown Pointer Date Automatic Watch
prod_description: A classy dress watch that's highly legible, the Oris Big Crown Pointer Date displays the day unlike many other watches. Printed along the chapter ring is the date. As the days pass, the slim and lengthy center hand (that's not the seconds hand) rotates to cycle through them, a constant reminder of the current day. The Arabic numerals are tall, wide, and stylized. Framing the sapphire crystal is a seashell-grooved bezel a characteristic often found in high-end dress watches. The engine of the watch is an Oris 754 movement of 26 jewels. On a full charge, it'll tick for 38 hours. Finally, the Big Crown Pointer Date features a stainless steel case and is water resistant to 50 meters.

prod_name: Rama Works x Nautilus Nightmares Artisan Keycap
prod_description: Designed by Rama Works, who you may know from projects like the M10-B mini pad and the JamÃ³n and Oblivion artisans, this limited-edition keycap is designed to match Zambumon's Nautilus Nightmares keycap set. Made from anodized aluminum with enamel fill, the 2.25u keycap has a radiant, glowing quality to it. On it is Captain Nemo's famous Nautilus ship, which is being overtaken by the infamous sea monster that captured readers' imaginations everywhere in Jules Verne's 1870 novel Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea. Compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, the keycap is molded in GMK profile to match, too.

Upgrade your IEMs with a Linsoul LSC09 cable, available here with your choice of an MMCX or 0.78-millimeter two-pin connector. This cable features a high-quality single-crystal copper silver-plated wire to ensure near-lossless transfer of your music signal. Plus, the wire is soft to the touch and braided to provide excellent flexibility. Each one measures 3.9 feet long.

For some, a watch is a quick way to track the time; for others, it's a work of art, a constant source of enjoyment. In the case of our first homegrown timepiece designed entirely in-house it's both. Latin for lucky, the Felix is a take-anywhere, do-anything timepiece you'll never leave at home. It's a combination of features that puts the needs of the wearer above all else. With a Swiss-made Sellita SW-200 movement, a handsomely sculpted stainless steel case, a double-domed sapphire crystal, and a 100-meter water-resistance rating, the Felix is built to thrive under any conditions. And whatever those conditions may be, it comes in multiple styles to fit right in.

prod_description: On the sporty, outdoorsy side of the Tissot collection, you'll find the T-Navigator chronograph automatic watch. Filled with functionality, this rugged timepiece comes with a date window, a 6-hour chronograph that's accurate down to the second, and a tachymeter bezel to track speed and distance in a pinch. On top of that, the rotating bezel has the cardinal directions, allowing you to find your way in the wilderness. Here in your choice of sleek black or hunter orange, the watch has a sapphire crystal and is water resistant to 100 meters.

For those who prefer a sleek look in the sunshine, these sunglasses from Calvin Klein are an excellent fit. Available here in two styles, these shades showcase slim metal frames and two different lens shapes to suit all styles. The first pair features a silver-colored titanium frame, gray polycarbonate lenses, and a square, full-rim shape. The second pair has a gold-colored metal frame, maize-colored polycarbonate lenses, and a round, full-rim lens shape. One silver, the other gold make your choice and add a sophisticated minimalist touch to your look.

With a look that's unmistakably Lacoste, these sunglasses deliver performance and comfort fit for any outing. Available here in three options, each pair is made from injected plastic that's smooth, sturdy, and lightweight. The first two options are foldable great for travel and easy carry during changing weather. These are the L778S-001, which features a black frame and gray-gradient lenses, and the L778S-002, which features a matte-black frame and blue-mirror lenses. Inspired by the iconic Lacoste polo shirt, the final option is the non-foldable L884S-414, which showcases a matte-blue frame and gray lenses. All options sport the green Lacoste crocodile along each temple.

prod_name: Levenger True Writer Create Carbon Fountain Pen
prod_description: New from Levenger, the Aero-D carbon fountain pen offers a satisfying weight in the hand and loads of industrial appeal. Understated at first glance, the barrel reveals unexpected depth when it catches the light, the woven carbon fiber just visible beneath the clear lacquer coating. Strategically placed titanium accents help prevent damage if the pen is dropped, and are complemented by a gunmetal spring clip and trim. Handcrafted in Germany, the matte black stainless steel nib is interchangeable with all Levenger and True Writer fountain pens. The threaded cap bears the company logo around the ring, and posts securely to add length while you write.

prod_name: Kershaw Reverb XL CF/G-10 Folding Knife
prod_description: You carry your knife on you at all times. It should be easy to deploy when you need it, securely locked when you don't, and it should never weigh you down. These are the principles that governed the design of Kershaw Reverb XL CF/G-10 Folding Knife. Featuring a 3-inch 8Cr13MoV stainless steel blade with a two-tone stain/PVD finish, a modified drop point, and a thumb groove for easy opening, this knife is sharp, carry-sized, and a dream to deploy. It's designed with a deep-carry pocket and a steel frame lock back for secure carrying in your pocket or bag. Lastly, its handle is engineered with ultra-light carbon fiber material overlaid with a G-10 scale to minimize weight while maximizing durability. Weighing just over two ounces, and featuring a built-in carabiner for quick attachment, this is one knife you'll always be able to carry.

prod_name: Fallkniven SK2L Embla Fixed Blade Knife
prod_description: Fallkniven's SK2L Embla embodies the minimalist Swedish style the company has long been associated with. An outdoorsman's fixed blade, the knife has a natural, desert ironwood handle, like something your grandfather may have passed down to you. Thanks to its width and density (it won't even float in water), the handle offers a full grip for confidence during light and heavy-duty cuts. Because edge retention is of utmost importance in the field, the SK2L Embla comes with a 3.9-inch blade made of premium, laminated cobalt steel. Hardened to 60 on the Rockwell scale, the blade rarely ever needs sharpening. Finally, this mid-sized beauty comes with a low-hanging leather sheath for proper belt carry.

Around since 1937, Ray-Ban makes classic shades that exude style. Here we're offering two distinct pairs, perfect for a sunny day. The first RB3609-914071-54 style features metal hexagonal frames with a double-bridge design. Combining gold plating with green lenses, it has an old-school, vintage look. The second RB4305-60171-53 style has a rounded shape with a single bridge. Smoother and more modern, it's a versatile choice and doesn't skimp on sun protection. Both sunglasses are made in Italy to exacting standards.
prod_varities: ['Ray-Ban Hexagon Sunglasses  Gold', 'Ray-Ban Round Sunglasses  Black ']

prod_description: Developed for the German Navy Sea Battalion, this timepiece is fortified in all the right places. The case is made from titanium to keep weight down without sacrificing strength. It houses a Sellita SW 330-1 21-jewel movement with a 42-hour power reserve. That movement is protected all the way down to 300 meters. When diving, you can easily read the watch thanks to the prominent markers and lumed coating. For the world traveler, there's also a GMT hand to track another time zone. You can use the bidirectional rotating bezel to track time when you're submerged. Positioned at 4 o'clock, the crown won't get in the way underwater or on the move.

Now sourced directly from Seki Edge, this six-piece grooming kit features the same great essentials previously offered on Massdrop, but with the improved quality that comes from working directly with Seki. From the stainless steel and shaping of the blades to the finishing on the tools, the craftsmanship is second to none. And each piece is branded with the Seki name to prove it.

prod_name: KBDfans x ai03 2-in-1 Aluminum Switch Opener
prod_description: Like a little metal briefcase on your keychain, this two-in-one aluminum switch opener goes anywhere you go in style. Secured by magnets, it has two sides: one for Cherry MX switches, the other for Kailh BOX switches. To open a switch, just press it into the prongs on the corresponding side and watch as it opens up.

Full of retro vibes, the Everglide 9009 keycap set can transport your desktop to another time. This full set of PBT keycaps combines beige and gray alphas and mods with some colorful extras to spice things up. There are salmon-colored spacebars, mint-colored F keys, and a host of other modifiers to inspire your favorite board. Compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, the keycaps feature dye-sublimated legends that won't fade over time.

The latest DAC/amp in Aune's S series, the S6 uses the notable AK4495 DAC chip and aims for a neutral presentation. Along with a powerful built-in headphone amplifier, it has an impressive number of inputs and outputs including USB, coaxial, optical, and AES digital inputs, plus XLR and RCA outputs. The S6 is capable of decoding 32-bit/384kHz files and has native DSD support. On the front panel, you'll find a high-quality TFT screen alongside a headphone jack and a large volume dial.

prod_description: Between smartphones and headphones, there's often a problem. Most smartphones have USB-C ports, and most headphones have 3.5-millimeter jacks. The Link from Xduoo fixes this problem with excellent fidelity to audio. An adapter and a DAC/amp in one, it takes care of digital-to-audio conversion with a built-in ESS9118EC DAC. It supports PCM decoding up to 32bit/384kHZ and DSD256. Plus, it works as a USB DAC when connected to MAC, Windows 7/10, or Linux-enabled devices. It's also highly portable. Weighing only half an ounce and measuring just over 2 inches long (3.5 inches with the cable), it's a great choice for commutes, intercontinental plane rides, and everything in between.

Chane's highly-regarded A2.4 LCR speaker delivers wide, even dispersion and more natural dialog than many conventional horizontal center speakers. Used as a vertical pair, the A2.4 also makes for superb stereo. The A2.4's carefully aligned acoustical array improves dispersion linearity and lowers phase and time errors throughout the crossover region. Response is tightly matched, while the long-axis behavior for this three-driver MTM speaker is as linear as it is a pleasure to hear. The planar leaf tweeter and its molded aluminum face plate extend to over 30 kHz, while twin double-duty, XBL2 'SplitGap' mid-bass drivers make for better resolution and higher output.  The A2.4 LCR speaker's casework provides welcome weight and durability a step up from many mid-level speakers. Adding it all up, the A2.4 delivers extraordinary clarity, enveloping three-dimensional imaging, and substantial dynamic headroom.

prod_description: Many people prefer fixed blades to folders. For one thing, they don't have any moving parts, which makes them far stronger. For another, they're much easier to clean and allow you to twist, pry, and pierce without worrying about disengaging a lock. Our first fixed blade collaboration, the Massdrop x Bradford Guardian 3.5 is a twist on a popular existing design now with new materials and colorways. Featuring a 3.5-inch Nitro-V stainless steel blade, the American-made Guardian 3.5 is fit for the jobsite, warehouse, boat, or backyard. Thanks to the contoured CNC-machined scales and the large grip area behind the small sharpening choil, it's super easy to use. The design facilitates maximum control whether you choke up, choke down, or use a reverse grip. What's more, we're offering it in eight different styles with a handmade full-grain leather sheath for belt, bag, and pack carry.
