prod_description: If you can precision machine a heavy duty folding knife, then why not precision machine a tactical pen. Rike Knife did, and it's here in nine different striking colors. Evoking the same futuristic sense that many of the company's knives do, this pen is built on a foundation of TC4 titanium. Utilizing a twist-off construction, it features a carbide striker tip on one end and a cap on the other. A milled titanium clip makes for easy carry in a shirt pocket, jeans pocket, or in a pack. The cap is O-ring sealed for a tight hold.

This two-toned version of the Victorinox Maverick is the best of both worlds: It's as tough as a field watch and as dashing as a dress watch. Crafted with stainless steel, the Maverick features a 24-hour scale on the inner dial, a mix of Arabic numerals and stick markers, and a date window at 6 o'clock. For precise timing tasks, you can use the unidirectional bezel, which is flanked by gold ridges to match the two-toned bracelet. Lumed throughout, the Maverick is visible day or night. If you need to take it for a dip in the water, have no fear, as this Swiss-made timepiece is water resistant to 100 meters.

The CCCP Aurora is a fullsize diver-style watch with an easy-to-read aesthetic. The dial, which comes in multiple colors, has thick indexes and hands for quick time-telling at a glance. Plus, at 46 millimeters, it's readable from afar. The bezel has markings in increments of five and can be rotated to track elapsed time. It's easy to grasp and turn thanks to the wide, knurled grooves. At 4 o'clock, you'll find the crown, which is used to control the hands and the date. Set on a leather strap, the Aurora is water resistant to 100 meters in case you accidentally dunk it in water.

Essentials for any sunny day, these Japan-made sunglasses from respected designer John Varvatos combine retro and modern design elements with quality materials. First up are the Crosby Polarized Sunglasses, which feature minimalist round lenses, a black-and-tortoiseshell frame, and polarized lenses with 100-percent UV protection. Next are the Mulberry Sunglasses, which have a square shape, purple non-polarized lenses, and a frame with black-and-tortoiseshell temples and translucent plastic around the lenses. The last pair, the Bond Sunglasses, share the same frame shape as the Mulberry Sunglasses but have dark-tinted lenses and an all-black-and-tortoiseshell frame just as 007 would want it.
prod_varities: ['Bond Sunglasses  V510-BLACKTORT (-$-10)', 'Crosby Polarized Sunglasses  V605BLA50', 'Mulberry Sunglasses  V779-CRY-53145 (-$-10)']

prod_description: Featuring top-of-the-line specs and a high-end look to match, the SMSL VMV D1 DAC will take your audio setup to new heights. It has eight built-in channels, paralleled for a better signal-to-noise ratio. For each channel, it uses an ES9038PRO DAC chip: widely considered one of the best DAC chips available. Head-Fi user Baten says, This DAC has some of the lowest noise floor ever (at 44 kHz sampling at least). Nearly bottlenecking the audio analyzer ¦ Balanced dynamic range of 126 dB!! Just wow. Pairing this with the Massdrop x THX amp will give some of the most transparent results ever.

This 96-key mechanical keyboard strikes a perfect balance between a fullsize and tenkeyless board. It's got everything you need including function keys, arrows, and a numpad but it doesn't waste an inch of space. The case is a real standout for a couple reasons: First, it's made from a hefty chunk of aluminum to stay put on your desk. Second, it's got a noticeable angle for an ergonomic feel when typing. The keycaps are styled in the Dolch colorway and made from durable PBT to last a lifetime. You can get them in OEM, DSA, or Cherry profile, too. Of course, since we know all typists are different, we'll be offering a wide range of Gateron, Kailh, and Cherry MX switches as well. Program your board however you like with the QMK firmware. Get it assembled or go for the kit for a fun DIY project.

prod_name: Hamilton Khaki Aviation Air Race Automatic Watch
prod_description: Since 2003, Red Bull has been putting on the Red Bull Air Race, a competition in which pilots attempt to navigate a challenging obstacle course to the delight of fans everywhere. As the official timekeeper of the Red Bull Air Race, Hamilton created the Khaki Aviation Air Race collection, all backed by reliable Swiss automatic movements and proven Swiss craftsmanship. Available here in two styles, the watch offers a whopping 80-hour power reserve. Made with a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal, it's slim, aerodynamic, and water resistant to 50 meters. Printed with the race's logo, the caseback offers a peek at the movement. The base model has luminous coating on the hands and markers; the other model does not.

prod_name: The British Belt Co. Wellbrook Wallet
prod_description: The British Belt Co. Wellbrook Wallet combines size and style in a billfold shape built to carry your cards, cash, and more. Six card pockets and one large bill pocket make daily carry a breeze, while full-grain Italian leather delivers excellent durability and texture. Inside, The British Belt Co.'s branded insignia and precision-cut brogue perforations along the bottommost pockets add welcome aesthetic appeal. Single-needle stitching in the interior and exterior brings the entire wallet together.

The Hammer studio is full of creative minds, but for their latest artisan keycap, they didn't need to look too far for inspiration. Based on the plump cat that roams around the office, the Bubble Cat keycap can make any keyboard a whole lot cuter. Available in eight different colors, it can pair with a wide range of boards not to mention there's a Topre stem available as well.

prod_name: SharpEdge Makiri Hocho Hammer Fixed Blade
prod_description: Traditionally used by fisherman for cutting rope, twine, and fish but often used today by barmen carving ice for specialty cocktails  the Makiri Hocho is an all-purpose blade with excellent utility. The 5.3-inch blade has a wide spear-point shape for piercing, slicing, and skinning. The blade has just a single bevel for precision and control. It's made from high-carbon Shirogami #2 high-carbon steel with a very high hardness rating of 62 on the Rockwell scale. There's also a hammered texture to help food slide off when you're preparing food. A magnolia handle meets the blade for a traditional, yet effective grip. When you're not using the knife, store it in the included magnolia wood sheath, which is hand-shaped from a single piece of wood. This edition of Makiri Hocho Hammer was made especially for SharpEdge with focus on details, out-of-the-box sharpness, and a premium finish.

An adjustable book stand with a velvet-lined drawer, the Levenger Cubi storage stand makes a beautiful addition to any desk. Use it to prop up a novel, notebook, or tablet as you read or work the stand can be tilted at three different angles for easy visibility. The cord organizer in the center makes it an ideal charging station, and the drawer is great for storing fountain pens, inks, and other accessories.

Eterna has been making quality Swiss timepieces since 1856. Named for the founding location and year of the brand, the Granges 1856 automatic is an everyday watch with great specs. To start, it's powered by Eterna's in-house 3030 movement, which has 24 jewels and a 48-hour power reserve. The movement itself measures just 4.6 millimeters thick, which is a key reason for the watch's remarkably slim profile of just under 10 millimeters. Made of stainless steel, the case sports a sapphire crystal on both the front and back the back to showcase the movement's inner workings. Available with multiple dial layouts, the Granges 1856 has a minimal look and a date window at 3 o'clock. Get it on your choice of leather or stainless steel.

prod_name: Montegrappa Fortuna Resin & Ruthenium Fountain Pen
prod_description: Our latest offering from Montegrappa an Italian company that's been making beautiful, functional pens since 1912 is the Fortuna Resin and Ruthenium fountain pen. Here in your choice of bold yellow or candy red, the Fortuna offers a full grip for a comfy hold, whether you're jotting notes in a meeting or writing your next novel. Like the pen's name implies, the stainless steel nib is coated in ruthenium: a rare transition metal similar to platinum. Fitted with a handsome pocket clip on the cap, the Fortuna comes in your choice of a fine, medium, or broad tip.

Combining high-performing materials with meticulous craftsmanship, TRN has created a cable designed to help earphone listeners get the most out of their audio. Hand-braided with 8-core silver, which is more conductive and has better signal-carrying properties than copper, the T3 features a total of 96 densely-woven wires. On its exterior, the T3 is equipped with Kevlar fiber for durability and smoothness, as well as a gold-plated jack for improved stability at the input. With a tangle-free design, a larger Y-shape, and precise contouring around the ears, the T3 cable keeps things comfortable and convenient while delivering high-fidelity audio.

From Nitecore, a world leader in portable lighting, comes the NU32 550-lumen rechargeable headlamp: a lightweight and long-lasting lighting solution ideal for all-purpose use. Equipped with a CREE XP-G3 S3 LED, the NU32 emits a bright 550 lumens extending out to 408 feet. In addition to this primary LED, which offers four different brightness modes, the NU32 also features high-CRI auxiliary LEDs that can be activated for close-range tasks, like reading and repairs. Weighing just 3.5 ounces with a comfortable headband, it won't get in the way. Engineered with a 330-hour rechargeable battery, it won't stop during critical tasks either.

prod_name: MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte S.A.R. Rescue Timer Automatic Watch
prod_description: Designed with input from captains in the German Maritime Search and Rescue Service and worn by members of the distinguished team the S.A.R. Rescue Timer is built to withstand the perils of any mission. Fitted with a shockproof 26-jewel movement and a sapphire crystal that's 4 millimeters thick, the S.A.R. won't fail in extreme conditions. This construction also contributes to its paramount 1,000-meter water resistance rating. As far as layout, the watch is about as easy to read as it gets, without Arabic numerals that is. At the cardinal hours are large, triangular markers that are complemented by thick hands all of which are lumed for added visibility. The crown is positioned at 4 o'clock so as not to impede wrist movement if you're diving or on the job.

prod_name: TFZ Secret Garden & Secret Garden III IEM
prod_description: When it comes to high-value IEMs, TFZ has established itself as a serious contender in a variety of price ranges. On the higher end sits the Secret Garden II, the second generation of TFZ's flagship IEM. This model features a 12-millimeter double-magnetic-circuit graphene driver, which aims for a strong bass and midrange, along with a smooth treble and a large soundstage. Shaped like a CIEM, this earphone offers a snug, comfortable fit in the ear. It comes in a few different shell colors, all with an eye-catching silver faceplate, and the 0.78-millimeter two-pin connector makes for easy cable replacement in the future. Also available is the Secret Garden III, detailed below.

prod_name: Dekoni Premium Ear Pads for HIFIMAN HE Series
prod_description: Get a different finish on your Massdrop x HIFIMAN HE-350 or HE-4XX headphones with Dekoni's highly regarded line of ear pads. Featuring attachment rings that are designed to fit HE-series headphones, the pads are compatible with the  HE-300, HE-350, HE-400, HE-500, HE-6, HE-4, HE-5LE, and HE-5. These pads feature slow-rebound, high-density memory foam wrapped in your choice of velour, sheepskin, or a combination of the two. They provide a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening all while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. Plus, everyone at Dekoni wears glasses, so this was taken into account when designing the pads.

prod_name: Massdrop x AKG K7XX Audiophile Headphones (EU)
prod_description: Our first custom headphones ever, the Massdrop x AKG K7XX have been an enduring community favorite since they first launched more than two years ago. Since then, they've received praise from Head-Fi, Super Best Audio Friends, Z Reviews, and more for offering a rare value in the world of open-back cans. Inspired by the legendary AKG K702 65th-anniversary edition, this rendition features the same dynamic driver technology and superior build quality plus a few updates in the sound and comfort departments.

prod_name: Massdrop x NuForce EDC In-Ear Monitors (EU)
prod_description: Made in collaboration with NuForce, a company that's brought us high-performance audio gear from nearby Milpitas, California for more than a decade, the EDC in-ear monitors are ready to go everywhere with you. Wear them at home, in the office, at the gym, or while traveling or commuting. The lightweight plastic housing done in a smoky transparent color is built to stand up to regular use, while the included ear tips block out noise and the zippered case offers an easy carrying solution. What's more, you'll get two removable cables: a braided cable for top-notch performance and a second cable with an inline remote and microphone. At $59.99 with all accessories, these IEMs work as an upgrade to the beginner's portable music setup or an inexpensive set to round out the serious audiophile's collection.

prod_name: Massdrop x AKG K7XX Red Edition (EU)
prod_description: Last year, we teamed up with AKG on the K7XX, a Massdrop-configured edition of the highly regarded 65th Anniversary K702. Featuring its predecessor's legendary sound and build quality with a bass boost, matched transducers, and improved comfort the K7XX was a big hit with the Audiophile Community. As positive feedback poured in, so did one recurring request: Could we add a custom colorway to make the black-on-black aesthetic really pop? AKG was happy to oblige, and we launched a poll to determine which color to include in the next limited batch. More than 3,600 votes later, red came out on top, with blue and vintage black/gold not far behind. The final product boasts a Ruby Red accent ring, stitching, and rods (RAL 3003, to be exact).

prod_name: Handgrey H3 / H4 Titanium Quick-Release Carabiner
prod_description: Both designed as counterparts to Handgray's Bauhaus series, the H3 and H4 carabiner keychains are sleek and exceptionally strong everyday carry tools. Both the H3 and the H4 are 100% wirecut, a first for carabiners. This gives them incredible precision and detailing for uncompromising performance and exceptional aesthetic appeal. The H3 features a patent-pending quick release system that allows users to remove keys easily while keeping others protected via two regions protected by a quick-release gate. The H4 also features a two-pieced design with a hybrid custom gate. The slightly-longer H3 showcases a rounder design, while the slightly-wider H4, inspired by vintage motorcycles, showcases a rounded-angular design. Both are made from strong Ti6Al4V Grade 5 titanium and finished with light stone tumbling for a rugged-yet-refined appearance.

prod_name: Massdrop x Sennheiser PC37X Gaming Headset (EU)
prod_description: Based on Sennheiser's top-tier gaming headsets, our Sennheiser PC37X features the same exceptional audio and microphone quality, with some key tweaks to make it even better and it's only available here on Drop. Made with drivers that are positioned at an angle, which is typically seen in much more expensive headsets, the PC37X maximizes natural sound reproduction. This results in more clarity in your games and tunes. Most games discussed on Drop are optimized for stereo headphones, so we invested in high-quality drivers instead of headset-based audio processing. Pair that with a blacked-out look and a noise-canceling microphone, and this headset will suit any competitive gamer.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/alt-keyboard/FP/Bpc7ernARvCU1XPA1Fhh_AI7B4453 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-alt-mechanical-keyboard/FP/paou7NKSe6jZwmGWvy6g_AI7B6436-copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/alt-keyboard/FP/LqBtGF6vQNKfYd2SDrdO_AI7B3411 copy page.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdro-alt-mechanical-keyboard/FP/GU2apR4HTZeiwkKVlBN4_ai7b4223_copy_dual.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-alt-mechanical-keyboard/FP/Lnu1vobqTxyxfiNMBxVl_AI7B6407-copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/alt-keyboard/FP/phrVVRQQWaHxpwvgxalg_AI7B3353 copy page.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/alt-keyboard/FP/UuhgAgSISKegcioaa4ml_AI7B3322 copy page.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-alt-mechanical-keyboard/FP/JRZYGLy5Rdy5ZtnpHorD_AI7B6427-copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/alt-keyboard/FP/WNxwR19gTua3nxiiQWP3_AI7B3311 copy page.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/alt-keyboard/FP/yDG7xatcRkWJCbbsuJyZ_AI7B4141 copy page.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-alt-mechanical-keyboard/FP/UcGFy8uYQqiOKDMk1guM_AI7B1360-copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-alt-mechanical-keyboard/FP/TQ5sGMGPR6OoXZY1W8jO_AI7B6412-copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: The Massdrop ALT mechanical keyboard is just like the CTRL, but with 67 keys instead of 87. Absent of function keys, it wastes no space but it still has a full set of arrows and numerals. Constructed with a solid aluminum frame with a built-in switch plate, the ALT is rock solid. And thanks to the hot-swap switch sockets, it allows you to swap switches whenever you want with no soldering required. It's also fully programmable via QMK, meaning you can assign macros or custom keybinds to every key. With dual USB-C connectors, the ALT is outfitted with the latest connections. What's more, it has customizable RGB backlighting and underlighting. Set it to a single color or light it up with a rainbow wave pattern. To enhance the backlighting, there are shine-through doubleshot PBT keycaps, too. Grab it with your choice of switches to get just the feel you want.

prod_name: Moon Key Hand-Painted Koi Artisan Wrist Rest
prod_description: Koi are prized for their beautiful color patterns and lengthy lifespans often exceeding 100 years of age. Whether you have a koi fish yourself or you appreciate their unique look and serene demeanor, this hand-painted wrist rest might be the perfect fit for your desktop. Made through a rigorous process of layering that takes nine days to finish (one day for each layer), these luxurious wrist rests appear much more lively than a 2D drawing. There are even small leaves floating in the water next to the fish, just like you'd find in a koi pond. Because each wrist rest is entirely made by hand, no two are exactly alike.

Glycine has been producing timepieces since 1914, a testament to its ability to adapt to the modern world. Perhaps best known for its 24-hour Airman tool watch, Glycine has recreated the vibe of one of its most iconic watches with the Airman 18. While it may look busy, the dial's throng of numerals, hands, and markers serves a very specific purpose. The watch is capable of tracking time in a whopping three different time zones. The first is your current time zone, indicated by the innermost markers. The independently operated GMT hand tracks the time in two separate time zones: one is shown on the inner ring; the other is indicated by the bidirectional rotating bezel controlled by the screw-down lock at 4 o'clock.

Embrace your dark side with one of BEE's new Baby Devil artisan keycaps. Like a mythical creature from ancient folklore, or a lab experiment in Hades, the Baby Devil keycap depicts a young demon baby fast asleep inside a cocoon of craggy rocks. Measuring 1.2 inches tall including the casing, this artisan will make its presence known on any board. Handmade from resin, it comes in four styles and is compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

prod_name: Armand Nicolet JS9-44 Automatic GMT Watch
prod_description: With a classic diver aesthetic, the Armand Nicolet JS9-44 is bold, rugged, and ready for a night on the town or a dunk in the pool. The dial has all the cues you'd expect in a diver, with chunky indices that are masculine and easy to read. The hands are extra thick and lumed for visibility in the dark or underwater. Rotate the ceramic bezel to set the time for the GMT hand, which allows you to track the time in another time zone. For materials, Armand Nicolet spared no expense. Fitted with a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal, the JS9-44 is water resistant to a whopping 300 meters.

Sporting a classic tenkeyless layout, the Keycool KC-87 has a full set of arrows, numbers, function keys, and more. The keycaps are styled in the classic Dolch colorway, with gray alphas with black legends and dark gray modifiers. Made from PBT, they're durable and resistant to oils that can accumulate from long sessions of typing. For the fastest typists, there's N-key rollover, too. This means that no matter how fast you type, your keyboard will register each press. Depending on your desired feel, we've got you covered in the switch department. Choose Gaterons or Cherry MX switches to get just the feel you like. Also of note are the adjustable feet on the case and the covered USB port that helps protect the cord from damage over time.

prod_name: Philip Zepter PZYT Yachting Timer Watch
prod_description: Sometimes referred to as regatta timers or simply sailing watches, yacht timers are specifically designed for the start of a boat race. Because it's difficult to start a race on water (due to wind conditions, waves, etc.), yachts are typically allowed to start a race at full speed. With a built-in chronograph and colorful chapter ring, the Philip Zepter PZYT Yachting Timer is made to help your craft reach maximum speed at the perfect time, right before the starting gun sounds. This sporty, water-resistant stainless steel timepiece is primed to handle the inevitably harsh conditions encountered when sailing. Available in two styles, it gets power from an accurate quartz battery.

Designed and produced by Redditor /u/Pawnerd, these CNC-milled keycaps are made from the wood of cherry trees. They're compatible with Cherry switches and come in surprise! Cherry profile. Not only do these unique keycaps look and feel different, as they retain the natural grain of the wood, they also sound different slightly muffled compared with plastic keycaps.

prod_name: Rike Knife EDC-05 Damascus Keychain Folding Knife
prod_description: Measuring just 3.5 inches long, the Rike Knife EDC-05 is small, agile, and beautiful. It's not exactly a workhorse, but that's not the point. A great letter opener, box slicer, and nail picker, it'll also make a great gift. The overall construction is impressive: the flipper is made with a damascus steel blade, titanium handle, and ceramic ball bearing washer system. And as far as looks, it's got everything you'd expect in a Rike Knife, with precision-machined details and a smooth-as-butter opening system. Carry it in a pocket, in the leather pouch, or on the neck chain.

prod_name: Dekoni Audio Headphone Savior Carry Case
prod_description: From Dekoni, an industry leader in headphone earpads, comes a new carrying case designed for the most demanding headphone users. Durable yet soft to the touch, the Dekoni Savior is sized to fit the largest headphones on the market today, including the Focal Utopia, Audeze LCD Series, and Sennheiser HD800 headphones. It also includes several pockets to hold a digital audio player, adaptors, and even a spare cable. Inside, movable partitions enable custom equipment layouts; outside, a built-in climbing loop allows for quick attachment to other luggage or transformation into a satchel. For the most-prized headphone setups, the Savior truly lives up to its name.

To put it simply, the CTRL mechanical keyboard has it all. Constructed with a solid aluminum frame with a built-in switch plate, it's stable and fortified. And thanks to the hot-swap switch sockets, it allows you to change switches whenever you want with no soldering required. It's also fully programmable via QMK, meaning you can assign macros or custom keybinds to every key. With dual USB-C connectors, the CTRL is outfitted with the fastest available connections. Aesthetically, the keyboard is equally impressive. Featuring customizable RGB backlighting and underlighting, it puts on a colorful show; or you can set it to a single color for a more subtle look. The shine-through PBT keycaps only enhance the performance. What's more, the keyboard comes with your choice of switches, so you can get just the feel you like whether you prefer something heavy and tactile or lightweight and linear.

ZDP-189 is a specialty steel typically reserved for high-end pocket knives. Here it plays the starring role in a Western-style kitchen knife inspired by Japanese tradition. Made up of 3 percent carbon and nearly 20 percent chromium, the steel will stay sharp cut after cut, but it won't corrode or rust when put to the test (as long as you clean and dry it properly). The steel is laminated with multiple layers, and the outer layers protect the core steel from corrosion and other external factors. These outer layers also make the knife less prone to breaking, compared to a mono steel clad. The handle, made from strong walnut wood, has an octagonal shape for a comfy hold. The blade's shape lends itself to fast chopping, but the gently designed belly is suitable for long and short cuts, too. (The wooden sheath is not included this time around.)

Equipped with removable stylus tips, the Levenger L-Tech 3.0 fountain pen lets you go from paper to tablet with ease. The solid brass body has a satisfying heft, offering extra protection and more weight in the hand. The faceted barrel helps prevent the pen from rolling off your desk, while the knurled grip provides lasting comfort. The removable cap can be taken off entirely for a sleeker shape, or used with either the touchscreen-sensitive mesh fabric or silicone rubber stylus. This fountain pen is compatible with international standard cartridges and converters.

prod_name: Aune X1s 2020 Edition DAC/Amp or Aune X7s Amp
prod_description: The Aune X1s 2020 follows the popular Aune 10th Anniversary Edition, which provided an excellent value in an all-in-one DAC/amp solution. The X1s is the 7th generation of the Aune X1 Series. Featuring an upgraded DAC with an ES9038Q2M DAC chip with the ability to decode 32bit/768k and DSD512 files it's built to take your music, movies, and games to new levels of clarity. Coupled with a 5th-generation class-A amp that can drive demanding headphones, it's an excellent choice on any desktop. Also available as an add-on or standalone option is the X7s, a powerful Class-A balanced headphone amp  with three gain levels, plus eight power transistors split into four groups for a truly balanced output. According to reviewers at Headfonia, the X7s is "more powerful than a number of $1,000+ amps," and its sleek, polished appearance fits well with any setup.

Frequently named among the best budget power amplifiers on sites like Audiogon, the Topping TP60 features a powerful TA2022 Class-T amplifier and delivers an output of 80W x 2. This amp uses a double transformer linear power support, and these transformers are placed in the shield to prevent interferences and avoid transformer vibration. Easily chosen via the button on the front panel, the two-way input allows you to connect two players or devices at once and select the input you need. In addition to driving speakers, the TP60 has a hidden talent: Many Head-Fi members call it one of the best budget amps for the HIFIMAN HE-6 headphones. Describing the pairing, zenpunk says, The great thing about the TP60 is that it doesn't have any signature, just very detailed and transparent with fantastic extension for both bass and treble. From memory, it is very similar to the Schiit Mjolnir."

prod_name: KC Tool Knife Maintenance Kit  Drop Exclusive
prod_description: Like any tool, knives need to be cleaned and maintained to perform their best which is why we've assembled this collection of items to keep your favorite folders and fixed blades clean, sharp, and working like new. To do so, we worked with KC Tool, the number one German tool distributor in the US, to bring together a comprehensive assortment of enthusiast-grade components. Among them are a set of Torx tools, lubricant, cleaning solution, a strop block, and a protective work surface. Each piece has been selected based on community reviews and input. And it all comes in a nylon pouch for safekeeping. See below for more details on the components.

Making high-quality products since 1976, Sunshine Products USA started with a humble lathe and now utilize fully computerized, state-of-the-art machining equipment. This precision-machined brass container can be used for anything small like pills, tinder, small coins, cash, spices, and more. The quick-twist closure is safe and secure, and the body is strong enough to protect the contents inside.

Named for the legendary 18th-century Swiss watchmaker Pierre Jaquet-Droz, Jaquet Droz became a household name in the world of watches with timekeeping mechanisms that fascinated the rulers of Europe, China, India, and Japan. Today, the company's watches continue to astonish on a technical and artistic level. The Jaquet Droz Grande automatic doesn't necessarily shock and awe like some other models in the company's collection, but it's built to the same exacting standards. Featuring a minimal dial with a wide date window at 6 o'clock, the Grande is a handsome wear for a nice occasion. Measuring just 39 by 11 millimeters, it can easily conceal under a cuff for an understated look. Inside the sculpted stainless steel case is the company's in-house Caliber 1150P automatic movement with a silicone balance wheel and a lengthy 68-hour power reserve.

User-friendly and compact enough for travel, the WOLF Watch Winder makes for the perfect resting place for any automatic watch in your collection. Pre-programmed to rotate bi-directionally at least 900 turns per day, the watch winder keeps your timepieces charged and ready to wear.

Ingersoll, an American company founded in New York in 1892, creates vintage watches that can transition from the streets to a nice dinner with ease. The Reliance is a stainless steel timekeeper in two classic colors. Designed with diver-style indices and hands, the watch has a masculine look, but it won't take over your wrist, thanks to the modest 40-millimeter case size. Fitted with an automatic Miyota movement, the Reliance is also water resistant to 100 meters. Choose a black or blue dial and put a piece of Americana on your wrist.

prod_name: The Eye Key Chameleon Artisan Keycap
prod_description: The Eye Key brought us the Rose artisan and the Mini Scenes of Vietnam artisan keycaps. The company's latest takes a different direction one with every bit as much color as before. This cute little chameleon sits on a log, blending in with its surroundings. If you want to blend it with yours, it comes in seven different colors. You could even grab a few (or all seven) and put them in sequence on an F row or numbers row to show a gradual color transition. Made from resin, the keycaps are compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.
prod_varities: ['Original - Glowing in the dark (Medium Sea Green)', 'Equator (Red/Yellow/Orange)', 'Tropic (Yellow/Green/Blue)', 'Night Sky 2 (Blue/Purple/Red)', 'Illusion 2 (Green/ Purple/Orange)', 'Basic 2 (Yellow/Red/Blue)', 'Twinkle (+$5)', 'All 7 (+$170)']

prod_description: Manufactured with clear casings, Gateron Switches have quickly become one of the most sought after names in the keyboard community. Gateron Switches use copper contact leafs and soft plastic stems, making for an unparalleled, smooth typing experience. Gateron produces a secure fit for any keycaps and all stems are compatible with MX housing, letting you pick from the wide variety of available keycaps.

From storied Swiss watchmaker Tissot comes this modestly sized timepiece, the T-Classic automatic. Measuring 33 millimeters across, this watch fits comfortably on any wrist. The dial comes in your choice of understated cream with a polished bezel, or bold mother of pearl with a gold-toned bezel. Both models get power from Tissot's Calibre Powermatic 80 automatic movement, which ticks for up to 80 hours on a full charge. A scratch-resistant sapphire crystal helps prevent any dings and nicks, while a 50-meter water-resistance rating protects against slight water damage.

A flashlight comes in handy more often than you might think. Offering a 2,000-lumen beam with a frame that fits comfortably in one hand, the Nextool XPH50.2 is a portable powerhouse for camping, night walks, lighting up the night sky, and more. Capable of pumping out a 380-meter beam, this torch comes with five modes, including strobe and SOS mode for emergencies. Crafted with an aerospace-grade aluminum body, the light is both waterproof and impact resistant. Charging up is a breeze thanks to the USB-C port located directly on the body. After 3 to 5 hours of charge time, it can cast a low beam for nearly six days straight.

If you like to rotate your keyboards, there are undoubtedly a few on the back burner collecting dust. With the Orange acrylic anti-dust cover, you can keep them clean and pristine. The cover rests atop the keyboard, covering 80% of the upper case frame, so you don't have to worry about the height of your keyboard or the position of the USB. Since it's made from acrylic, the cover offers a clear view of the beauty of the board beneath.

Founded in Minneapolis in 2008, Hollows Leather draws inspiration from American heritage brands like Filson, Red Wing, and Pendleton. This pocket dump tray is cut from belt-weight leather and available in two sizes: the square version for all things pocket-size, from keys to coins to lighters, and the rectangular version, which can accommodate pens, stationery, and other desk items. Fastened with solid brass stud hardware, both are collapsible for easy transportation. Still, they won't lose their shape, even with extended use.

prod_name: The British Belt Co. Langdale Card Holder
prod_description: Stylish and strong, the Langdale Card Holder from The British Belt Co. cuts down on size without cutting corners on quality. Featuring a leather exterior, this compact wallet has three card pockets on one side, and a large essentials pockets lined with Halley Stevenson waxed twill on the other. Tasteful stitching can be found on both sides around the wallet's perimeter, while a brand insignia from The British Belt Co. is located just under the three card pockets.

prod_name: Mordeco Revov Beech Wood Coin Storage
prod_description: Ditch the coin jar, the plastic cup, the unsightly bowl, and find a new place for your change. The Mordeco Revov is convenient and contemporary. Made from beech wood, it has a funnel-style top to collect all your change. When you want to grab some coins on the way out, rotate the magnetic top open and dig in. Then flip it closed and it automatically settles (the motion is somewhat addictive). Weighted at the base, the container will stay put when empty, and it certainly won't budge once change starts to fill up.

prod_name: PlusSound Exo Bluetooth 5.0 IEM & Headphone Cables
prod_description: Have a favorite pair of headphones or IEMs that aren't Bluetooth enabled? Bring them up to speed with an ultra-small Bluetooth 5.0 cable from PlusSound. Available here in the Exo Series line, with several connector and termination configurations, these cables are capable of turning any pair of IEMs or headphones into a Bluetooth 5.0 device. Each cable supports SBC, AAC, aptX, aptX-LL, and aptX-HD and comes with a module located on its right end for easy control. To optimize sound quality, PlusSound revamped the circuitry for this generation and used Sony's audiophile-grade LDAC codec with up to 990 kbps for Hi-Res wireless performance. Connect up to three sources at one time, fast-charge via your computer with USB-C connectivity, and enjoy longer battery life than previous PlusSound models.

prod_name: American Bench Craft Leather Flashlight Holster
prod_description: Carrying a flashlight every day can be uncomfortable and harsh on your pockets. With this leather holster from American Bench Craft, you can carry your go-to torch in style. Made from premium leather, the holster is fastened with brass rivets no flimsy loops, slides, or clips that wear down over time. The holster can be worn vertically or positioned at an angle, depending on your preference. 100-percent made in the USA, it comes in your choice of black or brown and is compatible with belts up to 1.75 inches wide.

Driving the impressive sound of the Toneking P10 IEM is a 10-millimeter planar magnetic driver in each ear. Evenly suspended between magnetic fields, with even movement when current is introduced, this driver delivers ultra-low distortion with deep bass extension, transparent mids, and detailed highs. The earbuds themselves are ergonomically shaped to fit the ear and made from aluminum to minimize weight and maximize strength. Atop the earbuds, eartips made with medical-grade silicone to ensure lasting comfort. A detachable MMCX cable crafted from 6N OCC copper delivers a crystal-clear signal while allowing for easy cable replacement if necessary.

Done in a 60% layout, the Obinslab Anne Pro 2 takes up little space on the desktop. Factor in that it requires no cord thanks to Bluetooth wireless, and its footprint is even smaller. Yet, despite the keyboard's compact nature, it would be wrong to label it subtle. Backed by RGB backlighting with a cool white or sleek black look, the board makes a strong impression. Capable of being programmed to your liking, the keyboard is highly customizable. It boasts an 8-hour battery life, a vast improvement over the Anne Pro. It also has new firmware, which will be upgraded with expanded functionality in the future. Available with your choice of switches, the Anne Pro 2 is a worthy upgrade from the already popular original.

prod_name: Edox Les Vauberts Moonphase 80505 Automatic Watch
prod_description: Les Vauberts, where this collection of Edox watches takes its name, is a small area near Les Genevez, famous for hosting the first watchmakers more than four centuries ago. In tribute to these skilled artisans, the Les Vauberts Moonphase 80505 has a dressy, minimal look but plenty of functionality to go with it. The layout of the dial is well-balanced and clean. Even with a date window at 3 o'clock and a moonphase indicator at 6 o'clock, it maintains plenty of whitespace, so as not to overwhelm the wearer. The stainless steel case houses a Swiss SW280 movement, which is protected to 200 meters thanks to the screw-down caseback.

The SMSL SP100 Tube Headphone Amplifier is the perfect solution for anyone in search of smooth and rich audio for their headphones. Outfitted with an easy-to-change 6N3 tube, the SP100 delivers a warm and soft sound only attainable through quality tube amplification. That sound is improved even further with an onboard MCU + KELAY circuit, which reduces background noise, strengthens bass frequencies, and adds brilliance to treble frequencies. Also on board is a Japanese TOCOS Volume Potentiometer for better control of current, voltage, and resistance. The SMSL SP100 delivers an output of 95 mW (times two) at 32 ohms ideal for low-impedance headphones. Equipped with an RCA out, the SMSL SP100 can also be used as a stereo preamplifier for other amps and active speakers.

prod_name: Massdrop x Koss ESP/95X Electrostatic System (EU)
prod_description: A revival of the standard-setting ESP/950 released by Koss in 1990, these headphones bring electrostatic quality into a whole new price bracket. Initially designed for live recording, the ESP/950 came with a large carrying case and a battery pack to power the required energizer: a special amplifier for electrostatic drivers. Made for the modern audiophile's listening purposes, this version skips the case and battery pack to save on weight, space, and cost. The color has been updated to Massdrop's exclusive midnight blue and the pleather ear pads swapped for thicker, more comfortable foam wrapped in velour. The rest stays true to the original: same clean bass and unmatched sound quality; same pivoting cups and adjustable, detachable headband; and same energizer, now with new graphics and colorway all backed by the same lifetime warranty.

prod_name: Massdrop x Fostex TR-X00 Mahogany Headphones (EU)
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/zRCqIzYCRrW8ALryydNU_AI7B5926 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/X1APp1vyTA2Pb79TJB2f_AI7B2984 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/xy6KIEJTPmhiEdYTA0Zl_AI7B3032 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/ONJooWAR7u2slETwkO0Q_AI7B2956 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/UKyCPb4RRsWb1Ispu5bg_AI7B2957 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/Mg0zrbBkRXioBH7RFzww_AI7B2966 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/46dVioFsRMu9YnBy0Lbg_AI7B3012 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/Ho6z2y8hR4WUQ8cU56su_AI7B1843 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-mahogany-headphones/FP/MgT2Y51RJCkM6yxKovYd_AI7B9745 copy cc.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: When the Massdrop community asked for a closed-back headphone that redefined price-to-performance expectations, the TH-X00 was our answer. Made in collaboration with Fostex, a brand that's produced innovative audio gear since 1949, these headphones feature mahogany ear cups, a magnesium alloy frame, Fostex's signature biodynamic drivers, and a highly reviewed sound signature. Now, in another response to the community's requests, we've updated the original with a removable cable. Introducing the TR-X00 (the R stands for removable): everything you loved about the TH-X00, now with a detachable cable for greater flexibility.

Praised on Head-Fi as a great value DAC to build a system around, the Topping D30 is easy to use and easy to love. It features the highly regarded Cirrus Logic CS4398 DAC chip along with WIMA, EPCOS, and Nichicon FW capacitors and the OPA2134 high-fidelity opamp and supports DSD64, DSD128, and PCM formats up to 24 bit/192 kHz. The circuit has been specially designed to eliminate pop noise, and the laser-engraved aluminum shell is sleek, sturdy, and compact. Plus, it's as user-friendly as they come, its front panel fitted with two LED indicators and two switches: one for on/off and the other to switch between optical, coaxial, and USB.

A pilot's watch with tons of features, the Citizen Aviator works well in both active and formal settings. A chronograph and compass in addition to a regular timekeeper, the Aviator does triple duty. Crafted from stainless steel, it's water resistant to 100 meters. Of course, as part of the Eco-Drive lineup, it's powered by light and can hold a charge for months, even if you leave it in a drawer which you most likely won't, given its everyday appeal.

prod_name: Citizen AW7030-06E PRT Black Dial Watch
prod_description: No-frills functionality: That's what you get with the Citizen AW7030-06E. Backed by Citizen's light-powered Eco-Drive movement, the watch never needs a wind or a charge, so long as you give it some light every 8 months. Aesthetically, the AW7030-06E puts legibility above all else. Large Arabic numerals with lumed coating make it easy to glean the time at a glance, while a window with a white background make it easy to deduce the date. Also notable is the scale on the bottom left of the dial, which measures the watch's remaining power reserve. Set on a NATO nylon strap, this timepiece is comfy, tough, and water resistant to 100 meters.

prod_name: CCCP Shchuka Collection Chronograph Quartz Watch
prod_description: Shchuka-class submarines were the second most prevalent in the Soviet Navy, scattered throughout the Black Sea, Baltic Sea, and Pacific Ocean. Taking styling cues from these machines, the CCCP Shchuka collection is rugged and steadfast. The dial has vertically positioned subdials one to track running seconds, and the other to track chronograph seconds. A slim line bisects the subdials for a crosshair-style look. The crown is secured by a metal hatch, not unlike one you might find aboard a submarine. Additionally, the red pusher at 2 o'clock evokes a sense of utility and importance, like an emergency button.

prod_name: Bertucci A-3P Sportsman's Quartz Field Watch
prod_description: Bertucci makes durable watches for adventurers, outdoorsman, and active individuals. The A-3P is a no-frills timepiece that won't let you down, no matter where you roam. Made with Bertucci's patented Unibody design, the stainless steel case measures a versatile 42 millimeters. Long-lasting and comfortable, the webbed nylon band is a one-size-fits-all design. Water resistant to 100 meters, the A-3P can accompany you on a dip in the water, too. The dial is clean and easy to read thanks to the luminous coating on the hands and markers. Inside the Arabic numerals are markings for military time.

New from the renowned audio team at Knowledge Zenith (KZ), the KZ ZSX IEM is tailor-made for an excellent listening experience. Each earbud in the KZ ZSX features five balanced armatures two sets of DWEK medium- and high-frequency balanced armatures and one 30095 high-frequency balanced armature to clearly articulate mid and high frequencies. Each earbud also features one 10-millimeter double-magnetic low frequency dynamic driver for full-bodied bass. Both comfortable and durable, the KZ ZSX IEM has a faceplate made of zinc alloy and a molded cavity made of imported resin. With physical electronic compound tuning and a detachable 0.75-millimeter 2-pin cable, this IEM delivers on sound and ease of use.

If you know audio gear, you know the Sennheiser HD 650. The company's flagship from 2003 to 2009, this open-back headphone has shown serious staying power. Praised for its richly detailed, effortlessly enjoyable sound, it remains one of the most talked-about products on Head-Fi today and is still widely considered among the best headphones under $1,000. So when we teamed up with Sennheiser on its first-ever community-driven design partnership, the HD 650 was a natural place to start. A new revision of the popular all-rounder, the Massdrop x Sennheiser HD 6XX has that same great sound plus a few updates, and a price that makes it even easier to love.

Utilizing electro-capacitive key switches, the NiZ Plum84 Pro combines the silent operation of a rubber dome keyboard with the reliability and tactility of a mechanical keyboard. The construction consists of a rubber dome that houses a slider, over which is a coiled spring and a printed circuit board. The result? Limited resistance from a soft tactile bump, and individually weighted keys for a consistent feel. Outfitted with strong PBT keycaps, the board is durable and resistant to the oils that build up from your fingertips over time. If you want to adjust the layout, feel free: It's fully programmable as well.

With Persol's peerless craftsmanship and a smooth circular shape, each pair of sunglasses in this run showcases a style great for any setting. The first pair features a black acetate frame with polarized yellow-green lenses and a high bridge. The second gets a slimmer Havana tortoise-shell plastic frame with non-polarized dark-green lenses and a more centered bridge. Choose the style that best fits your look, or cover your bases and get both.
prod_varities: ['Persol Polarized Sunglasses - Black - Yellow/Green Photo Polarized - 56-20-145 MM', 'Persol Round Sunglasses - Havana - Green - 52-21-145 MM (-$10)']

prod_description: You may never have heard of Jenny Watches, but the company's impact on dive watch history is hard to overstate. Formed in 1963, the family-owned Swiss company actually created the world's first 1,000-meter water-resistant diver. The Jenny 300 is an updated version of the Jenny 700, the outfit's first-ever design. Sporting lumed hands and indices and a date window at 3, it conforms to some traditional diver standards. However, the bezel is where this watch really stands out. Measuring 3.5 millimeters high, it displays technical information about proper decompression times when coming back to the surface. Powering this one-of-a-kind timepiece is the formidable ETA 2824-2 movement. Part of a limited-edition run, each watch is limited to just 500 total pieces.

Crafted for comfort and cutting-edge sound articulation, the new Phantom planar magnetic headphones from Thieaudio deliver a powerful listening experience at an attractive price point. Sound quality is driven by advanced 101-millimeter planar magnetic drivers, which feature ultra-light German composite diaphragms with dual magnetic circuits. These magnets are engineered with high-pass magnet technology for balanced strength that minimizes harmonic distortion and maximizes detail. Handcrafted with a natural black walnut shell and high-grade metal covering, the Phantom puts acoustic performance and strength in the right places. Topping things off are a pair of padded velvet earpads for uncompromising comfort.

Combining a host of popular items from the world of lockpicking, this kit is a thorough starting point for anyone interested in the field. The beauty of the kit is that it allows you to learn at your own pace. It comes with the Cyclops Stand: a 4-by-4-inch aluminum base that's compatible with standard and cutaway locks and allows you to position the head any way you like. Also included is a SouthOrd pick set with a total of 14 pieces, plus nine different locks to work your way from one pin all the way up to six. To guide you, there's the Master Resource CD-ROM, full of tips, tricks, and techniques to different types of lockpicking. The Kwikset keyway is generally easier to start with than the Schlage, which can be more difficult to pick due to its shape.

prod_name: The British Belt Co. Langdale Wallet
prod_description: Sporting a unique texture with impressive durability and plenty of space, the Langdale Wallet from The British Belt Co. is both a statement piece and a lifelong carry solution. Its exterior features weather-resistant Halley Stevenson waxed twill, which is accented by tasteful leather trim. On the interior, it's all leather. Six card pockets and a large currency pocket make carrying essentials easy, while meticulous stitching and The British Belt Co. branding add extra aesthetic appeal.

Burja is a Slovenian word for the cold, dry gusts of wind that hammer Italy from the Northeast. These winds provide the perfect climate for ageing prosciutto, the dry, Italian cured ham known for its savory depth of flavor. Aptly named, this knife is designed for precisely slicing prosciutto from any region of the world. Thanks to a long, slim blade, it makes cutting uniform paper-thin slices easy and it can do so just as easily with other meats and fish as well. The blade is constructed of Japanese Aichi 1K6M VM steel, which is fashioned into a single thin layer to promote blade flexibility. The handle is made of black Japanese pakkawood for a comfy hold and lasting build. Stored in a wooden gift box, this slicer is built for precision.

Edge performance is closely tied to sharpness. To keep your kitchen knives and fixed blades in great working condition, you need a good set of tools. Enter the SharpEdge Home Basic sharpening set. This three-piece set comes with a combination whetstone used for putting a new edge on a blunt knife, fine sharpening, and removing burrs. One side is #1000 grit, and the other #3000 grit. To use it, soak the stone in water for 10 minutes and drag the edge at a continuous angle back and forth, on both sides. The included sharpening guide clip helps maintain the same angle. It has a soft plastic build to prevent damage to your favorite blades. After initial sharpening, use the leather strop to remove the remainder of the burr from the blade. If you prefer a more specialty combination whetstone, there's a #1000/#6000 grit and #3000/#8000 grit whetstone, plus a simple #400 grit whetstone at checkout.

Stylish and practical, the Kershaw Copper Cinder Tactical Knife is a keychain knife designed for knife users who prioritize performance and aesthetic appeal. Upgraded from the previous Cinder model, this knife features a copper handle and a stonewashed sheepsfoot blade. Designed from concept to completion by Rick Hinderer, a renowned name in the knifemaking world, this knife has ergonomics engineered into every edge. Its non-threatening EDC blade makes it perfect for purses and pockets, and it's innovative three-finger grip fits nearly any hand while helping to provide cutting power. Plus, the new Cinder has a built-in bottle opener and a large elongated hole for a variety of keychain attachments. Carry yours wherever you go for portable performance accented by the timeless appeal of copper. Get a two-pack with your order so you can share or stay extra-supplied the choice is yours.

This combination diamond/ceramic whetstone is capable of sharpening virtually any type of steel. To use it, align your blade at a 15- to 20-degree angle, stroke the blade three to 10 times, reverse the blade, and repeat the process. Use the golden diamond side for major blade repairs like resetting the bevel and reshaping the edge. Use the black ceramic side for touching up and finishing your edge. It also comes with a leather pouch for convenient carry.

prod_name: MEE Audio MMCX Balanced Audio Cable w/ Adapters
prod_description:
Easily install a balanced cable on your MMCX IEMs without the hassle of changing the cable on the IEM shells. This cable's 2.5-millimeter balanced termination can be alternated with adapters for 3.5-millimeter single-ended, 3.5-millimeter balanced, or 4.4-millimeter balanced. This is especially useful when you're switching between a phone and a high-end digital audio player, or various other sources, as it eliminates the need to remove the cable from the connectors. Plus, the cable construction is improved from previous MEE Audio offerings, with an updated conductor composition for lower impedance, a new plug, reinforced strain reliefs, and enhanced resistance to sweat and oils from your skin. It's compatible with MMCX IEMs, as well as many MEE Audio IEMs, including the Pinnacle P1, P2, and M7 Pro.
To learn more, check out this Head-Fi review.

Backed by more than 100 years of expertise, the Glycine Combat Sub Automatic is a robust diver's watch. Water resistant to 200 meters, it features Glycine's GL224 automatic movement. This Swiss-made movement offers a 38-hour power reserve and features a sweeping seconds hand that vibrates at 28,800 beats per hour. A sapphire crystal and stainless steel case ensure the watch's durability. The rotating bezel helps keep track of elapsed time when under water, completing the classic diver watch design. The case back is adorned with the signature Glycine logo.

prod_name: Massdrop x NuForce EDC3 In-Ear Monitors (EU)
prod_description: Following the success of the Massdrop x NuForce EDC, named The Absolute Sound's 2017 Earphone of the Year, we're excited to announce its big brother: the EDC3. This new IEM swaps the original's single dynamic driver for three balanced armatures per ear, and the lightweight housing is entirely translucent to showcase the drivers within. The tuning is different, too: While the EDC has a fun sound with a bit of extra bass, the EDC3 is more neutral and less warm but still retains its musicality. The two complement one another well for those who like to have a pair of IEMs (one neutral, one fun) to cover all the bases. On its own, the EDC3 makes a great everyday all-rounder, complete with two cables, five sets of ear tips, and a carrying case.

prod_name: Massdrop Liquid Carbon X + SDAC DAC/Amp (EU)
prod_description: This DAC/amp brings two of the community's favorite designers together in one convenient, great-sounding package. It features the Massdrop x Alex Cavalli Liquid Carbon X amp, built by the founder of Cavalli Audio a legend in the world of headphone amps. For the DAC section, it uses the Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC (or SDAC), a collaboration with a company long known for its incredibly accurate, transparent studio gear. The result is an all-in-one unit made of high-grade, CNC-milled aluminum that's more portable and easily stackable than the sum of its parts. It works well with a variety of driver types and impedances, including all previous Massdrop over-ear headphones.

If you're short on space and long overdue on a new keyboard, the NYM84 is a great option. It's got everything you need including function keys, arrows, and numerals but it doesn't waste an inch of space. The hefty aluminum case is angled for a natural feel, and it's heavy enough to stay put on any desktop. Available as a kit (which will require soldering) or fully assembled, the NYM84 is also outfitted with 16 underglow LEDs to give it more presence. Since we know all typists are different, we'll be offering a wide range of Gateron, Kailh, and Cherry MX switches as well. Program your board however you like with the QMK firmware. The base price does not include keycaps, but you can add a full set of dye-subbed PBT keycaps in DSA profile at checkout.

The Kershaw Natrix series is characterized by its patented sub frame lock mechanism, in which one side of the handle has a steel plate for secure lockup, while the rest of the handle can be made from other materials. On this version, the handle is constructed from solid copper, the blade from D2 steel. Machined holes on both sides allow you to position the clip on either side, too. Featuring a 2.75-inch drop-point blade, the Natrix is versatile enough for slicing, piercing, chopping, and more. Flip it open with a press on the flipper tab. Thanks to the sub frame lock construction, the knife weighs just over 3.5 ounces despite its 6.5-inch-long body.

prod_name: Everglide Crystal Violet Custom Mechanical Switches
prod_description: With a round tactile bump similar to v2 Zealios or Holy Panda switches, the Everglide Crystal Violet custom mechanical switches offer a satisfying typing experience for hours on end. Rated for 50 million presses, they have a clear purple ABS plastic housing and a violet stem. The initial force of 45 grams provides a welcome tactile threshold to overcome for a nice feel. Available in packs of 70 or 110, these switches will elevate any board you put them in.

The Galaxy T2 is a new value IEM from TFZ, a brand that's earned a great reputation on Massdrop for making products that perform well above their price. This one features a 12-millimeter double-magnetic-circuit graphene driver, and at 16 ohms, it can be easily driven by most mobile sources. Take your pick of four stylish finishes to pair with your phone or digital audio player. Complete with removable cables with two-pin 0.78-millimeter connectors, the Galaxy T2 comes with six pairs of ear tips, a shirt clip, and a carrying pouch.

prod_name: Victorinox I.N.O.X. Pro-Diver Titanium Quartz Watch
prod_description: If an underwater adventure is afoot, the Victorinox I.N.O.X. Pro-Diver is a sure bet on the wrist. Virtually everything about this rugged watch is built to handle the elements from its lightweight and tough titanium case to its rubber strap and 200-meter water resistance rating. Aesthetically, it's easy to see, too. The white strap and silver-gray case make a nice pair that jives in sporty settings. Lumed circular and rectangular indexes make timekeeping at a glance easy, while orange and red accents around the chapter ring add a welcome splash of color to the overall look.

prod_name: Hot Keys Project Dead Man Artisan Keycap
prod_description: Nobody wants to be a dead man walking but a dead man typing? That's a different story. Here to tell it is the Hot Keys Project, back with another artisan keycap to shake up your favorite set. The Dead Man artisan is an ominous, hooded figure with demonic eyes and an evil glare. The cap comes in five wildly different colorways, so you can more than likely match one to your keyboard. Compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, the keycaps are made from resin for durability, press after press.
prod_varities: ['Light Olive Green', 'Metallic Blue', 'Ocean Blue', 'Pearl White', 'Wild Frog']

prod_description: You'd be hard pressed to find a more fun way to test switches than with CLICKEYbits. In fact, though they were originally developed as switch testers, people loved them so much that they started buying them as fidget toys. Building on the success, the father-son team that created them set out to expand the lineup. Now available with three different clicky switches (Cherry Greens, Greetech Blues, and Kailh Navies), this version is as clicky as it gets. At about 2 inches wide, it's the perfect size to fill the palm for a satisfying feel in the hand. Each one comes in an ornamental ball, if you want to give it as a gift.

Done in a classic diver style, the JS9 is bold, rugged, and ready for a night on the town or a dunk in the pool. This particular model scales down the overall size to a wrist-friendly 41 millimeters (as opposed to the 44-millimeter models made originally). The dial has all the cues you'd expect in a diver, with indices that are split in two for a unique twist. The hands are extra thick and lumed for visibility. Rotate the ceramic bezel and set it to the minutes hand if you need to time something. Beneath the handsome exterior lies an automatic SW-200 (or ETA 2824-2) movement. For materials, Armand Nicolet spared no expense. Fitted with a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal, the JS9 is water resistant to a whopping 300 meters.

The Nextorch E51 (Updated for 2019) can pump out up to 1,400 lumens and cast a beam as far as 200 meters but you wouldn't know it looking at its small stature. At just 5 inches long, it's small enough to easily take on the go, which is easy given the included pocket clip. The hard anodized aluminum body is built to stand up in the field. Meanwhile five modes allow you to take on anything that comes at you. Low mode offers up to 55 hours of runtime, while high mode still offers a solid 2.5 hours. If trouble arises, you can signal for help or stun a foe with strobe mode, too. Cycle through them all with the tail switch. Plus, if the light runs out of power, use the included USB C cable to bring it back to life.

prod_name: Corum Admiral's Cup Quartz Wall Clock
prod_description: A staple in the Corum collection for more than half a century, the Corum Admiral is instantly recognizable thanks to its 12-sided case. While the design is typically reserved for Corum's automatic watches, here it gets a reboot in the form of a quartz-powered wall clock. Measuring 19 inches across, this clock makes a statement on any surface.  This clock maintains all the functionality of the Admiral's Cup watch.  Available in two distinct styles, it'll make a great gift for anyone who wants to add a distinguishing piece to their home or office decor.

The Chios from J. Brackett is a hefty dive watch with some visual cues that will catch eyes. The dial is laid out with polished geometric markers and an arcing date window at 3 o'clock. The inner portion of the dial is cut with a diamond-like pattern to add depth to the overall design. Powered by a Seiko NH35 automatic movement, the Chios has a stainless steel case that's water resistant to a solid 200 meters. The crystal is domed and coated with sapphire to prevent scratching.

Specifically designed for the medical market, the Nextorch Dr. K3S delivers clear, accurate output to help diagnose and effectively tackle medical problems. With a color-rendering index greater than 90 and a color temperature of about 5000K, it helps to display lesions, rashes, infections, and more in the most accurate light possible. The photobiological hazard level of K3S is RG0, which causes no eye damage. The beam also has a uniform spot without dark areas to help clearly see the target at a glance and avoid misjudgement. Measuring just 4.2 inches long, the DR. K3S takes a standard AAA battery. It's not just for doctors, either: stash one in the glove box or the kitchen cabinet in case a friend or family member needs attention.

prod_name: Rike Knife M1 S35VN Frame Lock Knife
prod_description: From its aggressive, skeletonized tanto blade to its futuristic, grooved titanium handle, the Rike Knife M1 looks like something from another dimension. Armed with an S35VN blade and a titanium frame lock, this tanto flipper is well-equipped for tough cuts and pierces. Though it measures 9 inches overall, it clocks in at just 5.6 ounces for ease of carry and control. The spine of the M1 looks almost reptilian: It features a bevy of cutouts and a scalloped groove at the base of the blade for added grip retention. Finishing the design is a 3D-milled titanium clip for right-handed carry.

prod_name: Durgod Taurus 320 Nebula RGB Mechanical Keyboard
prod_description: A reliable TKL keyboard with 87 keys, the Durgod Taurus 320 Nebula comes with your choice of Cherry MX switches, allowing you to get just the feel you want whether you prefer a switch with some bump or a speedy linear feel. On top of the switches go the shine-through doubleshot PBT keycaps, which are backlighting compatible to enhance the colors you can program beneath. And if you're looking for a show, you can choose from more than 16 million colors of backlighting. Thanks to full N-key rollover and anti-ghosting technology, the keyboard will register all of your commands, even when input rapidly. The case, made from plastic, comes with adjustable feet so you can prop the keyboard up at an angle to relieve your wrists. Included is a dust cover, two USB type-C cables, and a keycap puller.

Originally worn by military snipers as camouflage, the ghillie suit is now available to civilians. The woodland ghillie suit by Red Rock Outdoor Gear mimics the appearance of brush, leaves, moss, and twigs. Hunters, gamekeepers, fly fishermen, even nature photographers can wear it to conceal themselves and blend into their surroundingsfrom forest to mountain terrain to wetlands. Lightweight and breathable with a polyester construction, this suit is the color of nature's greenery and dirt, and is covered in loose strips that blow with the wind like real foliage.

The Bauhaus Carabiner has a titanium build to last a lifetime. Made in Thailand under direct supervision of the designer, the Carabiner is extremely lightweight and virtually unbreakable. It also sports a stylish, low profile look that won't show damage easily.

prod_name: SharpEdge SG2 Bunka Matte 6.5" Chef's Knife
prod_description: Handcrafted in Seki City, Japan, the knifemaking capital of the world, the SG2 Bunka from SharpEdge excels when prepping vegetables, meat, and fish. Thanks to the slim blade profile and tall, ergonomic design, this knife effortlessly glides through produce, poultry and more all while maintaining a lasting edge. The blade steel is a true standout. Made from the core SG2/R2 steel, it's hardened to 63 on the Rockwell scale for superior performance. As for looks, it doesn't disappoint, either. Featuring a handsome matte finish, a sleek pakkawood handle, and traditional Japanese markings, the knife looks as good as it feels. Also included is a wooden sheath to protect the blade in downtime.

prod_name: Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC Balanced
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-grace-design-standard-dac-balanced/FP/ohYOI4rT8WfCZH2ZhVPz_Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC Balanced MD-882067666.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-grace-design-standard-dac-balanced/FP/jSx1gozQTLWDsfzwoHu0_Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC Balanced MD-882067478.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-grace-design-standard-dac-balanced/FP/Fs0DeapmSPClpXtEzjqm_Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC Balanced MD-882067484.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-grace-design-standard-dac-balanced/FP/aZhIpkceSJe1ePLuAncX_Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC Balanced MD-882067491.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-grace-design-standard-dac-balanced/FP/IbXa6F8YRzKConlaSGsj_Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC Balanced MD-882067481.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-grace-design-standard-dac-balanced/FP/1nzGqu9ITNrx7nr0TAaX_Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC Balanced MD-882067488.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Following the success of the Massdrop x Grace Design Standard DAC, we're excited to release the much-requested balanced version. It's the least-expensive small standalone balanced DAC on the market, designed to complement high-end balanced amplifiers like the Massdrop x THX AAA¢ 789, the Massdrop x Alex Cavalli Liquid Carbon X, and more. Grace Design is known for its incredibly accurate, transparent gear, and this new DAC doesn't disappoint. Based on the single-ended SDAC, it has the same objectivist-minded performance, USB bus-powered design, and simple plug-and-play operation. Plus, it boasts a number of advanced features and supports sample rates up to 384 kHz and DSD256 in USB 2.0 mode.

prod_name: Massdrop x Fostex TR-X00 Purpleheart Headphones, EU
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/ulK15ut2SIq0O3ZRxj7r_AI7B5458 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/KZ7VCJ1wQFOguQebb0P4_AI7B3129 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/0Td5OouT9ieIZazb4RT1_AI7B1795 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/WdPvHjF4Qju02mPdH42t_AI7B3155 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/dOoIVblIR2ac6P66xjPv_AI7B3107 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/YzTkZiEhSXmGOSQ95X88_AI7B3189 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/p3ic4JTQRdqSJfC9wDTP_AI7B3163 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/anRIV9TSqdKOzK771Tzg_AI7B3104 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/zJRY6YhRVu2xalIEPHdw_AI7B1825 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/eWCgZGRvTuis7MVBhUZY_AI7B3222 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-purpleheart-headphones/FP/aR2IQIYORLWD06KFTJqV_AI7B9664 copy tint.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: When the Massdrop community asked for a closed-back headphone that redefined price-to-performance expectations, the TH-X00 was our answer. Made in collaboration with Fostex, a brand that's produced innovative audio gear since 1949, these headphones feature purpleheart ear cups, a magnesium alloy frame, and Fostex's signature biodynamic drivers. Purpleheart is among the densest woods in the world, and along with adding a darker, more sophisticated aesthetic, it delivers a slightly different sound signature. Now, in another response to the community's requests, we've updated the original with a removable cable. Introducing the TR-X00 (the R stands for removable): everything you loved about the TH-X00, now with a detachable cable for greater flexibility.

prod_name: WE Knife TP-05 Obex Titanium Pen  Drop Exclusive
prod_description: Round out your EDC with a tactical pen by WE Knife. Available exclusively on Drop, the Obex pen is made from solid titanium for a lightweight and durable construction. Deploying the pen can become addictive, as it's fitted with a bolt-action mechanism that clicks in and out. The base has a glassbreaker tip in case of emergency, and there's a pocket clip to attach the pen anywhere you want quick access. The pen comes in two exclusive colors with gold accents.

prod_name: Massdrop x Sennheiser HD 58X Jubilee Headphones, EU
prod_description: In 1991, Axel Grell joined Sennheiser and designed the HD 580 Precision: the headphone that would launch a much-loved series and the peak of the company's audiophile headphones for more than 25 years. Four years later, to mark its 50th anniversary, Sennheiser released the HD 580 Jubilee, which would later become the HD 600 and lead to the HD 650. In the spirit of the HD 580, with current technology and optimizations learned throughout the series' rich history, we're excited to release the newest evolution: the Massdrop x Sennheiser HD 58X Jubilee. Tuned by Axel Grell and Massdrop based on feedback from the audiophile community, it features new 150-ohm drivers and a colorway inspired by the HD 580 Precision that started it all.

Topre's capacitive key switches are hailed for their buttery-soft feel and reliability. No other switches really compare. This tenkeyless keyboard puts them on center stage, with a combination of 30-, 45-, and 55-gram keyweights in different areas for the most natural feel possible. Wherever you press, the switches are rated for 50 million lifetime clicks. On top of them are dye-sublimated PBT keycaps with legends that won't wear off over time. For fast typists, the keyboard offers full N-key rollover, meaning no matter how fast you go, it will register each and every key. The case and keycap profile are shaped for a comfy feel and reduced impact on the wrists and fingers. There are also adjustable feet for a more angled feel.
prod_varities: ['Tenkeyless / Black / Variables', 'Tenkeyless / Ivory / Variables', 'Fullsize / Black / 55g', 'Fullsize / Black / Variables']

prod_description: Yet another proud dive watch in Seiko's growing lineup, the SRPD model is well-crafted and sized for outings both formal and adventurous. Utilizing Seiko's popular 4R36 movement, this collection is backed by 24 jewels and boasts a 41-hour power reserve. The dial meshes cylindrical indices with thick hands, all of which are lumed for legibility in hard-to-see conditions. At 3 o'clock, you'll find a day-date window as well. The case has an ever-so-slight barrel shape and a 4 o'clock crown. These design choices make for a comfy wear on any wrist. At 100 meters water resistance, this line is good to go if you need to take a dip, and the Hardlex crystal and stainless steel case will keep each watch from taking damage when you're out and about.

prod_name: XC Carbon Carbon Fiber Bottle Opener
prod_description: Stronger than steel and lighter than aluminum, it's no surprise why carbon fiber is such a sought-after material. Here, it takes the form of a trusty bottle opener. Available in your choice of a glossy or matte finish, this durable accessory is perfect for the kitchen, the tailgate, or the backyard bash. The finish on the matte version has been engineered specifically to resist scratching, while the glossy finish can add a touch of class to any space.

The Division Billfold Wallet from Pioneer doubles down on durability and doubles up on size. With a large flat bill pocket, six main card slots, and two internal card slots, it has ample room to store your essentials. To suit different carry demands, it's available in two material options. The first, 3PN, is a 3-ply nylon with a luxurious matte finish and a smooth in-hand feel. The second, 10XD, is an ultra-durable polyethylene that's 10 times stronger than steel ideal for those working in rugged conditions. Both materials are equipped with a DWR waterproof finish, while RFID protection is available in the 10XD onyx colorway.

If you frequently use photo-editing software, play games, or input data, macro pads are a lifesaver. This one from the Cooler Master MakerHub features six programmable buttons to speed up your day to day. The key bindings and macros for each switch can be changed using a simple GUI all with no programming skills necessary. They all have their own red LED that can be programmed, too. The Knops is also based on an open-source QMK firmware for future improvements and experimentation. Outfitted with your choice of Cherry MX switches, it provides you with a tactile, linear, or clicky feel. This product is designed and made by Pawnerd. Although Cooler Master has been actively supportive in this project, they are not responsible for the quality and troubleshooting of this project. For this, you can contact support@knops.io or send a message on Reddit to /u/pawnerd.

Founded in New York in 1892, Ingersoll has a way with vintage American watches. The Linden is a shining example. An automatic watch that emphasizes both legibility and style, this 46-millimeter beast showcases large Arabic numerals and an eye-catching onion crown. The case has a rustic, distressed look that helps minimize nicks and scratches. On top of that, it's water resistant to 100 meters, in case you spill or need to take it for a quick dip. Available in four styles, the Linden comes on your choice of a Horween leather band or nylon strap.

prod_description: You never thought your keyboard could make you hungry, did you? Think again. New from Dwarf Factory, these scrumptious handmade keycaps capture the satisfaction that only a great meal can deliver. Available in five unique styles from waffles topped with butter and maple syrup to sandwiches stacked high with all the fixings these artisans are like something off the menu at your favorite diner. Choose your favorite meal, or get all five to create a feast on your favorite keyboard. All options are made from resin and available in an open design or with an OEM cover to jive with your existing keycap profile.
