prod_description: Designed to fit most universal 60% keyboard cases, this PCB is fully programmable via QMK firmware, which means, once assembled, you can program any key you like to do whatever you like. With support for RGB underglow, this third version of the PCB can help you create a radiant look on your desktop. It's made with the latest USB-C connection as well.

Like a vision of the future from the mid-20th-century, these Ermenegildo Zegna sunglasses showcase styles that are simultaneously vintage and cutting-edge. Choose from thick-frame, small-rim wayfarers in three colors, or circular, minimalist aviators in a single metallic-gray finish. Made in Italy to the exacting standards of craftsmanship that have come to define the Ermenegildo Zegna brand, these sunglasses add detail and character to any ensemble.

prod_description: Pocket-sized and engineered for performance, the second-generation Radsone Earstudio ES100 MK2 Bluetooth DAC/amp delivers impressive digital-to-audio conversion for Bluetooth devices. It's built with two high-quality AK4375a DACs and has both a 3.5-millimeter unbalanced output and a 2.5-millimeter balanced output. This model adds a shirt clip, scratch-resistant coating, a clear LED color, better button finish, and a new midnight blue colorway. A proprietary DCT algorithm eliminates noises in digital sound sources and enhances 16-bit audio into high-resolution 24-bit audio. Connect the DAC/amp to your phone via Bluetooth and download the companion Radsone app for full control over your audio tuning. Complete your listening experience by adding a Radsone HE100 IEM to your order. Get more details on the HE100 below.

Need a replacement for the pads on your Massdrop x Focal Elex headphones? Pick up a pair of these. Identical to the pads that ship with the Elex, they're also compatible with the Elear, Clear, and Utopia models. Made with memory foam, they're a plush 20 millimeters thick. And based on community feedback, they're wrapped in perforated microfiber to bring the bass down to a tasteful emphasis: ~3 dB above neutral, compared to the 5 to 10 dB of the Elear.

If you like slim and effective folding knives, the Briar from CJRB is right up your alley. Made with a 3.7-inch D2 blade, this agile folder is able to get into tight spaces with pinpoint accuracy. Opened by way of a flipper, which runs on a smooth ceramic bearing assembly, the knife is quick and fun to deploy. The handle sports a reliable stainless steel liner lock and your choice of G-10 or carbon fiber scales. (Both options are textured for a good hold.) To carry the Briar, you can secure it on the right or left side, thanks to the reversible pocket clip.

prod_description: Engineered using select audio components and enclosed in an all-aluminum casing to protect the circuitry, the Audio-Technica AT-PHA1000 DAC/amp will give your headphones a serious boost. The sound is rich and detailed throughout the frequency range with ultra-low distortion. You'll find a 3.5-millimeter input and a USB micro-C input, as well as a high/low gain switch, a machined aluminum knob, and a five-stage sampling indicator for the digital input. And don't worry about running out of juice: the AT-PHA1000 has a 6-hour battery life when used with a digital input and lasts 14 hours when receiving an analog signal. Head-Fi user Army-Firedawg adds, The overall sound is very transparent and, to my ears, doesn't add any bias towards the sound, thus keeping the signature of your headphones true.

The Nextool Pallas is made from hardy aluminum with a hard-anodized exterior. The body itself is a sight to behold. It features a curved design with machined holes throughout, evocative of the Greek goddess Athena's trusty spear, where the pen gets its name. The tapered point serves more of a purpose than just looks. In fact, because it's made from nano ceramic, the end can be used as a self-defense weapon in a pinch. The Pallas pen takes a Fisher Space Pen refill and comes with a pocket clip for ease of carry. The NASA-approved cartridge is capable of writing at any angle, in any temperature, and even under water.

prod_name: Rike Knife M2 S35VN Folding Knife
prod_description: Making its official debut on Massdrop, the Rike Knife M2 looks like something out of another dimension. At nearly 9 inches long, it's got enough size for most cutting tasks you'll come across. The blade looks the part, too: A wicked tanto with a long tip, it's excellent for piercing but at about 4 inches long, it has ample surface for slicing, too. Made from S35VN stainless steel, the blade is highly corrosion resistant and will hold a good edge. It opens with the flipper tab, which, once open, acts as a finger guard to prevent your hands from slipping forward. Also notable is the lock slider. Engage it when the blade is open to make sure it won't close during heavy duty work. Futuristic cutouts and grooves in the titanium handle help facilitate a sure grip. Available in three bold styles, the M2 will stand out in any knife collection.

An updated version of the highly regarded GT100S, the Macaw GT600S IEM combines great acoustics with a glossy, eye-catching design. The housing is metal injection molded using thin but strong stainless steel, and the dual drivers one dynamic and one balanced armature produce a full, natural sound with rich details. The selection of ear tips help you find the perfect fit, while the MMCX detachable cables give you the flexibility to switch them out down the road. And because Macaw knows everyone listens to music differently, the GT600S comes with tuning filters that emphasize different parts of the frequency range. Replace the tuning nozzle with the black filter for more bass (recommended for hip-hop or heavy metal), swap in the gold filter for more treble (for classical music), or use the silver filter if you prefer the default sound.

prod_name: Massdrop x Noble Kaiser 10 Universal IEMs (EU)
prod_description: Lauded by Forbes, The Verge, and InnerFidelity, and long rated Head-Fi users' favorite IEM, the Noble Kaiser 10 returns as the Massdrop x Noble Kaiser 10. Also known as the K10, this model uses the same tuning as the company's previous flagship, with 10 Knowles balanced-armature drivers per ear. Each pair is assembled and matched by hand, and the precision-machined aluminum housings feature Noble's updated universal form factor and geometry now with red faceplates and matte black shells. This IEM is sensitive enough for use with smartphones, as well as portable digital audio players and amps. Available only on Massdrop, and for nearly half the price of the original, it offers a new entry into Noble's high-end line.

prod_name: OMO Rainbow HHKB PBT Keycap Set
prod_description: Give your HHKB Professional 2 a makeover with the OMO Rainbow keycap set. Designed to bring a colorful spark to the iconic compact keyboard, the set features 60 keys. Each one is made from thick PBT plastic that's dip-dyed for a long-lasting build that stands the test of time. The set is compatible with HHKB switches and clones.

prod_name: DOMIKEY ABS Doubleshot SA Orange Dolch Set
prod_description: On uniforms, costumes, and TV shows, orange and black make a great combo. So why should keyboards be any different? Highlighting a combination of dark gray alphas, black mods, and orange legends, the DOMIKEY SA Orange Dolch keycap set has a contrasting colorway to keep your keyboard fresh. Sculpted in SA profile, the set is tall and comfy. As for the build quality, it's top-notch, thanks to the ABS construction and doubleshot legends.

prod_description: Citizen's Eco-Drive line encompasses virtually any style of watch you can imagine. It makes sense, since the technology behind each one is a lifesaver: All these timepieces need is a little bit of light every once in a while and they'll stay powered. The Calendrier is part of this consumer-friendly lineup. Decked out in black, it brings a lot of function to the table, including 12/24-hour time and world time in 24 cities, plus an analog day and date subdial. Set on a sleek mesh bracelet, the Calendrier has luminous hands and a water-resistance rating of 100 meters.

prod_name: Jaquet Droz Grande Seconde SW Automatic Watch
prod_description: Featuring a bowl case that calls to mind an ancient Roman tripod, the Jaquet Droz Grande Seconde SW has plenty of personality. The figure-eight-style dial has an oversized seconds subdial (where the watch gets its name) and an hours subdial with Roman numerals. The case is textured, which creates a different effect in the light when held at different angles. Inside the stainless steel case lies Jaquet Droz's own 2663A-S 30-jewel movement, which delivers an impressive 68-hour power reserve. Both the front and back of the case are equipped with sapphire crystals to protect the precious components inside.

prod_name: CIVIVI Baklash Folding Knife - Drop Exclusive
prod_description: WE Knife has earned a reputation for its knives with premium build quality, fit, and finish. However, some of the company's offerings can get expensive fast. If you want the same level of quality in a more accessible package, turn to WE Knife's subsidiary, CIVIVI. The Baklash, one of the first under CIVIVI, features a 3.5-inch drop-point made from high-carbon 9Cr18MoV stainless steel, which has good corrosion resistance and is relatively easy to sharpen. The handle is made from grippy G-10 with contours for finger placement there's even a Drop-exclusive blue model you won't find anywhere else. A liner lock secures the blade and a flipper deploys it. Carry the Baklash on either side with the polished tip-up pocket clip.

prod_name: Tai-Hao PBT Backlit Keycap Set for CTRL/ALT
prod_description: These tasteful two-toned keycap sets are the perfect complement to our ALT and CTRL mechanical keyboards. Made with the highest-quality PBT plastic that's doubleshot with backlit legends, each set is resistant to friction, fading, and shining. They'll look like new after months of intensive use, and they'll shine bright to highlight our flagship keyboards' brilliant array of LED settings. Compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, the keycaps come in your choice of three colors to match your style.

prod_name: Shield Marius Pro Diver Quartz Watch
prod_description: Shaped and constructed like a bank vault, the Shield Marius Pro Diver is a watch you can knock around without worry. Measuring 45 millimeters wide (47 with the crown), it's no small piece. The stainless steel case houses an accurate quartz movement and is water resistant to a solid 200 meters. The dial design is a modern take on a classic diver aesthetic. It fuses a massive hour hand, tubular minutes hand, and lengthy seconds hand set against a backdrop of geometric indexes. At the end of the day, it's one of the most legible ensembles you could dream up. To keep up with the latest trends, the Marius comes in your choice of six styles as well.

New from RAAL-requisite, the SR1a Earfield headphone is the first monitor to employ the company's trademarked Earfield technology. Driving this technology are highly specialized ribbon drivers that reproduce 30Hz to 30kHz bandwidth, eliminating the need for sealed chambered bass and allowing for open air baffles. The result is a densely detailed, full-frequency sound signature that's unapologetically, fundamentally different, [and] somehow manage[s] to also be great, per Head-Fi's 5-star review. This engineer-grade sound signature, together with an ergonomic floating-ear design, puts the RAAL-requisite SR1a in in the same conversation as if not outright besting the biggest players in the market.

prod_name: Oris BC3 Advanced DayDate Automatic Watch
prod_description: Having been producing timepieces for more than a century, Oris has earned its reputation among watch enthusiasts and casual wearers alike.  At 6 o'clock is a day and date window, where the watch takes its name. Thick sword hands and large Arabic numerals make the watch easy to read in any conditions. Underneath them lies an Oris 735 26-jewel movement that'll tick for 38 hours on a full charge. If you take it in the water, it's protected to 100 meters not to mention the dial is fitted with a sapphire crystal.

Craighill's products live at the intersection of utility and curiosity, efficiency and exploration.  The curvilinear Closed Helix Keyring is utilitarian and eye-catching. It features a knurled end cap, which can be unscrewed to easily add or remove keys. And the "D" shape Wilson Keyring is minimal and elegant, with a secure closure and the capacity to hold a whole lot of keys. Both styles are available in a variety of colors and materials.

prod_name: Cold Steel Luzon Leaf-Spring Folding Knife
prod_description: The Cold Steel Luzon takes inspiration from several balisong knives in the president of Cold Steel, Lynn C. Thompson's collection. Large, easy to wield, and wicked sharp, the Luzon features a stout GFN handle with contoured grooves for a comfy grip not unlike those on a bamboo shoot. For ease of sharpening, the blade is made from 8Cr13MoV stainless steel, which has been hardened to 58 on the Rockwell scale. These folders utilize a leaf-spring locking mechanism with a secondary safety to prevent accidental closure under enormous pressure. There's no two ways about it: the knife is large.

Fallkniven knives are proven companions on outdoor adventures. The A1x is, too. This 11-inch full-tang fixed blade is armed with a chunky drop-point blade for all kinds of rigorous cutting tasks. The knife features Fallkniven's premium laminated cobalt steel, which is hardened to 60 on the Rockwell scale for an edge that'll hold through taxing work and light duty tasks. A grippy Thermorun handle forms the backbone of a sure hold. Available in two finishes (satin or non-reflective black), the A1x is built for any mission.

prod_name: The Eye Key Ha Long Bay V2 Artisan Keycap
prod_description: An update to the original Ha Long Bay keycap, this new version features an even greener oasis set in the emerald waters of the Gulf of Tonkin, where towering limestone pillars form small islands and wave-eroded grottoes, Vietnam's Ha Long Bay is a place unlike any other. Maybe you've been lucky enough to visit and want a reminder of the magical land, or maybe you want to add some tropical pizzazz to your keyboard just because: Whatever the case, these handcrafted artisans capture a little sliver of Vietnamese paradise. Sculpted in SA R1 profile, the keycaps are compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones. Each one is made from a combination or resin, clay, and colored powder to achieve a 3D effect on your keyboard.

prod_name: The British Belt Co. Cordovan Leather Bifold Wallet
prod_description: A collaboration from two of Britain's most storied leather brands, The British Belt Co. Thomas Ware Bifold Wallet brings an impressive pedigree to your pocket. Made from outer leather sourced, tanned, and dyed by Thomas Ware England's premier leather maker for over 150 years this wallet delivers lasting durability and lustrous color in black or oxblood. On the inside, it features full-grain Italian vegetable-tanned leather for a soft, hand-friendly texture. Hand-stitched by the revered leatherworkers at The British Belt Co., it's just over 4 inches tall and 3.5 inches wide, while less than half an inch thick. To store all of your essentials, it includes 10 card pockets and a full bill pocket in a classic bifold shape.

If diamonds are a girl's best friend, then the JACY ACE watch is sure to expand your friend group. Outfitted with a bezel packing 76 single-cut diamonds, all sourced from non-conflict regions, the ACE is dressy and radiant. The dial, too, is made from mother of pearl, while the crown features another gem to add to the collection of jewels. Other than materials, the watch is rather minimal, with stick markers at every hour and a subdial at 6 to track running seconds. Of course, to protect the treasures beneath, the sapphire crystal is resistant to scratching and dings. It also contributes to the watch's overall water resistance of 50 meters.

prod_description: Looking for a no-compromises DAC to be the centerpiece of your high-end audio setup? Put the LKS MH-DA004 at the top of your list. It features dual ESS flagship ES9038pro chips, each of which work in mono mode and individually function for the left and right channel. Plus, this unit has all of the inputs and outputs you could want from a flagship DAC including USB optical, I2S-H, I2S-E, coaxial, BNC, and EBU inputs, and dual XLR and RCA outputs. To make sure the MH-DA004 is properly implemented and properly powered, LKS Audio equipped it with two high-quality transformers to achieve six sets of AC power supply: a total of 13 groups of low-noise regulator circuits.

The next time you're caught in a blizzard or shivering in the bleachers, don't rely on your jacket alone to fight frostbite in your fingers. A refillable, odorless, and entirely safe way to stay nice and toasty, Zippo hand warmers give you complete protection against the elements in a package that comfortably slips into your pocket.

Born in the 1960s, Leandri Laboratorio is an authentic Swiss watchmaker with Italian roots. Known for its innovative movements and precision performance, the company showcases two distinct styles throughout its work: one sporty and one classic. Here, we're featuring a watch from the classic side of things. This manual-wind timepiece has large, stylized Arabic numerals and a subdial for running seconds at 6 o'clock. The hands are skeletonized and arrow-shaped, making it easy to tell the time at a glance. To quickly check minutes, the large hand extends all the way out to the chapter ring. Because it's a manual movement, the watch requires a full wind every day or so but that's all part of the vintage charm.

prod_name: Massdrop x Fitsok Mountain Crew Socks (2-Pack)
prod_description: Whether you spend the colder months hiking, snowshoeing, or hanging out with the family indoors, you'll be warm and comfortable in the Massdrop x Fitsok Mountain Crew Socks. They feature a blend of merino wool, Coolmax polyester, and nylon that's durable enough for the great outdoors and cozy enough for lounging around the house or cabin, especially if you have tile or hardwood floors. The fabric is infused with silver for extra antimicrobial, odor-fighting, and temperature-regulating power. And because the socks are breathable and fast drying, you can easily wear them on warmer days, too. Each pair is made, dyed, and preshrunk in Fitsok's North Carolina mill, family owned for three generations.

prod_description: This casual military-inspired watch can mesh with virtually anyone's wardrobe. It's easy to read at a glance, thanks to the large hands and extra-large Arabic numerals at the cardinal hours. Outside of the numerals are 24-hour markings in the outer chapter ring if you like to go by military time. Water-resistant to 100 meters, the watch is powered by a Citizen Eco-Drive E101 solar movement so if you're out and about in the sun, it'll stay charged for a long time. The case is made from stainless steel with a heavily knurled crown to hit home the rugged vibes. There's also a day-date window at the traditional 3 o'clock position.

prod_name: Tai-Hao ALPS ABS Doubleshot Keycap Set
prod_description: Put some flair on your ALPS board withese these ALPS-compatible caps. Available in two classic colorways, they're made from ABS plastic with a doubleshot printing process to keep them from wearing out over time. The set comes with 104 total keys to cover a fullsize board. Sculpted in OEM profile, they're angled for a satisfying feel.

Datamancer has built a solid reputation making wooden cases for popular keyboards like the Pok3r, Planck, and ErgoDox. Now, they've created one for the Preonic (Rev 3), available in two different woods (cherry or walnut). Fitted with a total of 24 3-millimeter neodymium magnets, the case creates a secure hold when you're on the go. Pull off the top lid and it will magnetically attach to the edge of the case, too, acting as a natural wrist rest. The base of the case is fitted with rubber feet to keep it stable, and there are machined holes for the USB cord.

prod_name: Luminox XS.3057.WO Navy SEAL Colormark Watch
prod_description: Luminox is a fan favorite for a couple of reasons: For one, the company developed the first Navy SEAL watch series in 1993; for another, the self-powered illumination system employed in its watches will last up to 25 years with no need for exterior power. Offering the grab-and-go convenience that only a quartz watch can, this model dons a striking white look to stand out on the wrist. Made with carbon-reinforced polycarbonate, the watch is lightweight, tough, and water resistant to 200 meters. It's fitted with a unidirectional bezel to track elapsed time and a silicone strap for added comfort.

The latest high-end offering from TFZ, the Series 7 IEM is built with five drivers: four Knowles balanced armatures and a single dynamic driver. Together, these deliver high-resolution sound with ample detail, excellent instrument separation, and strong transient dynamics. The IEM's textured metal finish gives it a sleek look, and the housings are molded to comfortably fit a variety of ear shapes. Rounding out the package, the high-quality silver-plated OFC cable is detachable and connects via the 0.78-millimeter connector.

The most accurate and reliable meat thermometer you'll ever need, the Javelin PRO Duo gives you a reading in just 3 seconds. And just because it's fast doesn't mean it isn't accurate: The Javelin is accurate to within less than 1 degree Fahrenheit. It's also got a 2-inch anti-fog display with a motion-activated backlight and an ambidextrous design that automatically flips when used by both righties and lefties. It has an integrated magnet for storage, an IP65 splash-resistance rating, and silver-based antimicrobial protection to keep it going for the long haul a whopping 4,000 hours on a single battery, to be exact. It's got you covered whether you're cooking meat, baking bread, boiling candy, or deep frying potatoes.

prod_name: Bear OPS Rancor II CPM-S30V Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: Bear OPS' latest tactical design is the Rancor II, an update to the popular Rancor, now with a skeletonized stainless steel handle and a blade made from impressive CPM-S30V stainless steel. This versatile folding knife is lightweight and durable, making it suitable for everyday carry and tough jobs when camping, hiking, and much more. The handle features G-10 scales for a sure grip in rain and muck, while jimping throughout the spine helps promote an even more reliable hold. Carrying the knife is easy already, but it gets even easier thanks to the reversible stainless steel clip. Donning an all-black look, the Rancor II won't reflect light and won't show too much grime when you put it to work.

There's something satisfying about writing with a wooden pen. It feels like part of another era, and lends a sense of purpose to the writer. Our latest offering from Montegrappa an Italian company that's been making beautiful, functional pens since 1912 is the Heartwood fountain pen. Featuring a body made of light teak wood, it's both comfortable and elegant. The medium steel nib offers leeway for broad strokes and precision when you need it. To match the wooden body, the Heartwood comes with a notebook reminiscent of the woodworking tradition found across Italy.

Next to sound quality, comfort is the most important characteristic in any pair of headphones and no component is more crucial to comfort than earpads. If you have a favorite pair of headphones that need an earpad replacement, the Choice Series from Dekoni has you covered. World-renowned for headphone pads, Dekoni has created a series of leather and suede earpads made with ultra-slow rebound memory foam each custom-tuned and shaped to fit a specific pair of brand-name headphones. Choose your material, select your pair of headphones, and enjoy custom comfort crafted to last.

prod_name: Swiss Legend Diamond Women's Quartz Watches
prod_description: Moderately sized and sturdily built, these watches from Swiss Legend are perfect for the adventurous lady. Sporting a radiant look full of diamonds and flair, they toe the line between fashion and function. The first watch available is the Karamica, which comes in two styles. The first is set on a white ceramic bracelet with a dial completely covered in diamonds. The other Karamica swaps some of the diamonds for gold accents and Roman numerals. Finally, there's the Neptune, which has a rotating bezel appointed with diamonds and an offset crown at 4 o'clock. Each Swiss Legend watch available has a scratch-resistant sapphire crystal and is water resistant to 100 meters.

prod_description: If you've paid a pretty penny for high-end cans or home speakers, why keep streaming audio straight from your headphone port? Designed to significantly upgrade any computer's sound output and extract great detail from your music collection, the NuForce uDAC3 is powerful enough for noisy environments yet small enough to fit in your pocket.

The first thing you'll notice on the Seiko 5 SNKD99K1 is the sapphire-colored dial. Deep blue in color, it glimmers slightly lighter when the watch is held at different angles. The next thing you'll notice is the size of the case. Just 37 millimeters, it sits small on the wrist for an understated look. Powered by Seiko 7S26 21-jewel automatic movement, it's got a 41-hour power reserve. Also notable are the lumed hands and indexes, the day-and-date window at 3 o'clock (also in Spanish), and the fixed stainless bezel with numerals in intervals of five. Adding to the solid construction is the stainless steel case and mineral crystal.

Antoine de Saint-ExupÃ©ry said, Perfection is achieved not when there is nothing left to add, but when there is nothing left to take away. This is the guiding principle of the ZERO fountain pen: a minimalist design from Trilogy Pens. Made with a fanatical attention to detail over the course of 2 years, the pen features a CNC-machined 6000 series aluminum alloy body and a smooth-writing German-made Bock nib. Every aspect seen and unseen has the sole purpose of enhancing your writing experience. Super sleek and substantial in size, the ZERO comes with a wooden pen cradle and an international Schmidt K5 converter for use with bottled inks.

prod_description: The perfect partner for any pair of high-impedance headphones, DAC, or both, the Topping A50 headphone amp delivers powerful amplification to fit any setup. This portable headphone amplifier includes three different headphone outputs a 6.35-millimeter single end, a 3.5-millimeter single end, and a 2.5-millimeter balanced end for all types of headphones. It can output an impressive 2200 mW at 64 ohms out of the balanced 2.5-millimeter jack, or 1110 mW at 32 ohms out of the 3.5- and 6.35-millimeter outputs. Sturdy and space-efficient, the A50 pairs well with any DAC particularly the Topping D50 or D50s.

Modeled after an original Soviet Spetsnaz entrenching tool, this Special Forces Shovel from Cold Steel is suitable for utility or self defense. Made with a stout hardwood handle and a carbon steel head, it's built to take abuse in the field. The head has three sharp edges so you can just as easily dig out a foxhole or chop through a stubborn branch. Thanks to its head-heavy design, it will make a great thrower for sport or you can chuck it as a last ditch-effort. Store it in the included Cor-Ex sheath when not in use.

The LKS Audio USB-100 is ideal for those who have high-end audio systems and don't want to sacrifice any part of their setup including their DAC, which might not have the best USB implementation. This USB interface has three output options: I2S-E, I2S-H, and coaxial. It uses the Crystek CCHD-957 clock to obtain precise digital audio signal reconstruction.

Think about everything that's ever bugged you about earphones: They tangle, they break, they fall out, they don't sound good. Now throw all of that out the window. There's a better earphone out there, one specifically engineered to address those common pain points: the Echobox Audio Finder X1. It uses German-made PEEK diaphragms to deliver bright, entertaining sound with plenty of power and detail. Plus, the AFT (or acoustic filter tuning) system allows you to adjust the sound signature to your preferences using three pairs of filters. Made of titanium, which has double the strength-to-weight ratio of steel, the housings are small, light, and virtually indestructible. Naturally hypoallergenic and sweat resistant, they're fitted with tangle-free cables great for tossing into your bag without worrying about pesky untangling down the line. To learn more, check out this review.

prod_description: Keys, wallet, phone, Gent: Our third collaboration with Ferrum Forge Knife Works, the Gent is the classiest, most portable, and most affordable to date. Designed by Ferrum Forge, a two-man operation out of San Diego known for producing small batches of custom knives, it's an exciting new direction compared with the beefy folders they've built their reputation on. Made to fit just as well in a pair of blue jeans as a pair of slacks, it's also small enough that you'll hardly notice it in your pocket. The 3-inch blade, made from premium CPM-S35VN steel, is suitable for anything from opening packages and cutting loose threads off a shirt, to slicing an apple and removing staples. Crafted with a 6AL4V titanium frame that's surrounded by smooth G-10 scales (in three handsome colors), the handle features a deep-carry pocket clip for tip-up carry on either side.

If you want to make your keyboard feel and perform its best, consider lubricating the switches. Mechanical keyboard lubrication gained popularity in Korea in 2012. Since, it's become the standard for anyone who wants to reduce upstroke noise, increase smoothness, and prevent spring crushing and grinding. Here, we're offering three different lubricants specially made for the mech keys community by Switchmod Keyboards, Miller-Stephenson, and Hunger Work Studios. The 3203 lube is a low-thickness lube that specializes in grind reduction. The 3204 lube is great as a general-purpose lube for all types of switches. Finally, the 205g0 lube is designed for linear or Topre switches for an extra smooth feel.

prod_description: The Glycine Combat Sub is a favorite of the watch community. However, calls for a GMT hand have been echoing for years. It's official: We've answered the call. The Drop + Glycine Combat Sub GMT is the first-ever Combat Sub with a GMT hand. This auxiliary fourth hand, together with the 24-hour bezel, allows the wearer to track a second time zone in a complete 24-hour cycle. What's more, the watch features a two-toned bezel and a vintage, lumed look you won't find anywhere else. Another notable addition is the reversion to the original Glycine logo and the exhibition caseback to showcase the 26-jewel GL293 movement. Crafted with a stainless steel case and a sapphire crystal, this timepiece works as hard in the depths of the ocean as it does in an important meeting.

Like something a 19th-century businessman might have carried, the Ingersoll Trenton looks like a piece of vintage Americana and it is. Made by Ingersoll, which was founded in New York in 1892, this pocket watch has a rustic look and feel, and it's part of a limited-edition run of just 250 serialized pieces. The details are everything on this timepiece. From the aged bronze case to the large onion crown and old-school stainless steel chain, it's got plenty of retro vibes in its favor. The 50-millimeter housing holds an automatic movement and a mineral crystal that's resistant to scratching.

The Index from FrÃ©dÃ©rique Constant is a Swiss-made watch that pairs just as well with a collared shirt and slacks as it does a t-shirt and jeans. Sporting a white dial, slim markers, and lumed hands, the watch has a subdued look. Details like the exhibition caseback, butterfly clasp, and polished edges are what make this timepiece really stand out. In addition, its calibre FC-303 helps keep accurate time for up to 38 hours on a full charge. Armed with a sapphire crystal and a water-resistance rating of 100 meters, this watch is tougher than it looks, too.

From Salt Optics, a leader in high-end eyewear for men and women, come the Harrison sunglasses: a modern blend of boldness and performance. Starting with the bold, the Harrisons showcase a tasteful acetate trim around each lens for an instantly noticeable pop of color and dimension. Behind this trim, a sleek titanium body wastes no weight or space, making these shades great for compact carry. Strong UV protection on the Harrisons' sizable lenses provides welcome protection on even the brightest days, while meticulous made-in-Japan craftsmanship ensures longevity to last a lifetime.

prod_description: The Nitecore P18 is the smallest 1,800-lumen flashlight with rear thumb-switch activation on the market today. Measuring just over 4 inches long and weighing less than 4 ounces, it's compact and super powerful. How powerful, you ask? It can cast a beam as far as two football fields and hold at max output for a half hour. Packed with five different brightness modes, strobe mode, SOS mode, beacon mode, and an auxiliary red light, it can adapt to virtually any situation you find yourself in and clicking the tailcap makes no sound whatsoever, so you can remain stealthy. The battery is a rechargeable IMR18650, which comes included in addition to a lanyard, holster, and spare O-ring.

Seiko is always a sure bet on the wrist and at a price like this, that's even more true. Here, we're featuring a collection of solar-powered timepieces that fit the bill for formal and casual settings. Powered by a Japanese quartz movement, they measure just 38 millimeters across. The markers are slim and dressy to add an elegant touch to the overall design. At 7 millimeters thick, these timepieces easily slip under a cuff, and they won't weigh you down on the go. Fitted with stainless steel cases and scratch-resistant Hardlex crystals, each watch here is set on a leather strap that molds to your wrist over time.

prod_name: Maurice Lacroix Les Classiques Automatic Watch
prod_description: Dressy and minimal, the Maurice Lacroix Les Classiques Automatic Watch wouldn't look out of place on James Bond's wrist. Based on the manufacturer's own ML115, an automatic movement of 26 jewels, it features a 38-hour power reserve. The back of the stainless steel case offers a peek at the decorated movement. Both the caseback and crystal are made from sapphire to resist scratches. The onion crown is cut with the Maurice Lacroix logo. As for the dial, it's got subtle grooves upon close inspection and an outer chapter ring with Arabic numerals in intervals of 10. And while you wouldn't take this timepiece on a dive, it still offers 30 meters of water resistance so don't worry if you happen to spill your martini on the case.

For those that want a simple look with modern functionality, the IKBC TypeMaster X is the keyboard to beat. Available in both TKL and full-size options, it features double-coated ABS keys in black and a sturdy plastic frame in dark gray. Onboard Cherry MX Low-Profile Red switches ensure streamlined speed, while full N-key rollover prevents ghosting. A host of multimedia keys and an intuitive volume knob make controlling movies, games, and other media easy, and white LED lighting adds welcome illumination. Connect quickly and seamlessly through the TypeMaster X's USB-C port, and enjoy ergonomic performance compatible with Mac and Windows systems.

prod_description: A perfect display of German craftsmanship, the MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte Panova is a sporty, easy-wearing timepiece for the guy on the go. Measuring 40 millimeters wide, the watch combines lumed pips with slim markers at every hour. The hands are simple, rounded off at the ends, and coated with SuperLumiNova for legibility in any setting. Behind the minimal aesthetic, the Panova gets its power from an SW 200-1 automatic movement with a 38-hour power reserve. Fitted with an anti-glare sapphire crystal, it's water resistant to 100 meters as well.

Seiko is always a sure bet on the wrist and at a price like this, that's even more true. Here, we're featuring a collection of solar-powered timepieces that fit the bill for formal and casual settings. Powered by a Japanese quartz movement, they measure just 27 millimeters across perfect for smaller wrists. The markers are slim and dressy to add an elegant touch to the overall design. At 6 millimeters thick, these timepieces easily slip under a cuff, and they won't weigh you down on the go. Fitted with stainless steel cases and scratch-resistant Hardlex crystals, each watch here is set on a leather strap that molds to your wrist over time.

NuForce's HEM line features the latest balanced armature driver technology, custom-designed linear-phase crossovers, and the excellent sound quality we've come to expect from the company. Inside the acoustically calculated, vibration-free Lexan earpiece, each in-ear monitor has a different number of Knowles drivers that increases with the model number: The HEM1 and HEM2 have one per side, while the HEM4 has two. Along with a selection of ear tips, you'll get two replaceable cables: one with a microphone, and the other a high-end proprietary cable made from silver and OFC copper. To learn more, check out this Head-Fi review.

The name of the company behind these sleek pens, Tactile Turn, reveals much of their charm. To deploy the pen tip, press the stainless steel button and feel the satisfying bolt-action mechanism slide the tip into place it's a truly addictive way to open and close a pen. Precisely machined from your choice of bronze, copper, or titanium, these pens come in two sizes. No matter what you choose, it measures just 0.4 inches thick for a comfy feel in the hand and an unobtrusive fit in a pocket. It's important to note that both the bronze and copper models will develop a natural patina over time, and the titanium version is significantly lighter than either of the former.

The Arozzi Arena gaming desk maximizes comfort and versatility to take your gaming to a whole new level. The height can be adjusted from 27.9 to 31.9 inches, and the huge field of play 63 inches wide and 32.3 inches deep offers plenty of room for your mouse, keyboard, three large monitors, and other devices. The 14-square-foot surface is entirely covered by a custom desk pad, which measures a plush 5 millimeters thick and has stitched edges. The microfiber cloth top is water-resistant and machine-washable, and the non-slip underside ensures it stays put during lightning-fast movements. The Arena also comes with built-in gromet mounts that support up to three ultrawide gaming displays and custom cutouts and netting to help keep your cables organized.

The key to making a good cup of coffee is time and temperature. Thanks to extensive research and testing, the folks over at Technivorm have created a device for both. The Moccamaster KBS is like having a personal barista. It makes drip coffee automatically at the optimum temperature (between 196 and 205 degrees Fahrenheit) in the optimum timeframe (between 4 and 8 minutes). The manual-adjust brew basket gives you full control over your coffee's taste. Made from BPA/BPS-free materials, the Moccamaster KBS features an 8-cup carafe and an auto-shut-off function 2 hours after brewing. It also takes standard coffee filters and has removable parts for easy cleaning. Handmade and individually tested, all Moccamaster brewers come with a five-year limited warranty, to boot. Pick one up for dad to help kickstart his big day.

Whether you like a heavy switch or something lighter, a linear feel or some tactile feedback, this drop allows you to select exactly what you need. The main switches featured are the new Tealios, which have been tweaked with wobble reduction and improved smoothness not to mention they're done in sleek teal, just like the name implies. Also available are the standard Zealios switches with your choice of weight; the Zilent switches, which are similar but silent to keep a low profile in the office or shared workspace. Depending on the size of your keyboard, quantities are flexible, too.

prod_name: Gen.S Resin Astrolokeys DSA Artisan Keycap
prod_description: While scouring the stars to find keycaps worthy of your keyboard, we brought a few celestial bodies back with us. Showcasing the lighter side of outer space, these Astrolokeys artisan keycaps by Gen.S feature warm colors and playfully simple 3D artwork. Made from smooth resin, shaped in DSA profile, and compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, these keycaps are designed to fit the Drop + DSA Astrolokeys Keycap Set but they also make great standalone additions to any keyboard. Choose from a white sun, pink star, or purple moon to complete your solar system.

prod_name: Cold Steel VG-10 San Mai Outdoorsman Fixed Blade
prod_description: The Outdoorsman has been a staple in the Cold Steel lineup for years. With a wide belly and an upswept point for skinning, plus a secondary edge on the spine for breaking bones and hacking through brush, the Outdoorsman lives up to its name. At 11 inches overall and over a half pound, the knife is burly. Despite its heft, the Kray-Ex handle makes it easy to control through rain, sweat, and grime. The 6-inch-long VG-10 stainless steel blade has good edge retention and corrosion-fighting properties. Stick it in the included sheath when you're not putting this beast to work.

In 2001, Fallkniven knifemakers created the Pd folder, a handsome liner-lock knife that quickly became one of the company's most popular models. Now, in celebration of Fallkniven's 35th year in the knifemaking business, the Pd is back in a special commemorative edition with exciting extras. The Pd Folder 3.0 Damascus Knife adds a new 65-layer powder steel blade, gold-plated bolts and medallions, and a desert ironwood handle for a regal-yet-rustic presentation that performs as well as the original. With only 1,000 pieces made, this limited run is one you'll want to get your hands on.

Good work at a fair price. That's founder Tony from A&H Leather Goods' calling card. The Front Pocket Wallet is designed for carry right where it sounds. Made from leather in your choice of five styles, it features a multitude of pockets for the essentials. Store your cards in the three credit card pockets, extra cards and receipts in the side-entry pocket, bills in the center compartment, and your identification in the ID window. The ID window features a thumb cutout, which allows for better access when removing the ID. To ensure your identity and important information is protected, it's RFID protected, too.

prod_description: One of the first American watch factories, Ingersoll has been making quality timepieces since 1892. The Scovill is the company's take on a classic dive watch. This 43-millimeter timepiece has thick geometric stick markers at the hours and a large triangular marker at 12 to help frame the dial. The date window is a deep black to match the dial and bezel, which is styled like vintage dive watches from the 60s. Available with your choice of a red or black bezel, the Scovill has a solid water-resistance rating of 100 meters. Fitted with a leather strap, it gets power from an automatic Miyota movement that's visible via the exhibition caseback.

Swiss-made since 1856, Eterna watches are a mark of quality craftsmanship. The Eternity Legacy is minimal by design, but the details are what really speak to its beauty. Between the polished arrowhead-shaped indices are markers broken up into fourths of a second. The dial, available in multiple colors, has a sunburst effect that shimmers differently when held at different angles. The date window at 3 o'clock also has a 3D effect, as if the numerals are sunken into a rectangular hole. To match the polished case, there's a polished onion crown with the Eterna logo.

prod_name: Franck Muller Vanguard Swiss Automatic Watch
prod_description: Watchmaker Franck Muller's slogan is the master of complications. With a motto like that, your timepieces better be impressive. In this case, they are so impressive that they've been worn by A-list celebrities like Demi Moore, Elton John, 50 Cent, and more. The Vanguard Series is certainly of A-list proportions, too. A 44-millimeter timepiece with a robust automatic movement, the watch is a showstopper. With a large tonneau-shaped case and tall Arabic numerals that expand at every corner to fill the dial, this watch has a one-of-a-kind look. In terms of materials, the Vanguard has a titanium or stainless steel case, a combination rubber-and-leather strap, and a scratch-resistant sapphire crystal. Get your Vanguard in a wide range of eye-catching styles.

prod_name: Bestech Kendo S35VN Titanium Frame Lock Knife
prod_description: Inspired by the traditional Japanese martial art of Kendo, this Bestech flipper is agile, powerful, and easy to control. In addition to its lengthy, robust design, the knife is made of the best materials on the market. For the blade, Bestech opted for S35VN stainless steel, a true powerhouse in terms of edge retention and corrosion resistance. For the handle, the company employed a titanium frame lock, which won't fail even through taxing slicing and piercing tasks. Because the blade rides on ceramic bearings, this knife opens like a dream with a simple press on the flipper tab. Once open, the jimped spine makes a perfect resting place for a thumb. Rounding out the Kendo is a tip-up pocket clip on the right side and a gritty two-toned finish to hide scratches yet shine in the process.

With its earthy, outdoorsy look and reliable build, the Victorinox I.N.O.X. 241778 model excels in tough conditions. Since this watch is made by the creators of the original Swiss Army knife, it only makes sense it's primed for rigorous outings. Thanks to a 200-meter water-resistance rating, a sapphire crystal, and a lightweight titanium case, the I.N.O.X. is a force to be reckoned with. The dial sports a combination of black, khaki, and red for visibility. Add in lumed hands and markers and it's easy to read no matter the lack of light. Powered by an accurate quartz movement, the watch is ready to take on and off without winding.

prod_name: Raymond Weil Freelancer Chronograph Automatic Watch
prod_description: Like any good freelancer, Raymond Weil's Freelancer Chronograph automatic watch can easily transition from job to job, setting to setting. The dial layout is smart and legible, with plenty of function to spare. To start, there's a chronograph that tracks for up to 12 hours in 60-second and 30-minute increments. In conjunction with the tachymeter bezel, the chronograph can help you track distance and speed as well. Finally, there's a day-date window at 3 o'clock. Regarding the Freelancer's construction, it features a stainless steel case (water resistant to 100 meters) and a scratch-resistant sapphire crystal. All that to protect an ETA SA 7750 movement with a noteworthy 46-hour power reserve.

When you're out in the backcountry and want a fresh cup of coffee, the last thing you want to do is fiddle with a clunky brewing apparatus. Enter the Vargo travel coffee filter: a clean and simple one-piece brewer that makes a mean cup of joe in minutes. It has an ultra-fine double mesh panel that's made from biocompatible titanium, so it won't corrode or leach chemicals or flavors into your coffee. Three sturdy talon-style folding legs allow you to adjust the filter to sit on a variety of different cups. A folding handle on the top lets you lift it up without burning your fingers. When you're finished brewing, simply turn the filter over, rinse it clean, and pack it away in the included mesh bag.

Done in a classic diver style, the JS9 is bold, rugged, and ready for a night on the town or a dunk in the pool. The dial has all the cues you'd expect in a diver, with indices that are split in two for a unique twist. The hands are extra thick and lumed for visibility in the dark or underwater. Rotate the ceramic bezel and set it to the minutes hand if you need to time something. Beneath the handsome exterior lies an Armand Nicolet AN2846-9 movement of 21 jewels with a solid 48-hour power reserve. For materials, Armand Nicolet spared no expense. Fitted with a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal, the JS9 is also water resistant to a whopping 300 meters not to mention it comes in a wide range of styles to suit your wardrobe.

There's a reason Cardas Audio calls its Anniversary-Edition IEM the A8 Ear Speaker. It's because this portable audio solution is designed to sound just like a high-performance loudspeaker. The driver is a 10.85-millimeter, ultra-linear dual-magnetic unit with a contour-field design that produces brilliant highs and powerful bass, while maintaining musicality across all frequencies. For lasting performance, the A8 Anniversary-Edition gets a black chromeplated body and stranded conductors wrapped in a Golden-Ratio helix pattern around a textile core. As a 4.5-star review on Head-Fi writes: "The Cardas A8 is one seriously impressive ear speaker,' and provides a good musical alternative to the more reference-tuned IEMs you will find in this price bracket.

prod_name: DOMIKEY 1980S ABS Doubleshot HHKB Keycap Set
prod_description: Meant for the HHKB keyboard, this set can take your keyboard back to another era. Full of cream-colored alphas, beige modifiers, and orange accents, it's retro with a bit of pop. The keycaps are compatible with Topre stems and clones. Made from doubleshot ABS plastic, the set comes with 66 keys.

Named among the best pens for everyday carry by GearMoose and Gear Patrol, this Machine Era ballpoint is built to go wherever you do. The body is precision-machined from solid brass, with a sleek silhouette that's 4.5 inches capped for easy storage in your pocket or bag. Despite its weight, it's exceptionally balanced, and the threaded cap screws on to post for a satisfying in-hand feel. Over time, the metal will develop a golden-brown patina but thanks to the pen's structural durability (no moving parts or rubber O-rings), not much else will change.

prod_description: Designed by Ferrum Forge Knife Works, a two-man operation out of San Diego known for producing small batches of custom knives, this folder is small enough to take anywhere, yet rugged enough to open boxes, cut rope, slice food, and much more. The blade is made from S35VN stainless steel for excellent edge retention and resistance to corrosion. It flips open effortlessly thanks to the caged bearing system a mechanism used in nearly all of Ferrum Forge's custom knives. The 6AL4V titanium handle is both lightweight and strong. A 3D-machined titanium clip is reversible for righties and lefties.

prod_name: Audio-Technica ADX5000 with AT-B1XA Balanced Cable
prod_description: Audio-Technica's high-end open-back headphone, the ADX5000 builds off of classics like the AD2000 and AD2000X. This model uses newly developed Core Mount Technology to position the driver unit optimally within the housing and improve airflow efficiency. This helps the headphones reproduce highly transparent mids and highs, as well as rich, precise bass. The 58-millimeter integrated driver combines a tungsten-coated diaphragm, baffle, and Permendur magnetic circuit in a single unit to reduce unwanted vibrations and since no screw clamps are required decrease the weight. To optimize the listening experience, these headphones come with an upgraded B1XA/3.0 cable with a 4-pin connection. Specially made for ADX5000, this cable makes a perfect pairing for high-end balanced DAC/amp setups, which are great matches for the ADX5000.

BOLDR watches are bold, brave, and hungry for adventure. The aptly named Venture is a field watch that goes anywhere you go, effortlessly. Made with a lightweight titanium case that measures just 38 millimeters, it's easy to wear in any setting. The engine of the Venture is a Japanese NH35A automatic movement, which is protected down to 200 meters. Time-telling is a breeze, thanks to the clean dial and lumed hands and pips. Inside the large Arabic numerals on the outer edge of the case are smaller numerals for military time. Bringing everything together is a sapphire crystal with anti-reflective coating.

prod_name: Orient Executive Sun & Moon V3 Automatic Watch
prod_description: Like a vintage astronomical clock, the Orient Executive Sun & Moon V3 has every bit of old-world charm you could ever ask for. The main attraction is the sun and moon complication between 5 and 6 o'clock. As time passes, the rotating disc displays the position of the sun or moon, depending on the time of day. The other subdial tracks the day of the week, while the date window spanning from 7 to 8 o'clock adds another, somewhat unconventional twist. Raised Roman numerals line the chapter ring, and a guillochÃ© dial ties everything together. The materials used are stainless steel for the case and sapphire for the crystal. Inside the case is Orient's own F6B24 21-jewel automatic movement, an upgrade from the previous version.

prod_name: The British Belt Co. Marden Belt
prod_description: The British Belt Co. has been producing leather goods since 1946, using centuries-old leather-working techniques to bring out the most in each piece. A vintage-inspired belt available in three classic colors, the Marden is sure to earn a place in any guy's wardrobe. It's made of Italian full-grain leather and complemented by an antique nickel buckle. Rugged-looking and wider than the average formal belt at 40 millimeters, it's great for pairing with jeans during the weekend or a casual night out.

If keyboards are your thing, you know there's a wide world of switches to explore. Some are smooth and silent. Others are tactile and clicky. All of them are covered in the Mechanical Switch Data Book 2: the expansive sequel to Romly's first Mechanical Switch Data Book. At once an encyclopedia and an eye-catching coffee table centerpiece, this book is filled with vivid visuals and information in both English and Japanese. Use it to research new options for your collection, and leave it out for your friends to immerse themselves in the world of mechanical switches.

Stout and rugged, the CJRB Crag earns its name from its aggressively angled sheepsfoot blade, which looks like something chipped off the side of a boulder. Measuring 3.4 inches long, the blade is made from D2 tool steel for reliability, cut after cut. Overall, the Crag clocks in at a sizeable 8.15 inches, but there's a finger groove in the handle to accommodate extra-large hands. Gripping the Crag is easy, thanks to a G-10 handle in your choice of three colors (or you can upgrade to carbon fiber). Built with a ceramic-bearing opening system, the knife opens fast with a press on the flipper.

The Taiga knife from CJRB Cutlery embodies efficiency and style. Sporting a 3.6-inch blade with an ergonomic folding-and-locking mechanism, it's space-efficient and great for everyday carry. Available here at an attractive price point, it's cost-efficient, too. In terms of style and performance, the drop-point blade impresses with stonewashed D2 steel, a smooth belly, and subtle style accents. Deployment is quick and locking is safe thanks to a strong liner lock mechanism. A G-10 or optional carbon fiber handle ensures a good grip, while a reversible pocket clip and a lanyard hole allow for versatile carry.

prod_name: Oris Greenwich Mean Time Automatic Watch
prod_description: In the Swiss luxury timepiece market for well over a century, Oris has earned a loyal following. The Greenwich Mean Time automatic is an excellent presentation of the company's know-how. Filled with undulating guillochÃ© grooves, the dial is more than meets the eye. The large subdial has a globe graphic inside it, which is fitting as it offers the wearer the advantage of tracking another time zone. The smaller subdial is for running seconds. It helps balance the overall design and reduces clutter. Powered by an Oris 690 movement of 30 jewels, the timepiece has a 38-hour power reserve and is water resistant to 50 meters.

German-made and built for adventure, the MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte Sea-Timer is equally stealthy and bold. Blacked out from head to toe, this 44-millimeter timepiece gets its name from its high water-resistance rating and accurate movement: a MÃ¼hle-GlashÃ¼tte Version SW200-1 of 26 jewels. The stainless steel case maintains a low profile, thanks to the black titanium-carbide coating and offset crown at 4 o'clock. Despite the distinctly dark aesthetic, the Sea-Timer has bright, lumed white indexes for telling time at a glance. To complete the look, the watch has a black textile strap and a ratcheted black and white bezel to track elapsed time.

prod_name: Tai-Hao Rainbow Sherbet PBT Backlit Keycaps
prod_description: Your keyboard deserves a sweet treat. Give it a cool, colorful twist with a set of Rainbow Sherbet keycaps from Tai-Hao. Spanning greens, pink, purple, and more, this eye-catching set has a horizontal theme full of bright tones. To do the colorway justice, the keycaps feature a durable PBT plastic construction with shine-through legends to emphasize backlit boards. The doubleshot legends are bold and thick for excellent legibility.

Established in 1962 in Tokyo, Japan, Audio-Technica is known around the world for its lineup of headphones, microphones, and turntables. In the US, the company has gained particular acclaim for its classic M50X studio headphones, along with its audiophile-grade A and AD Series. This special promotion includes a range of models within these series. While the A Series features closed-back headphones and the AD Series is all open-back models, you'll find many similarities between the two. Every pair of headphones is built with large 53-millimeter drivers and Audio-Technica's signature 3D Wing Support Housing, which adjusts to the wearer to ensure a perfect fit. A vibration-proof mechanism provides comfortable support for a better listening experience.

Keep your automatic watches powered at all times with these Heritage Watch Winders from WOLF. Capable of completing 900 turns per day in three directions (clockwise, counterclockwise, or bi-directional), they're pre-programmed with pause and sleep phases thanks to WOLF's patented rotation program. The watch cuff is made to hold large, heavy watches for those with wrist sizes up to 10 inches. Plus, with a sophisticated black faux leather exterior, chrome closure, and tempered glass case, these winders will certainly look the part in the office, bedroom, or lounge.

prod_description: Maybe you don't need a full macro pad, or maybe the appeal of a tiny one is just too much to pass up. This mini two-key macro pad won't make a big footprint on your desktop, but it can have a huge impact. Made with a CNC-aluminum case with hot-swappable switch sockets, it allows you to put whatever type of switches inside you want and you can swap them out later if you like. RGB underglow ensures the macro pad won't go unnoticed wherever you place it. Set the lighting to match your keyboard or PC, or use it to complement your keycap set.

prod_name: Artisan Cutlery Hyperion S35VN Frame Lock Knife
prod_description: The Artisan Cutlery Hyperion looks like a slip-joint your grandfather may have handed down, but it's backed by some of the best materials around. The primary material used is S35VN stainless steel, which is hailed for its excellent corrosion resistance and ability to hold an edge. To gain access to its impressive capabilities, press the flipper tab and the blade flies right open, thanks to the ceramic bearings. Keeping the blade secure is a titanium frame lock. The frame is surrounded by carbon fiber scales, a design choice that complements the satin-finished blade nicely. At 9 inches overall, the Hyperion is no small knife, but it weighs just under 5 ounces for ease of carry.

A trowel that doubles as a tent stake, the Vargo Dig Dig Tool is made of strong, lightweight titanium and weighs just over an ounce so you'll have no trouble fitting it in your pack. When you're digging catholes, the ergonomic design and rounded handle ensure a comfortable grip, while the serrated edges slice through roots and tough ground with ease. Plus, it can be used with two hands like a shovel for better digging power. Using the tool to stake down your tent? Count on its U shape to hold well in all soil types, along with sand and snow.

prod_name: The British Belt Co. Cordovan Leather Cardholder
prod_description: The British Belt Co. is one of Britain's most respected names in handmade leather goods. Thomas Ware is one of Britain's most storied leather-making brands. Together, they bring over 200 years of heritage to one compact carry solution. Less than a quarter-inch thick with the dimensions of a playing card, The British Belt Co. Thomas Ware Leather Cardholder opens to contain two card slots, each capable of holding several cards and folded bills. On the outside, it features luxury leather sourced, tanned, and dyed by Thomas Ware. On the inside, it's lined with soft and flexible full-grain Italian vegetable-tanned leather. Available in two colors, this cardholder keeps things minimal without sacrificing quality.

Bertucci is back with the DX3 Series watch this time with an improved band made from G-10 NATO E-TYPE nylon webbing. Durable, rugged, and comfortable in any conditions, this band is ideal for even the most active watch-wearers. Tighten yours with integrated-durability-certified band retention lug bars for a fit that won't slip. An Active Comfort ergonomic crown located at the 4 o'clock position eliminates wrist impingement, while a U.S.-patented fiber-reinforced poly-resin Unibody case and stainless steel hardware complete a tactical appearance that holds up where it counts.

The TFZ Balance 7 IEM takes balanced driver performance to new heights, improving sound articulation to create a better listening experience. Unlike traditional dynamic drivers, which have overlapping voice coils, the planar drivers in the Balance 7 have a fine layer of aluminum foil laid on their ultra-thin diaphragms. This allows the diaphragms to evenly stress, which reduces distortion caused by segmentation vibration and creates a smooth and supple frequency response. Hear substantial lows, clear and thick mids, and highs that cut through without harshness, all while enjoying an acoustic response speed up to three times faster than that of traditional headphones. Easily replace cables with onboard 0.78 mm 2-pin connectors, and listen longer with a feather-light feel that fits comfortably in your ears.

AAW's in-ear monitors have earned acclaim in both the universal-fit and custom-fit categories. These are three of the company's universal models, each complete with a 4-foot detachable cable and all the accessories you need. The A3H features one 10-millimeter proprietary dynamic driver and two balanced armatures, assembled in a three-way crossover. Meanwhile, the premium ASH uses a 13-millimeter graphene driver (an industry first!) and six balanced armatures in a four-way crossover. By using TruXross technology, these models address the crossover problems found in many multi-driver IEMs, which can lead to chaotic phase shift and scrambled arrival timing. Another breakthrough by AAW, the Canary electrostatic IEM features cutting-edge miniature electrostatic tweeter technology with a six microgram, gold-plated membrane held against a plate charged up to 400 volts.  For clear-clear articulation across all frequencies, the Canary utilizes a 4-way passive/acoustic crossover design with each driver is meticulously configured to perform in its designated frequency range, optimally minimizing phase shift.

Large and in charge, the Citizen NH8380 is a sporty timepiece for active individuals. Featuring a 46-millimeter case, it's water resistant to 100 meters. The dial dons a traditional diver aesthetic with dot markers and thick hands (the minutes hand is outlined in orange for extra visibility). The markers at the cardinal hours are a bit different, however. With two prongs and a lengthy tip that points toward the center, they look like warrior helmets from the Middle Ages. Positioned at 4 o'clock, the crown won't impinge wrist movement. If you need to keep track of elapsed time, use the unidirectional rotating bezel. If you need to track the day and date, just glance at 3 o'clock and you're covered. Fueling this beastly watch is a 21-jewel Citizen 8200 movement with a solid 43-hour power reserve.

prod_name: The British Belt Co. Woodchester Weekender

prod_description: Whether you know Pegasus from Greek mythology, the constellations, or Disney movies, his legend has made a lasting impact. The majestic winged horse has made an impression on MiTo, too. Introducing Pegaso: MiTo's latest custom keycap set, and the first set in the Project Mythos series. A combination of pearly white and pale blue (with fun golden accents in the novelties), Pegaso captures the celestial tones associated with Pegasus and the Greek Gods.

Made in Finland, the Suunto MC-2 NH USGS Mirror Compass features a high-grade steel needle with jewel bearing for super-precise navigation. It's balanced for use in the northern hemisphere and is adjustable for declination correction. The liquid-filled capsule ensures stable operation, while the mirror comes in handy for both signaling and sighting bearings.

prod_description: Lumintop's Prince flashlight offers 1,000 lumens in a compact and distinct package. Constructed from your choice of brass, copper, or stainless steel with a carbon fiber inlay, this IPX-8 waterproof torch is both durable and distinguished. The body will oxidize when exposed to air and touch, giving the exterior a natural patina that changes over time. The Prince's CREE XPL LED provides over 550 feet of beam distance, and three different modes allow users to adjust brightness according to a variety of situations. Clip it onto your pocket with the included pocket clip, or slip it into the leather holster for added protection on the go.

To wear a CCCP watch is to be a part of history. A nod to another era, the Heritage CP-7021 automatic features stylized Arabic numerals and a date window at 3 o'clock. Created by avant-garde watch designer Alexander Shorokhoff, who's known for his outlandish and forward-thinking work, the watch is more a bit more subdued than his other designs. However, the dial has subtle vertical stripes to add depth, and the four stars in the CCCP logo harken back to a Soviet aesthetic. The watch is powered by a Slava 2427 27-jewel movement with a 39-hour power reserve. To protect the movement, there's a stainless steel case and mineral crystal.

prod_name: Kinesis Gaming Freestyle Edge RGB Mech Keyboard
prod_description: New from Kinesis Gaming, the Freestyle Edge RGB mechanical keyboard is the next step in split keyboard performance, with its styling, features, and ergonomics that are great for both gaming and office settings. Showcasing the placement flexibility of a classic split keyboard, the Freestyle Edge RGB comes with a host of additional state-of-the-art features, including adjustable RGB lighting, plug-and-play connectivity, built-in wrist rests with a new-and-improved cushioned palm pad included, and full onboard programmability for Windows, Mac, and Linux. Choose from five Cherry MX switches at checkout, and build your ideal setup with a host of available add-ons, including a Lift Kit, V3 Pro Tenting Kit, XL Mousepad, and MAC modifier keycaps.
prod_varities: ['Lift Kit (+$20)', 'V3 Pro Tent Kit (+$20)', 'Mac Keycaps (+$20)', 'XL Mousepad (+$20)']

prod_description: TW Steel is known for its rugged timepieces packed with function. The Racing quartz watch is a chunky chronograph with a look inspired on the track. Featuring luminous hands, a date window (cleverly sandwiched between 4 and 5 o'clock), a chronograph, and a tachymeter, this watch is ready for action on the road, on the boat, or at a nice dinner. The case is stainless steel and houses a mineral crystal. Beneath it is a layer of carbon fiber that glistens when the watch is held at different angles. At 50 meters water resistance, the watch is A-ok in a little bit of moisture. On top of that, it comes in three different styles to match your wardrobe.

Invicta's Pro Diver series has a classic look that works in any both formal and casual settings. Featuring a cyclops lens for the date window at 3 o'clock, luminous geometric markers, and a rotating bezel to track elapsed time, the Pro Diver ticks all the boxes a good watch should. This version is sized at 42 millimeters, with a stainless steel case and a water-resistance rating of 200 meters. Available in a whopping eight styles, it's powered by an NH35A movement.

prod_name: Varmilo Dragon & Phoenix VA104M Mechanical Keyboard
prod_description: Inspired by legendary fire creatures of fable and folklore, the Dragon and Phoenix are mechanical keyboards of mythic proportions. In Chinese culture, they represent good prosperity and happiness. Designed and manufactured by Varmilo, these full-size keyboards each feature a black iron plate with matching doubleshot black keycaps, plus a plastic case with tasteful hydrographic transfer wood printing. Upon this printing, each board showcases a detailed engraving in the upper right-hand corner: the mahogany-colored Phoenix gets a long-tailed phoenix, while the slightly-darker Dragon gets a traditional Chinese dragon. Equipped with LED backlighting, a mini-USB connection, angled rubber-protected feet, and your choice of eight switches, these boards make an elegant statement on any desk.

Maserin, an Italian company known for its gentleman's folding knives, makes a strong play in the multi-tool category with the High-Tech Citizen. Made with 440 stainless steel tools and a G-10 handle, it's got solid materials to stand up to any job. The main tool is the 2.6-inch blade, but there are plenty of others for different jobs, like a carabiner, a can opener, a bottle opener, and a slotted screwdriver system. Weighing just 3.45 ounces, the tool is easy to carry on the go, and even easier to throw in a pack, glovebox, or kitchen drawer.

Perfect for players who want to skip Standard format and go straight to Modern, the MTG Modern Horizons booster box will help you build a seriously potent deck. Each pack is chock-full of new and reprinted cards that will become Modern legal for the first time. The box includes 36 booster packs with 15 cards apiece. Inside each, you'll find a rare or mythic rare card, three uncommon cards, ten common cards, and a basic land card.

At the intersection of style and performance, the SF160S sunglasses from Salvatore Ferragamo offer strong sun protection with a unique look. Made in Italy, these glasses feature a full-rim frame made out of metal for lasting durability and just the right amount of weight. The lenses on the SF160S are made from CR39: a lightweight, scratch-resistant plastic that allows for a wide range of tint and coating choices, while offering excellent UV protection. Available here in a tortoise shell color with a double-bridge design, these shades are great for pairing with formal wear and casual attire alike.

Designed in partnership with WOODCHUCK USA and their Buy One. Plant One. program, these Zippos promote a great cause: for every lighter sold, a tree will be planted. Each Zippo comes with a unique code that you can use to learn about your tree, it's location and the direct impact you are having on the planet. Handcrafted in the US since 1932, authentic Zippo lighters are famed for their durability, windproof design, and lifetime warranty.

prod_name: The Eye Key Snail Artisan Keycap
prod_description: Snails always seem to show up when you least expect them. Now, they're making a grand entrance onto your keyboard. 100-percent handmade from smooth resin, the Snail artisan keycap from The Eye Key is durable, colorful, and strangely cute. Compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, and available in 10 shimmering colors, these snails are sure to add a bit of character to any keyboard. We promise they won't leave a trail.
