prod_description: Both sleek and sturdy, the Vargo Titanium Hinge Wallet delivers space efficiency without sacrificing strength. A titanium plate on one side of the wallet keeps cards secure, while on the other side, a black leather card and cash pocket optimizes accessibility. The two are connected with a black stretch band, which expands to accommodate more cards and cash. A pull tab and hinge system make accessibility a breeze, while an onboard bottle opener lets you enjoy your most important purchases right when you buy them.

Looking for a pair of wood headphones that won't break the bank? The BLON BossHifi B8 is that and more. Featuring real wood ear cups, protein leather pads, and aluminum hardware, they look and feel high quality. The 50-millimeter beryllium-alloy dynamic drivers are another rarity at this price point. Great for at-home and portable listening, these headphones have removable cables and rotating cups for storage when you're on the go. Plus, with an impedance of 16 ohms, they can be easily driven by mobile sources.

The EM5813 is the debut IEM from Cardas Audio, an Oregon-based, family-run manufacturer that specializes in premium audio cables and component parts. The result of years of meticulous design by founder George Cardas, it's efficient, natural, musical, and complete with an eye-catching copper finish. The 11.45-millimeter dynamic driver features a neodymium magnet drive motor and a PEN-type thin-film diaphragm. This makes for, according to one Head-Fi reviewer, an accurate, detailed, balanced, and, most of all, alive and engaging sound. The review goes on to say, Buy a set, and you will find yourself having it in your ears all the time. Fitted with the high-quality Clear Light cable Cardas is known for, the EM5813 comes with three sets of ear tips.

The most accurate and reliable meat thermometer you'll ever need, the Javelin PT12 gives you a reading in just 4 to 5 seconds. And just because it's fast doesn't mean it isn't accurate: The Javelin PT12 is accurate to within less than 1 degree Fahrenheit. It's also got a 1.5-inch display with easy-to-use controls. If you want to store it on the fridge or on the knife block, it has built-in magnets to do so. Furthermore, it's got an IP62 splash-resistance rating, and silver-based antimicrobial protection to keep it going for the long haul a whopping 4,000 hours on a single battery, to be exact. It's got you covered whether you're cooking meat, baking bread, boiling candy, or deep frying potatoes.

New from Topping, a world leader in audio, the DX7 Pro is a DAC/amp designed for the most demanding listener. Following Topping's highly regarded DX7, the Pro model showcases improved hardware and a sophisticated presentation. Highlights include an ESS DAC ES9038PRO chip with near-zero distortion and a SCR8675 chipset that supports Bluetooth 5.0 across all protocols for reliable streaming. The DX7 Pro also packs powerful headphone output: 840 milliwatts at 32 ohms via its single-ended connection, or an impressive 1700mW at 32 ohms out of its 4-pin balanced output. An onboard switch allows you to choose between 115 volts or 230 volts to meet your power requirements.

prod_name: Tai-Hao Sunshine PBT Doubleshot Keycap Set
prod_description: Designed with longevity and style in mind, this Taihao keycap set is notable for its six color rainbow pattern and affordability. Featuring OEM profiles with PBT doubleshot injection legends, they're ideal for MX compatible boards.

prod_name: Seki Edge Takumi No Waza 9-Piece Grooming Kit
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/takumi-no-waza-9-piece-grooming-kit-by-seki-edge/FP/Imz3BHOcR92iVBZBHJmP_pc p.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/takumi-no-waza-9-piece-grooming-kit-by-seki-edge/FP/gxDJmPnPSTqROkUioKjT_Tool shot.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/takumi-no-waza-9-piece-grooming-kit-by-seki-edge/FP/SHbD9xVTCmQijbzN636Q_Tweezers shot.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/takumi-no-waza-9-piece-grooming-kit-by-seki-edge/FP/bSZrHFKdTGybZ1Gtw8at_Clippers up close shot.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/takumi-no-waza-9-piece-grooming-kit-by-seki-edge/FP/HfmWysU9TTOIcayZrVrm_Up close on tools.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/takumi-no-waza-9-piece-grooming-kit-by-seki-edge/FP/DflzIY1TIeYZWTm8Otnz_fixed.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Featuring nine essential tools for daily grooming, the Takumi No Waza kit by Seki Edge will help you make a good impression wherever you go. It contains everything you need to keep your nails, cuticles, and facial hair in tip-top shape, all in a travel-friendly zippered leather case. Made of stainless steel and meant to last a lifetime, this kit is a great gift for anyone who pays attention to the details.

Get a different finish on your headphones when you upgrade to Dekoni Audio's highly regarded line of audiophile earpads, available in five variants that mold the sound and comfort to your ears. They come in Elite Velour, Elite Hybrid, Protein Leather, Elite Sheepskin, and Fenestrated Sheepskin, each with their own set of sonic and comfort properties. Each finish provides a breathable, cushioned, enveloped feel for hours of fatigue-free listening all while leaving you with enough isolation to enjoy your favorite records. Unlike other aftermarket earpads, these are vastly more comfortable than stock pads, even for people with glasses. They're compatible with Audeze LCD, Focal, Sennheiser HD series, Koss ESP95X, AKG K7XX, Fostex TH series, Beyerdynamic DT series, Audio-Technica M50x, Audio-Technica AD series, Sony, Meze, and HIFIMAN HE series (to name a few).

prod_name: Citizen Satellite Wave World-Time GPS Solar Watch
prod_description: Citizen consistently pushes the watch industry forward. Featuring a satellite GPS timekeeping system with a worldwide reception area, this timepiece can track the time in 27 cities around the world. In addition, it has a perpetual calendar, daylight savings time indicator, power-reserve indicator, and light-level power indicators. Of course, because it's backed by Eco-Drive technology, it's powered by light and never needs a battery. Water resistant to 100 meters, the watch has a sapphire crystal and a tough stainless steel case.

Spanning nearly 3 feet wide, these Varmilo desk mats provide plenty of space for your keyboard, mouse, and other accessories. Made with a smooth cloth-top surface and stitched edges, they're optical-sensor friendly and smooth as butter whether you use them for gaming, work, or play.

Though function-loaded watches bring a lot to the table, they tend to be gaudy and overbuilt. While dress watches look great with a collared shirt, they don't offer much functionality. From Tissot, a brand synonymous with Swiss watchmaking prowess, the T-Touch Expert gives you the best of both worlds. Available here in three different styles, this watch is lighter than it looks, thanks to its 100-meter water-resistant titanium build. The dial is a combination of analog and digital styles. This allows it to pack a ton of useful features for the outdoorsman most notably a compass, thermometer, barometer, altitude indicator, chronograph, GMT hand, and more. All styles offered are backed by an accurate quartz movement and a sapphire crystal to prevent scratching.

prod_name: Edox Les Vauberts Moonphase Date Quartz Watch
prod_description: Les Vauberts, where this collection of Edox watches takes its name, is a small area near Les Genevez, famous for hosting the first watchmakers more than four centuries ago. In tribute to these skilled artisans, the Les Vauberts Moonphase Date Quartz watch has a dressy look but plenty of functionality to go with it. The layout of the dial is well-balanced and clean. There's a subdial at 3 that tracks the day of the month and a subdial at 9 for the day of the week. Beneath them is the main event: a proportionately sized subdial that keeps track of the moon and its phases throughout the month. Finally, a stainless steel case houses an accurate Swiss quartz movement, which is protected to 200 meters, thanks to the screw-down caseback.

Most of the time you don't need a full-size folder on your hip. For the times you don't, reach for the Maserin Turtle. Like its namesake insinuates, the Turtle is stout and compact. It packs a 1.6-inch blade into a handle made from a combination of steel and wood. Just like a turtle, the knife conceals itself easily: slide it into a pocket with the pocket clip or stuff it into a fifth pocket on a pair of jeans or slacks. The blade on these little tanks is made from AUS-8 stainless steel, but you can upgrade to Damascus steel if you want a knife worthy of any upscale get-together. You'll also have your choice of wood for the handle.

By nurturing the ideas that most excite them, the folks at Dango Products are coming up with simple solutions to everyday problems like how to make a wallet that balances minimalism and security, a distilled design and a sense of style. Enter the D01 Dapper Wallet, made of leather secured to an anodized aluminum chassis with military-spec bolts. Tuck it into your front or back pocket, or use the CNC'd aluminum tab to tether it to your belt. The pockets can fit up to 12 cards total, while the integrated silicone band holds folded bills and receipts. Thoughtful details include RFID blocking and a built-in bottle opener.

On October 25th, the world saw the launch of #TeamTrees: an eco-friendly global initiative to plant 20 million trees before January 1st, 2020. To achieve the goal, #TeamTrees is asking for 20 million dollars (a dollar per tree). At Drop, we want to do our part the best way we know how: by mobilizing our dedicated Mech Keys Community and creating the Treecap! This dye-subbed PBT keycap is the perfect way to support the cause, and earn a lasting memento in the process. The best part? Every single dollar we raise not a penny less will go directly to supporting #TeamTrees.

prod_name: CLICKEYbits Tall Fidget Clicky Switch Tester
prod_description: You'd be hard pressed to find a more fun way to test switches than with CLICKEYbits. In fact, though they were originally developed as switch testers, people loved them so much that they started buying them as fidget toys. Building on the success, the father-son team that created them set out to expand the lineup. Now available with tall, SA row-3 keycaps from Signature Plastics, each CLICKEYbits is made with authentic Green (heavy clicky) mechanical switches from Cherry. At about 2 inches wide, they're the perfect size to fill the palm for a satisfying feel in the hand.

Handcrafted in the U.S. since 1932, authentic Zippo lighters are famed for their durability, windproof design, and lifetime warranty. If you're into a more minimal aesthetic, then this is your lucky day. Crafted with the classic Zippo shape, this one has an antique copper finish for a vintage look. Like all Zippo lighters, it's packaged in an environmentally friendly gift box.

A sharp knife in the kitchen is essential for safety and efficiency. These kitchen knives from Masazumi feature blades made from three layers of stainless steel. At the center is a V Gold stainless steel core that's sandwiched between two layers of soft stainless steel. The slim profile of the blade allows them to tear through veggies and meats with ease. The hammered texture, reminiscent of craters on the surface of the moon, helps release food by reducing friction on the blade. Black Pakkawood scales and stainless steel bolsters make up the handle, which is shaped with a protruding curve at the base for pinkie placement.

With the T1 IEM from Tin HiFi, you can take your favorite sounds with you wherever you go all without sacrificing quality or serious cash. This ergonomic IEM has 16-ohm impedance, making it great to use with any portable audio source. Made from metal with a non-removable cable plus a y-splitter with three button controls and a mic it's durable and equipped to handle all of your audio needs. In regards to sound quality, the T1 delivers what reviewers on Prime Audio rightly call a balanced and linear sound signature, with smooth transitions from lows to highs.

prod_name: Artisan Cutlery Proponent D2 Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: Like a boxcutter on steroids, the Artisan Cutlery Proponent is a proponent of getting things done fast. This nearly 10-inch folder is built like a tank. It features a 4-inch blade made from tough D2 steel with a stonewashed finish to hide nicks and scratches. The blade rides on ceramic ball bearings, which allows it to open and close effortlessly with a simple press on the thumb stud. To prevent accidental closure when you're hard at work, the Proponent is backed by a solid liner lock. Finally, this beefy folder comes with your choice of G-10 or carbon fiber scales to match your existing carry.

prod_name: Varmilo Christmas Dye-Subbed PBT Keycap Set
prod_description: It's beginning to look a lot like Christmas¦ keycaps. New from Varmilo and ready just in time for the holiday season, these milk white and red keycaps are as sweet as a candy cane and as tough as Santa's trusty sleigh. Comprising 108 keys (enough to cover a full-size board), the set is full of holiday cheer, including fun novelties like reindeer, bells, chimneys, and Santa hats. Made from durable dye-subbed PBT plastic, the keycaps are built to last for many Christmases to come.

Nothing says Merry Christmas quite like a festive holiday keycap. New from the makers at MEMEDA, these Merry Christmas artisan keycaps are sure to put you in the right spirit. There are three fun options to choose from, each inside a frosty snowglobe: a reindeer with a sleigh full of presents, Santa Claus seated next to a decorated tree, and a snowman posted outside a log cabin. Made from resin, these jolly caps are compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones.

Handcrafted in Germany, this special edition of the DT990 Premium improves upon the original with an updated headband and end pieces, plus a sleek all-black colorway and a hard-shell carrying case. The build quality is second to none, and the detail and soundstage are among the best available at this price point. This is also the lightest headphone in its class, so hours of use will induce little to no fatigue. The sonic reproduction is the cornerstone of Beyerdynamic's design and comes through with forward-sounding highs and a punchy, rich bass response. Have you ever noticed John and Ringo whispering in the background of a Beatles outro? No? Sounds like you could use the Beyerdynamic DT990.

Designed for the discerning ears of sound engineers and audiophiles, the closed-back Beyerdynamic Custom Studio headphones are a state-of-the-art studio essential. Outfitted with cutting-edge, professional-grade 80-ohm drivers handmade in Germany, these headphones deliver precise and powerful playback for frequencies between 5 to 35,000 Hz. Switch between four different audio profiles including analytical, bass-heavy, midcentric, and balanced signatures using adjustable bass-reflex vents in the housing shells. Equipped with a variable noise-reduction system and engineered with replaceable components (including a detachable cable), the Beyerdynamic Custom Studio is a long-term investment you can take with you to the studio and beyond.

prod_name: Massdrop x MiTo Pulse CTRL High-Profile Keyboard
prod_description: Missed out on MiTo's electric Pulse custom keycap set? Looking for a handsome, heavyweight keyboard with all the bells and whistles you could ever need? How about both. This version of the Massdrop CTRL High-Profile is just like the original, but now it comes with a set of iconic Pulse keycaps and a matching anodized aluminum case both of which are available in two colorways to make it your own. Machined to have a 6-degree angle, the case is ergonomically crafted for a natural feel. Thanks to the Kaihua switch sockets, the keyboard allows you to swap switches whenever you want with no soldering required. It's also fully programmable via QMK, meaning you can assign macros or custom keybinds to every key. What's more, it comes with customizable RGB backlighting and underlighting, dual USB-C connectors, and your choice of switches.
prod_varities: ['Pulse SA - Noire', 'Pulse SA - Standard Sculpted', 'Pulse SA - Flat']

prod_description: CJRB's Talla is a mid-size folding knife that carries easy and slices well. Fitted with a 3.4-inch wharncliffe blade made of D2 tool steel, it delivers great control and precision. For even more control, you can rest your thumb on the concave spine. To keep the blade in place when opened, the Talla has a sturdy stainless steel liner lock. Available with your choice of G-10 or carbon fiber for the handle, the knife comes with a reversible stainless steel clip for carry on either side.

MEMEDA is back with a new artisan keycap that's sure to ruffle feathers. Called the Chick, this hand-painted keycap depicts a cute, bulbous chicken in five different colors to match your keyboard and desktop decor. At nearly 26 millimeters tall, the Chick might have some people gawking, but it's cute enough to calm any doubters once you see it up close. Compatible with Cherry MX switches and clones, the keycap is made from resin for a long-lasting build.

prod_name: Heritor Matador Automatic Watch Gift Set
prod_description: From Heritor, the Matador commands the stage like the entertainer its named after. A dive watch with materials and construction to match, this timepiece is reliable and strong. It's accurate, too, thanks to a Seiko NH35 automatic movement with a 41-hour power reserve. The movement, which beats 21600 times an hour, is visible via the display caseback. As for the dial design, the Matador has thick, luminous indexes and large hands to tell time at a glance. Also worth noting? The watch comes in your choice of four styles, each nicely packed with both a rubber and stainless steel strap, depending on your preference.

When you think of Swiss watches, Tissot quickly comes to mind. A proven Swiss maker since 1853, the company has been carefully crafting quality timepieces for decades. The Belle quartz watch is a slim piece designed for smaller wrists. Minimally styled with slim markers and hands, it's constructed with a combination of white ceramic and stainless steel. The resulting duo has excellent contrast and appeal in many a setting. To preserve the pristine look, the Belle has a sapphire crystal to boot.

prod_name: Edox C1 Chronograph Big Date Quartz Watch
prod_description: The Edox C1 Chronograph Big Date has the functionality you'd find in a rugged outdoor watch and the elegance of a traditional dress watch. At 45 millimeters wide, this timepiece is large and in charge, but the design looks great in virtually any setting. Featuring slim, lumed hands and markers, the C1 is easy to read in dark conditions. The coin-edge bezel allows the wearer to track elapsed time with a simple rotation, and the chronograph can act as a stopwatch. For durability, there's a 200-meter water-resistant case and a scratch-resistant sapphire crystal. Plus, there's no need to worry about winding the C1 every time you wear it: It's powered by a Swiss quartz battery.

prod_name: Oris Artelier Translucent Skeleton Automatic Watch
prod_description: Swiss made since 1904, Oris watches are a mark of true craftsmanship. The Artelier translucent skeleton watch is a sight to behold. As if looking under the hood of a luxury automobile, it has absolutely nothing to hide. In fact, it puts each of its 26 jewels on full display, visible from the front or back. The movement is suspended in mid-air, held in place by steel bars, which, in this case, act as the hour markers. At 40.5 millimeters, the stainless steel case is sized to complement most wrists. The hands are painted in an offsetting color for legibility, while the onion crown at 3 o'clock adds to the luxurious vibes. To protect the goods inside, the Artelier has a sapphire crystal and is water resistant to 50 meters.

prod_description: Made from heavy-duty thin-pressed nylon, these braided watch straps are tough and available in a wide range of colors to match your watch or offset it with something new. Covered with waterproof material, they'll hold up in the rain and under the faucet. The buckle, available in two finishes, is pressed with the Da Luca name, a reminder of the quality they've come to be known for over the years. Because they're braided, the straps don't come with holes. Just place the prong through a small opening in the braids and it will shut securely.

From proven Swiss watchmaker Certina, the DS Royal Quartz Watch is built for active wear. Made with a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal, the watch is durable and sturdy. Its movement is, too: an ETA caliber 251.272 quartz movement, it won't lose track of time until it's time to change out the battery. Additionally, the DS Royal makes a great stopwatch. In fact, the chronograph can track time for up to 30 minutes down to a tenth of a second. There's even a tachymeter scale on the bezel to track distance and speed in a pinch. Set on a leather strap, this watch is lumed for visibility and built for adventures far and wide.

Watchmaker Romain Jerome made waves in the watch world by crafting timepieces out of materials from the sunken Titanic, the moon, and other rare sources. Now, the company is back with an eye-catching clock engineered for everyday use. The XPOS.020.SI clock features an automatic movement and chronograph functionality with a 30-minute counter and a 12-hour counter. It's small enough to fit in the palm of your hand or attach to a band, yet large enough to read from several feet away. With a polished rose gold bezel complemented by a black dial and matte-black exterior details, the XPOS.020.SI sports an aesthetic combination that feels both modern and classic.

From IKBC, the Table E mechanical keyboard is like a keyboard and wrist rest built into one. Complete with multimedia keys and a volume-adjustment knob, the keyboard comes in two sizes: tenkeyless or full-size, which includes a numpad. The keycaps are one of a kind. Designed with a wider surface area and an ergonomic curve, they help you type more comfortably and more accurately than standard keycaps. Thanks to N-key rollover technology, you can type as fast as you want without input mistakes. When it comes to backlighting, the keyboard has five brightness levels and seven effects to choose from. Armed with your choice of Cherry MX switches, the Table E gives you control of the feel, too.

prod_name: Revue Thommen Airspeed XLarge Automatic Watch
prod_description: At 40 millimeters, the Revue Thommen Airspeed XLarge's name is a bit deceiving. Perhaps in the vintage watch era where this one certainly takes some cues a 40-millimeter timepiece was considered gargantuan. Or perhaps it commands more attention than most others in that size range. Whatever the case, the Airspeed XLarge can make a big difference in your collection. Featuring simple and bold Arabic numerals, it's straightforward and easy to read. The hour and minutes hands sport a combination of white and black or blue, and the seconds hand is tipped in red. The overall ensemble is cohesive and legible. Materials wise, the watch is built with a stainless steel case and a sapphire crystal, owing to a water resistance rating of 50 meters. The ETA 2824-2 movement can be viewed through the display caseback, which is also made from sapphire.

prod_name: Maserin Nimrod M390 Tactical Folding Knife
prod_description: Named for the adroit hunter and king of Shinar, the Maserin Nimrod is an imposing all-around folder. The blade is a 3.5-inch drop-point made from Bohler M390 stainless steel, arguably the best commercial steel on the market. Tumbled to a stonewashed finish, the blade complements the handle, whether micarta, G-10, or carbon fiber. A lockback provides the folder's backbone, creating a secure feeling in the hand, even when the going gets rough. Another win for security's sake is the finger choil in the handle scales, which makes a perfect place for an index finger. Though the knife is nearly 9 inches overall, it carries discreetly thanks to the deep-carry pocket clip. Flanking the clip is a glassbreaker for emergencies.

Whether you're an audiophile, mechanical keyboard enthusiast, or blade collector, at Drop we want to help you dive deeper into your passions. The Drop Bounty Box is a curated collection of high-end products from our Audiophile, EDC, and Mechanical Keyboard interest groups from well-reviewed IEMs and keyboards, to proven folding knives, stunning keycaps, Drop-exclusive headphones, and more. Each box is filled with a thoughtful assortment of quality products that have been previously featured on our site. No matter what box you choose, you'll get a collection of great items. To make things even more interesting, some boxes will feature special Rare and Epic items, detailed below.

Your keys say something about you. Every time you take them out to open something, pass them to a friend, or leave them on the table, they catch eyes. Let yours make a classy statement with a Bellroy leather key cover. Made of premium, environmentally friendly leather, these key covers sport a bifold design with a magnetic closure to safely secure up to four keys. When you're ready to use one, rotate it out like you would a pocket knife. The key cover also has a leather loop for attachment to car keys.

prod_name: Bestech Bison D2 Frame Lock Knife
prod_description: With a name like Bison, you'd think this flipper would be bulkier than it is. In reality, the Bestech Bison is a sleek, easy-to-control folder made with premium materials. The handle is comprised of two materials: titanium for the frame lock and your choice of G-10 or carbon fiber for the opposite-side scale. The blade, a 3.6-inch D2 drop-point, deploys fast and effortlessly, courtesy of the ceramic ball bearings and flipper tab. For carry, the knife has a titanium pocket clip that provides tip-up carry on the right side. Finally, you'll get your choice of color and blade finish, whether you prefer something more sophisticated or tactical.

prod_description: Combining detailed audio with fine-tuned comfort, the Beyerdynamic Amiron Wireless headphones take true-wireless listening to new heights. Like the Amiron Home, the wireless uses high-end Tesla drivers to deliver strong sound articulation across all frequencies. Unlike the Home, the Wireless features a closed-back design, which leads to a darker more relaxed signature than the Home edition, according to reviewers on Headfonics. To ensure a seamless wireless connection capable of Hi-Res sound, the Wireless offers support for Qualcomm aptX HD and Apple AAC  plus aptX LL codecs, plus an app that allows for fine-tuned level adjustment. Its 32-ohm impedance makes it perfect to pair with today's portable devices, while its plush, precisely balanced earpads optimize comfort.

Decades ago, when transatlantic trade brought the world closer together, the Montblanc 4810 Dual Time automatic watch would have been a godsend. Today, it still is. Featuring a dual-time complication, the watch tells the local time with the rose gold hands in the center, and the time at home (or wherever you desire), with the 24-hour display at 12 o'clock. Separated into light and dark halves, the subdial has an a.m. and p.m. indicator, too. Decorated with a star-shaped guillochÃ© pattern, the dial has a wavy look that dazzles at different angles. Thirty four jewels make up the MB 29.19 movement, which can be viewed via the display caseback. Both crystals (front and back) are made of sapphire for scratch resistance and protection.

The SMSL M500 is an all-in-one DAC/amp optimized for high-end audio and user-friendly operation. Engineered with a highly regarded ESS ES9038PRO DAC, an XMOS XU-208 USB chipset, and dual OPA1612 op amps, the M500 delivers precisely articulated sound into any pair of headphones or monitors. To make level adjustment a breeze, the M500 features a vivid 2.19-inch LG TFT LCD display a rarity on today's desktop DACs. Plus, it offers a wide range of inputs and outputs, including a true balanced XLR output, an RCA out, dual optical inputs, and a coaxial input. The SMSL can also be used as a preamp unit with independent headphone volume preamp volume controls. Listen your way with options and an onboard display that give you total control.

Powerful but compact, the Aune B1S portable headphone amp makes a great pairing for high-end digital audio players when you're trying to drive more demanding headphones. It features a class-A amplifier, a spec generally reserved for pricier desktop amplifiers. This allows the B1S to drive full-size, power-hungry headphones like the Massdrop x Sennheiser HD 6XX and the HD 800. Two output options can be toggled on the side of the unit: the 20mA mode for 10 hours of play, or the more powerful 40mA mode for 5 hours of play with more demanding cans. Head-Fi's ahmadfaizadnan used the B1S with the HD 6XX and had this to say: If you're looking for a mellow-sounding amp that has tons of detail and clarity, look no further, because the Aune B1S has got you covered.

prod_name: Massdrop x Fostex TR-X00 Ebony Headphones (EU)
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/tbV0NOaT8qhV8NZ5CIHM_fixeroni 3.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/R1Q0hwtQSeTOfhNYEAEu_AI7B2832 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/U8o2RmipTniPmdpXvx6Y_AI7B2772 copy .jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/E1ivOGl6TjG7KJ88f8X5_AI7B2925 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/lJ2BIOKhSymNrdyaOWyA_AI7B2910 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/vqX7X3iTRcaTFpIOmlRO_AI7B1909 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/cwvSSR81RB26UsW6v6W5_AI7B2871 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/qVIkDRvRq618UZw8ln5g_AI7B1882 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/oV6W24gcQX2tYlCoxBx7_AI7B1764 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-fostex-tr-x00-ebony-headphones/FP/dOeV9hsMRnW47oSQYWnW_AI7B7614 copy filter.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: When the Massdrop community asked for a closed-back headphone that redefined price-to-performance expectations, the TH-X00 was our answer. Made in collaboration with Fostex, a brand that's produced innovative audio gear since 1949, these headphones feature ebony ear cups, a magnesium alloy frame, and Fostex's signature biodynamic drivers. Prized for its hardness and density as much as its beauty, ebony makes for a darker aesthetic and a smoother, more refined sound signature. Now, in another response to the community's requests, we've updated the original with a removable cable. Introducing the TR-X00 (the R stands for removable): everything you loved about the TH-X00, now with a detachable cable for greater flexibility.

Good work at a fair price. That's founder Tony from A&H Leather Goods' calling card. The Micro Billfold Wallet downsizes the traditional billfold design to make it even easier to carry on the go. Instead of a compartment for cash or receipts, there's a flat elastic band down the middle that can hold up to 10 bills. Inside, you'll find three card pockets on each side, plus hidden pockets behind them. Backed by RFID-blocking technology, the wallet will protect your precious information on the go. Each one is made from full-grain leather and available in multiple styles.

prod_name: ESEE Zancudo Frame Lock Folder w/ D2 Steel
prod_description: Spanish for mosquito, the Zancudo is a smaller and easier to maneuver version of the popular ESEE Avispa. Designed by Mike Perrin and Jeff Randall for Blue Ridge Knives, the svelte folder features a utilitarian drop-point blade made from reliable D2 tool steel. Two thumbstuds make for easy opening, while the frame lock secures the blade once open. The handle, shaped like an hourglass for a comfy grip, is made from a combination of steel and polymer with a dimpled pattern similar to the surface of a golf ball. Also notable, the Zancudo gives you two options for carry: tip-up or tip-down depending on your preference.

prod_description: Compact and discreet, the Lumintop IYP365 Pen Light fits is roughly the size of a typical office pen. It's easy to control one-handed via a clickable tail switch that smoothly cycles through low, medium, and high settings. Made from hard-anodized aerospace-grade aluminum, it's IPX-8 water resistant and impact resistant to 1.5 meters. The light comes with your choice of either a CREE LED with a max of 200 lumens, or a NICHEA LED with a max of 125 lumens. At just under 1 ounce the light slides easily in your pocket and stays secure with its stainless-steel pocket clip.

These are the sunglasses you'll always be glad to have around: durable, affordable, and universally flattering, too. Keep them in your glove compartment, toss them in your backpack, and rock them while wearing a suit, jeans, or swimsuit by the pool. Featuring a bold and robust frame with plenty of coverage, the Torrey Pines sunglasses are an excellent choice when the sun shines bright. Get these polarized shades in your choice of seven styles.

prod_name: TOPS Knives C.U.T. 4.0 Combat Utility Tool Knife
prod_description: The TOPS Knives C.U.T. 4.0 is the best of two worlds two worlds that designer Joshua Swanagon knows all too well. With his background in martial arts, he has an affinity for karambits. However, he's also an avid outdoorsman, and fails to see the practicality of the hawkbill blade in the field. As a result, Swanagon designed his own blade that excels in both. Featuring a 4.1-inch 1095 steel drop-point, this fixed blade is apt to handle most anything you throw at it at the campsite or on the hunt. What's more, if you prefer to or have to use it for self defense, you can stick a finger through the ring and use it just like a karambit. Crafted from micarta, the handle offers a sure grip for any type of task. For carry, it comes with a Kydex sheath.

Marc Jacobs has shown consistent appeal since its first menswear line in 1994. These made-in-Italy eyeglasses showcase a classic look with durable, modern construction. Available in three styles, these eyeglasses feature a full-rim frame and signature Marc Jacobs accents on the temples like those you'll find on the company's famous handbags. Here in your choice of color, the glasses are the perfect way to bring some clarity and style to your day-to-day. Each pair comes with a carrying case and cleaning cloth.

prod_description: A fullsize keyboard with a retro look, the Akko 9009 is built for a satisfying experience at the keys. The colorway is a combination of cream and beige with splashes of green and orange, just like the famous 9009 keycap set. Made from dye-subbed PBT, the keycaps are durable and vivid. Running on a USB-C connection, the keyboard processes commands fast and N-key rollover only helps it get even faster. Finally, it comes with your choice of Cherry MX switches to get just the right feel.

When you think of Swiss automatic watches, Tissot comes to mind right away. In business since 1853, the company has a knack for making impressive timepieces that can be passed down for generations. The PRS 516 Powermatic 80 is a detailed automatic watch that toes the line between dressy and sporty. Powered by Tissot's Powermatic 80 automatic movement, the timepiece will tick for an impressive 80 hours on a full charge (without wear). On top of that, the watch is 100 meters water resistant and has and dual sapphire crystals on the front and back one to showcase the movement.

A symbol of strength, pride, and courage, the lion is nothing to take lightly. Put one on your keyboard and you'll dignify it at once. From B.O.B. Handcraft, these handcrafted keycaps are made from resin in great detail. They depict a lion with a steely gaze, flowing mane, and glowing eyes. The backside of each cap has the B.O.B. logo engraved in large, spooky letters. Put them on your Cherry MX (or clone) switches.

prod_description: Like something out of your grandfather's old trunk in the attic, the Ingersoll Trenton looks like a piece of vintage Americana and it is. Made by Ingersoll, which was founded in New York in 1892, the watch has a rustic look and feel. The details are everything on this timepiece. From the aged stainless steel case and Horween leather strap to the large onion crown and wire lugs, it's got plenty of retro vibes in its favor. The 44-millimeter housing holds an automatic movement and a mineral crystal that's resistant to scratching. At 50 meters water resistance, the Trenton will keep ticking even if it faces a sprinkling or splash, too.

Cvstos, which means guardian in Latin, sprung onto the scene in 2005 with a slew of watches that pushed the boundaries of traditional design. The ChallengeR TT is a fine example of the company's watchmaking prowess. This intricately detailed timepiece gets its TT moniker from its twin-time function: a secondary dial spanning from 5 to 7 o'clock that allows the wearer to track another time zone. Another unique feature is the date window at 12. Two rotating discs numbered 0 through 9 work in tandem to display the correct date. To keep these features working swiftly is a Calibre CVSTOS 551 automatic movement. Structurally, the watch employs a stainless steel case and sapphire crystals on the front and the back. The prominent crown not only adds a touch of welcome contrast, but it's made from titanium to boot.

prod_name: Pelikan M205 Star Ruby Special-Edition Fountain Pen
prod_description: Styled in translucent red to match the color of Pelikan's Edelstein Ink of the Year, the M205 Star Ruby fountain pen features the same high-capacity differential piston-fill system as the renowned SouverÃ¤n series. This means you can use it with any bottle of fountain pen ink for a smooth writing experience. The body has a burgundy pink color, just like the Star Ruby gemstone its named after. As you write, you'll notice the pen glisten as light hits it at different angles. Tying it all together is a stainless steel pocket clip and nib in your choice of three sizes.

prod_name: Morphic M83 Series Quartz Chronograph Watch
prod_description: Morphic doesn't make dainty watches. The M83 is a good example. A 44-millimeter chronograph, this watch is crafted from a thick chunk of stainless steel. Water resistant to 100 meters, it's powered by a Japanese quartz movement for accuracy and hassle-free wear. The dial has lumed Arabic numerals and hands for legibility, plus three separate subdials, two of which are tied to the chronograph. A scratch-resistant mineral crystal ensures the face stays clean, while a stainless steel bracelet gives the watch a hefty feel on the wrist. Get the M83 in your choice of seven styles to round out your collection.

Somewhere between a gentleman's folder and a tactical knife, the Maserin Trigger sports an unconventional look. The handle is made up of two parts: a stainless steel frame surrounded by your choice of bocote, cocobolo, or ebony wood scales that cover about two thirds of the surface. The bare section of the frame is where the folder gets its name. A raised piece of metal on the scale is where the knife is opened and closed, acting like a trigger for the back lock. Press it down to deploy the blade, and again to close it. The slim 440 stainless steel blade is great for detail work and getting into tight areas. Another touch of style? The blue titanium pocket clip on the backside of the handle. Feel free to remove it if you want a more subtle piece.

prod_name: Maserin 550 OneFold Pocket Knife w/ Money Clip
prod_description: A knife, a money clip, and a work of craftsmanship, the 550 OneFold is the latest from Italian knifemaker Maserin. Measuring just under 5 inches when open, it's portable to say the least not to mention it weighs less than 2 ounces. The blade is made from hardy and easy-to-sharpen 440C steel. It locks in place with the built-in frame lock, which is handy for tougher jobs. Flip the knife over and you'll see a sturdy stainless steel clip. About half the width of the handle, it doubles as a money clip for bill storage. The handle is available in two distinct woods, each of which displays a unique grain to round out the piece.

Making its exclusive debut right here on Massdrop, the MEE Audio Matrix3 headphones deliver comfort, portability, and clear, balanced sound all in a wireless form factor for cable-free listening at home or on the go. A sequel to the popular Matrix2, they're equipped with an ultra-efficient Bluetooth 4.0 chipset (plus support for aptX and AAC) for 24 hours of playback, 28 hours of talk, and 1,000 hours of standby time. And even when the battery is charging or depleted, you can keep the music going by using the Matrix3 in wired mode with the included 3.5-millimeter cable. Great for new owners of the latest iPhone or Android smartphone, these headphones feature an integrated microphone with intuitive controls to manage calls and media from up to two devices simultaneously.

An IF Design Award winner in 2017, the Nitecore LR12 doubles as a 360-degree lantern and a flashlight. At 4.2 inches long, it's smaller than just about any lantern out there, but that doesn't mean it sacrifices power. In fact, on the highest setting, the light delivers 1,000 lumens and casts a beam as far as 166 meters. Knock the light down to the lowest setting and it can last over five weeks, too. Attach the torch by the hanging loop or stick it onto a metal surface and it will magnetically stay put. No matter how bright you turn it up, it stays cool thanks to the advanced temperature regulation system. There's even a beacon mode if you need to signal for help.

prod_name: Sabbat X12 Ultra TWS Bluetooth 5.0 IEM
prod_description: The Sabbat X12 Ultra is a true-wireless IEM designed for today's traveling listener. Great for commutes, errands, and workouts, the X12 Ultra is both lightweight and long-lasting. The earbuds can play continuously for 68 hours on a single charge, and the Qi-compatible charging case that provides up to 30 hours of battery. For superb stereo sound, each earbud houses a 10-millimeter driver that delivers booming bass, strong mids, and detailed treble frequencies. For a stable and seamless connection, the X12 Ultra comes equipped with a Bluetooth 5.0 smart dual chip and a high-sensitivity antenna.

A higher-end DAC/amp from community favorite xDuoo, the TA-10 features the flagship AKM AK4490 DAC and a classic 12AU7 tube. Its variety of interfaces make it incredibly versatile and include two sets of auxiliary inputs, a USB input, an SPDIF out, and an RCA out. Fully balanced from input to output, the TA-10 is complete with a top-level XMOS eight-core chip. It's ideal for driving balanced recabled headphones (like the Massdrop x Sennheiser HD 6XX) without breaking the bank, and its single-ended output works well if you don't have a balanced headphone, delivering the same high power and accuracy. Made of high-grade aluminum alloy, this solidly built DAC/amp looks great as part of your desktop computer setup.

prod_name: Massdrop x Airist Audio R-2R DAC
prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/ihFwrcLWTeCCFL3SkGqb_AI7B7042 copy_straight2.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/Av7gPljGQoG9FE2UWoiK_AI7B6411 copy_new.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/HPayjSVO2OgUNFz5gqQo_dacpickup.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/Eam3OrZ6QjCnyZW0bgZk_AI7B6489 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/Egh12bEERSmZ24AM3cFg_AI7B6341 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/Z4JZlNR8CBRlVvOsyndA_AI7B6390 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/3qp64E62RguFZRrTOtOZ_dacpickup2.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/AZujtJflQkyOybRW6Iyv_x3Xo26EfSxuPJB5kLGwv_AI7B0212 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/XneJYbTaGjcDKIiXQcWw_AI7B7987 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/JB7clo6kQj2lUW9y9iir_AI7B7978 copy_new.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/wmqAg9BSQxOuGDadwNlz_airistinterior copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/massdrop-x-airist-audio-r-2r-dac/FP/vG9zILIPRsyrM9NwqLv7_AI7B7838 copy.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Featuring discrete resistor ladder technology at an unheard-of price, the Massdrop x Airist Audio R-2R DAC is one of our most requested and anticipated products this year: a DAC with the looks and quality to match our new lineup of amps. An older technology that's been making a comeback, R-2R is known to produce rich, warm, natural sound and can have benefits in spatial awareness and staging. But because this type of design requires expensive high-precision matched resistors (and a lot of them), for a long time, well-implemented R-2R DACs could only be found in $5,000-plus products. More than 2 years in the making, this sign-magnitude DAC has two independent 24-bit ladders with 48 resistors apiece per each of the two channels, which cancel out errors and distortion for purer processing. It has a short, solid form factor and is designed to pair well with the Cavalli Tube Hybrid, Liquid Carbon X, and THX AAA¢ 789.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/t88I8UpgTRuIAC9uCNqf_2609 3714129.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/ZKZqnZOSaObGUhVObr2H_Cover Gagarin 2609 with glass 1.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/Ld9Xlj7PS4mz7qNfo3lV_Cover Gagarin 2609 with glass.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/zE43IAo2RyOBCOPeShs8_26093705125.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/6WxlQaGRR3Ce8GI4q4k3_2609_3745200.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/eKdfKLYsRJK6cldQmJMz_2609-3745130.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/DkzGOfe0RLWHHpwW78hV_pcbanner.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/t88I8UpgTRuIAC9uCNqf_2609 3714129.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/sturmanskie-gagarin-commemorative-mechanical-watch/FP/6YksiFBHQV6aQEv2Shh0_2609 3714130.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: The first-ever human to enter space, Russian pilot Yuri Gagarin, wore a Sturmanskie mechanical watch just like this one. Originally standard issue for air force pilots in 1949, these Sturmanskie watches maintained performance in the toughest conditions, even at zero gravity. Though this timepiece has been updated considerably with a larger case and a commemorative caseback with Gagarin's engraved image it's still powered by the Poljot 2609 17-jewel manual movement, which is the same caliber as the iconic first generation. The numbered limited-edition titanium watch is made with a mineral crystal and leather strap and has a 42-hour power reserve.

Great for pens, knives, tools, supplies, and whatever else you can fit inside, this adjustable tool roll can be customized to your liking. Made from Allegory Goods' signature Latigo leather, it's durable and supple. The interior has adjustable loops, which you can thread through different holes to support your daily carry. Create a few loops for multiple tools, or spread them out to hold larger accessories and feel free to change it up, too. A zipper pouch on the side is great for smaller gear and change, while the exterior button-snap closure can be used for larger things.

prod_name: Kershaw 1730SS Zing Stainless Steel Folding Knife
prod_description: The latest in Kershaw's long line of RJ Martin designed Zings, the Kershaw Zing SS combines the size of the Leek with the styling of the Cryo II in a sleek, all stainless steel construction. Giving you a powerful blade with a frame lock at a very reasonable price, the latest Zing keeps your blade game on point.

prod_name: American Bench Craft Working Man's Belt
prod_description: Constructed from a single strip of full-grain, vegetable-tanned leather, the Working Man's Belt by American Bench Craft is cut to size, measuring 1.5-inches wide and more than an eighth-inch thick. Each is handcrafted in the US in their workshop using traditional techniques and hand tools. And because they use the highest quality leather, each will develop a unique patina over time. The buckle is secured with heavy-duty snap fasteners to hold up longer against heat and friction, and can easily be switched out with any custom buckle in your collection. Wear it with any pair of jeans, khakis, or shorts.

The Audio-Technica ATH-DSR9BT is considered by many including Head-Fi founder Jude Mansilla to be one of the best-sounding wireless headsets on the market. It features the company's Pure Digital Drive system, an exciting new development that allows the headphone to operate without the sound-degrading D/A converter that conventional wireless headphones rely on. Instead, the ATH-DSR9BT uses Trigence Semiconductor's Dnote chipset to receive the digital audio signal from a Bluetooth wireless transmission, then process and transfer it to the 45-millimeter True Motion driver, where the digital pulses move the voice coil and diaphragm forward and backward to create the sound waves heard by the listener. The ATH-DSR9BT also overcomes the sonic limitations of typical Bluetooth transmissions by supporting 24-bit/48kHz high-resolution audio through the Qualcomm aptX HD codec.

prod_name: MelGeek Mojo60 Ember Bluetooth Mechanical Keyboard
prod_description: Made by MelGeek and designed by Muni, an avid Drop user and rising keyboard designer, the Mojo60 Ember brings the best in modern engineering and retro styling. With 61 keys in a standard ANSI layout, this board thrives in tight spaces. The PCB offers hotswappable capabilities and per key RGB. Its double-shot MG-profiled ABS keycaps are both ergonomic and durable, keeping your hands comfortable while ensuring that the vintage-colored keys won't fade even with intensive use. A sturdy steel plate gives the Mojo60 stability, while an electroplated polycarbonate case faithfully recreates the look of polished metal without the unnecessary weight. Choose from two styles and four different Gateron switches to suit your preferences, and connect this versatile, QMK-programmable keyboard with USB-C or Bluetooth.

Colorful and satisfyingly simple, the Astrolokey Artisan Keycap by Hammer brings the best parts of outer space to the top of your keyboard. Choose a star, crescent moon, or a cratered planet, each set against a colorful purple or pink background. Made from strong resin material in DSA profile, this keycap is long-lasting and a joy to press. Add it to the Drop + DSA Astrolokeys Keycap Set or use it as an accent on your existing keyboard.

Featuring four balanced armatures and two dynamic drivers per ear, the BGVP DMG IEM competes closely with the FiiO FH5 in both driver layout and looks. It's made the rounds on Head-Fi's discovery thread, and aims for an ergonomic design with excellent noise isolation and comfortable long-term wear. Equipped with MMCX connectors, it comes with a 5N OCC silver-plated MMCX cable: a high-quality, eye-catching pairing for an IEM of this price. Along with 11 pairs of ear tips and a shirt clip, you'll get three nozzles for fine-tuning the sound to three distinct signatures.

prod_name: Raymond Weil Nabucco GMT Automatic Watch
prod_description: The Raymond Weil Nabucco has all the panache you'd expect in a watch that takes its name from a famous four-part Italian opera. From its prominent bezel to its thick crown and stainless steel bracelet, the watch calls attention to center stage. Add carbon fiber accents and a GMT hand into the mix and you've got a timepiece that'll keep its composure all the way until curtain call. Capable of tracking two different time zones and the date, the Nabucco is just as functional as it is elegant. Based on an ETA 2893-2 movement of 21 jewels, it ticks for 42 hours before coming to a stop. What's more, it's fortified with a sapphire crystal and a water resistance rating of 200 meters.

Large and uniquely styled, the Reign Lafleur commands attention on the wrist. This 45-millimeter watch takes a slightly different approach to dial design with Arabic-numeral minute markers that sit close to the center and larger hour-numerals on the outer ring. The center of the watch is dominated by a rotating geometric piece that catches the eye as it turns. There's also a cyclops eye to magnify the date window. Inside the stainless steel case, which is water resistant to 50 meters, lies a Seiko NH35 movement with a 41-hour power reserve. A sapphire-coated mineral crystal protects the dial, while luminous hands help it stand out in dark conditions.

Soft to the touch yet primed for performance, a cat's paw is the perfect combination of comfort and poise. With the silicone Kitty Paw keycap from ZOMO, you can bring that same form and feel to your keyboard. Available in four eye-catching colors, this keycap features the pawprint of a cat set atop a sturdy base. The pawprint is crafted from silicone for a soft and comfortable feel, while the base of the key is made from plastic for durability and responsiveness. Give your fingers the gift of feline performance.

Weighing just 2.8 ounces, the Maserin Carbon is easy to carry, and even easier to look at. It features a lightweight yet sturdy carbon fiber handle with a gleaming weave pattern running throughout, which gives the folder a refined aesthetic. The blade is made from N690 stainless steel and measures 3 inches long a good size for everyday slicing and piercing tasks. To deploy the blade, press on the protruding jimping on the blade's spine and it smoothly flips into place. For added convenience, the folder comes with a pocket clip for tip-down carry on the right side.

With its stout, aggressively jimped blade and thick handle, the Bestech Goblin looks like it sounds. A compact folder with premium materials, the Goblin is easy to control and easier to carry. The pudgy modified wharncliffe blade is great for small, repeatable tasks, and thanks to its CPM-S35VN build, it'll keep an edge for a long time. The handle is short and stubby, but offers a surprisingly full grip in the hand. Made from a combination of titanium and carbon fiber, it'll hold up through stressful work, and it looks the part, to boot. Inside it is a strong frame lock to secure the blade. The outside is fitted with a tip-up clip, also made from titanium. If you don't want this little monster wreaking havoc in your pocket, you can clip it to a lanyard if you like.

prod_description: Handcrafted in the US since 1932, authentic Zippo lighters are famed for their durability, windproof design, and lifetime warranty. This collection is a subtle nod to the fall season. Comprising geometric designs and earthy patterns, these lighters are a classy way to ring in the new season. Each Zippo comes packaged in an environmentally friendly gift box and includes a lifetime warranty.

prod_name: Alpha & Delta Elite True Wireless Bluetooth IEM
prod_description: Combining detailed audio with true wireless performance, the Elite IEM from Alpha & Delta allows listeners to take calls and enjoy music with cutting-edge convenience. Each earbud features a 6-millimeter dynamic driver for powerful and vivid sound, plus a comfortable IPX5 waterproof case shaped to precisely fit the human ear. For reliable connectivity, the Elite is equipped with a Qualcomm QCC3026 Bluetooth chipset with support for aptX and Qualcomm's True Wireless Plus technology. The included charging case adopts a type-C port and supports both wireless and reverse charging.

prod_name: Vulture Premium Badalassi Carlo Leather Watch Strap
prod_description: Made from Minerva Box, a rare vegetable-tanned leather from an artisanal tannery in Tuscany, these watch straps are tanned the old fashioned way, with extracts of bark and liquored with animal fats in wooden barrels. The leather itself is known for its soft temper and suppleness, so it will adapt to any wrist without a hitch. As you wear it, the leather will shift tonality and develop a unique patina over time, so no two straps will be exactly alike. Each strap is fitted with a polished stainless steel buckle and two keepers.

Sitting at the throne of portable audio is the TFZ King Edition: an ergonomic IEM that offers adjustable sound with vivid detail. A step up from TFZ's highly regarded No. 3 IEM, the TFZ King Edition is equipped with 11.4-millimeter Tesla magnetic group drivers engineered for powerful articulation across all frequencies. It also features two switchable sound settings. In the off position, the IEM delivers audio tuned for enjoyment. In the on position, it emits balanced sound tuned for analytic listening in professional settings. An electroplated oxygen-free copper panel and aluminum alloy shell improve signal transmission, durability, and comfort, while a 0.78-millimeter connector makes cable replacement easy.

prod_name: Orient Sun & Moon Version 2 Automatic Watch
prod_description: The sun and moon are two of the most powerful forces governing our planet. To recognize their power and mystique, the Orient Sun & Moon Version 2 automatic features a rotating subdial at 10 o'clock that provides a unique look at where they are throughout the course of the day. This version is laid out with a second subdial at 2 for the day and a window spanning 7 to 8 o'clock to track the date. Looking more closely, the dial has a great sense of depth, which is evidenced by the 14.1-millimeter case. Powered by Orient's own 46B40 automatic movement, the watch is accurate and precise. Protecting the dial is a sapphire crystal, and on the back of the case is a display window to peek at the movement. It's also 50 meters water resistant to withstand your day-to-day activities.

Bulova's Precisionist collection is aptly named. Capable of precise timing to 1/1000th of a second, the watch is powered by Bulova's proprietary three-prong quartz crystal Precisionist movement, which vibrates eight times faster than standard quartz watches. (It even has a continuous-sweep seconds hand despite being a quartz-powered timepiece.) Aesthetically, the watch is appropriately sporty. Styled in black and red, it features carbon fiber accents for an almost tactical look. It has a near-tactical build as well: made from stainless steel with black coating, the watch is water resistant to an impressive 300 meters.

A paladin is a knight renowned for his heroism and chivalry. The Bestech Paladin is a knife renowned for its cutting ability. See the parallels? Bestech did, too. Sporting a G-10 handle in multiple colors including the new Massdrop-exclusive OD green colorway the Paladin is stately and comfy in the hand. The handle houses a stainless steel liner lock to keep the blade secure when opened. Speaking of opening, it deploys with a simple press on the jimped flipper tab thanks to the bearing system. The straight-edge blade lends itself to piercing and slicing and at 3.6 inches long, it can do plenty of it. Made from D2, the Paladin can hold a good edge over time as well. What's more, the blade comes in two different finishes to suit your style.

prod_description: Bring a rustic touch to your modern space with this linen bedding from Olive Wren. Made from French flax, then preshrunk and stonewashed, it's more durable than cotton with a higher density yet still wonderfully soft to the touch. It launders well, softening over time and requiring little to no ironing, and with its vintage drape, it'll look and feel great year-round. The fabric is so well liked, in fact, that it's been featured in publications like Forbes, Vogue, and Business Insider. The duvet covers have a mother-of-pearl button closure and internal ties at each corner to prevent insert slippage. All bedding sets come in a linen bag for easy storage.

prod_description: When the sun comes out, the 171/S sunglasses from Marc Jacobs shine. Styled for summer settings, these shades feature an eye-catching retro shape with dark-havana acetate accents. They provide welcome UV400 protection to handle the brightest sunlight, plus a sturdy full rim made of metal for welcome durability that won't weigh you down. Great for styling with formal attire, beach wear, and everything in between, these sunglasses will quickly become a staple in any wardrobe.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/sIaD8xkvTZupPoqHqxtQ_MD-16624_20160307094818_4233668dbf8cec24.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/Ps2fUVuaRCyIkHmZZup8_izrezane slusalice br 2.psd?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/2sKUzrfURpSfk7F5FbMI_MD-16624_20160307094819_83c307de7e0d94df.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/d2CB9UU2SP2LRT7ESS4y_MD-16624_20160307094820_d21b0f290cb6e9ca.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/eWsoqMnVQlp0WhTUFTJE_3.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/L6eReXnXRXyHP0zDPeiJ_MD-16624_20160307094821_743483ec98c8ad02.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/LkpPLWnS5GiCdforvGCw_20190609 bamboo-2.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/Ps2fUVuaRCyIkHmZZup8_izrezane slusalice br 2.psd?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/emu-wood-series-headphones/FP/5wUmBQM9TzG9MeRj6kvg_20190609 Bamboo-3.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: From E-MU's Wood Series, these headphones feature full-size circumaural enclosures handcrafted from your choice of bamboo or teak. And now, they're available with a 1.5-meter cable something fans of the Fostex TH and Denon D Series have been wanting for a while. Both the chassis and sound signature recall Denon's much-missed D2000/5000, the black leather and golden-brown wood complemented by gleaming chrome accents. Inside, powerful neodymium drivers with bio-cellulose diaphragms deliver crystal-clear highs and deep, warm bass. Coupled with the soft sheepskin earpads and adjustable padded headband, the lightweight frame provides hours of listening comfort.

You'd be hard pressed to find a more fun way to test switches than with CLICKEYbits. In fact, though they were originally developed as switch testers, people loved them so much that they started buying them as fidget toys. Building on the success, the father-son team that created them set out to expand the lineup. Now available in four different versions, each CLICKEYbits is made with authentic mechanical switches. At about 2 inches wide, they're the perfect size to fill the palm for a satisfying feel in the hand.

For watch lovers who desire brawn and functionality, the Seiko Arnie so named because Arnold Schwarzenegger wore it in several 1980s action movies is a sure bet. Powered by the sun, this 47-millimeter tank boasts a full-auto calendar (that's accurate to year 2100), a dual-time function, a built-in LED light, an alarm function, a unidirectional rotating bezel, a chronograph, and more. While it may sound like a lot, every key piece of information is easily accessible via the digital display at 12 o'clock. Of course, in the name of legibility, all the indices and hands are highly lumed not to mention the Arnie is water resistant to 200 meters.

Made in the Netherlands from 100-percent recycled materials, the Combekk dutch oven is the only one of its kind. It features a single layer of stain-resistant matte enamel for durability and resistance to cracking, plus a thick base for even heat distribution throughout the entire cooking process. Used for anything from making soups and stews to roasting meats and veggies and making casseroles, dutch ovens are designed to retain their heat for hours and produce consistent results. The main model includes a thermometer to keep an eye on your food's temperature. If you don't need the thermometer, there are standard versions available, too.

prod_name: Combekk Railway Cast Iron Fry Pan
prod_description: Valued for their heat-retention properties, cast iron pans make for reliable companions in any kitchen and, when treated correctly, they'll last a lifetime. This one is made in the Netherlands from 100-percent recycled materials. It features a single layer of stain-resistant matte enamel for durability and resistance to cracking, plus a thick base for even heat distribution throughout the entire cooking process. The handle is made from FSC-Certified wood for a solid grip. Use the pan to bake a cake, sear a filet, roast a chicken, or stir fry vegetables: they're as versatile as they are durable.

prod_name: B Swiss by Bucherer Prestige Moonphase Automatic
prod_description: Moonphase watches are rare. Automatic moonphase watches are even more so. The Prestige Moonphase automatic gives you a way to track the moon's flight path, the day, the date, and the current time all in a sophisticated 37.5-millimeter package that won't weigh you down. Around the chapter ring you'll see a track with numerals for days of the month. The current date is indicated with a dark blue, crescent moonshaped hand that extends all the way out to the edge of the chapter ring. At 10 o'clock is a large subdial for the day, and of course, at 6 is the moonphase indicator, which can be adjusted via the subtle button beneath the crown. To power all of that, there's a 26-jewel movement that can be viewed by way of the exhibition caseback. To protect it is a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal.

This modestly sized dress watch from Swiss maker FrÃ©dÃ©rique Constant won't overpower anybody's wrist. Polished from head to toe, it features a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal. The dial, laid out with a combination of Arabic numerals and trapezoidal markers, has a slightly grainy texture to it when viewed up close but you won't see it at a glance. The expanded date window offers a view of the previous and next day, in addition to the current one, of course. Inside the case lies the brand's own FC-303 automatic movement, providing a power reserve of 38 hours fully charged. The partial display caseback shows just a peek at the movement, rather than the whole thing. Also worthy of a mention? The 60-meter water resistance rating, a number not often seen on timepieces.

prod_name: Ajazz Chocolate Cubes Full-Size Mechanical Keyboard
prod_description: The holiday season is upon us, and what better way to celebrate than with a sweet treat? The full-size Chocolate Cubes mechanical keyboard from Ajazz satisfies on multiple levels. In terms of looks, it's covered in milky and dark brown to resemble a big candy bar. The alphas are designed like an advent calendar, with varying symbols in the form of wildlife, waves, mountains, and other fun patterns. In terms of feel, the keyboard comes with your choice of Cherry MX switches, all of which are rated for more than 50 million keystrokes. Finally, the keyboard comes with rubber feet and adjustable legs should you prefer a more angled setup.

Whether you're mechanically inclined or you love a good show of luxury, the Eterna 1856 Skeleton Mechanical watch can be appreciated by just about anyone. The entire dial is a magnificent display of craftsmanship, as you can see each individual jewel of the Eterna 3902 movement at work. Look at the dial too long and you might get lost in it. To protect the movement, the timepiece has a stainless steel case and sapphire crystal. It wears on a handsome, braided leather strap and comes in two styles.

prod_name: Revue Thommen XL Diver Automatic Watch
prod_description: Revue Thommen's beginnings date all the way back to 1853 in the small Swiss town of Waldenburg. After nearly a century of crafting its own watch movements, the company began producing aviation instruments for the Swiss Air Force in 1936. Since, it's been at the forefront of Swiss watchmaking tradition. The Revue Thommen XL Diver automatic is, unlike its title suggests, medium sized at 42 millimeters. It features an ETA 2824-2 movement of 25 jewels with a power reserve of 38 hours. To protect it? A stainless steel case and sapphire crystal. If you'd like to track of elapsed time, there's a unidirectional rotating bezel, a different color on each model. This statuesque diver also boasts a 300-meter water resistance rating.

Take your kitchen prowess anywhere you go with the Messermeister Adventure Chef's Knife Collection. Created by chef Adam Glick and the skilled artisans at Messermeister, this six-piece kit includes everything you need to slice, trim, fillet, and more when you're camping, hiking, or otherwise in the wild. Included? The highly versatile chef's knife for all-purpose cuts; the folding fillet knife for fresh catches; the folding peeler and parer for the little things around the campsite; the triple-duty fork, knife, and spoon; and the substantial, folding TPE cutting board. Each utensil is made from high-quality German 1.4116 steel and folds nicely into the included canvas carrying case for easy storage. If you don't need all the extras, opt for the three-piece set instead.

By nurturing the ideas that most excite them, the folks at Dango Products are coming up with simple solutions to everyday problems like how to make a wallet that balances minimalism and security, a distilled design and a sense of style. Enter the T01 tactical wallet, made of full-grain leather secured to a 6061 aerospace-grade CNC'd aluminum chassis with military-spec bolts. Tuck it into your front or back pocket, or use the tab to tether it to your belt. The pockets can fit up to 12 cards total, while the integrated silicone band holds folded bills and receipts. Thoughtful details include RFID blocking and a built-in bottle opener. Each wallet comes with an MT02 multi-tool.

prod_name: Macaw NE1s True Wireless Bluetooth 5.0 IEM
prod_description: What good are true-wireless headphones if you can't take them where you want to go? Engineered for strength and sound quality, the Macaw NE1s IEM is the ultimate listening solution for active individuals. Equipped with Bluetooth 5.0 and multipoint connectivity, it features a waterproof-grade IPX7 rating, so you don't have to worry about rain or sweat. Inside each earbud, an 8-millimeter dynamic driver ensures vivid sound with a frequency response range of 2020kHz. Great for sustained listening, the NE1s can play for up to 4 hours without needing a charge. Plus, its portable charging case is equipped with a 600mA battery capacity that allows for an additional 5 charges enough for even the longest trips.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/italia-in-progress-colombo-bag/FP/7m0ZURoRbSYjZQm4UFVA_pc.JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/italia-in-progress-colombo-bag/FP/1Sh24UfNSfaSQEr8KndW_ITB924BR - Marrone 1 (4).JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/italia-in-progress-colombo-bag/FP/rtCoyphqSIKaEsbEqiW4_ITB924BR - Marrone 1 (2).JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/italia-in-progress-colombo-bag/FP/rtCoyphqSIKaEsbEqiW4_ITB924BR - Marrone 1 (2).JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/italia-in-progress-colombo-bag/FP/KfdYwrITCmpJ9vRyNMkl_ITB924NE - Nero 1 (2).JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/italia-in-progress-colombo-bag/FP/DSOGyMjDQtupmL6IzSOz_ITB924RD - Rosso 1 (2).JPG?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/italia-in-progress-colombo-bag/FP/YAbQJLe7TNGVQwl5Rzd9_ITB924TDM - Moro 1 (2).JPG?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Crafted from genuine leather, the Colombo from Italia in Progress offers protection, security, and good looks.  Internally, the travel bag has plenty of space, plus inside and outside pockets with zipper pulls. Carry it by the double handles or the adjustable shoulder strap, which can be removed for a more minimal look. Made in Italy, the bag has metal feet for support wherever you take it.

Looking at the Nitecore C2's unusual rectangular form factor, its shocking output power makes even more sense. Capable of producing 6,500 lumens, the torch is backed by four CREE XHP35 LEDs. The output spans five brightness modes and three special modes, including strobe, SOS, and beacon mode for signaling and emergencies. Thanks to a built-in 12400 mAh battery, it can go for a remarkable 2,000 hours on ultralow mode. IP68 waterproof rated, the tough aluminum body is also impact resistant, should you drop it on the go. All modes are regulated by a single button on the bezel, so you don't have to worry about a complicated interface like you would with some other robust lights. Whether you use it to search, light the way, or point out stars, the C2 is easy to take with and comes with a holster and lanyard.

A combination of cream and gray, these neutral keycaps will complement most keyboards. Available with Russian or Japanese legends, they feature red sublegends for a splash of color. Constructed from dye-subbed PBT plastic, the caps are durable and resistant to the oils that accumulate from fingers. The base set comes with 87 Cherry-profile keycaps, but you can add some extra kits at checkout.

prod_description: For discerning audiophiles looking to get better sound quality out of their computers, the unit packs a heck of a punch for the size. It contains a preamp, DAC, and high-current, low-distortion Class-A headphone amplifier all housed in a sleek, compact aluminum chassis that stands vertically to occupy minimal space on your desk. It can easily drive high-impedance headphones up to 600 ohms for clear, transparent sound with full, rich bass reproduction.

Equipped with a 4-inch drop-point blade made from N690 stainless steel, the full-size Maserin Police Tactical Folding Knife is built for heavy-duty tasks. A cobalt-enriched, high-chromium-content steel hailing from Austria, Bohler's N690 offers many of the same properties as VG10: supreme hardness, ease of sharpening, and edge-holding ability, to name a few. The front of the handle is made from textured G10 for grip, while the back of the handle sports an industrial stonewashed look to offset the aesthetic. A right-handed, tip-up pocket clip offers convenient carry, while a built-in glass breaker comes in handy for emergencies.

Available on Massdrop before anywhere else, the Rike Knife 802G is a lengthy folder for hard use. Perhaps most notable about it is its two-piece handle. The knife is a titanium frame lock, but the opposing side is made entirely out of G-10. This means you get a clean single-colored surface on one side, and an all-business side on the other. The resulting structure is both lightweight and strong. A 3.7-inch drop-point, the blade is made from premium 154CM stainless steel for maximum performance. To access it, all you'll need is a firm press on the flipper (this is a 4-millimeter-thick blade, after all). The handle has ridges around the edges, almost like the wrapper on a Reese's peanut butter cup. If you want to go full Reese's, pick up the orange model; or you can go for something more subtle like black, green, or tan.

Designed by knifemaker Dylan Mallery and manufactured by trusted artisan brand CJRB, the Centros Folding Knife packs affordable performance into a slim profile. Weighing just 4.6 ounces, this knife is neither heavy nor wide but it does have ample length. The drop-point D2 blade is 3.7 inches long, while the entire knife measures 8.4 inches in length. A ceramic ball-bearing pivot and liner lock ensure smooth deployment and closure, while a steel clip makes pocket carry safe and secure. Choose a G-10 or carbon fiber handle, and add this slim standard to your arsenal.

Wasting not a millimeter of space, the Akko 3084 makes excellent use of its medium form factor. It houses 84 keys, including arrows, numbers, and a full set of function keys along the top row. Perhaps best of all, the board runs on Bluetooth wireless, which means there's no fussing with annoying USB connections. It'll last for up to 120 hours when you're typing and 250 days in standby mode. The retro, muted gray and white colorway has splashes of blue for a little pizzazz. And because the PBT caps are made through a process of dye sublimation, they won't fade over time. Get the wireless Akko 3084 with your choice of Cherry MX switches for a unique feel.

Arcanent, or spin box in latin, specializes in watch winders. The founder started it in response to an industry-wide disconnect, in which quality watch winders could only be had for exorbitant prices. Now, Arcanent is one of the premiere manufacturers of winders and other watch accessories. Take this nine-slot beauty, for example. Featuring powerful Japanese motors (one per slot), it runs quietly and efficiently. Using the remote-controlled and LCD display, you can program it for 650, 750, 850, 1000, or 1,950  turns per day. For protection, the winder has a locking door and sensor. There's also a pull-out drawer on the bottom for straps, tools, and extra watches that might not get quite as much wear.

For more than 100 years, Persol has been creating luxury eyewear. When you've been around for that long, it goes without saying you're doing something right. In Persol's case, it's crafting quality sunglasses, each pair handmade by talented craftsmen in Italy. Here, we're offering four different models. Whether you prefer a blue or green lens, a double-bridge or single-bridge design, polarized or non-polarized lenses, there's something for everyone. Each pair comes with a carrying case and cleaning cloth to keep them safe and pristine.
