prod_description: Featuring the same design, but now produced with an updated mold and tooling, the stock Invyr Panda switches make their long-awaited return. Featuring POM, ivory colored housings with black, factory-lubed linear stems, these switches are super satisfying. Designed with a 67-gram spring, they have a linear feel and MX switch compatibility but if you want to take them to the next level, you can use these switches to create your own Holy Pandas instead. To make things even easier, we'll be offering Halo True switches as add-ons.

prod_name: QSP Harpyie S35VN Liner Lock Knife
prod_description: New from QSP, the Harpyie delivers on looks and performance. A full-sized knife measuring 8.6 inches, this folder carries itself like one half its size. At just 4.9 ounces, it's very lightweight for its stature. But thanks to the 3.75-inch S35VN blade, it can handle repeated piercing and slicing tasks with no problem. The handle is a combination of carbon fiber and G-10 for a sleek look and a strong hold. Inside the scales are stainless steel liners, which help secure the blade when opened. Speaking of opening, the Harpyie is smooth as butter: A simple press on the flipper tab and the blade effortlessly glides along the ceramic ball bearings to the open position.

prod_gallery: ['https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/P2aZ0tbnSAlCw2DEW4yP_visconti-Breeze-Blueberry-fountain-pen-posted-nibsmith.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/oakDReH1QvOsfQJFcyqQ_Screen Shot 2019-07-23 at 1.18.23 PM.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/UxZo0jgRQ5uUji0QBHjm_Screen Shot 2019-07-23 at 1.18.29 PM.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/juhcJdnoR6cpbvTMLfj3_visconti-kp0801fp-1.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/fJV5GgfLTFWxvntJVL4b_12020-Blueberry.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/erSJjoXQMmxJNvHmzbTg_12020-Cherry.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/goP1sfW1RV2mV5KgzoAT_12020-Lemon.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/RBNhc1STt2CGzJ5102Uw_12020-Lime.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/e29GgfbTHaTyh8Lj0N3Q_12020-Mandarin.jpg?bg=f0f0f0', 'https://massdrop-s3.imgix.net/product-images/visconti-breeze-fountain-pens/FP/IGshQ9W7TUgHSwshCyci_12020-Plum.jpg?bg=f0f0f0']
prod_description: Made entirely in Visconti's Florence, Italy factory, the Breeze fountain pen is characterized by its fresh look and quality construction. The shape of this writer calls to mind Visconti's iconic torpedo design, a form factor that's both lightweight and comfortable in the hand. Made from vegetal resin, the body of the pen comes in six eye-catching colors. Engraved on the band, you'll find the pen's name. The cap features guidance grooves and a magnetic seal for secure closure. As for the nib, it's made of steel and comes in your choice of three sizes.

prod_name: Red Scarf II+ Ver. D Custom Mechanical Keyboard Kit
prod_description: The fourth iteration in the popular line of Red Scarf keyboards, the Red Scarf II+ Ver. D sports a highly efficient layout with a full numpad on the right-hand side and this kit comes with brass feet, a PCB, a plate, a case, and stabilizers to help you assemble it. The keyboard features bottom-lit RGB LEDs and supports through-hole LEDs for those who really want to light up their desktop. The ultra-thin shell design and translucent acrylic material further accentuate the keyboard's sleek look. Once assembled, pop on the brass feet for an ergonomic angle that will stay put when you're typing.

Ready for all your workout and travel needs, the TFZ X1 IEM boasts Bluetooth 5.0 lossless transmission and an IPX7 waterproof rating. It doesn't skimp on sound, either: each channel features a balanced armature driver, a rarity among fully wireless IEMs. The smooth, glossy housing is lightweight at just 4.6 grams per side, and the built-in battery gives you up to 7 hours of playback or call time. It's no surprise this IEM comes from TFZ: a company that's gained a reputation on Massdrop for offering stylish products at an attractive price.

With more than 10 successful Kickstarter campaigns under his belt, Michael Sargent head of Carbon Tactics has a knack for bringing the EDC crowd what it never knew it needed. Carbon Tactics' latest creation is the R2Key2 key clip. This belt- and waistband-friendly accessory offers high-speed, low-drag access to your keys (or whatever else you feel like clipping). Simply push to connect your gear, then squeeze to release it instantly. Thanks to the secure, dual-latch design, you'll never accidentally unclip your keys. What's more, the R2Key2 comes in your choice of aluminum, copper, or titanium to match your other carry.

If motorcycle racing is your bread and butter, get a load of the Tissot T-Racer. This quartz-powered chronograph is built for speed from head to toe. It features large Arabic numerals (like those on a speedometer), a tachymeter scale, and chronograph subdials that measure in 60-second, 30-minute, and 12-hour increments. There's also a unidirectional rotating bezel to track elapsed time. Set on a rubber strap, the T-Race is water resistant to 100 meters. It comes in your choice of three racing-approved styles: There's one themed to honor professional racer Stefan Bradl, one for racer Thomas LÃ¼thi, and one for Moto GP in general.

The sequel to the Yulong Canary DAC/amp, the Canary II sees several improved features and a few returning favorites. The biggest change is in the chips, where the Canary II showcases an upgraded XU208 chipset with support for Native DSD512 and PCM 768KHz decoding, as well as ESS's well-regarded 9038Q2M DAC chip for improved digital-to-audio conversion. Like its predecessor, the Canary II delivers impressive amplification rated at 1000mw at 32 ohms. Yulong has fine-tuned its fully discrete component Class-A JFET preamplifier module to create a cleaner, more realistic tone while delivering strong headphone amplification.

prod_name: Zeno-Watch Basel Cockpit Digital Quartz Watch
prod_description: You've probably never worn or seen anything quite like this jumping-hour timepiece from Zeno-Watch Basel. The main dial has a macaroni-shaped window to indicate the hour. Every 60 minutes, once the minutes hand has completed a full revolution, the hour hand jumps forward to the next hour a feature that's as mesmerizing as it is unique. To track running seconds, use the secondary subdial, positioned on the bottom right of the dial. It rotates like a disc and is marked in intervals of five, just like the minutes track. Because of the dials' layout, you can actually see through the watch in the negative space. Another detail to note is the crown, which can be found at 9 o'clock. Finally, the watch is fitted with a sapphire crystal and is water resistant to 50 meters.

A great way to practice your lockpicking skills, and to help understand how a lock functions, this six-pin lock offers thousands of possible pin combos. It requires no tools and no previous experience: All you need to do is grab a lockpicking set and start cracking it open. Set it up as a simple two-pin lock or use all six the choice is yours. Included are extra pins, instructions, and a set of keys.

The KXXS IEM is an improved version of Moondrop's original Kanas Pro, the company's flagship dynamic driver IEM. Redesigned to have a more comfortable and eye-catching design than its predecessor, it features a zinc-aluminum alloy housing that's carefully polished to a satin finish. Inside each ergonomic earpiece, a 10-millimeter dynamic driver with a DLC (Diamond-Like Carbon) diaphragm delivers excellent response speed, damping, and details. For easy cable replacement, the IEM has 0.78mm 2-pin connectors, too. Animagus gives the IEM a 5-star review on Head-fi, writing, "Moondrop KXXS does everything right. The bass is good, mids are natural, drums and vocals are a joy to listen to, and treble is crisp and clear yet smooth. KXXS at its price is quite accessible and I think it is one dynamic driver IEM that everyone should have.

Arozzi a company that specializes in high-performance products for gamers, coders, and PC users the Vernazza gaming chair is made for comfort throughout marathon gaming sessions and long work days. It features 3D adjustable armrests, an adjustable backrest, an extra high seat back, and a wide seat to accommodate larger gamers. The sculpted foam head pillow reduces strain on the neck, while a lumbar support pillow helps to support the spine and back. Lastly, to be as comfortable and ergonomic as possible the Vernazza features more cold cured molded foam than any other model Arozzi Manufactures.

Perhaps best known for its 24-hour Airman tool watch, Glycine has been producing quality timepieces since 1914. This one, powered by the company's own GL293 21-jewel automatic movement, wouldn't look out of place on a pilot's wrist. It features a 24-hour bidirectional rotating bezel to help track time in other time zones. The bezel locks down via the crown at 4 o'clock. Rounding out the dial is a magnified date window and lumed hands, including a GMT hand for an extra time zone. Made from stainless steel with a sapphire crystal, the watch is water resistant to 200 meters. For quickset date, pull the crown out to the first position. Rotate it clockwise to adjust the GMT hand. Pull the crown out to the second position to set the time.

Keycaps are only getting more popular, and if you're like us, you have plenty of extras laying around. For those sets you don't feel like giving a space on your keyboard, put them in the mStone keycap collection box. Made from acrylic with space for dozens of keycaps, it offers a flattering, protective space for your favorite set on the side. The box is compatible with all kinds of keycap profiles (except SA), so don't worry about your most flamboyant artisans fitting inside, either.
